{"name":"Conchobhar","type":"npc","img":"https://assets.forge-vtt.com/5f43f8ea1a91d63438d13159/artwork-adventures/pirates-of-cyre/characters/conchobhar-turlach-tomraan.webp","data":{"attributes":{"agility":{"die":{"sides":8,"modifier":0},"wild-die":{"sides":6}},"smarts":{"die":{"sides":6,"modifier":0},"wild-die":{"sides":6},"animal":false},"spirit":{"die":{"sides":8,"modifier":0},"wild-die":{"sides":6},"unShakeBonus":0},"strength":{"die":{"sides":6,"modifier":0},"wild-die":{"sides":6},"encumbranceSteps":0},"vigor":{"die":{"sides":6,"modifier":0},"wild-die":{"sides":6}}},"stats":{"speed":{"runningDie":4,"runningMod":0,"value":5},"toughness":{"value":0,"armor":0,"modifier":0},"parry":{"value":5,"modifier":0},"size":-1},"details":{"biography":{"value":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p>Conchobhar Shortstone is a handsome, honey-tongued gnome who wears a foppish purple hat, an eye patch, and a white silk shirt, and carries a dandyish cane. His appearance is that of someone pretending to be a pirate, rather than a true buccaneer. </p>"},"species":{"name":""},"currency":500,"wealth":{"die":6,"modifier":0,"wild-die":6},"conviction":{"value":0,"active":false},"autoCalcToughness":true,"autoCalcParry":true},"powerPoints":{"value":11,"max":11,"Gnome Magic":{"value":0,"max":0},"Bard":{"value":0,"max":0}},"fatigue":{"value":0,"min":0,"max":2},"wounds":{"value":0,"min":0,"max":3,"ignored":0},"advances":{"value":0,"rank":"Novice","details":""},"bennies":{"value":2,"max":2},"status":{"isShaken":false,"isDistracted":false,"isVulnerable":false,"isStunned":false,"isEntangled":false,"isBound":false},"initiative":{"hasHesitant":false,"hasLevelHeaded":false,"hasImpLevelHeaded":false,"hasQuick":false},"additionalStats":{},"wildcard":true},"token":{"name":"Blank NPC","img":"https://assets.forge-vtt.com/5f43f8ea1a91d63438d13159/tokens/bestiary/monstrous%20humanoid/harpy-*.png","displayName":30,"actorLink":false,"width":1,"height":1,"scale":1,"mirrorX":false,"mirrorY":false,"lockRotation":false,"rotation":0,"alpha":1,"vision":false,"dimSight":0,"brightSight":0,"dimLight":0,"brightLight":0,"sightAngle":0,"lightAngle":0,"lightAlpha":0.25,"lightAnimation":{"speed":5,"intensity":5},"disposition":-1,"displayBars":0,"bar1":{"attribute":""},"bar2":{"attribute":""},"flags":{},"randomImg":true,"actorId":null,"tint":null,"lightColor":null,"x":null,"y":null,"elevation":null},"items":[{"_id":"Bf0NpaRHtHmfrLb3","name":"Athletics","type":"skill","img":"icons/magic/control/buff-strength-muscle-damage.webp","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p>Athletics combines an individual&rsquo;s coordin&shy;ation with learned skills such as climbing, jumping, balancing, biking, wrestling, skiing, swimming, throwing, or catching. Characters who rely on physical power more than coordination can take the @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Brute]{Brute} Edge to link this skill to @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Traits]{Strength} instead of @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Traits]{Agility}.</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"attribute":"agility","isCoreSkill":false,"die":{"sides":6,"modifier":0},"wild-die":{"sides":6}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_azxylmvr7yo","path":"Skills","color":"#008000"},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.swade-core-rules.swade-skills.sAig03GZiFKqBX7p"}}},{"_id":"bJxCFLP4a8BEU0Qm","name":"Common Knowledge","type":"skill","img":"icons/sundries/documents/document-official-capital.webp","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\"><p>Characters roll Common Knowledge to know people, places, and things of their world, including etiquette, geography, culture, popular technology, contacts, and customs.</p></div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"attribute":"smarts","isCoreSkill":false,"die":{"sides":6,"modifier":0},"wild-die":{"sides":6}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_azxylmvr7yo","path":"Skills","color":"#008000"},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.swade-core-rules.swade-skills.8N1uMThntsjaUPem"}}},{"_id":"gMAJFeCm5e3Oporq","name":"Fighting","type":"skill","img":"icons/skills/melee/hand-grip-sword-white-brown.webp","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p>Fighting covers all hand-to-hand (melee) attacks, whether it&rsquo;s with fists, axes, laser swords, or martial arts. See @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Combat]{Chapter Three} for the combat rules and the various maneuvers a warrior might attempt.</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"attribute":"agility","isCoreSkill":false,"die":{"sides":6,"modifier":0},"wild-die":{"sides":6}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_azxylmvr7yo","path":"Skills","color":"#008000"},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.swade-core-rules.swade-skills.wWiwjPlzAQU3TN9l"}}},{"_id":"9coycVPgGdTGpbmh","name":"Language (Common)","type":"skill","img":"icons/sundries/documents/document-letter-formal-tan.webp","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p>In some settings, such as those that focus on pulp action or &ldquo;planetary romance&rdquo; (where characters frequently travel among many strange civilizations), speaking various languages can simply be roleplayed with halting dialogue and campy accents that start out a little difficult and are quickly forgotten. The GM may ignore this skill altogether in these settings, or use the @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Multiple Languages]{Multiple Languages}&nbsp;&shy;option in the @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Setting Rules]{Setting Rules}.</p>\n<p>In more realistic settings, communication can be a major barrier that requires characters to put skill points into additional languages. In a 1980s World War Three game, for example, a group of United Nations paratroopers won&rsquo;t be able to speak with their foes unless they take Russian, Polish, or other languages common to the Warsaw Pact.</p>\n<p>If the Language skill is in use, it should be listed as Language (Spanish), Language (American Sign Language), etc. A character&rsquo;s die type also notes how fluent he is in it. (Characters start with a d8 in their own Language.)</p>\n<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<table class=\"table value-table\"><caption class=\"table-caption\">\n<h2 class=\"table-title\">Language Proficiency</h2>\n</caption>\n<tbody>\n<tr class=\"table-header-row\">\n<th class=\"table-column-header\" scope=\"col\">Skill</th>\n<th class=\"table-column-header\" scope=\"col\">Ability</th>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td>d4</td>\n<td>The character can read, write and speak common words and phrases.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>d6</td>\n<td>The speaker can carry on a prolonged but occasionally halting conversation.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>d8</td>\n<td>The character can speak fluently.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>d10</td>\n<td>The hero can mimic other dialects within the language.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>d12</td>\n<td>The speaker can masterfully recite important literary or oral works.</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>\n</div>\n<p><strong>Limited: </strong>Use whichever skill is lowest when performing an action that requires knowledge of a foreign language. @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Intimidation]{Intimidation} (if verbal), @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Persuasion]{Persuasion}, @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Research]{Research}, @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Taunt]{Taunt}, etc., are all limited by the character&rsquo;s Language skill.</p>\n<p>This limitation never applies to a character&rsquo;s native tongue.</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"attribute":"smarts","isCoreSkill":false,"die":{"sides":8,"modifier":0},"wild-die":{"sides":6}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_azxylmvr7yo","path":"Skills","color":"#008000"},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.swade-core-rules.swade-skills.XIuR2IyQtewm5BZP"}}},{"_id":"TWqtRMnChmXvwXvN","name":"Notice","type":"skill","img":"icons/creatures/eyes/human-single-blue.webp","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p>Notice is a hero&rsquo;s general awareness and alertness. It&rsquo;s used to sense sights, sounds, tastes, and smells, spot clues, detect ambushes, spot hidden weapons on a foe, or tell if a rival is lying, frightened, happy, etc.</p>\n<p>@Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{Success} conveys basic information&mdash;the character hears movement in the forest, smells distant smoke, or senses someone isn&rsquo;t being completely truthful.</p>\n<p>A @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{raise} grants more detail, such as the direction of a sound or odor or what topic a person is avoiding or lying about.</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"attribute":"smarts","isCoreSkill":false,"die":{"sides":6,"modifier":0},"wild-die":{"sides":6}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_azxylmvr7yo","path":"Skills","color":"#008000"},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.swade-core-rules.swade-skills.yvw9bMgsrWQXuZN2"}}},{"_id":"rk3ft5Cc4sHxF5ay","name":"Stealth","type":"skill","img":"icons/magic/nature/stealth-hide-eyes-green.webp","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p>Stealth is the ability to hide and move quietly. A simple @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{success} on a Stealth roll means the character avoids detection if enemies aren&rsquo;t particularly alert. If the character @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{fails} the roll, the enemy realizes something is amiss and begins actively searching for whatever roused them.</p>\n<p>Once foes are alerted and active, Stealth is opposed by @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Notice]{Notice} (a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{group roll} if there are many foes.</p>\n<p>The GM should apply any circumstantial penalties to @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Notice]{Notice} rolls for @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Illumination]{darkness}, @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Cover and Obstacles]{cover}, noise, distractions, and any difference in the target&rsquo;s @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Size and Scale]{Scale} (just like when attacking). Sneaking through dry leaves might subtract 2 from the Stealth roll, for example, while spotting someone in the dark uses the @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Illumination]{Illumination} penalty (&minus;4). Don&rsquo;t apply the same modifier to both rolls, however. If Stealth is at &minus;2 for the leaves, don&rsquo;t give Notice a +2 for them as well.</p>\n<p><strong>Sneak Attack: </strong> Sneaking up close enough to make a melee attack <em>always</em> requires an @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{opposed} Stealth roll versus the target&rsquo;s @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Notice]{Notice}, whether the guard is actively looking for trouble or not. If successful, the victim is @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Distracted and Vulnerable]{Vulnerable} to the attacker, but only until the attacker&rsquo;s turn ends. With a raise, the attacker has @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.The Drop]{The Drop} instead.</p>\n<p><strong>Movement:</strong> In combat, characters roll Stealth each turn as a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Actions]{free action} at the end of their move or any action the GM thinks might draw attention.</p>\n<p>Out of combat, the distance moved depends entirely on the situation. The GM might want a roll every minute if the group is sneaking around the perimeter of a defensive position, or every few miles if they&rsquo;re trying to quietly walk the path through a dark forest without alerting the creatures that live there.</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"attribute":"agility","isCoreSkill":false,"die":{"sides":8,"modifier":0},"wild-die":{"sides":6}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_azxylmvr7yo","path":"Skills","color":"#008000"},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.swade-core-rules.swade-skills.z9FmdFVGOOW2kufm"}}},{"_id":"6BeiHr2FDzQaAZll","name":"Unskilled Attempt","type":"skill","img":"icons/magic/symbols/question-stone-yellow.webp","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p>If a character doesn&rsquo;t have a skill for an action he&rsquo;s attempting, he rolls a d4 for his skill die (and a Wild Die if a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Wild Cards and Extras]{Wild Card}) and subtracts 2 from the total.</p>\n<p>The GM may decide certain tasks cannot be attempted unskilled, such as performing complex surgery or flying a commercial jet.</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"attribute":"agility","isCoreSkill":false,"die":{"sides":4,"modifier":-2},"wild-die":{"sides":6}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_azxylmvr7yo","path":"Skills","color":"#008000"},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.swade-core-rules.swade-skills.1Pl2ZL8MPyKnaVEg"}}},{"_id":"dKrkxQ780O1QyNfq","name":"Unarmed Strike","type":"weapon","img":"icons/skills/melee/unarmed-punch-fist.webp","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p>See @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Unarmed Defender]{Unarmed Defender}.</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"quantity":1,"weight":0,"price":0,"equippable":false,"equipped":true,"isVehicular":false,"mods":1,"actions":{"skill":"Fighting","skillMod":"","dmgMod":"","additional":{}},"damage":"@str","range":"","rof":"1","ap":"0","minStr":"","shots":"0","currentShots":"0","ammo":"","autoReload":false},"effects":[],"folder":"651LNce8no6HR9rY","sort":100000,"permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"flags":{"journal-links":{},"core":{"sourceId":"Item.X31v8asHtqhgiaM2"}}},{"_id":"cUCXNAyC28lHwJ1j","name":"Obsessive (Lore)","type":"ability","img":"icons/magic/nature/plant-sproud-hands-dirt-green.webp","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p>Gnomes start with a d4 in any one Smarts-related skill.</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"subtype":"special","grantsPowers":false},"effects":[],"folder":"UUZJk5Z5jpjqw5rC","sort":400000,"permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"flags":{"journal-links":{},"core":{"sourceId":"Item.5NAJSxm6K1Vya1aZ"}}},{"_id":"r14ToNyzKEQE0zho","name":"Bard","type":"edge","img":"icons/skills/trades/music-singing-voice-blue.webp","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p>The bards of Eberron bring epic tales of heroism and tragedy to the people. Many are renowned far and wide for their talents, but few realize how crucial they are to parties of brave adventurers. They bolster their allies in dire circumstances, beguile their enemies, and often battle evil with a sword in one hand and a lute in the other.</p>\n<p>Bards cast spells by singing, playing an instrument, reciting poetry, or reciting epic tales. They are usually erudite individuals, traveling the land to learn bawdy songs, great histories, and epic legends.</p>\n<p>Allies must be able to hear the bard to benefit from his various abilities.</p>\n<p>Bards gain the following abilities:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Arcane Background (Bard)]{Arcane Background (Bard)}</li>\n<li>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Bard Armor Interference (Light)]{Bard Armor Interference (Light)}</li>\n<li>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Lore Keeper]{Lore Keeper}</li>\n<li>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Sharp Tongued]{Sharp Tongued}</li>\n</ul>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Novice, Spirit d6+, Common Knowledge d6+"}},"effects":[],"folder":"YstCBrpWUVlhJwXz","sort":100000,"permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"flags":{"journal-links":{},"core":{"sourceId":"Item.zphGBAJ4gdUCFIqa"}}},{"_id":"Ufqcrdnfi8AiACko","name":"Arcane Background (Bard)","type":"edge","img":"icons/skills/trades/music-singing-voice-blue.webp","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Arcane Background (Bard)]{Arcane Background (Bard)}</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"isArcaneBackground":true,"requirements":{"value":"Novice"}},"effects":[],"folder":"YstCBrpWUVlhJwXz","sort":500000,"permission":{"default":2,"ZvqefCj0L7TxJS56":3,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"flags":{"journal-links":{},"core":{"sourceId":"Item.zVLHayWmSMnBSupy"}}},{"_id":"XaMmQdQvRi2YKPR4","name":"Lore Keeper","type":"edge","img":"icons/skills/trades/music-singing-voice-blue.webp","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p>A bard learns special techniques for memorizing things he has heard or read, and he is well versed in many topics as part of his training. They have +1 to all @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Common Knowledge]{Common Knowledge} rolls, as well as rolls relating to riddles, history, folklore, and such like. Bards are also particularly popular with nobility and commoners alike and receive +1 @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Persuasion]{Persuasion} checks to @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Networking]{Networking} if they are known as a bard.</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Bard"}},"effects":[],"folder":"YstCBrpWUVlhJwXz","sort":300000,"permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"flags":{"journal-links":{},"core":{"sourceId":"Item.Yg6gxH0XZX9gc1gm"}}},{"_id":"9XMrHtpMcPksl1iM","name":"Sharp Tongued","type":"edge","img":"icons/skills/trades/music-singing-voice-blue.webp","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p>Bards may use @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Performance]{Performance} to @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Test]{Test} a foe. They may also ignore the Repetition advice given under @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Test]{Tests}, as long as they recite different verses, stanzas, lyrics, etc. Bards may also substitute @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Performance]{Performance} for @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Intimidation]{Intimidation} to meet Edge Requirements.</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Bard"}},"effects":[],"folder":"YstCBrpWUVlhJwXz","sort":300000,"permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"flags":{"journal-links":{},"core":{"sourceId":"Item.pD0DjyWGZctqf2qX"}}},{"_id":"zZSwUDYGQpshnUdl","name":"Gambling","type":"skill","img":"icons/sundries/gaming/dice-pair-white-green.webp","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\"><p>Gambling is common in the saloons of the Old West, the back rooms of criminal organizations, the barracks of most armies, or the flight decks of scifi spaceships.</p>\n<p>To simulate an hour of gambling without having to roll for every single toss of the dice or hand of cards, have everyone agree on the stakes, such as $10, 10 gold coins, etc. Everyone in the game then makes a Gambling roll. The lowest total pays the highest total the difference times the stake. The next lowest pays the second highest the difference times the stake, and so on. If there&rsquo;s an odd man left in the middle, he breaks even.</p>\n<p class=\"embedded-example\"><strong>Example:</strong> Red rolls highest with a 10 and Gabe rolls lowest with a 4. The difference is 6, so Gabe pays Red 6 &times; the stake of $10, or $60.</p>\n<p><strong>Cheating: </strong>A character who cheats adds +2 to his roll. The GM may raise or lower this modifier depending on the particulars of the game or the method of cheating. If a cheater rolls a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{Critical Failure}, however, he&rsquo;s caught. The consequences depend on the circumstances and who noticed, but are usually unpleasant!</p></div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"attribute":"smarts","isCoreSkill":false,"die":{"sides":8,"modifier":0},"wild-die":{"sides":6}},"effects":[],"folder":"cgfmurTJRwbCvmCc","sort":1900001,"permission":{"default":0,"3HvtK4sMp7flYKmT":3,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_qals24wpyph","path":"Skills","color":"#8c160f"},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.swade-core-rules.swade-skills.zPegv65RzQXUbQIz"}}},{"_id":"QBpBKVYkadCy2IOC","name":"Thievery","type":"skill","img":"icons/skills/social/theft-pickpocket-bribery-brown.webp","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p>Lockpicking, safecracking, picking pockets, sleight of hand, setting and disabling traps and similar acts of misdirection, sabotage, subterfuge, and manipulation are called Thievery.</p>\n<p>If used to pick a lock, crack a safe, disable a trap, or perform a simple unopposed action, @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{success} opens or disables the device, and a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{raise} does it in less time, without tripping alarms, or whatever else the GM feels is appropriate.</p>\n<p>Sleight of hand, hiding or planting an item, or picking a pocket require a simple @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{success}. If foes are actively watching the character, Thievery is @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{opposed} by @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Notice]{Notice}.</p>\n<p>The Game Master should assign @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{penalties} for particularly difficult circumstances. Picking a heavy padlock might have a &minus;4 penalty, while hiding a revolver in bulky winter clothing might grant a +1 bonus. @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{Failure} typically means the character is spotted or it takes too much time (after which the character can try again). A @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{Critical Failure} typically sets off the trap, alerts the victim, or jams the device so that it must be opened or interacted with in a different way.</p>\n<p><strong>Limited: </strong>Using Thievery on an electronic device, such as a keypad, is limited by the thief&rsquo;s @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Electronics]{Electronics} skill. Use the lowest of the two skills.</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"attribute":"agility","isCoreSkill":false,"die":{"sides":6,"modifier":0},"wild-die":{"sides":6}},"effects":[],"folder":"cgfmurTJRwbCvmCc","sort":1087501,"permission":{"default":0,"3HvtK4sMp7flYKmT":3,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_qals24wpyph","path":"Skills","color":"#8c160f"},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.swade-core-rules.swade-skills.wZbyJkisWIfmcZNt"}}},{"_id":"JqoohAdH7GrGar6d","name":"Performance","type":"skill","img":"icons/tools/instruments/lute-gold-brown.webp","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p>A good entertainer can lift the spirits, rally a crowd to action, or simply earn a few bucks from the locals. Specifics depend on the situation, setting, and how well the character is known in the area.</p>\n<p>Performance covers singing, acting, playing an instrument, or similar tasks that require an audience to appreciate.</p>\n<p><strong>Raising Funds:</strong> The amount of money a character can raise by performing is extremely subjective, but as a general rule a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{successful} performance raises 20% of the setting's @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Characters]{Starting Funds} with a success and 30% with a raise. The GM can multiply this amount by the performer's @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Advancement]{Rank} if she feels it's appropriate. These numbers work for typical performers who might be known in a small establishment or area. Larger performances can greatly boost the performer's fee, but also require more time, energy, and setup.</p>\n<p><strong>Deception: </strong>Performance can be used instead of @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Persuasion]{Persuasion} if the character is attempting to deceive, bluff, or disguise herself and the GM agrees it makes sense in the context of the situation.</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"attribute":"spirit","isCoreSkill":false,"die":{"sides":8,"modifier":0},"wild-die":{"sides":6}},"effects":[],"folder":"cgfmurTJRwbCvmCc","sort":2400001,"permission":{"default":0,"3HvtK4sMp7flYKmT":3,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_qals24wpyph","path":"Skills","color":"#8c160f"},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.swade-core-rules.swade-skills.SJ1nN0CmOHNQhfOQ"}}},{"_id":"LKSgjqNeDhS4PsEx","name":"Gnome Magic","type":"ability","img":"icons/magic/nature/plant-sproud-hands-dirt-green.webp","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p>Gnomes are inherently magical creatures. They can cast cantrips as if they knew each of the following powers:&nbsp;<em>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Light/Darkness]{light}</em>,&nbsp;<em>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Sound/Silence]{sound}</em>,&nbsp;<em>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Telekinesis]{telekinesis}</em>, and&nbsp;<em>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Beast Friend]{beast friend}</em> using their @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Traits]{Smarts} (or @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Arcane Backgrounds]{arcane skill} if they have one). They have 1 @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Arcane Backgrounds]{Power Point} for activating these cantrips, regained as usual. Gnomes with an Arcane Background or Mystic Power&nbsp; or Dragonmark add their bonus @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Arcane Backgrounds]{Power Point} to their pool but must still learn the spells if they wish to cast them normally.</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"subtype":"special","grantsPowers":true},"effects":[],"folder":"UUZJk5Z5jpjqw5rC","sort":400000,"permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"flags":{"journal-links":{},"core":{"sourceId":"Item.wgvTOJ8MnESHB6rQ"}}},{"_id":"1IK9S7J34ibAK8G4","name":"Light (Cantrips Only)","type":"power","img":"icons/magic/light/torch-fire-orange.webp","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p><strong>School:&nbsp;</strong>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Schools of Magic]{Evocation}</p>\n<p><em>Light </em>creates bright @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Illumination]{illumination} in a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Area Effect Attacks]{Large Blast Template}. With a raise, the light can be focused into a 5&Prime; (10 yard) beam as well.</p>\n<p><em>Darkness </em>blocks @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Illumination]{illumination}&nbsp;in an area the size of a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Area Effect Attacks]{Large Blast Template}, making the area Dark, or Pitch Darkness with a raise (see @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Illumination]{Illumination}).</p>\n<p>If <em>light </em>and <em>darkness </em>overlap, they create a patch of @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Illumination]{Dim light} (&minus;2).</p>\n<p><strong>Helpful Links:</strong> @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Using Magic]{Using Magic} - @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Power Modifiers]{Power Modifiers}</p>\n<h3>@Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Power Modifiers]{Modifiers}</h3>\n<ul class=\"red-bullet-list\">\n<li class=\"star\"><strong>Area Effect (+2): </strong>The <em>light</em> expands to the caster&rsquo;s @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Traits]{Smarts} in radius, with a Range of @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Traits]{Smarts} &times;2. The light is sunlight and has the same effect on certain creatures (such as vampires) as natural sunlight.</li>\n<li class=\"star\"><strong>True Darkness (+2):</strong> The <em>darkness</em> blocks @Compendium[savage-eberron-bestiary.savage-eberron-bestiary-abilities.Infravision]{Infravision}, @Compendium[savage-eberron-bestiary.savage-eberron-bestiary-abilities.Low Light Vision]{Low Light Vision}, and @Compendium[savage-eberron-bestiary.savage-eberron-bestiary-abilities.Darkvision]{Darkvision}. It has no effect on magical sight such as <em>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Detect/Conceal Arcana]{detect arcana}</em>.</li>\n<li><strong>Mobile (+1):</strong> The caster can move the area of effect up to his @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Arcane Backgrounds]{arcane skill} die type each @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Actions]{round} after casting, or attach it to an inanimate object when first cast.&nbsp;</li>\n</ul>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"equippable":false,"equipped":true,"actions":{"skill":"Performance","skillMod":"","dmgMod":"","additional":{}},"rank":"Novice","pp":"2","damage":"","range":"Smarts","duration":"10 minutes","trapping":"Illusionary torch, sunlight, darkness, thick fogs","arcane":"Gnome Magic","skill":"","modifiers":[]},"effects":[],"folder":"8NyF3ZLDhkqHw0IP","sort":2300000,"permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"flags":{"cf":null,"journal-links":{},"core":{"sourceId":"Item.gEg0cmKVXZN0LEYt"}}},{"_id":"LOOuzkdblxBCfEXu","name":"Sound (Cantrips Only)","type":"power","img":"icons/magic/sonic/scream-wail-shout-teal.webp","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p><strong>School:&nbsp;</strong>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Schools of Magic]{Illusion}</p>\n<p><em>Sound </em>mimics any known sound or voice, emanating from a point of origin within @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Range]{Range} at a volume up to the sound of a loud shout. If used as a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Test]{Test}, the defender @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{opposes} the casting roll with @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Traits]{Smarts}.</p>\n<p><em>Silence </em>does the opposite, muting all sound up to a loud shout within a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Area Effect Attacks]{Large Blast Template}. This subtracts 4 from @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Notice]{Notice} rolls made by those inside the area of effect, as well as anyone trying to hear sounds made from within. A @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{raise} completely mutes all sound inside the template&mdash;such @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Notice]{Notice} rolls automatically fail.</p>\n<p><strong>Helpful Links:</strong> @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Using Magic]{Using Magic} - @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Power Modifiers]{Power Modifiers}</p>\n<h3>@Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Power Modifiers]{Modifiers}</h3>\n<ul class=\"red-bullet-list\">\n<li><strong>Greater Sound/Silence</strong><strong> (+1):</strong> The @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Traits]{Smarts} roll made to resist a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Test]{Test} (or Targeted modifier) is made at &minus;2.</li>\n<li><strong>Mobile (+1):</strong> The caster can move the area of effect up to his @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Arcane Backgrounds]{arcane skill} die type each @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Actions]{round}.</li>\n<li><strong>Targeted (+0):</strong> Instead of casting <em>silence </em>in an @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Area Effect Attacks]{area of effect}, the caster may instead target individuals in @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Range]{Range} for 1 @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Arcane Backgrounds]{Power Point} each. Unwilling targets resist with @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Traits]{Spirit} (at &minus;2 if the caster gets a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{raise}).</li>\n</ul>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"equippable":false,"equipped":true,"actions":{"skill":"Performance","skillMod":"","dmgMod":"","additional":{}},"rank":"Novice","pp":"1","damage":"","range":"Smarts ×5 (sound); Smarts (silence)","duration":"Instant (sound); 5 (silence)","trapping":"Magical effects, a brief ripple in the air, a bell or chime that starts or stops ringing","arcane":"Gnome Magic","skill":"","modifiers":[]},"effects":[],"folder":"8NyF3ZLDhkqHw0IP","sort":3500000,"permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"flags":{"cf":null,"journal-links":{},"core":{"sourceId":"Item.2XWZLvwndmibm5gP"}}},{"_id":"6LgnGbY7UalTaPqv","name":"Mage Hand (Cantrips Only)","type":"power","img":"icons/magic/light/hand-sparks-smoke-green.webp","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p><strong>School:&nbsp;</strong>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Schools of Magic]{Transmutation}</p>\n<p><em>Telekinesis </em>is the ability to move objects or creatures (including oneself) with arcane will. It has a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Traits]{Strength} of d10, or d12 with a raise.</p>\n<p>Unwilling opponents resist the caster&rsquo;s @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Arcane Backgrounds]{arcane skill} with an @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{opposed} @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Traits]{Spirit} roll when targeted and at the start of each of their @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Actions]{turns} afterward until they&rsquo;re released. They can be moved up to the caster&rsquo; @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Traits]{Smarts} per turn in any direction, and can be bashed into walls, ceilings, or other obstacles for Str+d6 @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Dealing Damage]{damage}.</p>\n<p>Dropped creatures suffer @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Falling]{falling damage} as usual.</p>\n<p><strong>Telekinetic Tools</strong>: A caster can wield tools (including weapons) with <em>telekinesis </em>as an action. Use the caster&rsquo;s relevant @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Traits]{skill} when attacking in this way (not his @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Arcane Backgrounds]{arcane skill}).</p>\n<p><strong>Helpful Links:</strong> @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Using Magic]{Using Magic} - @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Power Modifiers]{Power Modifiers}</p>\n<h3>@Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Power Modifiers]{Modifiers}</h3>\n<ul class=\"red-bullet-list\">\n<li class=\"star\"><strong>Power (+3): </strong>The Strength of telekinesis is d12, or d12 + 2 with a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{raise}. Objects weighing 1,000 pounds or more automatically deal @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Heavy Weapon (HW)]{Heavy} @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Dealing Damage]{Damage} when used as weapons.</li>\n</ul>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"equippable":false,"equipped":true,"actions":{"skill":"Performance","skillMod":"","dmgMod":"","additional":{}},"rank":"Seasoned","pp":"5","damage":"","range":"Smarts x2","duration":"5","trapping":"A wave of the hand, magic wand, steely gaze","arcane":"Gnome Magic","skill":"","modifiers":[]},"effects":[],"folder":"ISCYYNpA2xp2iRN8","sort":100001,"permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"flags":{"cf":null,"journal-links":{},"core":{"sourceId":"Item.KLsRF4Gf0QBakUZu"}}},{"_id":"JQ5qQ1ibkZZqIIEf","name":"Beast Friend (Cantrips Only)","type":"power","img":"icons/environment/creatures/horses.webp","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p><strong>School:&nbsp;</strong>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Schools of Magic]{Enchantment}</p>\n<p>This spell allows an individual to speak with and guide the actions of nature&rsquo;s beasts. The cost to cast is equal to the sum of their @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Size and Scale]{Size} (minimum 1 per creature). Controlling five @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-bestiary.Dog / Wolf]{wolves} (Size &minus;1) costs 5 points (remember the minimum cost of 1), for example. Controlling a rhino (Size 5) costs 5 points.</p>\n<p>@Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{Success} means the creatures obey simple commands, like a well-trained dog. They attack foes and endanger their lives for their master. A @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{raise} on the arcane skill roll means the beasts are more obedient. They won&rsquo;t kill themselves but overcome their natural fears to follow their orders.</p>\n<p>@Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-bestiary.Swarm]{Swarms} can also be controlled. Small Swarms cost 1 point, Medium Swarms cost 2, and Large Swarms cost 3.</p>\n<p><em> Beast friend</em> works only on natural creatures with animal intelligence, not humanoids, and has no effect on conjured, magical, or otherwise &ldquo;unnatural&rdquo; animals.</p>\n<p><strong>Helpful Links:</strong> @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Using Magic]{Using Magic} - @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Power Modifiers]{Power Modifiers}</p>\n<h3>@Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Power Modifiers]{Modifiers}</h3>\n<ul class=\"red-bullet-list\">\n<li class=\"star\"><strong>Bestiarium (+2):</strong> The caster may affect magical and mythical beasts with animal intelligence.</li>\n<li><strong>Duration (+1):</strong> The base Duration increases to 30 minutes per rank.</li>\n<li><strong>Mind Rider (+1):</strong> The caster can communicate and sense through any of the beasts they've befriended.</li>\n</ul>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"equippable":false,"equipped":true,"actions":{"skill":"Performance","skillMod":"","dmgMod":"","additional":{}},"rank":"Novice","pp":"Special","damage":"","range":"Smarts","duration":"10 minutes","trapping":"The caster concentrates and gestures with his hands.","arcane":"Gnome Magic","skill":"","modifiers":[]},"effects":[],"folder":"8NyF3ZLDhkqHw0IP","sort":400000,"permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"flags":{"cf":null,"journal-links":{},"core":{"sourceId":"Item.YL9RGHSkkkLJEF2f"}}},{"_id":"xYBLzjuJIOtAZQFx","name":"Dirge of Haunting","type":"power","img":"icons/creatures/magical/spirit-fear-energy-pink.webp","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p><strong>School:&nbsp;</strong>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Schools of Magic]{Necromancy}</p>\n<p>This power causes overwhelming dread and horror. The target makes a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Fear]{Fear} roll. @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Wild Cards and Extras]{Extras} who fail are @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-tables.Fear Table]{Panicked} and @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Wild Cards and Extras]{Wild Cards} roll on the @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-macros.Fear Table]{Fear Table}. If the power is cast with a raise, the Fear roll is at &minus;2 and Wild Cards add +2 to @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-macros.Fear Table]{Fear Table} results.</p>\n<p><strong>Helpful Links:</strong> @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Using Magic]{Using Magic} - @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Power Modifiers]{Power Modifiers}</p>\n<h3>@Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Power Modifiers]{Modifiers}</h3>\n<ul class=\"red-bullet-list\">\n<li><strong>Area of Effect (+2/+3):</strong> For +2 @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Arcane Backgrounds]{Power Points} the power affects everyone in a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Area Effect Attacks]{Small} or @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Area Effect Attacks]{Medium Blast Template}. For +3 points the area of effect is increased to a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Area Effect Attacks]{Large Blast Template}.</li>\n<li class=\"star\"><strong>Greater Fear (+2): </strong>Fear rolls are made at&minus;2, or &minus;4 if cast with a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{raise}.</li>\n</ul>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"equippable":false,"equipped":true,"actions":{"skill":"Performance","skillMod":"","dmgMod":"","additional":{}},"rank":"Novice","pp":"2","damage":"","range":"Smarts","duration":"Instant","trapping":"Haunting, grating song.","arcane":"Bard","skill":"","modifiers":[]},"effects":[],"folder":"8NyF3ZLDhkqHw0IP","sort":1800000,"permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"flags":{"cf":null,"journal-links":{},"core":{"sourceId":"Item.RkKW0hhkT9E7bK1C"}}},{"_id":"1YgjVPecCPKIlsRR","name":"Hideous Laughter","type":"power","img":"icons/magic/symbols/question-stone-yellow.webp","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p><strong>School:&nbsp;</strong>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Schools of Magic]{Enchantment}</p>\n<p><em>Confusion </em>confounds all targets in a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Blast Templates]{Medium Blast Template}, making them either @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Distracted and Vulnerable]{Distracted or Vulnerable}, or both with a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{raise}. The same effect applies to all those affected. These states are removed at the end of the victims&rsquo; next turn as usual.</p>\n<p><strong>Helpful Links:</strong> @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Using Magic]{Using Magic} - @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Power Modifiers]{Power Modifiers}</p>\n<h3>@Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Power Modifiers]{Modifiers}</h3>\n<ul class=\"red-bullet-list\">\n<li><strong>Area of Effect (+0/+1):</strong>The caster can focus the <em>confusion </em>to a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Area Effect Attacks]{Small Blast Template} for no extra cost, or a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Area Effect Attacks]{Large Blast Template} for +1.</li>\n<li><strong>★ Greater Confusion (+2):</strong> On a success, targets are @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Damage Effects]{Shaken} in addition to being @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Distracted and Vulnerable]{Distracted} or @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Distracted and Vulnerable]{Vulnerable} (or both with a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{raise}). <em>Confusion </em>is a non-damaging effect and cannot cause a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Damage Effects]{Wound} on an already @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Damage Effects]{Shaken} target.</li>\n</ul>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"equippable":false,"equipped":true,"actions":{"skill":"Performance","skillMod":"","dmgMod":"","additional":{}},"rank":"Novice","pp":"2","damage":"","range":"Smarts","duration":"Instant","trapping":"Upbeat song that causes laughter.","arcane":"Bard","skill":"","modifiers":[]},"effects":[],"folder":"8NyF3ZLDhkqHw0IP","sort":1000000,"permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"flags":{"cf":null,"journal-links":{},"core":{"sourceId":"Item.fffVpphTGKxBvT6q"}}},{"_id":"nZR8GLqsdKIALaN6","name":"Sleep","type":"power","img":"icons/magic/control/sleep-bubble-purple.webp","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p><strong>School:&nbsp;</strong>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Schools of Magic]{Enchantment}</p>\n<p>Those who favor stealth or want to avoid harming their foes are drawn to this spell, which puts its victims into a deep and restful sleep.</p>\n<p>Anyone affected by <em>slumber </em>must make a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Traits]{Spirit} roll (at &minus;2 if the caster got a raise on her @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Arcane Backgrounds]{arcane skill} roll). Those who fail fall asleep for the @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Powers]{Duration} of the spell. Very loud noises or attempts to physically wake a sleeper (by shaking him, for example), grant another @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Traits]{Spirit} roll.</p>\n<p><strong>Helpful Links:</strong> @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Using Magic]{Using Magic} - @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Power Modifiers]{Power Modifiers}</p>\n<h3>@Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Power Modifiers]{Modifiers}</h3>\n<ul class=\"red-bullet-list\">\n<li><strong>Area of Effect (+2/+3):</strong>&nbsp;For +2 points the power affects everyone in a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Area Effect Attacks]{Medium Blast Template}. For +3 points the area of effect is increased to a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Area Effect Attacks]{Large Blast Template}.</li>\n</ul>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"equippable":false,"equipped":true,"actions":{"skill":"Performance","skillMod":"","dmgMod":"","additional":{}},"rank":"Seasoned","pp":"2","damage":"","range":"Smarts","duration":"One hour","trapping":"A lullaby","arcane":"Bard","skill":"","modifiers":[]},"effects":[],"folder":"ISCYYNpA2xp2iRN8","sort":100001,"permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"flags":{"cf":null,"journal-links":{},"core":{"sourceId":"Item.5bw0RKYgOReACsnM"}}},{"_id":"NOdveTlTfgwoTRRT","name":"Cane, Sword","type":"weapon","img":"icons/weapons/staves/staff-orb-feather.webp","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p>At first glance, a sword cane looks like an ordinary walking cane often decorated and carved.</p>\n<p>It is difficult to tell that a sword cane is a weapon. An observer has to study the cane's owner carefully, making a successful @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Notice]{Notice} roll at &ndash;2 (or at no penalty if the observer has the @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Danger Sense]{Danger Sense} Edge) to discern that the cane is dangerous in his hands. The wielder can make a @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Persuasion]{Persuasion} roll or @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Stealth]{Stealth} roll to avoid giving away his proficiency.</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"quantity":1,"weight":1,"price":15,"equippable":false,"equipped":true,"isVehicular":false,"mods":1,"actions":{"skill":"Fighting","skillMod":"+1","dmgMod":"","additional":{}},"damage":"@str+d6","range":"","rof":"1","ap":"0","minStr":"d6","shots":"0","currentShots":"0","ammo":"","autoReload":false},"effects":[],"folder":"tnIhNgfhxgoXoVDh","sort":200001,"permission":{"default":0,"ZvqefCj0L7TxJS56":3,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"flags":{"journal-links":{},"core":{"sourceId":"Item.QLPZVwdHPYs6Arx6"}}},{"_id":"K17UQBuvOJAiHwnd","name":"Trademark Weapon (Sword Cane)","type":"edge","img":"icons/environment/people/charge.webp","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p>The hero knows one unique weapon (Excalibur, Old Betsy, Sting) like the back of his hand. When using it, he adds +1 to his @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-skills.Athletics]{Athletics} (throwing), @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-skills.Fighting]{Fighting}, or @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-skills.Shooting]{Shooting} rolls, and +1 to @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Characters]{Parry} when readied (even if it&rsquo;s a ranged weapon).</span></p>\n<p>A fighter can take this Edge multiple times, applying it to a different weapon each time. If a Trademark Weapon is lost, he can replace it but the benefits don&rsquo;t kick in for a few days (however long the GM feels is dramatically appropriate).</span></p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Novice, skill with chosen weapon of d8+"}},"effects":[{"_id":"viA65GSpKV0IFwsX","changes":[{"key":"data.stats.parry.value","mode":2,"value":"1"}],"disabled":false,"duration":{"startTime":null},"icon":"icons/environment/people/charge.webp","label":"Trademark Readied Weapon","transfer":true,"flags":{},"tint":null}],"folder":"hsEO07bFB8oM1LJo","sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"3HvtK4sMp7flYKmT":3,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"flags":{"cf":null,"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.swade-core-rules.swade-edges.QHBtO0jmIzfl8TDE"}}},{"_id":"dsCHatrzLODMx6Fg","name":"Low Light Vision","type":"ability","img":"icons/creatures/eyes/human-single-brown.webp","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p>Low Light Vision ignores up &ndash;2 penalties for @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Illumination]{Dim and Dark Illumination}. @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Illumination]{Pitch Darkness} remains unaffected.</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"subtype":"special","grantsPowers":false},"effects":[],"folder":"kFghWjY7gP7MEqav","sort":100001,"permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"flags":{"journal-links":{},"core":{"sourceId":"Item.OL3T8otZVCkOoir3"}}},{"_id":"C84DIQsyGijZCyHU","name":"Language (Gnomish)","type":"skill","img":"icons/sundries/documents/document-letter-formal-tan.webp","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p>In some settings, such as those that focus on pulp action or &ldquo;planetary romance&rdquo; (where characters frequently travel among many strange civilizations), speaking various languages can simply be roleplayed with halting dialogue and campy accents that start out a little difficult and are quickly forgotten. The GM may ignore this skill altogether in these settings, or use the @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Multiple Languages]{Multiple Languages}&nbsp;&shy;option in the @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Setting Rules]{Setting Rules}.</p>\n<p>In more realistic settings, communication can be a major barrier that requires characters to put skill points into additional languages. In a 1980s World War Three game, for example, a group of United Nations paratroopers won&rsquo;t be able to speak with their foes unless they take Russian, Polish, or other languages common to the Warsaw Pact.</p>\n<p>If the Language skill is in use, it should be listed as Language (Spanish), Language (American Sign Language), etc. A character&rsquo;s die type also notes how fluent he is in it. (Characters start with a d8 in their own Language.)</p>\n<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<table class=\"table value-table\"><caption class=\"table-caption\">\n<h2 class=\"table-title\">Language Proficiency</h2>\n</caption>\n<tbody>\n<tr class=\"table-header-row\">\n<th class=\"table-column-header\" scope=\"col\">Skill</th>\n<th class=\"table-column-header\" scope=\"col\">Ability</th>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td>d4</td>\n<td>The character can read, write and speak common words and phrases.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>d6</td>\n<td>The speaker can carry on a prolonged but occasionally halting conversation.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>d8</td>\n<td>The character can speak fluently.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>d10</td>\n<td>The hero can mimic other dialects within the language.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>d12</td>\n<td>The speaker can masterfully recite important literary or oral works.</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>\n</div>\n<p><strong>Limited: </strong>Use whichever skill is lowest when performing an action that requires knowledge of a foreign language. @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Intimidation]{Intimidation} (if verbal), @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Persuasion]{Persuasion}, @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Research]{Research}, @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Taunt]{Taunt}, etc., are all limited by the character&rsquo;s Language skill.</p>\n<p>This limitation never applies to a character&rsquo;s native tongue.</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"attribute":"smarts","isCoreSkill":false,"die":{"sides":8,"modifier":0},"wild-die":{"sides":6}},"effects":[],"folder":"UUZJk5Z5jpjqw5rC","sort":300000,"permission":{"default":0,"3HvtK4sMp7flYKmT":3,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_nsugutrpau","path":"Skills","color":"#8c160f"},"journal-links":{},"core":{"sourceId":"Item.udHxlHKPSrGG5QjZ"}}},{"_id":"lKqp3CXbisb5umX6","name":"Language (Halfling)","type":"skill","img":"icons/sundries/documents/document-letter-formal-tan.webp","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p>In some settings, such as those that focus on pulp action or &ldquo;planetary romance&rdquo; (where characters frequently travel among many strange civilizations), speaking various languages can simply be roleplayed with halting dialogue and campy accents that start out a little difficult and are quickly forgotten. The GM may ignore this skill altogether in these settings, or use the @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Multiple Languages]{Multiple Languages}&nbsp;&shy;option in the @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Setting Rules]{Setting Rules}.</p>\n<p>In more realistic settings, communication can be a major barrier that requires characters to put skill points into additional languages. In a 1980s World War Three game, for example, a group of United Nations paratroopers won&rsquo;t be able to speak with their foes unless they take Russian, Polish, or other languages common to the Warsaw Pact.</p>\n<p>If the Language skill is in use, it should be listed as Language (Spanish), Language (American Sign Language), etc. A character&rsquo;s die type also notes how fluent he is in it. (Characters start with a d8 in their own Language.)</p>\n<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<table class=\"table value-table\"><caption class=\"table-caption\">\n<h2 class=\"table-title\">Language Proficiency</h2>\n</caption>\n<tbody>\n<tr class=\"table-header-row\">\n<th class=\"table-column-header\" scope=\"col\">Skill</th>\n<th class=\"table-column-header\" scope=\"col\">Ability</th>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td>d4</td>\n<td>The character can read, write and speak common words and phrases.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>d6</td>\n<td>The speaker can carry on a prolonged but occasionally halting conversation.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>d8</td>\n<td>The character can speak fluently.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>d10</td>\n<td>The hero can mimic other dialects within the language.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>d12</td>\n<td>The speaker can masterfully recite important literary or oral works.</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>\n</div>\n<p><strong>Limited: </strong>Use whichever skill is lowest when performing an action that requires knowledge of a foreign language. @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Intimidation]{Intimidation} (if verbal), @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Persuasion]{Persuasion}, @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Research]{Research}, @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Taunt]{Taunt}, etc., are all limited by the character&rsquo;s Language skill.</p>\n<p>This limitation never applies to a character&rsquo;s native tongue.</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"attribute":"smarts","isCoreSkill":false,"die":{"sides":6,"modifier":0},"wild-die":{"sides":6}},"effects":[],"folder":"RXzRwNmHRkixYrfR","sort":300000,"permission":{"default":0,"3HvtK4sMp7flYKmT":3,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_nsugutrpau","path":"Skills","col