ly halting conversation.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>d8</td>\n<td>The character can speak fluently.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>d10</td>\n<td>The hero can mimic other dialects within the language.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>d12</td>\n<td>The speaker can masterfully recite important literary or oral works.</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>\n</div>\n<p><strong>Limited: </strong>Use whichever skill is lowest when performing an action that requires knowledge of a foreign language. @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Intimidation]{Intimidation} (if verbal), @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Persuasion]{Persuasion}, @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Research]{Research}, @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Taunt]{Taunt}, etc., are all limited by the character&rsquo;s Language skill.</p>\n<p>This limitation never applies to a character&rsquo;s native tongue.</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"attribute":"smarts","isCoreSkill":false,"die":{"sides":6,"modifier":0},"wild-die":{"sides":6}},"effects":[],"folder":"cgfmurTJRwbCvmCc","sort":2200001,"permission":{"default":0,"3HvtK4sMp7flYKmT":3,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_qals24wpyph","path":"Skills","color":"#8c160f"},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.swade-core-rules.swade-skills.XIuR2IyQtewm5BZP"}}},{"_id":"sMQJqYunmrAYzP5A","name":"Lore","type":"skill","img":"icons/sundries/books/book-stack.webp","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p>Lore reflects knowledge and your ability to recall bits of information about history, archaeology, different Ages, legends, other continents, literature, song, poetry, and similar fields. This would also include knowledge about the more common races of the worlds.</p>\n<p>If an explorer wants to remember when the Dhakaani empire collapsed or know when the Qualabrin were destroyed on Xen'drik, this is the skill to have.</p>\n<p>A successful Lore roll reveals basic information about a topic, and a raise grants more details.</p>\n<p><em><strong>Source: Savage Eberron replaces Academics</strong></em></p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"attribute":"smarts","isCoreSkill":false,"die":{"sides":6,"modifier":0},"wild-die":{"sides":6}},"effects":[],"folder":"cgfmurTJRwbCvmCc","sort":700001,"permission":{"default":0,"ZvqefCj0L7TxJS56":3,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"flags":{"journal-links":{},"core":{"sourceId":"Item.E0BVumGwbaczoPjD"}}},{"_id":"dYfnkLV74q9n4eVu","name":"Arrogant","type":"hindrance","img":"icons/magic/holy/yin-yang-balance-symbol.webp","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\"><p>Your hero doesn&rsquo;t think he&rsquo;s the best&mdash;he knows he is. Whether it&rsquo;s swordsmanship, kung fu, or painting, few compare to his skills and he flaunts it every chance he gets. Winning isn&rsquo;t enough for this champion. He wants to dominate his opponent and prove there&rsquo;s no one better. He&rsquo;s the kind of fighter who disarms an opponent in a duel just to pick the sword up and hand it back with a smirk. Arrogant individuals look for the greatest threat in battle, hacking their way through lesser minions only because they&rsquo;re in the way.</span></p></div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"major":true},"effects":[],"folder":"1updrtPaYhKD0fRY","sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"3HvtK4sMp7flYKmT":3,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"flags":{"cf":null,"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.swade-core-rules.swade-hindrances.YpLBVlqcaIEy8oYq"}}},{"_id":"4NfflUuJjZQ7zehu","name":"Quirk (Womanizer)","type":"hindrance","img":"icons/magic/holy/yin-yang-balance-symbol.webp","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\"><p>This individual has some minor foible that is usually humorous but can occasionally cause him real trouble. A swashbuckler may always try to slash his initials on his foes, a dwarf may brag constantly about his culture, or a snobby d&eacute;butante might not eat, drink, or socialize with the lower class, for example.</span></p></div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"major":false},"effects":[],"folder":"1updrtPaYhKD0fRY","sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"3HvtK4sMp7flYKmT":3,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"flags":{"cf":null,"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.swade-core-rules.swade-hindrances.y0lUBhYHhl2LdjZZ"}}},{"_id":"qT0juD8PKGanAQyc","name":"Deception","type":"skill","img":"icons/skills/toxins/poison-skull-herbs-bottle-pink.webp","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p>Deception determines whether the hero can convincingly hide the truth, either verbally or through her actions. This deception can encompass everything from misleading others through ambiguity to telling outright lies.</p>\n<p>Typical situations include trying to fast-talk a guard, con a merchant, dull someone's suspicions with false assurances, or maintain a straight face while telling a blatant lie.</p>\n<p>Usually, a character successfully passing herself off in a disguise, or trying to impersonate the sound of someone else's voice would be a @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Performance]{Performance} check rather than a deception check.&nbsp;</p>\n<p><em><strong>Source: Savage Eberron</strong></em></p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"attribute":"spirit","isCoreSkill":false,"die":{"sides":6,"modifier":0},"wild-die":{"sides":6}},"effects":[],"folder":"cgfmurTJRwbCvmCc","sort":700001,"permission":{"default":0,"ZvqefCj0L7TxJS56":3,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"flags":{"journal-links":{},"core":{"sourceId":"Item.E0BVumGwbaczoPjD"}}}],"effects":[{"_id":"JWzHw9SU5Y4zNRJV","changes":[{"key":"data.stats.parry.value","mode":2,"value":"1"}],"disabled":true,"duration":{"startTime":28973116800},"icon":"icons/environment/people/charge.webp","label":"Trademark Readied Weapon","origin":"Actor.sLKblh4aPfMgTnut.Item.K17UQBuvOJAiHwnd","tint":null,"transfer":false,"flags":{}}],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_3a04s0jrz4j","path":"Pirates of Cyre Bestiary#/CF_SEP/NPC's","color":"#000000"}},"_id":"2OH6BHW2dWwq8OFH"}
{"name":"Crewmember","type":"npc","img":"https://assets.forge-vtt.com/5f43f8ea1a91d63438d13159/tokens/characters/nautical/token_2218.png","data":{"attributes":{"agility":{"die":{"sides":6,"modifier":0},"wild-die":{"sides":6}},"smarts":{"die":{"sides":4,"modifier":0},"wild-die":{"sides":6},"animal":false},"spirit":{"die":{"sides":6,"modifier":0},"wild-die":{"sides":6},"unShakeBonus":0},"strength":{"die":{"sides":6,"modifier":0},"wild-die":{"sides":6},"encumbranceSteps":0},"vigor":{"die":{"sides":6,"modifier":0},"wild-die":{"sides":6}}},"stats":{"speed":{"runningDie":6,"runningMod":0,"value":6},"toughness":{"value":0,"armor":0,"modifier":0},"parry":{"value":5,"modifier":0},"size":0},"details":{"biography":{"value":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p>Shipmates are ordinary sailors, the rank-and-file deckhands who keep any vessel, great or small, afloat and moving. They are alert for danger and quick on their feet, weathered by wind and wave and sun, but always with an eye for what waits beyond the horizon.</p>\n<p>Shipmates can be used as low-level marines, rivermen, bargefolk, or even swamp rats living in stilt-houses.</p>\n</div>"},"species":{"name":""},"currency":500,"wealth":{"die":6,"modifier":0,"wild-die":6},"conviction":{"value":0,"active":false},"autoCalcToughness":true,"autoCalcParry":true},"powerPoints":{},"fatigue":{"value":0,"min":0,"max":2},"wounds":{"value":0,"min":0,"max":0,"ignored":0},"advances":{"value":0,"rank":"Novice","details":""},"bennies":{"value":2,"max":2},"status":{"isShaken":false,"isDistracted":false,"isVulnerable":false,"isStunned":false,"isEntangled":false,"isBound":false},"initiative":{"hasHesitant":false,"hasLevelHeaded":false,"hasImpLevelHeaded":false,"hasQuick":false},"additionalStats":{},"wildcard":false},"token":{"flags":{"perfect-vision":{"visionRules":"default","monoVisionColor":"","sightLimit":null}},"name":"Pirate","displayName":30,"img":"https://assets.forge-vtt.com/5f43f8ea1a91d63438d13159/tokens/characters/nautical/token_*.png","tint":null,"width":1,"height":1,"scale":1,"mirrorX":false,"mirrorY":false,"lockRotation":false,"rotation":0,"vision":true,"dimSight":0,"brightSight":0,"dimLight":0,"brightLight":0,"sightAngle":0,"lightAngle":0,"lightColor":null,"lightAlpha":1,"lightAnimation":{"speed":5,"intensity":5},"actorId":null,"actorLink":false,"disposition":0,"displayBars":0,"bar1":{"attribute":""},"bar2":{"attribute":""},"randomImg":true,"alpha":1,"x":null,"y":null,"elevation":null},"items":[{"_id":"g51OdceqBLOvsYIZ","name":"Unskilled Attempt","type":"skill","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p>If a character doesn&rsquo;t have a skill for an action he&rsquo;s attempting, he rolls a d4 for his skill die (and a Wild Die if a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Wild Cards and Extras]{Wild Card}) and subtracts 2 from the total.</p>\n<p>The GM may decide certain tasks cannot be attempted unskilled, such as performing complex surgery or flying a commercial jet.</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"attribute":"agility","isCoreSkill":false,"die":{"sides":4,"modifier":"-2"},"wild-die":{"sides":6}},"sort":100000,"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_nsugutrpau","path":"Skills","color":"#8c160f"},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.swade-core-rules.swade-skills.zcn1epcU4FEJGGyI"}},"img":"icons/magic/symbols/question-stone-yellow.webp","effects":[],"folder":null,"permission":{"default":0}},{"_id":"LAGjXeGIlviM5MXX","name":"Athletics","type":"skill","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p>Athletics combines an individual&rsquo;s coordin&shy;ation with learned skills such as climbing, jumping, balancing, biking, wrestling, skiing, swimming, throwing, or catching. Characters who rely on physical power more than coordination can take the @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Brute]{Brute} Edge to link this skill to @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Traits]{Strength} instead of @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Traits]{Agility}.</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"attribute":"agility","isCoreSkill":false,"die":{"sides":6,"modifier":0},"wild-die":{"sides":6}},"sort":200000,"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_nsugutrpau","path":"Skills","color":"#8c160f"},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.swade-core-rules.swade-skills.Athletics"}},"img":"icons/magic/control/buff-strength-muscle-damage.webp","effects":[],"folder":null,"permission":{"default":0}},{"_id":"SHK9HItDWPN7ZPJN","name":"Notice","type":"skill","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p>Notice is a hero&rsquo;s general awareness and alertness. It&rsquo;s used to sense sights, sounds, tastes, and smells, spot clues, detect ambushes, spot hidden weapons on a foe, or tell if a rival is lying, frightened, happy, etc.</p>\n<p>@Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{Success} conveys basic information&mdash;the character hears movement in the forest, smells distant smoke, or senses someone isn&rsquo;t being completely truthful.</p>\n<p>A @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{raise} grants more detail, such as the direction of a sound or odor or what topic a person is avoiding or lying about.</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"attribute":"smarts","isCoreSkill":false,"die":{"sides":6,"modifier":0},"wild-die":{"sides":6}},"sort":300000,"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_nsugutrpau","path":"Skills","color":"#8c160f"},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.swade-core-rules.swade-skills.ZvwjzMLxsneptV4T"}},"img":"icons/creatures/eyes/human-single-blue.webp","effects":[],"folder":null,"permission":{"default":0}},{"_id":"sRNLdF1QqG36IxQ8","name":"Stealth","type":"skill","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p>Stealth is the ability to hide and move quietly. A simple @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{success} on a Stealth roll means the character avoids detection if enemies aren&rsquo;t particularly alert. If the character @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{fails} the roll, the enemy realizes something is amiss and begins actively searching for whatever roused them.</p>\n<p>Once foes are alerted and active, Stealth is opposed by @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Notice]{Notice} (a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{group roll} if there are many foes.</p>\n<p>The GM should apply any circumstantial penalties to @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Notice]{Notice} rolls for @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Illumination]{darkness}, @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Cover and Obstacles]{cover}, noise, distractions, and any difference in the target&rsquo;s @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Size and Scale]{Scale} (just like when attacking). Sneaking through dry leaves might subtract 2 from the Stealth roll, for example, while spotting someone in the dark uses the @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Illumination]{Illumination} penalty (&minus;4). Don&rsquo;t apply the same modifier to both rolls, however. If Stealth is at &minus;2 for the leaves, don&rsquo;t give Notice a +2 for them as well.</p>\n<p><strong>Sneak Attack: </strong> Sneaking up close enough to make a melee attack <em>always</em> requires an @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{opposed} Stealth roll versus the target&rsquo;s @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Notice]{Notice}, whether the guard is actively looking for trouble or not. If successful, the victim is @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Distracted and Vulnerable]{Vulnerable} to the attacker, but only until the attacker&rsquo;s turn ends. With a raise, the attacker has @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.The Drop]{The Drop} instead.</p>\n<p><strong>Movement:</strong> In combat, characters roll Stealth each turn as a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Actions]{free action} at the end of their move or any action the GM thinks might draw attention.</p>\n<p>Out of combat, the distance moved depends entirely on the situation. The GM might want a roll every minute if the group is sneaking around the perimeter of a defensive position, or every few miles if they&rsquo;re trying to quietly walk the path through a dark forest without alerting the creatures that live there.</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"attribute":"agility","isCoreSkill":false,"die":{"sides":4,"modifier":0},"wild-die":{"sides":6}},"sort":400000,"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_nsugutrpau","path":"Skills","color":"#8c160f"},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.swade-core-rules.swade-skills.Stealth"}},"img":"icons/magic/nature/stealth-hide-eyes-green.webp","effects":[],"folder":null,"permission":{"default":0}},{"_id":"ZSTpfYVuyj30bPk4","name":"Fighting","type":"skill","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p>Fighting covers all hand-to-hand (melee) attacks, whether it&rsquo;s with fists, axes, laser swords, or martial arts. See @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Combat]{Chapter Three} for the combat rules and the various maneuvers a warrior might attempt.</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"attribute":"agility","isCoreSkill":false,"die":{"sides":6,"modifier":0},"wild-die":{"sides":6}},"sort":600000,"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_nsugutrpau","path":"Skills","color":"#8c160f"},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.swade-core-rules.swade-skills.Fighting"}},"img":"icons/skills/melee/hand-grip-sword-white-brown.webp","effects":[],"folder":null,"permission":{"default":0}},{"_id":"SFe8t0TKOWMe1koT","name":"Language (Common)","type":"skill","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p>In some settings, such as those that focus on pulp action or &ldquo;planetary romance&rdquo; (where characters frequently travel among many strange civilizations), speaking various languages can simply be roleplayed with halting dialogue and campy accents that start out a little difficult and are quickly forgotten. The GM may ignore this skill altogether in these settings, or use the @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Multiple Languages]{Multiple Languages}&nbsp;&shy;option in the @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Setting Rules]{Setting Rules}.</p>\n<p>In more realistic settings, communication can be a major barrier that requires characters to put skill points into additional languages. In a 1980s World War Three game, for example, a group of United Nations paratroopers won&rsquo;t be able to speak with their foes unless they take Russian, Polish, or other languages common to the Warsaw Pact.</p>\n<p>If the Language skill is in use, it should be listed as Language (Spanish), Language (American Sign Language), etc. A character&rsquo;s die type also notes how fluent he is in it. (Characters start with a d8 in their own Language.)</p>\n<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<table class=\"table value-table\"><caption class=\"table-caption\">\n<h2 class=\"table-title\">Language Proficiency</h2>\n</caption>\n<tbody>\n<tr class=\"table-header-row\">\n<th class=\"table-column-header\" scope=\"col\">Skill</th>\n<th class=\"table-column-header\" scope=\"col\">Ability</th>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td>d4</td>\n<td>The character can read, write and speak common words and phrases.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>d6</td>\n<td>The speaker can carry on a prolonged but occasionally halting conversation.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>d8</td>\n<td>The character can speak fluently.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>d10</td>\n<td>The hero can mimic other dialects within the language.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>d12</td>\n<td>The speaker can masterfully recite important literary or oral works.</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>\n</div>\n<p><strong>Limited: </strong>Use whichever skill is lowest when performing an action that requires knowledge of a foreign language. @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Intimidation]{Intimidation} (if verbal), @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Persuasion]{Persuasion}, @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Research]{Research}, @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Taunt]{Taunt}, etc., are all limited by the character&rsquo;s Language skill.</p>\n<p>This limitation never applies to a character&rsquo;s native tongue.</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"attribute":"smarts","isCoreSkill":false,"die":{"sides":8,"modifier":"0"},"wild-die":{"sides":6}},"sort":700000,"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_nsugutrpau","path":"Skills","color":"#8c160f"},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.swade-core-rules.swade-skills.IoNMK5MtKODpwVjP"}},"img":"icons/sundries/documents/document-letter-formal-tan.webp","effects":[],"folder":null,"permission":{"default":0}},{"_id":"2wGuS0Zl5FyLJtOa","name":"Common Knowledge","type":"skill","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\"><p>Characters roll Common Knowledge to know people, places, and things of their world, including etiquette, geography, culture, popular technology, contacts, and customs.</p></div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"attribute":"smarts","isCoreSkill":false,"die":{"sides":4,"modifier":0},"wild-die":{"sides":6}},"sort":800000,"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_nsugutrpau","path":"Skills","color":"#8c160f"},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.swade-core-rules.swade-skills.Common Knowledge"}},"img":"icons/sundries/documents/document-official-capital.webp","effects":[],"folder":null,"permission":{"default":0}},{"_id":"RBsOqQKi50j2VM4Q","name":"Persuasion","type":"skill","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p>Persuasion is the ability to convince others to do what you want through reason, cajoling, deception, rewards, or other friendly means. Persuasion isn&rsquo;t mind control. It can change someone&rsquo;s attitude but not their goals. A bandit may let you keep a sentimental piece of jewelry with a good Persuasion roll but still takes all your other goods.</p>\n<p>When used to @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Support]{Support} allies it&rsquo;s an unopposed roll. If the target is resistant, it&rsquo;s an @JournalEntry[JBxsGv2wAoAmoCDe]{opposed} roll vs. the target&rsquo;s @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Traits]{Spirit}. The GM should modify the roll as she sees fit based on roleplaying, any pertinent @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Edges]{Edges} or @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Hindrances]{Hindrances} that affect the conversation, and the circumstances.</p>\n<p><strong>Reaction Level:</strong> How much a person is willing to cooperate depends largely on their attitude toward whoever&rsquo;s talking to them. The Game Master can decide how nonplayer characters feel based on the setting, or roll on the @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-tables.Reaction Table]{Reaction Table} if she has no preconceived notions.</p>\n<p>@Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{Success} improves the target&rsquo;s attitude one level and a raise improves it two. Further increases aren&rsquo;t generally possible in the same encounter&mdash;it takes individuals a little time to adjust their biases.</p>\n<p>@Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{Failure} means the target won&rsquo;t change his mind this scene or until the situation changes in some important way. A @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{Critical Failure} also <em>reduces</em> the target&rsquo;s attitude two levels.</p>\n<p>Only one roll should generally be allowed per interaction unless new information is revealed, a substantial reward is offered, etc.</p>\n<p><strong>Networking: </strong>Characters can also use Persuasion as a &ldquo;macro skill,&rdquo; simulating a few hours or an evening&rsquo;s time hobnobbing and socializing to gain favors or information. See @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Networking]{Networking}.</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"attribute":"spirit","isCoreSkill":false,"die":{"sides":4,"modifier":0},"wild-die":{"sides":6}},"sort":1000000,"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_nsugutrpau","path":"Skills","color":"#8c160f"},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.swade-core-rules.swade-skills.Persuasion"}},"img":"icons/skills/social/diplomacy-handshake.webp","effects":[],"folder":null,"permission":{"default":0}},{"_id":"cwPBxwLZzL3RjNfi","name":"Shooting","type":"skill","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p>Shooting covers all attempts to hit a target with a ranged weapon such as a bow, pistol, or rocket launcher (thrown weapons use @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Athletics]{Athletics}). See @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Combat]{Chapter Three} for details on ranged combat.</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"attribute":"agility","isCoreSkill":false,"die":{"sides":4,"modifier":0},"wild-die":{"sides":6}},"sort":1100000,"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_nsugutrpau","path":"Skills","color":"#8c160f"},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.swade-core-rules.swade-skills.Shooting"}},"img":"icons/skills/ranged/target-bullseye-arrow-glowing.webp","effects":[],"folder":null,"permission":{"default":0}},{"_id":"RAsB5RnqXChEqKyD","name":"Boating","type":"skill","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\"><p>Characters with this skill can handle most any boat or ship common to their setting. They also know how to handle common tasks associated with their vessel such as tying knots, rigging sails, or following currents.</p></div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"attribute":"agility","isCoreSkill":false,"die":{"sides":6,"modifier":0},"wild-die":{"sides":6}},"sort":2500000,"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_qals24wpyph","path":"Skills","color":"#8c160f"},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.swade-core-rules.swade-skills.WMWgIVDuAW4cHxj2"}},"img":"icons/environment/settlement/ship.webp","effects":[],"folder":null,"permission":{"default":0}},{"_id":"GFn2A0OT8af3Miye","name":"Repair","type":"skill","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p>Repair is the ability to craft, take apart and/or fix mechanical gadgets, vehicles, weapons, and constructs including warforged.</p>\n<p>How long a Repair roll takes is up to the DM and the complexity of the task. Success means the item is functional. A @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{raise} on the Repair roll halves the time required.</p>\n<p><strong>Constructs: </strong>Repair can be used in the @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Healing]{Healing} of warforged and other constructs @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Damage Effects]{Wounds}.</p>\n<p><strong>Crafting:&nbsp;</strong>Adventurers sometimes take time to create items from raw materials using appropriate tools. Creating an item requires appropriate raw materials costing half the item's total cost. Making something is usually resolved as an extended skill check, with each skill roll representing roughly a day's work, though this may be smaller for particularly simple jobs.</p>\n<p>The number of successes required and modifiers depend on the complexity, size, and cost of the item to be created, as well as the availability of suitable plans and tools. A critical failure on a skill roll means the work has been ruined and the raw materials wasted.</p>\n<p><strong>Tools:</strong> Characters suffer a minor penalty (&ndash;1 to &ndash;2) to their roll if they don't have access to basic tools, or a major penalty (&ndash;3 to &ndash;4) if the device requires specialized equipment.</p>\n<p><em><strong>Source: Modified for Savage Eberron</strong></em></p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"attribute":"smarts","isCoreSkill":false,"die":{"sides":4,"modifier":0},"wild-die":{"sides":6}},"sort":2600000,"flags":{"journal-links":{},"core":{"sourceId":"Item.VBAYsBHznEUKcaNv"},"cf":{"id":"temp_v8ypmxc2q0l","path":"Skills","color":"#008000"}},"img":"icons/skills/trades/smithing-tongs-metal-red.webp","effects":[],"folder":null,"permission":{"default":0}},{"_id":"iB16vP0AtkDyWqIF","name":"Baley Pin","type":"weapon","img":"icons/weapons/clubs/club-baton-blue.webp","data":{"description":"","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"quantity":1,"weight":2,"price":0.2,"equippable":false,"equipped":true,"isVehicular":false,"mods":1,"actions":{"skill":"Fighting","skillMod":"","dmgMod":"","additional":{}},"damage":"@str+d4","range":"","rof":"1","ap":"0","minStr":"d4","shots":"0","currentShots":"0","ammo":"","autoReload":false},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"flags":{"journal-links":{},"core":{"sourceId":"Item.VZDUG0uVURTjmhW2"},"cf":{"id":"temp_5rp00xv6vmg","path":"Savage Eberron Equipment#/CF_SEP/2.1. Meleee Weapons#/CF_SEP/Simple Weapons","color":"#000000"}}},{"_id":"KiKLSWJNDe5CFvKd","name":"Dagger","type":"weapon","img":"icons/weapons/daggers/dagger-double-red.webp","data":{"description":"","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"quantity":1,"weight":1,"price":2,"equippable":false,"equipped":true,"isVehicular":false,"mods":1,"actions":{"skill":"Fighting","skillMod":"","dmgMod":"","additional":{"oyxuzdjora":{"name":"Athletics (throwing)","type":"skill","rof":null,"skillMod":"","skillOverride":"Athletics","shotsUsed":null}}},"damage":"@str+d4","range":"3/6/12","rof":"1","ap":"0","minStr":"d4","shots":"0","currentShots":"0","ammo":"","autoReload":false},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"flags":{"journal-links":{},"core":{"sourceId":"Item.GxVNY83rIxMpxCqB"},"cf":{"id":"temp_5rp00xv6vmg","path":"Savage Eberron Equipment#/CF_SEP/2.1. Meleee Weapons#/CF_SEP/Simple Weapons","color":"#000000"}}},{"_id":"VgAAzRSdMK0pkmSW","name":"Unarmed Strike","type":"weapon","img":"icons/skills/melee/unarmed-punch-fist.webp","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p>See @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Unarmed Defender]{Unarmed Defender}.</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"quantity":1,"weight":0,"price":0,"equippable":false,"equipped":true,"isVehicular":false,"mods":1,"actions":{"skill":"Fighting","skillMod":"","dmgMod":"","additional":{}},"damage":"@str","range":"","rof":"1","ap":"0","minStr":"","shots":"0","currentShots":"0","ammo":"","autoReload":false},"effects":[],"folder":"651LNce8no6HR9rY","sort":100000,"permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"flags":{"journal-links":{},"core":{"sourceId":"Item.X31v8asHtqhgiaM2"}}},{"_id":"84hQCzTgYZqNFvEV","name":"Gambling","type":"skill","img":"icons/sundries/gaming/dice-pair-white-green.webp","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\"><p>Gambling is common in the saloons of the Old West, the back rooms of criminal organizations, the barracks of most armies, or the flight decks of scifi spaceships.</p>\n<p>To simulate an hour of gambling without having to roll for every single toss of the dice or hand of cards, have everyone agree on the stakes, such as $10, 10 gold coins, etc. Everyone in the game then makes a Gambling roll. The lowest total pays the highest total the difference times the stake. The next lowest pays the second highest the difference times the stake, and so on. If there&rsquo;s an odd man left in the middle, he breaks even.</p>\n<p class=\"embedded-example\"><strong>Example:</strong> Red rolls highest with a 10 and Gabe rolls lowest with a 4. The difference is 6, so Gabe pays Red 6 &times; the stake of $10, or $60.</p>\n<p><strong>Cheating: </strong>A character who cheats adds +2 to his roll. The GM may raise or lower this modifier depending on the particulars of the game or the method of cheating. If a cheater rolls a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{Critical Failure}, however, he&rsquo;s caught. The consequences depend on the circumstances and who noticed, but are usually unpleasant!</p></div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"attribute":"smarts","isCoreSkill":false,"die":{"sides":4,"modifier":0},"wild-die":{"sides":6}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_azxylmvr7yo","path":"Skills","color":"#008000"},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.swade-core-rules.swade-skills.zPegv65RzQXUbQIz"}}},{"_id":"4IhUco89Om1pE4qe","name":"Intimidation","type":"skill","img":"icons/skills/wounds/injury-face-impact-orange.webp","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p>Intimidation is the art of frightening an opponent so that he backs down, reveals information, or flees.</p>\n<p>Intimidation is an @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{opposed roll} resisted by the opponent&rsquo;s @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Traits]{Spirit}. In combat, this is a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Test]{Test}. Out of combat, a successful roll means the foe backs down for the most part, reveals some information, or slinks away when the opportunity presents itself.</p>\n<p>A @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{raise} might mean he backs down for the remainder of the scene, spills all the beans, or runs away as fast as he can.</p>\n<p>In or out of combat, a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{Critical Failure} means the target is immune to this character&rsquo;s Intimidation attempts for the remainder of this encounter!</p>\n<p><strong>Networking:</strong> Intimidation can also be used as a &ldquo;macro&rdquo; skill to simulate several hours of working the streets. See&nbsp;@Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Networking]{Networking}&nbsp;to see how to crack some heads for favors or information.</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"attribute":"spirit","isCoreSkill":false,"die":{"sides":4,"modifier":0},"wild-die":{"sides":6}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_azxylmvr7yo","path":"Skills","color":"#008000"},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.swade-core-rules.swade-skills.RrgAZp50CgQyyY6w"}}}],"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"flags":{"journal-links":{"references":{}},"cf":{"id":"temp_3a04s0jrz4j","path":"Pirates of Cyre Bestiary#/CF_SEP/NPC's","color":"#000000"}},"_id":"56twwTP4lR2skY8E"}
{"name":"Sandara Quinn","type":"npc","img":"https://assets.forge-vtt.com/5f43f8ea1a91d63438d13159/artwork-adventures/pirates-of-cyre/characters/sandara-quinn.webp","data":{"attributes":{"agility":{"die":{"sides":6,"modifier":0},"wild-die":{"sides":6}},"smarts":{"die":{"sides":6,"modifier":0},"wild-die":{"sides":6},"animal":false},"spirit":{"die":{"sides":8,"modifier":0},"wild-die":{"sides":6},"unShakeBonus":0},"strength":{"die":{"sides":6,"modifier":0},"wild-die":{"sides":6},"encumbranceSteps":0},"vigor":{"die":{"sides":6,"modifier":0},"wild-die":{"sides":6}}},"stats":{"speed":{"runningDie":"6","runningMod":0,"value":6},"toughness":{"value":0,"armor":0,"modifier":0},"parry":{"value":4,"modifier":0},"size":0},"details":{"biography":{"value":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p>Crowned with a mane of fiery red locks, Sandara looks like someone not to be crossed. Yet the smile lines at the corners of her eyes and the easy way she holds herself hint at a lighter side. She dresses to accentuate her figure, and her whole appearance speaks of the sea, from the seagull feather in her tricorne hat to the sailor tattoos on her arms and the clay pipe thrust into the corner ofher mouth.</p>\n</div>"},"species":{"name":""},"currency":500,"wealth":{"die":6,"modifier":0,"wild-die":6},"conviction":{"value":0,"active":false},"autoCalcToughness":true,"autoCalcParry":true},"powerPoints":{"value":10,"max":10,"Cleric":{"value":0,"max":0}},"fatigue":{"value":0,"min":0,"max":2},"wounds":{"value":0,"min":0,"max":3,"ignored":0},"advances":{"value":0,"rank":"Novice","details":""},"bennies":{"value":3,"max":3},"status":{"isShaken":false,"isDistracted":false,"isVulnerable":false,"isStunned":false,"isEntangled":false,"isBound":false},"initiative":{"hasHesitant":false,"hasLevelHeaded":false,"hasImpLevelHeaded":false,"hasQuick":false},"additionalStats":{},"wildcard":true},"token":{"flags":{},"name":"Blank","displayName":30,"img":"modules/etu-rules/assets/bestiary_tokens/sonya-alvarez-min.png","tint":null,"width":1,"height":1,"scale":1,"mirrorX":false,"mirrorY":false,"lockRotation":false,"rotation":0,"vision":true,"dimSight":0,"brightSight":0,"dimLight":0,"brightLight":0,"sightAngle":0,"lightAngle":0,"lightColor":null,"lightAlpha":1,"lightAnimation":{"speed":5,"intensity":5},"actorId":null,"actorLink":true,"disposition":0,"displayBars":0,"bar1":{"attribute":""},"bar2":{"attribute":""},"randomImg":false,"alpha":1},"items":[{"_id":"UZW0tLJicg0VZOp4","name":"Athletics","type":"skill","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p>Athletics combines an individual&rsquo;s coordin&shy;ation with learned skills such as climbing, jumping, balancing, biking, wrestling, skiing, swimming, throwing, or catching. Characters who rely on physical power more than coordination can take the @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Brute]{Brute} Edge to link this skill to @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Traits]{Strength} instead of @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Traits]{Agility}.</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"attribute":"agility","isCoreSkill":false,"die":{"sides":6,"modifier":0},"wild-die":{"sides":6}},"sort":100000,"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_nsugutrpau","path":"Skills","color":"#8c160f"},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.swade-core-rules.swade-skills.Athletics"}},"img":"icons/magic/control/buff-strength-muscle-damage.webp","effects":[],"folder":null,"permission":{"default":0}},{"_id":"W5lfcCNjirSPUH42","name":"Common Knowledge","type":"skill","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\"><p>Characters roll Common Knowledge to know people, places, and things of their world, including etiquette, geography, culture, popular technology, contacts, and customs.</p></div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"attribute":"smarts","isCoreSkill":false,"die":{"sides":6,"modifier":0},"wild-die":{"sides":6}},"sort":200000,"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_nsugutrpau","path":"Skills","color":"#8c160f"},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.swade-core-rules.swade-skills.Common Knowledge"}},"img":"icons/sundries/documents/document-official-capital.webp","effects":[],"folder":null,"permission":{"default":0}},{"_id":"quj5jF3vNls1j5E3","name":"Notice","type":"skill","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p>Notice is a hero&rsquo;s general awareness and alertness. It&rsquo;s used to sense sights, sounds, tastes, and smells, spot clues, detect ambushes, spot hidden weapons on a foe, or tell if a rival is lying, frightened, happy, etc.</p>\n<p>@Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{Success} conveys basic information&mdash;the character hears movement in the forest, smells distant smoke, or senses someone isn&rsquo;t being completely truthful.</p>\n<p>A @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{raise} grants more detail, such as the direction of a sound or odor or what topic a person is avoiding or lying about.</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"attribute":"smarts","isCoreSkill":false,"die":{"sides":6,"modifier":0},"wild-die":{"sides":6}},"sort":300000,"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_nsugutrpau","path":"Skills","color":"#8c160f"},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.swade-core-rules.swade-skills.ZvwjzMLxsneptV4T"}},"img":"icons/creatures/eyes/human-single-blue.webp","effects":[],"folder":null,"permission":{"default":0}},{"_id":"TOEzoo2Lf4A5JXOF","name":"Persuasion","type":"skill","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p>Persuasion is the ability to convince others to do what you want through reason, cajoling, deception, rewards, or other friendly means. Persuasion isn&rsquo;t mind control. It can change someone&rsquo;s attitude but not their goals. A bandit may let you keep a sentimental piece of jewelry with a good Persuasion roll but still takes all your other goods.</p>\n<p>When used to @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Support]{Support} allies it&rsquo;s an unopposed roll. If the target is resistant, it&rsquo;s an @JournalEntry[JBxsGv2wAoAmoCDe]{opposed} roll vs. the target&rsquo;s @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Traits]{Spirit}. The GM should modify the roll as she sees fit based on roleplaying, any pertinent @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Edges]{Edges} or @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Hindrances]{Hindrances} that affect the conversation, and the circumstances.</p>\n<p><strong>Reaction Level:</strong> How much a person is willing to cooperate depends largely on their attitude toward whoever&rsquo;s talking to them. The Game Master can decide how nonplayer characters feel based on the setting, or roll on the @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-tables.Reaction Table]{Reaction Table} if she has no preconceived notions.</p>\n<p>@Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{Success} improves the target&rsquo;s attitude one level and a raise improves it two. Further increases aren&rsquo;t generally possible in the same encounter&mdash;it takes individuals a little time to adjust their biases.</p>\n<p>@Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{Failure} means the target won&rsquo;t change his mind this scene or until the situation changes in some important way. A @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{Critical Failure} also <em>reduces</em> the target&rsquo;s attitude two levels.</p>\n<p>Only one roll should generally be allowed per interaction unless new information is revealed, a substantial reward is offered, etc.</p>\n<p><strong>Networking: </strong>Characters can also use Persuasion as a &ldquo;macro skill,&rdquo; simulating a few hours or an evening&rsquo;s time hobnobbing and socializing to gain favors or information. See @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Networking]{Networking}.</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"attribute":"spirit","isCoreSkill":false,"die":{"sides":6,"modifier":0},"wild-die":{"sides":6}},"sort":400000,"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_nsugutrpau","path":"Skills","color":"#8c160f"},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.swade-core-rules.swade-skills.Persuasion"}},"img":"icons/skills/social/diplomacy-handshake.webp","effects":[],"folder":null,"permission":{"default":0}},{"_id":"8VzaSa3EEDrMz6PR","name":"Stealth","type":"skill","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p>Stealth is the ability to hide and move quietly. A simple @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{success} on a Stealth roll means the character avoids detection if enemies aren&rsquo;t particularly alert. If the character @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{fails} the roll, the enemy realizes something is amiss and begins actively searching for whatever roused them.</p>\n<p>Once foes are alerted and active, Stealth is opposed by @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Notice]{Notice} (a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{group roll} if there are many foes.</p>\n<p>The GM should apply any circumstantial penalties to @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Notice]{Notice} rolls for @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Illumination]{darkness}, @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Cover and Obstacles]{cover}, noise, distractions, and any difference in the target&rsquo;s @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Size and Scale]{Scale} (just like when attacking). Sneaking through dry leaves might subtract 2 from the Stealth roll, for example, while spotting someone in the dark uses the @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Illumination]{Illumination} penalty (&minus;4). Don&rsquo;t apply the same modifier to both rolls, however. If Stealth is at &minus;2 for the leaves, don&rsquo;t give Notice a +2 for them as well.</p>\n<p><strong>Sneak Attack: </strong> Sneaking up close enough to make a melee attack <em>always</em> requires an @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{opposed} Stealth roll versus the target&rsquo;s @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Notice]{Notice}, whether the guard is actively looking for trouble or not. If successful, the victim is @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Distracted and Vulnerable]{Vulnerable} to the attacker, but only until the attacker&rsquo;s turn ends. With a raise, the attacker has @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.The Drop]{The Drop} instead.</p>\n<p><strong>Movement:</strong> In combat, characters roll Stealth each turn as a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Actions]{free action} at the end of their move or any action the GM thinks might draw attention.</p>\n<p>Out of combat, the distance moved depends entirely on the situation. The GM might want a roll every minute if the group is sneaking around the perimeter of a defensive position, or every few miles if they&rsquo;re trying to quietly walk the path through a dark forest without alerting the creatures that live there.</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"attribute":"agility","isCoreSkill":false,"die":{"sides":4,"modifier":0},"wild-die":{"sides":6}},"sort":500000,"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_nsugutrpau","path":"Skills","color":"#8c160f"},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.swade-core-rules.swade-skills.Stealth"}},"img":"icons/magic/nature/stealth-hide-eyes-green.webp","effects":[],"folder":null,"permission":{"default":0}},{"_id":"BQ3OOQlkZvCl1Lfb","name":"Unskilled Attempt","type":"skill","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p>If a character doesn&rsquo;t have a skill for an action he&rsquo;s attempting, he rolls a d4 for his skill die (and a Wild Die if a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Wild Cards and Extras]{Wild Card}) and subtracts 2 from the total.</p>\n<p>The GM may decide certain tasks cannot be attempted unskilled, such as performing complex surgery or flying a commercial jet.</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"attribute":"agility","isCoreSkill":false,"die":{"sides":4,"modifier":"-2"},"wild-die":{"sides":6}},"sort":1100000,"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_nsugutrpau","path":"Skills","color":"#8c160f"},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.swade-core-rules.swade-skills.zcn1epcU4FEJGGyI"}},"img":"icons/magic/symbols/question-stone-yellow.webp","effects":[],"folder":null,"permission":{"default":0}},{"_id":"uaVAhwDnUDLFZFXm","name":"Unarmed strike","type":"weapon","data":{"description":"","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"quantity":1,"weight":0,"price":0,"equippable":false,"equipped":true,"isVehicular":false,"mods":1,"actions":{"skill":"","skillMod":"","dmgMod":"","additional":{}},"damage":"@str","range":"","rof":"1","ap":"0","minStr":"","shots":"0","currentShots":"0","ammo":"","autoReload":false},"sort":1400000,"flags":{},"img":"icons/skills/melee/unarmed-punch-fist.webp","effects":[],"folder":null,"permission":{"default":0}},{"_id":"GjcL17dCtOeFUvbu","name":"Fighting","type":"skill","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p>Fighting covers all hand-to-hand (melee) attacks, whether it&rsquo;s with fists, axes, laser swords, or martial arts. See @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Combat]{Chapter Three} for the combat rules and the various maneuvers a warrior might attempt.</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"attribute":"agility","isCoreSkill":false,"die":{"sides":4,"modifier":0},"wild-die":{"sides":6}},"sort":1500000,"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_qals24wpyph","path":"Skills","color":"#8c160f"},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.swade-core-rules.swade-skills.wWiwjPlzAQU3TN9l"}},"img":"icons/skills/melee/hand-grip-sword-white-brown.webp","effects":[],"folder":null,"permission":{"default":0}},{"_id":"rnaYYVJUWiKmHIEq","name":"Religion","type":"skill","img":"icons/environment/settlement/gazebo.webp","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p>Religion reflects knowledge about ancient religions, mythic history, eccelsiastic tradition, holy symbols, undead, as well as details about all the religions of Eberron.</p>\n<p>A successful Religion roll reveals basic information about a topic, and a raise grants more details.</p>\n<p><em><strong>Source: Savage Eberron</strong></em></p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"attribute":"smarts","isCoreSkill":false,"die":{"sides":6,"modifier":0},"wild-die":{"sides":6}},"effects":[],"folder":"vdiWDU7Bqdgk8RH2","sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"flags":{"journal-links":{},"core":{"sourceId":"Item.HdShAatiWIBLgv8z"},"cf":null}},{"_id":"W863k0rTlzte6ZVH","name":"Shooting","type":"skill","img":"icons/skills/ranged/target-bullseye-arrow-glowing.webp","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p>Shooting covers all attempts to hit a target with a ranged weapon such as a bow, pistol, or rocket launcher (thrown weapons use @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Athletics]{Athletics}). See @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Combat]{Chapter Three} for details on ranged combat.</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"attribute":"agility","isCoreSkill":false,"die":{"sides":6,"modifier":0},"wild-die":{"sides":6}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"3HvtK4sMp7flYKmT":3,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_qals24wpyph","path":"Skills","color":"#8c160f"},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.swade-core-rules.swade-skills.sOHfVvBDhe3Oy3r1"}}},{"_id":"1ZGuEqSa5Nq3W0rL","name":"Healing","type":"skill","img":"icons/magic/nature/root-vine-caduceus-healing.webp","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p>Healing has multiple uses, from treating @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Damage Effects]{Wounds} to diagnosing diseases and analyzing certain kinds of forensic evidence.</p>\n<p>See @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Healing]{Healing} for rules on mending and treating @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Damage Effects]{Wounds}, and @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Hazards]{Hazards} for treatment of disease or poison.</p>\n<p><strong>Forensics: </strong> Healing can also be used to analyze evidence that relates to anatomical trauma, including cause and time of death, angle of attack, and similar matters. @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{Success} provides basic information and a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{raise} increases the details uncovered.</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"attribute":"smarts","isCoreSkill":false,"die":{"sides":6,"modifier":0},"wild-die":{"sides":6}},"effects":[],"folder":"vdiWDU7Bqdgk8RH2","sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"3HvtK4sMp7flYKmT":3,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"flags":{"cf":null,"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.swade-core-rules.swade-skills.Dc50EUXxlsJl7sph"}}},{"_id":"TxsVd8wipyZmfMJ8","name":"Performance","type":"skill","img":"icons/tools/instruments/lute-gold-brown.webp","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p>A good entertainer can lift the spirits, rally a crowd to action, or simply earn a few bucks from the locals. Specifics depend on the situation, setting, and how well the character is known in the area.</p>\n<p>Performance covers singing, acting, playing an instrument, or similar tasks that require an audience to appreciate.</p>\n<p><strong>Raising Funds:</strong> The amount of money a character can raise by performing is extremely subjective, but as a general rule a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{successful} performance raises 20% of the setting's @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Characters]{Starting Funds} with a success and 30% with a raise. The GM can multiply this amount by the performer's @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Advancement]{Rank} if she feels it's appropriate. These numbers work for typical performers who might be known in a small establishment or area. Larger performances can greatly boost the performer's fee, but also require more time, energy, and setup.</p>\n<p><strong>Deception: </strong>Performance can be used instead of @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Persuasion]{Persuasion} if the character is attempting to deceive, bluff, or disguise herself and the GM agrees it makes sense in the context of the situation.</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"attribute":"spirit","isCoreSkill":false,"die":{"sides":4,"modifier":0},"wild-die":{"sides":6}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"3HvtK4sMp7flYKmT":3,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_qals24wpyph","path":"Skills","color":"#8c160f"},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.swade-core-rules.swade-skills.SJ1nN0CmOHNQhfOQ"}}},{"_id":"c4D6T1p2nkLcWMrM","name":"Faith","type":"skill","img":"icons/magic/holy/prayer-hands-glowing-yellow.webp","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\"><p>Faith is the arcane skill required for @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Arcane Background (Miracles)]{Arcane Background (Miracles)}.</p></div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"attribute":"spirit","isCoreSkill":false,"die":{"sides":8,"modifier":0},"wild-die":{"sides":6}},"effects":[],"folder":"cgfmurTJRwbCvmCc","sort":1600001,"permission":{"default":0,"3HvtK4sMp7flYKmT":3,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_qals24wpyph","path":"Skills","color":"#8c160f"},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.swade-core-rules.swade-skills.YI5rxzYzsqXwAo9A"}}},{"_id":"2CDspjGP8uyG3SpP","name":"Lore","type":"skill","img":"icons/sundries/books/book-stack.webp","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p>Lore reflects knowledge and your ability to recall bits of information about history, archaeology, different Ages, legends, other continents, literature, song, poetry, and similar fields. This would also include knowledge about the more common races of the worlds.</p>\n<p>If an explorer wants to remember when the Dhakaani empire collapsed or know when the Qualabrin were destroyed on Xen'drik, this is the skill to have.</p>\n<p>A successful Lore roll reveals basic information about a topic, and a raise grants more details.</p>\n<p><em><strong>Source: Savage Eberron replaces Academics</strong></em></p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"attribute":"smarts","isCoreSkill":false,"die":{"sides":4,"modifier":0},"wild-die":{"sides":6}},"effects":[],"folder":"cgfmurTJRwbCvmCc","sort":700001,"permission":{"default":0,"ZvqefCj0L7TxJS56":3,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"flags":{"journal-links":{},"core":{"sourceId":"Item.E0BVumGwbaczoPjD"}}},{"_id":"KHgBtd5M9NUusdTx","name":"Cleric","type":"edge","img":"icons/environment/people/cleric-grey.webp","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p>In faith and the miracles of the divine, many find a greater purpose. Called to serve powers beyond most mortal understanding, all priests provide for the spiritual needs of their people. More than mere preachers, clerics serve as emissaries of their gods. These ecclesiastics vow to spread the tenets, knowledge, and truth of their faith.</p>\n<p>While clerics of different faiths may share similar abilities, they prove as different from one another as the divinities they serve. Some offer healing and redemption, others judge law and truth, and still others spread conflict and corruption.</p>\n<p>Clerics gain the following abilities:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Arcane Background (Cleric)]{Arcane Background (Cleric)}</li>\n<li>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Channel Energy]{Channel Energy}</li>\n<li>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Vow of Faith]{Vow of Faith}</li>\n</ul>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Novice, Spirit d6+, Religion d6+"}},"effects":[],"folder":"RlvFYBE8BDHKhq30","sort":100000,"permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"flags":{"journal-links":{},"core":{"sourceId":"Item.ouw6W4r3rYVJQIqG"}}},{"_id":"SLN29WvDxuI2HQZj","name":"Arcane Background (Cleric)","type":"edge","img":"icons/environment/people/cleric-grey.webp","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Arcane Background (Cleric)]{Arcane Background (Cleric)}</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"isArcaneBackground":true,"requirements":{"value":"Novice"}},"effects":[],"folder":"RlvFYBE8BDHKhq30","sort":600000,"permission":{"default":2,"ZvqefCj0L7TxJS56":3,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"flags":{"journal-links":{},"core":{"sourceId":"Item.E6yOW6PfzFWgHuPD"}}},{"_id":"DAsE1IVRzYWoDYcF","name":"Channel Energy","type":"edge","img":"icons/environment/people/cleric-grey.webp","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p>Clerics can cast the <em>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Healing]{healing}</em> power at a Range of Spirit rather than Touch. Their&nbsp;<em>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Healing]{healing}</em>&nbsp;power also has the Additional Recipients Power Modifier, allowing them to heal nearby allies at the cost of one extra Power Point each.</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Cleric"}},"effects":[],"folder":"RlvFYBE8BDHKhq30","sort":200000,"permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"flags":{"journal-links":{},"core":{"sourceId":"Item.VO5siJEofAatX9Hf"}}},{"_id":"PJzJ4ctYtPx62CSN","name":"Luck","type":"edge","img":"icons/environment/people/group.webp","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p>The adventurer seems to be blessed by fate, karma, the gods, or whatever external forces he believes in (or believe in him!). </span></p>\n<p>He draws one extra @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Bennies]{Benny} at the beginning of each game session, allowing him to succeed at important tasks more often than most, and survive incredible dangers.</span></p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Novice"}},"effects":[],"folder":"EnpCvbp1xbBRZIf1","sort":1700000,"permission":{"default":0,"3HvtK4sMp7flYKmT":3,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"flags":{"cf":null,"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.swade-core-rules.swade-edges.p00apKW5V2grVRw2"}}},{"_id":"FnP3wCwHjboMpiiN","name":"Curious","type":"hindrance","img":"icons/magic/holy/yin-yang-balance-symbol.webp","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\"><p>It killed the cat, and it might kill your warrior as well. Curious characters have to check out everything and always want to know what&rsquo;s behind a potential mystery or secret.</span></p></div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"major":true},"effects":[],"folder":"1updrtPaYhKD0fRY","sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"3HvtK4sMp7flYKmT":3,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"flags":{"cf":null,"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.swade-core-rules.swade-hindrances.GULnKHGQlhgqZ7Hn"}}},{"_id":"vDW5GGdBlqh54eDp","name":"Vow of Faith (Protect nature and the seas)","type":"hindrance","img":"icons/environment/people/cleric-grey.webp","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p>Clerics have a major vow to serve their deity. Those who wish to draw energy from divine sources must uphold the principles of their @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Domains]{Domains}.</p>\n<p>If the cleric violates their deity's trust (DM's call) the cleric subtracts 2 from @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Faith]{Faith} rolls for a week. Truly sacrilegious acts might rob her of her powers entirely until she atones in some way.</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"major":true},"effects":[],"folder":"RlvFYBE8BDHKhq30","sort":700000,"permission":{"default":0,"3HvtK4sMp7flYKmT":3,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_paujlrjlvl","path":"Hindrances","color":"#8c160f"},"journal-links":{},"core":{"sourceId":"Item.YwWXS95TWbqBIyLE"}}},{"_id":"GyeY5S2b007h2GaH","name":"Crossbow, Light","type":"weapon","img":"icons/weapons/crossbows/crossbow-simple-black.webp","data":{"description":null,"notes":"Hand-drawn","additionalStats":{},"quantity":1,"weight":5,"price":25,"equippable":false,"equipped":true,"isVehicular":false,"mods":1,"actions":{"skill":"Shooting","skillMod":"","dmgMod":"","additional":{}},"damage":"2d6","range":"10/20/40","rof":"1","ap":"2","minStr":"d6","shots":"20","currentShots":"20","ammo":"","autoReload":false},"effects":[],"folder":"zDTfLKxjq2F4ebrl","sort":600001,"permission":{"default":0,"ZvqefCj0L7TxJS56":3,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"flags":{"journal-links":{},"core":{"sourceId":"Item.cXYnSp8h1A8bQn7H"}}},{"_id":"SrGZN1xogifXjNxQ","name":"Rapier (mwk)","type":"weapon","img":"icons/weapons/swords/scimitar-guard-gold.webp","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p>@Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Parry]{Parry} +1</p>\n</div>","notes":"Parry +1","additionalStats":{},"quantity":1,"weight":3,"price":325,"equippable":false,"equipped":true,"isVehicular":false,"mods":1,"actions":{"skill":"Fighting","skillMod":"","dmgMod":"","additional":{}},"damage":"@str+d4","range":"","rof":"1","ap":"1","minStr":"d4","shots":"0","currentShots":"0","ammo":"","autoReload":false},"effects":[{"_id":"2K9kgErsmseqr2AH","flags":{},"changes":[{"key":"data.stats.parry.modifier","mode":2,"value":"1"}],"disabled":false,"duration":{"startTime":null},"icon":"icons/weapons/swords/scimitar-guard-gold.webp","label":"Rapier Parry Bonus","tint":null,"transfer":true}],"folder":"wKOO5vrTtLr5gJsf","sort":700001,"permission":{"default":0,"ZvqefCj0L7TxJS56":3,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"flags":{"journal-links":{},"core":{"sourceId":"Item.yPRx9vOmWYL1MgBF"}}},{"_id":"oEICVIuh21SDMqCp","name":"Dagger","type":"weapon","img":"icons/weapons/daggers/dagger-double-red.webp","data":{"description":"","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"quantity":1,"weight":1,"price":2,"equippable":false,"equipped":true,"isVehicular":false,"mods":1,"actions":{"skill":"Fighting","skillMod":"","dmgMod":"","additional":{"oyxuzdjora":{"name":"Athletics (throwing)","type":"skill","rof":null,"skillMod":"","skillOverride":"Athletics","shotsUsed":null}}},"damage":"@str+d4","range":"3/6/12","rof":"1","ap":"0","minStr":"d4","shots":"0","currentShots":"0","ammo":"","autoReload":false},"effects":[],"folder":"ofLOMYgHLqfG1MyP","sort":400001,"permission":{"default":0,"ZvqefCj0L7TxJS56":3,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"flags":{"journal-links":{},"core":{"sourceId":"Item.GxVNY83rIxMpxCqB"}}},{"_id":"tlD3nDmoApkuFlOI","name":"Waters of Life","type":"power","img":"icons/magic/life/heart-area-circle-red-green.webp","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p><strong>School:&nbsp;</strong>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Schools of Magic]{Conjuration}</p>\n<p><em>Healing </em>removes @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Damage Effects]{Wounds} less than an hour old. A @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{success} removes one Wound, and a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{raise} removes two. The power may be cast additional times to remove additional Wounds within that hour and as long as the healer has enough @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Arcane Backgrounds]{Power Points}.</p>\n<p>For @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Wild Cards and Extras]{Extras}, the GM must first determine if the ally is still alive (see @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Healing]{Aftermath}). If so, a successful arcane skill roll returns the ally to action (@Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Damage Effects]{Shaken} if it matters).</p>\n<p><strong>Helpful Links:</strong> @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Using Magic]{Using Magic} - @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Power Modifiers]{Power Modifiers}</p>\n<h3>@Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Power Modifiers]{Modifiers}</h3>\n<ul class=\"red-bullet-list\">\n<li><strong>Greater Healing (+10):</strong> <em>Greater healing</em> can restore any @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Damage Effects]{Wound}, including those more than an hour old.</li>\n<li><strong>Crippling Injuries (+20):</strong> The power can heal a permanent @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-tables.Injury Table]{Crippling Injury} (see @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Damage Effects]{Incapacitation}). This requires an hour of preparation and only one casting is permitted per injury. If it @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{fails}, this caster cannot <em>heal </em>that particular injury (but somoene else may try). If successful, the subject is @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Fatigue]{Exhausted} for 24 hours.</li>\n<li class=\"star\"><strong>Mass Healing (+2/+3):</strong> For a +2 @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Arcane Backgrounds]{Power Points}, healing affects all allies within a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Blast Templates]{Medium Blast Template} centered on the caster (or a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Blast Templates]{Large Blast Template} for +3).</li>\n<li><strong>Neutralize Poison or Disease (+1):</strong> A successful <em>healing&nbsp;</em>roll negates any @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Poison]{poison} or @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Disease]{disease}. If the poison or disease has a bonus or penalty associated with it, the modifier applies to the @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Arcane Backgrounds]{arcane skill} roll as well.</li>\n</ul>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"equippable":false,"equipped":true,"actions":{"skill":"Faith","skillMod":"","dmgMod":"","additional":{}},"rank":"Novice","pp":"3","damage":"","range":"Touch","duration":"Instant","trapping":"Using water to heal wounds","arcane":"","skill":"","modifiers":[]},"effects":[],"folder":"8NyF3ZLDhkqHw0IP","sort":2000000,"permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"flags":{"cf":null,"journal-links":{},"core":{"sourceId":"Item.L3HoTKUKSXvZNAqa"}}},{"_id":"BjEQUAm7nhUjq2o7","name":"Obscuring Mist","type":"power","img":"icons/magic/light/torch-fire-orange.webp","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p><strong>School:&nbsp;</strong>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Schools of Magic]{Evocation}</p>\n<p><em>Light </em>creates bright @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Illumination]{illumination} in a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Area Effect Attacks]{Large Blast Template}. With a raise, the light can be focused into a 5&Prime; (10 yard) beam as well.</p>\n<p><em>Darkness </em>blocks @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Illumination]{illumination}&nbsp;in an area the size of a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Area Effect Attacks]{Large Blast Template}, making the area Dark, or Pitch Darkness with a raise (see @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Illumination]{Illumination}).</p>\n<p>If <em>light </em>and <em>darkness </em>overlap, they create a patch of @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Illumination]{Dim light} (&minus;2).</p>\n<p><strong>Helpful Links:</strong> @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Using Magic]{Using Magic} - @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Power Modifiers]{Power Modifiers}</p>\n<h3>@Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Power Modifiers]{Modifiers}</h3>\n<ul class=\"red-bullet-list\">\n<li class=\"star\"><strong>Area Effect (+2): </strong>The <em>light</em> expands to the caster&rsquo;s @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Traits]{Smarts} in radius, with a Range of @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Traits]{Smarts} &times;2. The light is sunlight and has the same effect on certain creatures (such as vampires) as natural sunlight.</li>\n<li class=\"star\"><strong>True Darkness (+2):</strong> The <em>darkness</em> blocks @Compendium[savage-eberron-bestiary.savage-eberron-bestiary-abilities.Infravision]{Infravision}, @Compendium[savage-eberron-bestiary.savage-eberron-bestiary-abilities.Low Light Vision]{Low Light Vision}, and @Compendium[savage-eberron-bestiary.savage-eberron-bestiary-abilities.Darkvision]{Darkvision}. It has no effect on magical sight such as <em>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Detect/Conceal Arcana]{detect arcana}</em>.</li>\n<li><strong>Mobile (+1):</strong> The caster can move the area of effect up to his @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Arcane Backgrounds]{arcane skill} die type each @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Actions]{round} after casting, or attach it to an inanimate object when first cast.&nbsp;</li>\n</ul>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"equippable":false,"equipped":true,"actions":{"skill":"Faith","skillMod":"","dmgMod":"","additional":{}},"rank":"Novice","pp":"1","damage":"","range":"Smarts","duration":"10 minutes","trapping":"Thick fog","arcane":"","skill":"","modifiers":[]},"effects":[],"folder":"8NyF3ZLDhkqHw0IP","sort":2300000,"permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"flags":{"cf":null,"journal-links":{},"core":{"sourceId":"Item.gEg0cmKVXZN0LEYt"}}},{"_id":"GJNLSbYrjlDoVAcL","name":"Calm Sea Creatures","type":"power","img":"icons/skills/social/diplomacy-handshake-yellow.webp","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p><strong>School:&nbsp;</strong>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Schools of Magic]{Enchantment}</p>\n<p>A successful arcane skill vs @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Traits]{Spirit} roll gives the caster insight into a target's basic emotions. This grants him a +1 bonus (+2 with a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{raise}) to all @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Intimidation]{Intimidation}, @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Persuasion]{Persuasion}, @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Performance]{Performance}, or @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Taunt]{Taunt} rolls against the target for the Duration of the power.</p>\n<p><em>Empathy</em> works on animals, adding +1 (+2 with a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{raise}) to @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Riding]{Riding} or other rolls to interact with the creature.</p>\n<p><strong>Helpful Links:</strong>&nbsp;@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Using Magic]{Using Magic} - @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Power Modifiers]{Power Modifiers}</p>\n<h3>@Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Power Modifiers]{Modifiers}</h3>\n<ul class=\"red-bullet-list\">\n<li><strong>Additional Recipients (+1):</strong> The power may affect more than one target for 1 additional @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Arcane Backgrounds]{Power Point} each.</li>\n<li><strong>Charm (+2): </strong>If the target is Uncooperative or Neutral, a successful casting makes him Cooperative, or Friendly with a raise. The spell is instantly broken if the caster or her allies attack the victim or her allies.</li>\n<li><strong>Duration (+1):</strong> Duration is measured in minutes instead of rounds. If the character Critically Fails any of the affected skill rolls against the target, the effect terminates immediately.</li>\n<li class=\"star\"><strong>Truth (+2):</strong> The caster knows if the target believes he's telling the truth or not.</li>\n</ul>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"equippable":false,"equipped":true,"actions":{"skill":"Faith","skillMod":"+1","dmgMod":"","additional":{}},"rank":"Novice","pp":"1","damage":"","range":"Smarts","duration":"5","trapping":"Concentration when in sight of a sea creature","arcane":"","skill":"","modifiers":[]},"effects":[],"folder":"8NyF3ZLDhkqHw0IP","sort":1500000,"permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"flags":{"cf":null,"journal-links":{},"core":{"sourceId":"Item.eAQAHjnqokcoEg0F"}}},{"_id":"5Zex12p1RS3tEFix","name":"Deception","type":"skill","img":"icons/skills/toxins/poison-skull-herbs-bottle-pink.webp","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p>Deception determines whether the hero can convincingly hide the truth, either verbally or through her actions. This deception can encompass everything from misleading others through ambiguity to telling outright lies.</p>\n<p>Typical situations include trying to fast-talk a guard, con a merchant, dull someone's suspicions with false assurances, or maintain a straight face while telling a blatant lie.</p>\n<p>Usually, a character successfully passing herself off in a disguise, or trying to impersonate the sound of someone else's voice would be a @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Performance]{Performance} check rather than a deception check.&nbsp;</p>\n<p><em><strong>Source: Savage Eberron</strong></em></p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"attribute":"spirit","isCoreSkill":false,"die":{"sides":4,"modifier":0},"wild-die":{"sides":6}},"effects":[],"folder":"cgfmurTJRwbCvmCc","sort":700001,"permission":{"default":0,"ZvqefCj0L7TxJS56":3,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"flags":{"journal-links":{},"core":{"sourceId":"Item.E0BVumGwbaczoPjD"}}},{"_id":"eyvcxPWXw8oc71zS","name":"Arcana","type":"skill","img":"icons/magic/symbols/circled-gem-pink.webp","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p>Arcana reflects knowledge about spells, artifacts, magic items, eldritch symbols, magical traditions, dragons, forbidden lore, magical beasts, analyzing alchemical compounds and other ritual paraphernalia, translate magical runes, guess what spell was cast based on physical evidence left behind, etc.</p>\n<p>A successful Arcana roll reveals basic information about a magical topic, and a raise grants more details.</p>\n<p><em><strong>Source: Savage Eberron</strong></em></p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"attribute":"smarts","isCoreSkill":false,"die":{"sides":4,"modifier":0},"wild-die":{"sides":6}},"effects":[],"folder":"cgfmurTJRwbCvmCc","sort":200001,"permission":{"default":0,"ZvqefCj0L7TxJS56":3,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"flags":{"journal-links":{},"core":{"sourceId":"Item.lr6HSv7xgo5Dsp1N"}}}],"effects":[{"_id":"reSt8fiHSfjirLvv","changes":[{"key":"data.stats.parry.modifier","mode":2,"value":"1"}],"disabled":false,"duration":{"startTime":28973116800},"icon":"icons/weapons/swords/scimitar-guard-gold.webp","label":"Rapier Parry Bonus","origin":"Actor.B0KGbgsH18F6JMvD.Item.SrGZN1xogifXjNxQ","tint":null,"transfer":false,"flags":{}}],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"flags":{"journal-links":{"references":{}},"cf":{"id":"temp_3a04s0jrz4j","path":"Pirates of Cyre Bestiary#/CF_SEP/NPC's","color":"#000000"}},"_id":"7lLpzNGV5uDjF3qL"}
{"name":"Crimson Cogward","type":"npc","img":"https://assets.forge-vtt.com/5f43f8ea1a91d63438d13159/artwork-adventures/pirates-of-cyre/characters/crimson-cogward.webp","data":{"attributes":{"agility":{"die":{"sides":6,"modifier":0},"wild-die":{"sides":6}},"smarts":{"die":{"sides":6,"modifier":0},"wild-die":{"sides":6},"animal":false},"spirit":{"die":{"sides":6,"modifier":0},"wild-die":{"sides":6},"unShakeBonus":0},"strength":{"die":{"sides":8,"modifier":0},"wild-die":{"sides":6},"encumbranceSteps":0},"vigor":{"die":{"sides":6,"modifier":0},"wild-die":{"sides":6}}},"stats":{"speed":{"runningDie":6,"runningMod":0,"value":6},"toughness":{"value":0,"armor":0,"modifier":0},"parry":{"value":6,"modifier":0},"size":0},"details":{"biography":{"value":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p>Crimson Cogward so called after the color his neck turns when he&rsquo;s angry.</p>\n<p>He wears a blue Vistani scarf tied tight around his shaven head to hide the scar left when his ear when bitten off in a bar fight.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>"},"species":{"name":""},"currency":500,"wealth":{"die":6,"modifier":0,"wild-die":6},"conviction":{"value":0,"active":false},"autoCalcToughness":true,"autoCalcParry":true},"powerPoints":{},"fatigue":{"value":0,"min":0,"max":2},"wounds":{"value":0,"min":0,"max":0,"ignored":0},"advances":{"value":0,"rank":"Novice","details":""},"bennies":{"value":2,"max":2},"status":{"isShaken":false,"isDistracted":false,"isVulnerable":false,"isStunned":false,"isEntangled":false,"isBound":false},"initiative":{"hasHesitant":false,"hasLevelHeaded":false,"hasImpLevelHeaded":false,"hasQuick":false},"additionalStats":{},"wildcard":false},"token":{"name":"Blank NPC","img":"https://assets.forge-vtt.com/5f43f8ea1a91d63438d13159/tokens/bestiary/monstrous%20humanoid/harpy-*.png","displayName":30,"actorLink":false,"width":1,"height":1,"scale":1,"mirrorX":false,"mirrorY":false,"lockRotation":false,"rotation":0,"alpha":1,"vision":true,"dimSight":0,"brightSight":0,"dimLight":0,"brightLight":0,"sightAngle":0,"lightAngle":0,"lightAlpha":0.25,"lightAnimation":{"speed":5,"intensity":5},"disposition":-1,"displayBars":20,"bar1":{"attribute":""},"bar2":{"attribute":""},"flags":{"perfect-vision":{"visionRules":"default","monoVisionColor":"","sightLimit":null}},"randomImg":true,"actorId":null,"tint":null,"lightColor":null,"x":null,"y":null,"elevation":null},"items":[{"_id":"Bf0NpaRHtHmfrLb3","name":"Athletics","type":"skill","img":"icons/magic/control/buff-strength-muscle-damage.webp","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p>Athletics combines an individual&rsquo;s coordin&shy;ation with learned skills such as climbing, jumping, balancing, biking, wrestling, skiing, swimming, throwing, or catching. Characters who rely on physical power more than coordination can take the @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Brute]{Brute} Edge to link this skill to @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Traits]{Strength} instead of @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Traits]{Agility}.</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"attribute":"agility","isCoreSkill":false,"die":{"sides":6,"modifier":0},"wild-die":{"sides":6}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_azxylmvr7yo","path":"Skills","color":"#008000"},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.swade-core-rules.swade-skills.sAig03GZiFKqBX7p"}}},{"_id":"bJxCFLP4a8BEU0Qm","name":"Common Knowledge","type":"skill","img":"icons/sundries/documents/document-official-capital.webp","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\"><p>Characters roll Common Knowledge to know people, places, and things of their world, including etiquette, geography, culture, popular technology, contacts, and customs.</p></div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"attribute":"smarts","isCoreSkill":false,"die":{"sides":6,"modifier":0},"wild-die":{"sides":6}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_azxylmvr7yo","path":"Skills","color":"#008000"},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.swade-core-rules.swade-skills.8N1uMThntsjaUPem"}}},{"_id":"gMAJFeCm5e3Oporq","name":"Fighting","type":"skill","img":"icons/skills/melee/hand-grip-sword-white-brown.webp","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p>Fighting covers all hand-to-hand (melee) attacks, whether it&rsquo;s with fists, axes, laser swords, or martial arts. See @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Combat]{Chapter Three} for the combat rules and the various maneuvers a warrior might attempt.</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"attribute":"agility","isCoreSkill":false,"die":{"sides":8,"modifier":0},"wild-die":{"sides":6}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_azxylmvr7yo","path":"Skills","color":"#008000"},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.swade-core-rules.swade-skills.wWiwjPlzAQU3TN9l"}}},{"_id":"9coycVPgGdTGpbmh","name":"Language (Common)","type":"skill","img":"icons/sundries/documents/document-letter-formal-tan.webp","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p>In some settings, such as those that focus on pulp action or &ldquo;planetary romance&rdquo; (where characters frequently travel among many strange civilizations), speaking various languages can simply be roleplayed with halting dialogue and campy accents that start out a little difficult and are quickly forgotten. The GM may ignore this skill altogether in these settings, or use the @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Multiple Languages]{Multiple Languages}&nbsp;&shy;option in the @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Setting Rules]{Setting Rules}.</p>\n<p>In more realistic settings, communication can be a major barrier that requires characters to put skill points into additional languages. In a 1980s World War Three game, for example, a group of United Nations paratroopers won&rsquo;t be able to speak with their foes unless they take Russian, Polish, or other languages common to the Warsaw Pact.</p>\n<p>If the Language skill is in use, it should be listed as Language (Spanish), Language (American Sign Language), etc. A character&rsquo;s die type also notes how fluent he is in it. (Characters start with a d8 in their own Language.)</p>\n<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<table class=\"table value-table\"><caption class=\"table-caption\">\n<h2 class=\"table-title\">Language Proficiency</h2>\n</caption>\n<tbody>\n<tr class=\"table-header-row\">\n<th class=\"table-column-header\" scope=\"col\">Skill</th>\n<th class=\"table-column-header\" scope=\"col\">Ability</th>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td>d4</td>\n<td>The character can read, write and speak common words and phrases.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>d6</td>\n<td>The speaker can carry on a prolonged but occasionally halting conversation.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>d8</td>\n<td>The character can speak fluently.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>d10</td>\n<td>The hero can mimic other dialects within the language.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>d12</td>\n<td>The speaker can masterfully recite important literary or oral works.</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>\n</div>\n<p><strong>Limited: </strong>Use whichever skill is lowest when performing an action that requires knowledge of a foreign language. @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Intimidation]{Intimidation} (if verbal), @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Persuasion]{Persuasion}, @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Research]{Research}, @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Taunt]{Taunt}, etc., are all limited by the character&rsquo;s Language skill.</p>\n<p>This limitation never applies to a character&rsquo;s native tongue.</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"attribute":"smarts","isCoreSkill":false,"die":{"sides":8,"modifier":0},"wild-die":{"sides":6}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_azxylmvr7yo","path":"Skills","color":"#008000"},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.swade-core-rules.swade-skills.XIuR2IyQtewm5BZP"}}},{"_id":"TWqtRMnChmXvwXvN","name":"Notice","type":"skill","img":"icons/creatures/eyes/human-single-blue.webp","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p>Notice is a hero&rsquo;s general awareness and alertness. It&rsquo;s used to sense sights, sounds, tastes, and smells, spot clues, detect ambushes, spot hidden weapons on a foe, or tell if a rival is lying, frightened, happy, etc.</p>\n<p>@Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{Success} conveys basic information&mdash;the character hears movement in the forest, smells distant smoke, or senses someone isn&rsquo;t being completely truthful.</p>\n<p>A @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{raise} grants more detail, such as the direction of a sound or odor or what topic a person is avoiding or lying about.</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"attribute":"smarts","isCoreSkill":false,"die":{"sides":6,"modifier":0},"wild-die":{"sides":6}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_azxylmvr7yo","path":"Skills","color":"#008000"},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.swade-core-rules.swade-skills.yvw9bMgsrWQXuZN2"}}},{"_id":"rk3ft5Cc4sHxF5ay","name":"Stealth","type":"skill","img":"icons/magic/nature/stealth-hide-eyes-green.webp","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p>Stealth is the ability to hide and move quietly. A simple @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{success} on a Stealth roll means the character avoids detection if enemies aren&rsquo;t particularly alert. If the character @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{fails} the roll, the enemy realizes something is amiss and begins actively searching for whatever roused them.</p>\n<p>Once foes are alerted and active, Stealth is opposed by @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Notice]{Notice} (a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{group roll} if there are many foes.</p>\n<p>The GM should apply any circumstantial penalties to @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Notice]{Notice} rolls for @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Illumination]{darkness}, @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Cover and Obstacles]{cover}, noise, distractions, and any difference in the target&rsquo;s @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Size and Scale]{Scale} (just like when attacking). Sneaking through dry leaves might subtract 2 from the Stealth roll, for example, while spotting someone in the dark uses the @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Illumination]{Illumination} penalty (&minus;4). Don&rsquo;t apply the same modifier to both rolls, however. If Stealth is at &minus;2 for the leaves, don&rsquo;t give Notice a +2 for them as well.</p>\n<p><strong>Sneak Attack: </strong> Sneaking up close enough to make a melee attack <em>always</em> requires an @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{opposed} Stealth roll versus the target&rsquo;s @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Notice]{Notice}, whether the guard is actively looking for trouble or not. If successful, the victim is @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Distracted and Vulnerable]{Vulnerable} to the attacker, but only until the attacker&rsquo;s turn ends. With a raise, the attacker has @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.The Drop]{The Drop} instead.</p>\n<p><strong>Movement:</strong> In combat, characters roll Stealth each turn as a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Actions]{free action} at the end of their move or any action the GM thinks might draw attention.</p>\n<p>Out of combat, the distance moved depends entirely on the situation. The GM might want a roll every minute if the group is sneaking around the perimeter of a defensive position, or every few miles if they&rsquo;re trying to quietly walk the path through a dark forest without alerting the creatures that live there.</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"attribute":"agility","isCoreSkill":false,"die":{"sides":6,"modifier":0},"wild-die":{"sides":6}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_azxylmvr7yo","path":"Skills","color":"#008000"},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.swade-core-rules.swade-skills.z9FmdFVGOOW2kufm"}}},{"_id":"6BeiHr2FDzQaAZll","name":"Unskilled Attempt","type":"skill","img":"icons/magic/symbols/question-stone-yellow.webp","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p>If a character doesn&rsquo;t have a skill for an action he&rsquo;s attempting, he rolls a d4 for his skill die (and a Wild Die if a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Wild Cards and Extras]{Wild Card}) and subtracts 2 from the total.</p>\n<p>The GM may decide certain tasks cannot be attempted unskilled, such as performing complex surgery or flying a commercial jet.</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"attribute":"agility","isCoreSkill":false,"die":{"sides":4,"modifier":-2},"wild-die":{"sides":6}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_azxylmvr7yo","path":"Skills","color":"#008000"},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.swade-core-rules.swade-skills.1Pl2ZL8MPyKnaVEg"}}},{"_id":"N1OCwZvFIDN4gSVH","name":"Unarmed Strike","type":"weapon","img":"icons/skills/melee/unarmed-punch-fist.webp","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p>See @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Unarmed Defender]{Unarmed Defender}.</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"quantity":1,"weight":0,"price":0,"equippable":false,"equipped":true,"isVehicular":false,"mods":1,"actions":{"skill":"Fighting","skillMod":"","dmgMod":"","additional":{}},"damage":"@str","range":"","rof":"1","ap":"0","minStr":"","shots":"0","currentShots":"0","ammo":"","autoReload":false},"effects":[],"folder":"651LNce8no6HR9rY","sort":100000,"permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"flags":{"journal-links":{},"core":{"sourceId":"Item.X31v8asHtqhgiaM2"}}},{"_id":"2rgJhHIyr0HMWJAC","name":"Mean","type":"hindrance","img":"icons/magic/holy/yin-yang-balance-symbol.webp","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p>This curmudgeon is ill-tempered and disagreeable. He has trouble doing anything kind for anyone else, must be paid for his troubles, and doesn&rsquo;t accept awards or favors graciously. Besides the obvious roleplaying issues, Mean characters subtract 1 from @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-skills.Persuasion]{Persuasion} @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{rolls}.</span></p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"major":false},"effects":[],"folder":"1updrtPaYhKD0fRY","sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"3HvtK4sMp7flYKmT":3,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"flags":{"cf":null,"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.swade-core-rules.swade-hindrances.sNgSwqh2fGyM6i14"}}},{"_id":"sMzRq2ERvcGPZnIA","name":"Quirk (loner, dark moods, rages)","type":"hindrance","img":"icons/magic/holy/yin-yang-balance-symbol.webp","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\"><p>This individual has some minor foible that is usually humorous but can occasionally cause him real trouble. A swashbuckler may always try to slash his initials on his foes, a dwarf may brag constantly about his culture, or a snobby d&eacute;butante might not eat, drink, or socialize with the lower class, for example.</span></p></div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"major":false},"effects":[],"folder":"1updrtPaYhKD0fRY","sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"3HvtK4sMp7flYKmT":3,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"flags":{"cf":null,"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.swade-core-rules.swade-hindrances.y0lUBhYHhl2LdjZZ"}}},{"_id":"u6SIBWGiu10iNsTO","name":"Brawler","type":"edge","img":"icons/environment/people/charge.webp","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p>His fists hit like hammers or his talons cut like scythes. His body feels like it&rsquo;s made of stone. Brawlers increase their @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Characters]{Toughness} by 1 and roll @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Traits]{Strength} +d4 when hitting with their fists or feet (or claws if they have them). If they already have a damage die from&nbsp;</span><strong>@Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Special Ability (Claws)]{Claws}</strong>, the @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Martial Artist]{Martial Artist} Edge, etc., increase the damage die type by one instead. </span></p>\n<p>The Brawler Edge doesn&rsquo;t make the character&rsquo;s fists </span><strong>@Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Natural Weapons]{Natural Weapons}</span></strong></p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Novice, Strength d8+, Vigor d8+"}},"effects":[{"_id":"kjzlcYkuLXL4NwhC","changes":[{"key":"data.stats.toughness.value","mode":2,"value":"1"}],"disabled":false,"duration":{"startTime":null},"icon":"icons/environment/people/charge.webp","label":"Brawler","transfer":true,"flags":{},"tint":null}],"folder":"hsEO07bFB8oM1LJo","sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"3HvtK4sMp7flYKmT":3,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"flags":{"cf":null,"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.swade-core-rules.swade-edges.q5NKwGPeK9PKQdIb"}}},{"_id":"fFhVO9nuyyeWW5ub","name":"Shooting","type":"skill","img":"icons/skills/ranged/target-bullseye-arrow-glowing.webp","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p>Shooting covers all attempts to hit a target with a ranged weapon such as a bow, pistol, or rocket launcher (thrown weapons use @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Athletics]{Athletics}). See @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Combat]{Chapter Three} for details on ranged combat.</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"attribute":"agility","isCoreSkill":false,"die":{"sides":6,"modifier":0},"wild-die":{"sides":6}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_azxylmvr7yo","path":"Skills","color":"#008000"},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.swade-core-rules.swade-skills.sOHfVvBDhe3Oy3r1"}}},{"_id":"m4SZ6IfmO651jKbx","name":"Religion","type":"skill","img":"icons/environment/settlement/gazebo.webp","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p>Religion reflects knowledge about ancient religions, mythic history, eccelsiastic tradition, holy symbols, undead, as well as details about all the religions of Eberron.</p>\n<p>A successful Religion roll reveals basic information about a topic, and a raise grants more details.</p>\n<p><em><strong>Source: Savage Eberron</strong></em></p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"attribute":"smarts","isCoreSkill":false,"die":{"sides":6,"modifier":0},"wild-die":{"sides":6}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"flags":{"journal-links":{},"core":{"sourceId":"Item.HdShAatiWIBLgv8z"},"cf":{"id":"temp_azxylmvr7yo","path":"Skills","color":"#008000"}}},{"_id":"cnhn5TPjRhzOi1lz","name":"Intimidation","type":"skill","img":"icons/skills/wounds/injury-face-impact-orange.webp","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p>Intimidation is the art of frightening an opponent so that he backs down, reveals information, or flees.</p>\n<p>Intimidation is an @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{opposed roll} resisted by the opponent&rsquo;s @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Traits]{Spirit}. In combat, this is a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Test]{Test}. Out of combat, a successful roll means the foe backs down for the most part, reveals some information, or slinks away when the opportunity presents itself.</p>\n<p>A @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{raise} might mean he backs down for the remainder of the scene, spills all the beans, or runs away as fast as he can.</p>\n<p>In or out of combat, a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{Critical Failure} means the target is immune to this character&rsquo;s Intimidation attempts for the remainder of this encounter!</p>\n<p><strong>Networking:</strong> Intimidation can also be used as a &ldquo;macro&rdquo; skill to simulate several hours of working the streets. See&nbsp;@Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Networking]{Networking}&nbsp;to see how to crack some heads for favors or information.</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"attribute":"spirit","isCoreSkill":false,"die":{"sides":8,"modifier":0},"wild-die":{"sides":6}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_azxylmvr7yo","path":"Skills","color":"#008000"},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.swade-core-rules.swade-skills.RrgAZp50CgQyyY6w"}}},{"_id":"9O1VN6EyKI1oBOXu","name":"Boating","type":"skill","img":"icons/environment/settlement/ship.webp","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\"><p>Characters with this skill can handle most any boat or ship common to their setting. They also know how to handle common tasks associated with their vessel such as tying knots, rigging sails, or following currents.</p></div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"attribute":"agility","isCoreSkill":false,"die":{"sides":6,"modifier":0},"wild-die":{"sides":6}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_azxylmvr7yo","path":"Skills","color":"#008000"},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.swade-core-rules.swade-skills.WMWgIVDuAW4cHxj2"}}},{"_id":"VRabazJG4QkAhaTl","name":"Rogue","type":"edge","img":"icons/skills/melee/strike-dagger-skull-white.webp","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p>Life is an endless adventure for those who live by their wits. Ever just one step ahead of danger, rogues bank on their cunning, skill, and charm to bend fate to their favor. Never knowing what to expect, they tend to prepare for everything. Out of necessity, they become adept manipulators, agile acrobats, or shadowy stalkers. They are thieves and gamblers, fast talkers and diplomats, bandits and bounty hunters, or explorers and investigators.</p>\n<p>Although many rogues favor the opportunities of towns and cities, some embrace life on the road. They wander from place to place, meeting exotic people and facing fantastic danger in pursuit of endless riches. In the end, all rogues desire to shape their fates and live life on their own terms.</p>\n<p>Rogues gain the following abilities:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Rogue Armor Restriction (Light)]{Rogue Armor Restriction (Light)}</li>\n<li>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Skill Monkey]{Skill Monkey}</li>\n<li>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Trap Sense]{Trap Sense}</li>\n</ul>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Novice, Agility d6+, Notice d6+, Stealth d6+, Thievery d6+"}},"effects":[],"folder":"zzeiXM6YEGI9jNRc","sort":500000,"permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"flags":{"journal-links":{},"core":{"sourceId":"Item.UBXzgLMsycquNmh2"}}},{"_id":"YPZuh0XYnbGtpJP0","name":"Rogue Armor Restriction (Light)","type":"hindrance","img":"icons/skills/melee/strike-dagger-skull-white.webp","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p>Rogues are nimble and deadly acrobats. Bulky armor interferes with their abilities, so they subtract 4 from @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Traits]{Agility} and @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Traits]{Agility-based} skill rolls when wearing medium or heavy armor, or using medium or heavy shields.</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"major":false},"effects":[],"folder":"zzeiXM6YEGI9jNRc","sort":100000,"permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"flags":{"journal-links":{},"core":{"sourceId":"Item.B1jMHG6GDPNV0kYU"}}},{"_id":"qc62tiNMro0EeQiS","name":"Skill Monkey","type":"edge","img":"icons/skills/melee/strike-dagger-skull-white.webp","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p>To survive, rogues have become adept at learning all sorts of skills and trades, both to survive and to con people. Whether trained by a mentor, a guild member, a house, or the streets, rogues have picked up additional skills and training.</p>\n<p>Rogues gain two skill points they can put into increasing the die type of two of the following skills: @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Athletics]{Athletics}, @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Common Knowledge]{Common Knowledge}, @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Deception]{Deception}, @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Gambling]{Gambling}, @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Intimidation]{Intimidation}, @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Notice]{Notice}, @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Performance]{Performance}, @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Persuasion]{Persuasion}, @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Stealth]{Stealth}, or @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Thievery]{Thievery}.</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Novice, Rogue"}},"effects":[],"folder":"zzeiXM6YEGI9jNRc","sort":400000,"permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"flags":{"journal-links":{},"core":{"sourceId":"Item.Voq7KPCbPVjrEjZP"}}},{"_id":"gd6OYmWMR4a28phH","name":"Deception","type":"skill","img":"icons/skills/toxins/poison-skull-herbs-bottle-pink.webp","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p>Deception determines whether the hero can convincingly hide the truth, either verbally or through her actions. This deception can encompass everything from misleading others through ambiguity to telling outright lies.</p>\n<p>Typical situations include trying to fast-talk a guard, con a merchant, dull someone's suspicions with false assurances, or maintain a straight face while telling a blatant lie.</p>\n<p>Usually, a character successfully passing herself off in a disguise, or trying to impersonate the sound of someone else's voice would be a @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Performance]{Performance} check rather than a deception check.&nbsp;</p>\n<p><em><strong>Source: Savage Eberron</strong></em></p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"attribute":"spirit","isCoreSkill":false,"die":{"sides":4,"modifier":0},"wild-die":{"sides":6}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"flags":{"journal-links":{},"core":{"sourceId":"Item.E0BVumGwbaczoPjD"},"cf":{"id":"temp_azxylmvr7yo","path":"Skills","color":"#008000"}}},{"_id":"44v1BPzLmQyLvyZt","name":"Gambling","type":"skill","img":"icons/sundries/gaming/dice-pair-white-green.webp","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\"><p>Gambling is common in the saloons of the Old West, the back rooms of criminal organizations, the barracks of most armies, or the flight decks of scifi spaceships.</p>\n<p>To simulate an hour of gambling without having to roll for every single toss of the dice or hand of cards, have everyone agree on the stakes, such as $10, 10 gold coins, etc. Everyone in the game then makes a Gambling roll. The lowest total pays the highest total the difference times the stake. The next lowest pays the second highest the difference times the stake, and so on. If there&rsquo;s an odd man left in the middle, he breaks even.</p>\n<p class=\"embedded-example\"><strong>Example:</strong> Red rolls highest with a 10 and Gabe rolls lowest with a 4. The difference is 6, so Gabe pays Red 6 &times; the stake of $10, or $60.</p>\n<p><strong>Cheating: </strong>A character who cheats adds +2 to his roll. The GM may raise or lower this modifier depending on the particulars of the game or the method of cheating. If a cheater rolls a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{Critical Failure}, however, he&rsquo;s caught. The consequences depend on the circumstances and who noticed, but are usually unpleasant!</p></div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"attribute":"smarts","isCoreSkill":false,"die":{"sides":6,"modifier":0},"wild-die":{"sides":6}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_azxylmvr7yo","path":"Skills","color":"#008000"},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.swade-core-rules.swade-skills.zPegv65RzQXUbQIz"}}},{"_id":"8NlgE5Cpj4zyjrzl","name":"Trap Sense","type":"edge","img":"icons/skills/melee/strike-dagger-skull-white.webp","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p>Rogues are adept at spotting and defeating all but the most clever snares and traps. They get a @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Notice]{Notice} roll anytime a detectable trap is about to be sprung within 5&rdquo; (10 yards). They must have line of sight to the trap and can&rsquo;t be @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Damage Effects]{Shaken} or @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Stunned]{Stunned}. This works generally like @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Danger Sense]{Danger Sense} but applies only to mechanical and magical traps.</p>\n<p>If the trap is detected and may be @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Evasion]{Evaded}, the rogue and anyone she warns ignores 2 points of @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Evasion]{Evasion} penalties to do so. If the trap can&rsquo;t normally be @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Evasion]{Evaded}, anyone warned may @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Evasion]{Evade} at the usual &minus;2 penalty.</p>\n<p><strong>Disarming Traps:</strong> Rogues with Trap Sense ignore up 2 points of @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Thievery]{Thievery} penalties when attempting to disarm traps.</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Novice, Rogue"}},"effects":[],"folder":"zzeiXM6YEGI9jNRc","sort":400000,"permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"flags":{"journal-links":{},"core":{"sourceId":"Item.gMhsswekqyI1hslR"}}},{"_id":"ms9RvVzdF5cz5gwP","name":"Thievery","type":"skill","img":"icons/skills/social/theft-pickpocket-bribery-brown.webp","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p>Lockpicking, safecracking, picking pockets, sleight of hand, setting and disabling traps and similar acts of misdirection, sabotage, subterfuge, and manipulation are called Thievery.</p>\n<p>If used to pick a lock, crack a safe, disable a trap, or perform a simple unopposed action, @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{success} opens or disables the device, and a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{raise} does it in less time, without tripping alarms, or whatever else the GM feels is appropriate.</p>\n<p>Sleight of hand, hiding or planting an item, or picking a pocket require a simple @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{success}. If foes are actively watching the character, Thievery is @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{opposed} by @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Notice]{Notice}.</p>\n<p>The Game Master should assign @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{penalties} for particularly difficult circumstances. Picking a heavy padlock might have a &minus;4 penalty, while hiding a revolver in bulky winter clothing might grant a +1 bonus. @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{Failure} typically means the character is spotted or it takes too much time (after which the character can try again). A @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{Critical Failure} typically sets off the trap, alerts the victim, or jams the device so that it must be opened or interacted with in a different way.</p>\n<p><strong>Limited: </strong>Using Thievery on an electronic device, such as a keypad, is limited by the thief&rsquo;s @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Electronics]{Electronics} skill. Use the lowest of the two skills.</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"attribute":"agility","isCoreSkill":false,"die":{"sides":8,"modifier":0},"wild-die":{"sides":6}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_azxylmvr7yo","path":"Skills","color":"#008000"},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.swade-core-rules.swade-skills.wZbyJkisWIfmcZNt"}}},{"_id":"9tSxcdi6UUTG1Fab","name":"Cutlass","type":"weapon","img":"icons/weapons/swords/greatsword-blue.webp","data":{"description":"","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"quantity":1,"weight":2,"price":10,"equippable":false,"equipped":true,"isVehicular":false,"mods":1,"actions":{"skill":"Fighting","skillMod":"","dmgMod":"","additional":{}},"damage":"@str+d6","range":"","rof":"1","ap":"0","minStr":"d8","shots":"0","currentShots":"0","ammo":"","autoReload":false},"effects":[],"folder":"wKOO5vrTtLr5gJsf","sort":1000001,"permission":{"default":0,"ZvqefCj0L7TxJS56":3,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"flags":{"journal-links":{},"core":{"sourceId":"Item.bxg2xSSoDL9ZUkSk"}}},{"_id":"9PgSnkOzBjXa1s3y","name":"Leather Armor","type":"armor","img":"icons/equipment/chest/breastplate-layered-grey.webp","data":{"description":"","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"quantity":1,"weight":3,"price":5,"equippable":false,"equipped":true,"minStr":"d4","armor":1,"isNaturalArmor":false,"locations":{"head":false,"torso":true,"arms":true,"legs":false}},"effects":[],"folder":"XQoSmfkzvuK8FNo1","sort":100000,"permission":{"default":0,"ZvqefCj0L7TxJS56":3,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"flags":{"journal-links":{},"core":{"sourceId":"Item.PRPRsNmJyfvoy6hH"}}},{"_id":"MEOep7SQghsREc2S","name":"Dagger","type":"weapon","img":"icons/weapons/daggers/dagger-double-red.webp","data":{"description":"","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"quantity":1,"weight":1,"price":2,"equippable":false,"equipped":true,"isVehicular":false,"mods":1,"actions":{"skill":"Fighting","skillMod":"","dmgMod":"","additional":{"oyxuzdjora":{"name":"Athletics (throwing)","type":"skill","rof":null,"skillMod":"","skillOverride":"Athletics","shotsUsed":null}}},"damage":"@str+d4","range":"3/6/12","rof":"1","ap":"0","minStr":"d4","shots":"0","currentShots":"0","ammo":"","autoReload":false},"effects":[],"folder":"ofLOMYgHLqfG1MyP","sort":400001,"permission":{"default":0,"ZvqefCj0L7TxJS56":3,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"flags":{"journal-links":{},"core":{"sourceId":"Item.GxVNY83rIxMpxCqB"}}}],"effects":[{"_id":"uMqh6VsX8QTKAQbD","changes":[{"key":"data.stats.toughness.value","mode":2,"value":"1"}],"disabled":false,"duration":{"startTime":28973116800},"icon":"icons/environment/people/charge.webp","label":"Brawler","origin":"Actor.V1CNhfR8X7IKjik4.Item.u6SIBWGiu10iNsTO","tint":null,"transfer":false,"flags":{}}],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_3a04s0jrz4j","path":"Pirates of Cyre Bestiary#/CF_SEP/NPC's","color":"#000000"}},"_id":"CDp0gPIh75K20LjT"}
{"name":"Storm Reaver","type":"vehicle","img":"modules/savage-eberron-bestiary/assets/vehicle-tokens/watercraft/ship.webp","data":{"size":14,"scale":6,"classification":"Watercraft","handling":-2,"cost":300000,"topspeed":"12","description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p><strong>Masts:</strong> 4</p>\n<p><strong>Cargo Holds:</strong> 16</p>\n<p><strong>Notes: </strong>Square-rigged and fore-aft sails; true beast of the seas, @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Vehicle Notes]{Heavy Armor}.</p>\n<p>Galleons come in a wide variety of sizes and designs. These ships all have one thing in common: they are huge, often having 3 or more decks, usually have catapults or ballista on deck, and have large castles mounted fore and aft so that their defenders can fire on enemy crews from above.</p>\n<p><strong>Weapons:</strong> Galleons can hold up to 12 @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-equipment.Ballista]{Ballista} in banks of 6 positioned on the port and starboard sides of the ship. In addition, up to 2 @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-equipment.Catapult]{Catapults} or @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-equipment.Ballista]{Ballista} may be positioned on the forecastle and sterncastle sides of the ship. These seige engines can be swiveled to fire out the sides of the ship or either forward or aft, depending on their position.</p>\n</div>","toughness":{"total":"20","armor":"4"},"wounds":{"value":2,"max":6,"ignored":0},"crew":{"required":{"value":"20","max":"20"},"optional":{"value":"40","max":"40"}},"driver":{"id":null,"skill":"Boating","skillAlternative":""},"status":{"isOutOfControl":false,"isWrecked":false},"initiative":{"hasHesitant":false,"hasLevelHeaded":false,"hasImpLevelHeaded":false,"hasQuick":false},"additionalStats":{},"maxCargo":16,"maxMods":8},"token":{"flags":{},"name":"Galleon","displayName":30,"img":"modules/swade-core-rules/assets/art/vehicles/vehicle-water-galleon.webp","tint":null,"width":3,"height":3,"scale":1,"lockRotation":false,"rotation":0,"vision":false,"dimSight":0,"brightSight":0,"dimLight":0,"brightLight":0,"sightAngle":0,"lightAngle":0,"lightAlpha":1,"lightAnimation":{"speed":5,"intensity":5},"actorId":null,"actorLink":false,"disposition":-1,"displayBars":0,"bar1":{"attribute":null},"bar2":{"attribute":null},"randomImg":false,"mirrorX":false,"mirrorY":false,"alpha":1},"items":[{"_id":"zIMNBBFfdNnncDMc","name":"Ballista (x12)","type":"weapon","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p>@Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Heavy Weapon (HW)]{Heavy Weapon}, @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Reload]{Reload} time is 5 minutes for a solo operator, or 2 minutes with a crew of 2.</p>\n<hr />\n<p>A ballista is a mechanical engine designed to fire a massive crossbow bolt. One person can fire the device (@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Shooting]{Shooting}). One person can reload, although it&rsquo;s faster with two people.</p>\n</div>","notes":"HW","additionalStats":{},"quantity":1,"weight":0,"price":500,"equippable":false,"equipped":true,"isVehicular":true,"mods":1,"actions":{"skill":"Shooting","skillMod":"","dmgMod":"","additional":{}},"damage":"3d6","range":"15/30/60","rof":"1","ap":"4","minStr":"","shots":"0","currentShots":"0","ammo":"","autoReload":false},"sort":200001,"flags":{},"img":"icons/weapons/artillery/ballista-wood-green.webp","effects":[],"folder":null,"permission":{"default":0}},{"_id":"lIKUN2Xe9HwczqzA","name":"Catapult","type":"weapon","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p>@Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Area Effect Attacks]{Medium Blast Template}, @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Heavy Weapon (HW)]{Heavy Weapon}, @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Reload]{Reload} time is every 5 minutes with a crew of 4.</p>\n<hr />\n<p>Catapults are simple devices that hurl large stones at enemy defenses or ranks of troops. They normally require a crew of eight to load the projectile, crank down the lever that propels it, then sight and aim it. Firing can be done by a single person, but loading the projectile takes at least four.</p>\n</div>","notes":"MBT, Heavy Weapon, Reload time is every 5 minutes with a crew of 4.","additionalStats":{},"quantity":1,"weight":0,"price":800,"equippable":false,"equipped":true,"isVehicular":true,"mods":1,"actions":{"skill":"Shooting","skillMod":"","dmgMod":"","additional":{}},"damage":"3d6","range":"24/48/96","rof":"1","ap":"4","minStr":"","shots":"0","currentShots":"0","ammo":"","autoReload":false},"sort":300001,"flags":{},"img":"icons/weapons/artillery/catapult-simple.webp","effects":[],"folder":null,"permission":{"default":0}},{"_id":"JpnKrAAeohBHldC7","name":"Soarwood","type":"gear","img":"icons/commodities/wood/lumber-stack-grey.webp","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p>Rare even in the abundant forests of Aerenal, soarwood possesses a magical buoyancy. Ships made from soarwood skim effortlessly over the surface of the water. Soarwood is a necessary component of the airships and elemental galleons manufactured by @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-lore.House Lyrandar]{House Lyrandar} and @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-lore.House Cannith]{House Cannith}.</p>\n<p>The speed of a boat or ship made from soarwood is double that of an equivalent boat made from ordinary wood, and the cost is four times normal. it also improves the Handling of the ship by 1.</p>\n<p>Soarwood has the same physical characteristics as normal wood, but weighs only 75% as much.</p>\n<p><em><strong>Note: </strong></em>All elemental galleons are made from soarwood, so this is already included in the speed of the vessel.</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"quantity":1,"weight":0,"price":0,"equippable":true,"equipped":"true","isVehicular":true,"mods":1},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"flags":{}},{"_id":"wd3itVhwigGHRYZg","name":"Heavy Armor","type":"gear","img":"icons/commodities/wood/lumber-stack.webp","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p>Only weapons marked as Heavy Weapons can hurt this vehicle, regardless of the damage roll. This keeps a lucky bow shot from destroying a longship, for example. Vehicles with Heavy Armor halve damage they take from colliding with other obstacles (including vehicles) that don&rsquo;t have Heavy Armor. This is not to be confused with the heavy category of personal armor.</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"quantity":1,"weight":0,"price":0,"equippable":false,"equipped":"true","isVehicular":true,"mods":1},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"flags":{}}],"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_z59ej144gfl","path":"Pirates of Cyre Bestiary#/CF_SEP/Vehicles","color":"#000000"},"journal-links":{}},"_id":"HaEE59Dzh7i0zZov"}
{"name":"Master Scourge","type":"npc","img":"https://assets.forge-vtt.com/5f43f8ea1a91d63438d13159/artwork-adventures/pirates-of-cyre/characters/master-scourge.webp","data":{"attributes":{"agility":{"die":{"sides":8,"modifier":0},"wild-die":{"sides":6}},"smarts":{"die":{"sides":6,"modifier":0},"wild-die":{"sides":6},"animal":false},"spirit":{"die":{"sides":6,"modifier":0},"wild-die":{"sides":6},"unShakeBonus":0},"strength":{"die":{"sides":6,"modifier":0},"wild-die":{"sides":6},"encumbranceSteps":0},"vigor":{"die":{"sides":8,"modifier":0},"wild-die":{"sides":6}}},"stats":{"speed":{"runningDie":6,"runningMod":0,"value":6},"toughness":{"value":0,"armor":0,"modifier":0},"parry":{"value":6,"modifier":0},"size":0},"details":{"biography":{"value":"<div>\n<p>Master Scourge is a sneering man with a braided beard and a mouth full of gold teeth. His body is tall and thin, and even his long coat and heavy boots fail to give any impression of strength or bulk.</p>\n</div>"},"species":{"name":""},"currency":500,"wealth":{"die":6,"modifier":0,"wild-die":6},"conviction":{"value":0,"active":false},"autoCalcToughness":true,"autoCalcParry":true},"powerPoints":{},"fatigue":{"value":0,"min":0,"max":2},"wounds":{"value":0,"min":0,"max":3,"ignored":0},"advances":{"value":0,"rank":"Novice","details":""},"bennies":{"value":2,"max":2},"status":{"isShaken":false,"isDistracted":false,"isVulnerable":false,"isStunned":false,"isEntangled":false,"isBound":false},"initiative":{"hasHesitant":false,"hasLevelHeaded":false,"hasImpLevelHeaded":false,"hasQuick":true},"additionalStats":{},"wildcard":true},"token":{"flags":{},"name":"Blank","displayName":30,"img":"modules/etu-rules/assets/bestiary_tokens/sonya-alvarez-min.png","tint":null,"width":1,"height":1,"scale":1,"mirrorX":false,"mirrorY":false,"lockRotation":false,"rotation":0,"vision":true,"dimSight":0,"brightSight":0,"dimLight":0,"brightLight":0,"sightAngle":0,"lightAngle":0,"lightColor":null,"lightAlpha":1,"lightAnimation":{"speed":5,"intensity":5},"actorId":null,"actorLink":true,"disposition":0,"displayBars":0,"bar1":{"attribute":""},"bar2":{"attribute":""},"randomImg":false,"alpha":1},"items":[{"_id":"UZW0tLJicg0VZOp4","name":"Athletics","type":"skill","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p>Athletics combines an individual&rsquo;s coordin&shy;ation with learned skills such as climbing, jumping, balancing, biking, wrestling, skiing, swimming, throwing, or catching. Characters who rely on physical power more than coordination can take the @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Brute]{Brute} Edge to link this skill to @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Traits]{Strength} instead of @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Traits]{Agility}.</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"attribute":"agility","isCoreSkill":false,"die":{"sides":8,"modifier":0},"wild-die":{"sides":6}},"sort":100000,"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_nsugutrpau","path":"Skills","color":"#8c160f"},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.swade-core-rules.swade-skills.Athletics"}},"img":"icons/magic/control/buff-strength-muscle-damage.webp","effects":[],"folder":null,"permission":{"default":0}},{"_id":"W5lfcCNjirSPUH42","name":"Common Knowledge","type":"skill","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\"><p>Characters roll Common Knowledge to know people, places, and things of their world, including etiquette, geography, culture, popular technology, contacts, and customs.</p></div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"attribute":"smarts","isCoreSkill":false,"die":{"sides":4,"modifier":0},"wild-die":{"sides":6}},"sort":200000,"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_nsugutrpau","path":"Skills","color":"#8c160f"},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.swade-core-rules.swade-skills.Common Knowledge"}},"img":"icons/sundries/documents/document-official-capital.webp","effects":[],"folder":null,"permission":{"default":0}},{"_id":"quj5jF3vNls1j5E3","name":"Notice","type":"skill","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p>Notice is a hero&rsquo;s general awareness and alertness. It&rsquo;s used to sense sights, sounds, tastes, and smells, spot clues, detect ambushes, spot hidden weapons on a foe, or tell if a rival is lying, frightened, happy, etc.</p>\n<p>@Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{Success} conveys basic information&mdash;the character hears movement in the forest, smells distant smoke, or senses someone isn&rsquo;t being completely truthful.</p>\n<p>A @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{raise} grants more detail, such as the direction of a sound or odor or what topic a person is avoiding or lying about.</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"attribute":"smarts","isCoreSkill":false,"die":{"sides":8,"modifier":0},"wild-die":{"sides":6}},"sort":300000,"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_nsugutrpau","path":"Skills","color":"#8c160f"},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.swade-core-rules.swade-skills.ZvwjzMLxsneptV4T"}},"img":"icons/creatures/eyes/human-single-blue.webp","effects":[],"folder":null,"permission":{"default":0}},{"_id":"TOEzoo2Lf4A5JXOF","name":"Persuasion","type":"skill","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p>Persuasion is the ability to convince others to do what you want through reason, cajoling, deception, rewards, or other friendly means. Persuasion isn&rsquo;t mind control. It can change someone&rsquo;s attitude but not their goals. A bandit may let you keep a sentimental piece of jewelry with a good Persuasion roll but still takes all your other goods.</p>\n<p>When used to @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Support]{Support} allies it&rsquo;s an unopposed roll. If the target is resistant, it&rsquo;s an @JournalEntry[JBxsGv2wAoAmoCDe]{opposed} roll vs. the target&rsquo;s @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Traits]{Spirit}. The GM should modify the roll as she sees fit based on roleplaying, any pertinent @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Edges]{Edges} or @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Hindrances]{Hindrances} that affect the conversation, and the circumstances.</p>\n<p><strong>Reaction Level:</strong> How much a person is willing to cooperate depends largely on their attitude toward whoever&rsquo;s talking to them. The Game Master can decide how nonplayer characters feel based on the setting, or roll on the @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-tables.Reaction Table]{Reaction Table} if she has no preconceived notions.</p>\n<p>@Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{Success} improves the target&rsquo;s attitude one level and a raise improves it two. Further increases aren&rsquo;t generally possible in the same encounter&mdash;it takes individuals a little time to adjust their biases.</p>\n<p>@Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{Failure} means the target won&rsquo;t change his mind this scene or until the situation changes in some important way. A @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{Critical Failure} also <em>reduces</em> the target&rsquo;s attitude two levels.</p>\n<p>Only one roll should generally be allowed per interaction unless new information is revealed, a substantial reward is offered, etc.</p>\n<p><strong>Networking: </strong>Characters can also use Persuasion as a &ldquo;macro skill,&rdquo; simulating a few hours or an evening&rsquo;s time hobnobbing and socializing to gain favors or information. See @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Networking]{Networking}.</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"attribute":"spirit","isCoreSkill":false,"die":{"sides":6,"modifier":0},"wild-die":{"sides":6}},"sort":400000,"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_nsugutrpau","path":"Skills","color":"#8c160f"},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.swade-core-rules.swade-skills.Persuasion"}},"img":"icons/skills/social/diplomacy-handshake.webp","effects":[],"folder":null,"permission":{"default":0}},{"_id":"8VzaSa3EEDrMz6PR","name":"Stealth","type":"skill","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p>Stealth is the ability to hide and move quietly. A simple @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{success} on a Stealth roll means the character avoids detection if enemies aren&rsquo;t particularly alert. If the character @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{fails} the roll, the enemy realizes something is amiss and begins actively searching for whatever roused them.</p>\n<p>Once foes are alerted and active, Stealth is opposed by @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Notice]{Notice} (a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{group roll} if there are many foes.</p>\n<p>The GM should apply any circumstantial penalties to @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Notice]{Notice} rolls for @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Illumination]{darkness}, @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Cover and Obstacles]{cover}, noise, distractions, and any difference in the target&rsquo;s @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Size and Scale]{Scale} (just like when attacking). Sneaking through dry leaves might subtract 2 from the Stealth roll, for example, while spotting someone in the dark uses the @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Illumination]{Illumination} penalty (&minus;4). Don&rsquo;t apply the same modifier to both rolls, however. If Stealth is at &minus;2 for the leaves, don&rsquo;t give Notice a +2 for them as well.</p>\n<p><strong>Sneak Attack: </strong> Sneaking up close enough to make a melee attack <em>always</em> requires an @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{opposed} Stealth roll versus the target&rsquo;s @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Notice]{Notice}, whether the guard is actively looking for trouble or not. If successful, the victim is @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Distracted and Vulnerable]{Vulnerable} to the attacker, but only until the attacker&rsquo;s turn ends. With a raise, the attacker has @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.The Drop]{The Drop} instead.</p>\n<p><strong>Movement:</strong> In combat, characters roll Stealth each turn as a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Actions]{free action} at the end of their move or any action the GM thinks might draw attention.</p>\n<p>Out of combat, the distance moved depends entirely on the situation. The GM might want a roll every minute if the group is sneaking around the perimeter of a defensive position, or every few miles if they&rsquo;re trying to quietly walk the path through a dark forest without alerting the creatures that live there.</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"attribute":"agility","isCoreSkill":false,"die":{"sides":8,"modifier":0},"wild-die":{"sides":6}},"sort":500000,"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_nsugutrpau","path":"Skills","color":"#8c160f"},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.swade-core-rules.swade-skills.Stealth"}},"img":"icons/magic/nature/stealth-hide-eyes-green.webp","effects":[],"folder":null,"permission":{"default":0}},{"_id":"BQ3OOQlkZvCl1Lfb","name":"Unskilled Attempt","type":"skill","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p>If a character doesn&rsquo;t have a skill for an action he&rsquo;s attempting, he rolls a d4 for his skill die (and a Wild Die if a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Wild Cards and Extras]{Wild Card}) and subtracts 2 from the total.</p>\n<p>The GM may decide certain tasks cannot be attempted unskilled, such as performing complex surgery or flying a commercial jet.</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"attribute":"agility","isCoreSkill":false,"die":{"sides":4,"modifier":"-2"},"wild-die":{"sides":6}},"sort":1100000,"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_nsugutrpau","path":"Skills","color":"#8c160f"},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.swade-core-rules.swade-skills.zcn1epcU4FEJGGyI"}},"img":"icons/magic/symbols/question-stone-yellow.webp","effects":[],"folder":null,"permission":{"default":0}},{"_id":"uaVAhwDnUDLFZFXm","name":"Unarmed strike","type":"weapon","data":{"description":"","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"quantity":1,"weight":0,"price":0,"equippable":false,"equipped":true,"isVehicular":false,"mods":1,"actions":{"skill":"","skillMod":"","dmgMod":"","additional":{}},"damage":"@str","range":"","rof":"1","ap":"0","minStr":"","shots":"0","currentShots":"0","ammo":"","autoReload":false},"sort":1400000,"flags":{},"img":"icons/skills/melee/unarmed-punch-fist.webp","effects":[],"folder":null,"permission":{"default":0}},{"_id":"GjcL17dCtOeFUvbu","name":"Fighting","type":"skill","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p>Fighting covers all hand-to-hand (melee) attacks, whether it&rsquo;s with fists, axes, laser swords, or martial arts. See @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Combat]{Chapter Three} for the combat rules and the various maneuvers a warrior might attempt.</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"attribute":"agility","isCoreSkill":false,"die":{"sides":8,"modifier":0},"wild-die":{"sides":6}},"sort":1500000,"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_qals24wpyph","path":"Skills","color":"#8c160f"},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.swade-core-rules.swade-skills.wWiwjPlzAQU3TN9l"}},"img":"icons/skills/melee/hand-grip-sword-white-brown.webp","effects":[],"folder":null,"permission":{"default":0}},{"_id":"6Ier1mvn4BHudZkK","name":"Boating","type":"skill","img":"icons/environment/settlement/ship.webp","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\"><p>Characters with this skill can handle most any boat or ship common to their setting. They also know how to handle common tasks associated with their vessel such as tying knots, rigging sails, or following currents.</p></div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"attribute":"agility","isCoreSkill":false,"die":{"sides":8,"modifier":0},"wild-die":{"sides":6}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"3HvtK4sMp7flYKmT":3,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_qals24wpyph","path":"Skills","color":"#8c160f"},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.swade-core-rules.swade-skills.WMWgIVDuAW4cHxj2"}}},{"_id":"1kzaTdRoipFAiPwN","name":"Intimidation","type":"skill","img":"icons/skills/wounds/injury-face-impact-orange.webp","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p>Intimidation is the art of frightening an opponent so that he backs down, reveals information, or flees.</p>\n<p>Intimidation is an @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{opposed roll} resisted by the opponent&rsquo;s @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Traits]{Spirit}. In combat, this is a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Test]{Test}. Out of combat, a successful roll means the foe backs down for the most part, reveals some information, or slinks away when the opportunity presents itself.</p>\n<p>A @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{raise} might mean he backs down for the remainder of the scene, spills all the beans, or runs away as fast as he can.</p>\n<p>In or out of combat, a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{Critical Failure} means the target is immune to this character&rsquo;s Intimidation attempts for the remainder of this encounter!</p>\n<p><strong>Networking:</strong> Intimidation can also be used as a &ldquo;macro&rdquo; skill to simulate several hours of working the streets. See&nbsp;@Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Networking]{Networking}&nbsp;to see how to crack some heads for favors or information.</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"attribute":"spirit","isCoreSkill":false,"die":{"sides":8,"modifier":0},"wild-die":{"sides":6}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"3HvtK4sMp7flYKmT":3,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_qals24wpyph","path":"Skills","color":"#8c160f"},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.swade-core-rules.swade-skills.RrgAZp50CgQyyY6w"}}},{"_id":"uoRshBWE0ihCmMES","name":"Shooting","type":"skill","img":"icons/skills/ranged/target-bullseye-arrow-glowing.webp","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p>Shooting covers all attempts to hit a target with a ranged weapon such as a bow, pistol, or rocket launcher (thrown weapons use @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Athletics]{Athletics}). See @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Combat]{Chapter Three} for details on ranged combat.</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"attribute":"agility","isCoreSkill":false,"die":{"sides":8,"modifier":0},"wild-die":{"sides":6}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"3HvtK4sMp7flYKmT":3,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_qals24wpyph","path":"Skills","color":"#8c160f"},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.swade-core-rules.swade-skills.sOHfVvBDhe3Oy3r1"}}},{"_id":"o3ChBi570IETeE8m","name":"Thievery","type":"skill","img":"icons/skills/social/theft-pickpocket-bribery-brown.webp","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p>Lockpicking, safecracking, picking pockets, sleight of hand, setting and disabling traps and similar acts of misdirection, sabotage, subterfuge, and manipulation are called Thievery.</p>\n<p>If used to pick a lock, crack a safe, disable a trap, or perform a simple unopposed action, @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{success} opens or disables the device, and a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{raise} does it in less time, without tripping alarms, or whatever else the GM feels is appropriate.</p>\n<p>Sleight of hand, hiding or planting an item, or picking a pocket require a simple @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{success}. If foes are actively watching the character, Thievery is @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{opposed} by @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Notice]{Notice}.</p>\n<p>The Game Master should assign @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{penalties} for particularly difficult circumstances. Picking a heavy padlock might have a &minus;4 penalty, while hiding a revolver in bulky winter clothing might grant a +1 bonus. @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{Failure} typically means the character is spotted or it takes too much time (after which the character can try again). A @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{Critical Failure} typically sets off the trap, alerts the victim, or jams the device so that it must be opened or interacted with in a different way.</p>\n<p><strong>Limited: </strong>Using Thievery on an electronic device, such as a keypad, is limited by the thief&rsquo;s @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Electronics]{Electronics} skill. Use the lowest of the two skills.</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"attribute":"agility","isCoreSkill":false,"die":{"sides":6,"modifier":0},"wild-die":{"sides":6}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"3HvtK4sMp7flYKmT":3,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_qals24wpyph","path":"Skills","color":"#8c160f"},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.swade-core-rules.swade-skills.wZbyJkisWIfmcZNt"}}},{"_id":"k8v1L207iHau3c21","name":"Deception","type":"skill","img":"icons/skills/toxins/poison-skull-herbs-bottle-pink.webp","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p>Deception determines whether the hero can convincingly hide the truth, either verbally or through her actions. This deception can encompass everything from misleading others through ambiguity to telling outright lies.</p>\n<p>Typical situations include trying to fast-talk a guard, con a merchant, dull someone's suspicions with false assurances, or maintain a straight face while telling a blatant lie.</p>\n<p>Usually, a character successfully passing herself off in a disguise, or trying to impersonate the sound of someone else's voice would be a @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Performance]{Performance} check rather than a deception check.&nbsp;</p>\n<p><em><strong>Source: Savage Eberron</strong></em></p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"attribute":"spirit","isCoreSkill":false,"die":{"sides":8,"modifier":0},"wild-die":{"sides":6}},"effects":[],"folder":"vdiWDU7Bqdgk8RH2","sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"flags":{"journal-links":{},"core":{"sourceId":"Item.E0BVumGwbaczoPjD"},"cf":null}},{"_id":"hwO64Y6PkFzE7SMw","name":"Leather Armor","type":"armor","img":"icons/equipment/chest/breastplate-layered-grey.webp","data":{"description":"","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"quantity":1,"weight":3,"price":5,"equippable":false,"equipped":true,"minStr":"d4","armor":1,"isNaturalArmor":false,"locations":{"head":false,"torso":true,"arms":true,"legs":false}},"effects":[],"folder":"XQoSmfkzvuK8FNo1","sort":100000,"permission":{"default":0,"ZvqefCj0L7TxJS56":3,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"flags":{"journal-links":{},"core":{"sourceId":"Item.PRPRsNmJyfvoy6hH"}}},{"_id":"R5nE2NWsRvRUQICV","name":"Yellow","type":"hindrance","img":"icons/magic/holy/yin-yang-balance-symbol.webp","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p>Not everyone has ice water in their veins. Your hero is squeamish at the sight of blood and gore and terrified of coming to harm. He subtracts 2 from @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Fear]{Fear}&nbsp;</span>checks and when resisting @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-skills.Intimidation]{Intimidation}.</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"major":true},"effects":[],"folder":"1updrtPaYhKD0fRY","sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"3HvtK4sMp7flYKmT":3,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"flags":{"cf":null,"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.swade-core-rules.swade-hindrances.YZW0gutCe8gKBVnn"}}},{"_id":"g0QRC9Fnyn6VyRFj","name":"Greedy","type":"hindrance","img":"icons/magic/holy/yin-yang-balance-symbol.webp","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p>A miser measures worth in material possessions or wealth. If a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Characters]{Minor} Hindrance, he argues bitterly for more than his fair share of any loot or reward the party might come across. As a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Characters]{Major} @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Hindrances]{Hindrance}, he fights over anything he considers unfair, and may even kill for it if he feels slighted or covets something he cannot have.</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"major":false},"effects":[],"folder":"1updrtPaYhKD0fRY","sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"3HvtK4sMp7flYKmT":3,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"flags":{"cf":null,"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.swade-core-rules.swade-hindrances.rIWvJoLH8WegsbrL"}}},{"_id":"U1dF3bixY2xCw91a","name":"Mean","type":"hindrance","img":"icons/magic/holy/yin-yang-balance-symbol.webp","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p>This curmudgeon is ill-tempered and disagreeable. He has trouble doing anything kind for anyone else, must be paid for his troubles, and doesn&rsquo;t accept awards or favors graciously. Besides the obvious roleplaying issues, Mean characters subtract 1 from @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-skills.Persuasion]{Persuasion} @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{rolls}.</span></p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"major":false},"effects":[],"folder":"1updrtPaYhKD0fRY","sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"3HvtK4sMp7flYKmT":3,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"flags":{"cf":null,"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.swade-core-rules.swade-hindrances.sNgSwqh2fGyM6i14"}}},{"_id":"YibKi8hNWDOzbFQu","name":"Rogue","type":"edge","img":"icons/skills/melee/strike-dagger-skull-white.webp","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p>Life is an endless adventure for those who live by their wits. Ever just one step ahead of danger, rogues bank on their cunning, skill, and charm to bend fate to their favor. Never knowing what to expect, they tend to prepare for everything. Out of necessity, they become adept manipulators, agile acrobats, or shadowy stalkers. They are thieves and gamblers, fast talkers and diplomats, bandits and bounty hunters, or explorers and investigators.</p>\n<p>Although many rogues favor the opportunities of towns and cities, some embrace life on the road. They wander from place to place, meeting exotic people and facing fantastic danger in pursuit of endless riches. In the end, all rogues desire to shape their fates and live life on their own terms.</p>\n<p>Rogues gain the following abilities:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Rogue Armor Restriction (Light)]{Rogue Armor Restriction (Light)}</li>\n<li>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Skill Monkey]{Skill Monkey}</li>\n<li>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Trap Sense]{Trap Sense}</li>\n</ul>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Novice, Agility d6+, Notice d6+, Stealth d6+, Thievery d6+"}},"effects":[],"folder":"zzeiXM6YEGI9jNRc","sort":500000,"permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"flags":{"journal-links":{},"core":{"sourceId":"Item.UBXzgLMsycquNmh2"}}},{"_id":"mPsjNqsQiXccjHZ7","name":"Skill Monkey","type":"edge","img":"icons/skills/melee/strike-dagger-skull-white.webp","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p>To survive, rogues have become adept at learning all sorts of skills and trades, both to survive and to con people. Whether trained by a mentor, a guild member, a house, or the streets, rogues have picked up additional skills and training.</p>\n<p>Rogues gain two skill points they can put into increasing the die type of two of the following skills: @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Athletics]{Athletics}, @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Common Knowledge]{Common Knowledge}, @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Deception]{Deception}, @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Gambling]{Gambling}, @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Intimidation]{Intimidation}, @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Notice]{Notice}, @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Performance]{Performance}, @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Persuasion]{Persuasion}, @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Stealth]{Stealth}, or @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Thievery]{Thievery}.</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Novice, Rogue"}},"effects":[],"folder":"zzeiXM6YEGI9jNRc","sort":400000,"permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"flags":{"journal-links":{},"core":{"sourceId":"Item.Voq7KPCbPVjrEjZP"}}},{"_id":"x0RriqTjEan86VSh","name":"Trap Sense","type":"edge","img":"icons/skills/melee/strike-dagger-skull-white.webp","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p>Rogues are adept at spotting and defeating all but the most clever snares and traps. They get a @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Notice]{Notice} roll anytime a detectable trap is about to be sprung within 5&rdquo; (10 yards). They must have line of sight to the trap and can&rsquo;t be @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Damage Effects]{Shaken} or @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Stunned]{Stunned}. This works generally like @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Danger Sense]{Danger Sense} but applies only to mechanical and magical traps.</p>\n<p>If the trap is detected and may be @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Evasion]{Evaded}, the rogue and anyone she warns ignores 2 points of @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Evasion]{Evasion} penalties to do so. If the trap can&rsquo;t normally be @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Evasion]{Evaded}, anyone warned may @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Evasion]{Evade} at the usual &minus;2 penalty.</p>\n<p><strong>Disarming Traps:</strong> Rogues with Trap Sense ignore up 2 points of @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Thievery]{Thievery} penalties when attempting to disarm traps.</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Novice, Rogue"}},"effects":[],"folder":"zzeiXM6YEGI9jNRc","sort":400000,"permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"flags":{"journal-links":{},"core":{"sourceId":"Item.gMhsswekqyI1hslR"}}},{"_id":"stjuAnzvJS5al95M","name":"Sneak Attack","type":"edge","img":"icons/skills/melee/strike-dagger-skull-white.webp","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p>Rogues add an additional d6 to their damage when they have @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.The Drop]{the Drop} on their victim, or the victim is @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Distracted and Vulnerable]{Vulnerable}. This applies to @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Athletics]{Athletics} (throwing), @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Fighting]{Fighting}, or @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Shooting]{Shooting} attacks.</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Seasoned, Rogue"}},"effects":[],"folder":"zzeiXM6YEGI9jNRc","sort":300000,"permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"flags":{"journal-links":{},"core":{"sourceId":"Item.5ggl5Khobnfxq698"}}},{"_id":"zccYegdCY96cR2I1","name":"Quick","type":"edge","img":"icons/environment/people/group.webp","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p>Quick characters have lightning-fast reflexes and a cool head. Whenever you are dealt an @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Action Cards (Initiative)]{Action Card} of Five or lower, you may discard it and draw again until you get a card higher than Five.</span></p>\n<p>@Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Characters]{Characters} with both the @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Level Headed]{Level Headed} and Quick Edges first draw their additional card and choose which to take. If that card is a Five or less, the Quick Edge may be used to draw a replacement until it&rsquo;s Six or higher.</span></p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Novice, Agility d8+"}},"effects":[],"folder":"EnpCvbp1xbBRZIf1","sort":1800000,"permission":{"default":0,"3HvtK4sMp7flYKmT":3,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"flags":{"cf":null,"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.swade-core-rules.swade-edges.XHguf9iQ3N9yHN4Z"}}},{"_id":"7tCUPCgVHLXej974","name":"Rogue Armor Restriction (Light)","type":"hindrance","img":"icons/skills/melee/strike-dagger-skull-white.webp","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p>Rogues are nimble and deadly acrobats. Bulky armor interferes with their abilities, so they subtract 4 from @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Traits]{Agility} and @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Traits]{Agility-based} skill rolls when wearing medium or heavy armor, or using medium or heavy shields.</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"major":false},"effects":[],"folder":"zzeiXM6YEGI9jNRc","sort":100000,"permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"flags":{"journal-links":{},"core":{"sourceId":"Item.B1jMHG6GDPNV0kYU"}}},{"_id":"bsKrKyvrK8j2EGm5","name":"Language (Common)","type":"skill","img":"icons/sundries/documents/document-letter-formal-tan.webp","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p>In some settings, such as those that focus on pulp action or &ldquo;planetary romance&rdquo; (where characters frequently travel among many strange civilizations), speaking various languages can simply be roleplayed with halting dialogue and campy accents that start out a little difficult and are quickly forgotten. The GM may ignore this skill altogether in these settings, or use the @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Multiple Languages]{Multiple Languages}&nbsp;&shy;option in the @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Setting Rules]{Setting Rules}.</p>\n<p>In more realistic settings, communication can be a major barrier that requires characters to put skill points into additional languages. In a 1980s World War Three game, for example, a group of United Nations paratroopers won&rsquo;t be able to speak with their foes unless they take Russian, Polish, or other languages common to the Warsaw Pact.</p>\n<p>If the Language skill is in use, it should be listed as Language (Spanish), Language (American Sign Language), etc. A character&rsquo;s die type also notes how fluent he is in it. (Characters start with a d8 in their own Language.)</p>\n<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<table class=\"table value-table\"><caption class=\"table-caption\">\n<h2 class=\"table-title\">Language Proficiency</h2>\n</caption>\n<tbody>\n<tr class=\"table-header-row\">\n<th class=\"table-column-header\" scope=\"col\">Skill</th>\n<th class=\"table-column-header\" scope=\"col\">Ability</th>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td>d4</td>\n<td>The character can read, write and speak common words and phrases.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>d6</td>\n<td>The speaker can carry on a prolonged but occasionally halting conversation.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>d8</td>\n<td>The character can speak fluently.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>d10</td>\n<td>The hero can mimic other dialects within the language.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>d12</td>\n<td>The speaker can masterfully recite important literary or oral works.</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>\n</div>\n<p><strong>Limited: </strong>Use whichever skill is lowest when performing an action that requires knowledge of a foreign language. @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Intimidation]{Intimidation} (if verbal), @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Persuasion]{Persuasion}, @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Research]{Research}, @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Taunt]{Taunt}, etc., are all limited by the character&rsquo;s Language skill.</p>\n<p>This limitation never applies to a character&rsquo;s native tongue.</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"attribute":"smarts","isCoreSkill":false,"die":{"sides":8,"modifier":0},"wild-die":{"sides":6}},"effects":[],"folder":"kFghWjY7gP7MEqav","sort":1,"permission":{"default":0,"3HvtK4sMp7flYKmT":3,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_nsugutrpau","path":"Skills","color":"#8c160f"},"journal-links":{},"core":{"sourceId":"Item.B8Z0BJ0B2ULcZFmw"}}},{"_id":"34XXKChBYz4ixBQ6","name":"Language (Dwarvish)","type":"skill","img":"icons/sundries/documents/document-letter-formal-tan.webp","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p>In some settings, such as those that focus on pulp action or &ldquo;planetary romance&rdquo; (where characters frequently travel among many strange civilizations), speaking various languages can simply be roleplayed with halting dialogue and campy accents that start out a little difficult and are quickly forgotten. The GM may ignore this skill altogether in these settings, or use the @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Multiple Languages]{Multiple Languages}&nbsp;&shy;option in the @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Setting Rules]{Setting Rules}.</p>\n<p>In more realistic settings, communication can be a major barrier that requires characters to put skill points into additional languages. In a 1980s World War Three game, for example, a group of United Nations paratroopers won&rsquo;t be able to speak with their foes unless they take Russian, Polish, or other languages common to the Warsaw Pact.</p>\n<p>If the Language skill is in use, it should be lis