png","tint":null,"width":1,"height":1,"scale":1,"mirrorX":false,"mirrorY":false,"lockRotation":false,"rotation":0,"vision":true,"dimSight":0,"brightSight":0,"dimLight":0,"brightLight":0,"sightAngle":0,"lightAngle":0,"lightColor":null,"lightAlpha":1,"lightAnimation":{"speed":5,"intensity":5},"actorId":null,"actorLink":true,"disposition":0,"displayBars":0,"bar1":{"attribute":""},"bar2":{"attribute":""},"randomImg":false,"alpha":1},"items":[{"_id":"UZW0tLJicg0VZOp4","name":"Athletics","type":"skill","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p>Athletics combines an individual&rsquo;s coordin&shy;ation with learned skills such as climbing, jumping, balancing, biking, wrestling, skiing, swimming, throwing, or catching. Characters who rely on physical power more than coordination can take the @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Brute]{Brute} Edge to link this skill to @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Traits]{Strength} instead of @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Traits]{Agility}.</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"attribute":"agility","isCoreSkill":false,"die":{"sides":8,"modifier":0},"wild-die":{"sides":6}},"sort":100000,"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_nsugutrpau","path":"Skills","color":"#8c160f"},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.swade-core-rules.swade-skills.Athletics"}},"img":"icons/magic/control/buff-strength-muscle-damage.webp","effects":[],"folder":null,"permission":{"default":0}},{"_id":"W5lfcCNjirSPUH42","name":"Common Knowledge","type":"skill","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\"><p>Characters roll Common Knowledge to know people, places, and things of their world, including etiquette, geography, culture, popular technology, contacts, and customs.</p></div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"attribute":"smarts","isCoreSkill":false,"die":{"sides":4,"modifier":0},"wild-die":{"sides":6}},"sort":200000,"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_nsugutrpau","path":"Skills","color":"#8c160f"},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.swade-core-rules.swade-skills.Common Knowledge"}},"img":"icons/sundries/documents/document-official-capital.webp","effects":[],"folder":null,"permission":{"default":0}},{"_id":"quj5jF3vNls1j5E3","name":"Notice","type":"skill","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p>Notice is a hero&rsquo;s general awareness and alertness. It&rsquo;s used to sense sights, sounds, tastes, and smells, spot clues, detect ambushes, spot hidden weapons on a foe, or tell if a rival is lying, frightened, happy, etc.</p>\n<p>@Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{Success} conveys basic information&mdash;the character hears movement in the forest, smells distant smoke, or senses someone isn&rsquo;t being completely truthful.</p>\n<p>A @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{raise} grants more detail, such as the direction of a sound or odor or what topic a person is avoiding or lying about.</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"attribute":"smarts","isCoreSkill":false,"die":{"sides":4,"modifier":0},"wild-die":{"sides":6}},"sort":300000,"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_nsugutrpau","path":"Skills","color":"#8c160f"},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.swade-core-rules.swade-skills.ZvwjzMLxsneptV4T"}},"img":"icons/creatures/eyes/human-single-blue.webp","effects":[],"folder":null,"permission":{"default":0}},{"_id":"TOEzoo2Lf4A5JXOF","name":"Persuasion","type":"skill","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p>Persuasion is the ability to convince others to do what you want through reason, cajoling, deception, rewards, or other friendly means. Persuasion isn&rsquo;t mind control. It can change someone&rsquo;s attitude but not their goals. A bandit may let you keep a sentimental piece of jewelry with a good Persuasion roll but still takes all your other goods.</p>\n<p>When used to @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Support]{Support} allies it&rsquo;s an unopposed roll. If the target is resistant, it&rsquo;s an @JournalEntry[JBxsGv2wAoAmoCDe]{opposed} roll vs. the target&rsquo;s @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Traits]{Spirit}. The GM should modify the roll as she sees fit based on roleplaying, any pertinent @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Edges]{Edges} or @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Hindrances]{Hindrances} that affect the conversation, and the circumstances.</p>\n<p><strong>Reaction Level:</strong> How much a person is willing to cooperate depends largely on their attitude toward whoever&rsquo;s talking to them. The Game Master can decide how nonplayer characters feel based on the setting, or roll on the @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-tables.Reaction Table]{Reaction Table} if she has no preconceived notions.</p>\n<p>@Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{Success} improves the target&rsquo;s attitude one level and a raise improves it two. Further increases aren&rsquo;t generally possible in the same encounter&mdash;it takes individuals a little time to adjust their biases.</p>\n<p>@Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{Failure} means the target won&rsquo;t change his mind this scene or until the situation changes in some important way. A @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{Critical Failure} also <em>reduces</em> the target&rsquo;s attitude two levels.</p>\n<p>Only one roll should generally be allowed per interaction unless new information is revealed, a substantial reward is offered, etc.</p>\n<p><strong>Networking: </strong>Characters can also use Persuasion as a &ldquo;macro skill,&rdquo; simulating a few hours or an evening&rsquo;s time hobnobbing and socializing to gain favors or information. See @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Networking]{Networking}.</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"attribute":"spirit","isCoreSkill":false,"die":{"sides":4,"modifier":-1},"wild-die":{"sides":6}},"sort":400000,"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_nsugutrpau","path":"Skills","color":"#8c160f"},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.swade-core-rules.swade-skills.Persuasion"}},"img":"icons/skills/social/diplomacy-handshake.webp","effects":[],"folder":null,"permission":{"default":0}},{"_id":"8VzaSa3EEDrMz6PR","name":"Stealth","type":"skill","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p>Stealth is the ability to hide and move quietly. A simple @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{success} on a Stealth roll means the character avoids detection if enemies aren&rsquo;t particularly alert. If the character @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{fails} the roll, the enemy realizes something is amiss and begins actively searching for whatever roused them.</p>\n<p>Once foes are alerted and active, Stealth is opposed by @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Notice]{Notice} (a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{group roll} if there are many foes.</p>\n<p>The GM should apply any circumstantial penalties to @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Notice]{Notice} rolls for @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Illumination]{darkness}, @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Cover and Obstacles]{cover}, noise, distractions, and any difference in the target&rsquo;s @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Size and Scale]{Scale} (just like when attacking). Sneaking through dry leaves might subtract 2 from the Stealth roll, for example, while spotting someone in the dark uses the @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Illumination]{Illumination} penalty (&minus;4). Don&rsquo;t apply the same modifier to both rolls, however. If Stealth is at &minus;2 for the leaves, don&rsquo;t give Notice a +2 for them as well.</p>\n<p><strong>Sneak Attack: </strong> Sneaking up close enough to make a melee attack <em>always</em> requires an @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{opposed} Stealth roll versus the target&rsquo;s @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Notice]{Notice}, whether the guard is actively looking for trouble or not. If successful, the victim is @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Distracted and Vulnerable]{Vulnerable} to the attacker, but only until the attacker&rsquo;s turn ends. With a raise, the attacker has @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.The Drop]{The Drop} instead.</p>\n<p><strong>Movement:</strong> In combat, characters roll Stealth each turn as a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Actions]{free action} at the end of their move or any action the GM thinks might draw attention.</p>\n<p>Out of combat, the distance moved depends entirely on the situation. The GM might want a roll every minute if the group is sneaking around the perimeter of a defensive position, or every few miles if they&rsquo;re trying to quietly walk the path through a dark forest without alerting the creatures that live there.</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"attribute":"agility","isCoreSkill":false,"die":{"sides":8,"modifier":0},"wild-die":{"sides":6}},"sort":500000,"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_nsugutrpau","path":"Skills","color":"#8c160f"},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.swade-core-rules.swade-skills.Stealth"}},"img":"icons/magic/nature/stealth-hide-eyes-green.webp","effects":[],"folder":null,"permission":{"default":0}},{"_id":"BQ3OOQlkZvCl1Lfb","name":"Unskilled Attempt","type":"skill","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p>If a character doesn&rsquo;t have a skill for an action he&rsquo;s attempting, he rolls a d4 for his skill die (and a Wild Die if a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Wild Cards and Extras]{Wild Card}) and subtracts 2 from the total.</p>\n<p>The GM may decide certain tasks cannot be attempted unskilled, such as performing complex surgery or flying a commercial jet.</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"attribute":"agility","isCoreSkill":false,"die":{"sides":4,"modifier":"-2"},"wild-die":{"sides":6}},"sort":1100000,"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_nsugutrpau","path":"Skills","color":"#8c160f"},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.swade-core-rules.swade-skills.zcn1epcU4FEJGGyI"}},"img":"icons/magic/symbols/question-stone-yellow.webp","effects":[],"folder":null,"permission":{"default":0}},{"_id":"uaVAhwDnUDLFZFXm","name":"Unarmed strike","type":"weapon","data":{"description":"","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"quantity":1,"weight":0,"price":0,"equippable":false,"equipped":true,"isVehicular":false,"mods":1,"actions":{"skill":"","skillMod":"","dmgMod":"","additional":{}},"damage":"@str+d4","range":"","rof":"1","ap":"0","minStr":"","shots":"0","currentShots":"0","ammo":"","autoReload":false},"sort":1400000,"flags":{},"img":"icons/skills/melee/unarmed-punch-fist.webp","effects":[],"folder":null,"permission":{"default":0}},{"_id":"GjcL17dCtOeFUvbu","name":"Fighting","type":"skill","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p>Fighting covers all hand-to-hand (melee) attacks, whether it&rsquo;s with fists, axes, laser swords, or martial arts. See @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Combat]{Chapter Three} for the combat rules and the various maneuvers a warrior might attempt.</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"attribute":"agility","isCoreSkill":false,"die":{"sides":8,"modifier":0},"wild-die":{"sides":6}},"sort":1500000,"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_qals24wpyph","path":"Skills","color":"#8c160f"},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.swade-core-rules.swade-skills.wWiwjPlzAQU3TN9l"}},"img":"icons/skills/melee/hand-grip-sword-white-brown.webp","effects":[],"folder":null,"permission":{"default":0}},{"_id":"2S25FXQXotZBbOeW","name":"Boating","type":"skill","img":"icons/environment/settlement/ship.webp","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\"><p>Characters with this skill can handle most any boat or ship common to their setting. They also know how to handle common tasks associated with their vessel such as tying knots, rigging sails, or following currents.</p></div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"attribute":"agility","isCoreSkill":false,"die":{"sides":4,"modifier":0},"wild-die":{"sides":6}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"3HvtK4sMp7flYKmT":3,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_qals24wpyph","path":"Skills","color":"#8c160f"},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.swade-core-rules.swade-skills.WMWgIVDuAW4cHxj2"}}},{"_id":"YHhyv0RRpudIeQ8j","name":"Intimidation","type":"skill","img":"icons/skills/wounds/injury-face-impact-orange.webp","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p>Intimidation is the art of frightening an opponent so that he backs down, reveals information, or flees.</p>\n<p>Intimidation is an @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{opposed roll} resisted by the opponent&rsquo;s @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Traits]{Spirit}. In combat, this is a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Test]{Test}. Out of combat, a successful roll means the foe backs down for the most part, reveals some information, or slinks away when the opportunity presents itself.</p>\n<p>A @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{raise} might mean he backs down for the remainder of the scene, spills all the beans, or runs away as fast as he can.</p>\n<p>In or out of combat, a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{Critical Failure} means the target is immune to this character&rsquo;s Intimidation attempts for the remainder of this encounter!</p>\n<p><strong>Networking:</strong> Intimidation can also be used as a &ldquo;macro&rdquo; skill to simulate several hours of working the streets. See&nbsp;@Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Networking]{Networking}&nbsp;to see how to crack some heads for favors or information.</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"attribute":"spirit","isCoreSkill":false,"die":{"sides":8,"modifier":0},"wild-die":{"sides":6}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"3HvtK4sMp7flYKmT":3,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_qals24wpyph","path":"Skills","color":"#8c160f"},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.swade-core-rules.swade-skills.RrgAZp50CgQyyY6w"}}},{"_id":"oXD9LLAdtVm2vN8a","name":"Language (Common)","type":"skill","img":"icons/sundries/documents/document-letter-formal-tan.webp","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p>In some settings, such as those that focus on pulp action or &ldquo;planetary romance&rdquo; (where characters frequently travel among many strange civilizations), speaking various languages can simply be roleplayed with halting dialogue and campy accents that start out a little difficult and are quickly forgotten. The GM may ignore this skill altogether in these settings, or use the @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Multiple Languages]{Multiple Languages}&nbsp;&shy;option in the @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Setting Rules]{Setting Rules}.</p>\n<p>In more realistic settings, communication can be a major barrier that requires characters to put skill points into additional languages. In a 1980s World War Three game, for example, a group of United Nations paratroopers won&rsquo;t be able to speak with their foes unless they take Russian, Polish, or other languages common to the Warsaw Pact.</p>\n<p>If the Language skill is in use, it should be listed as Language (Spanish), Language (American Sign Language), etc. A character&rsquo;s die type also notes how fluent he is in it. (Characters start with a d8 in their own Language.)</p>\n<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<table class=\"table value-table\"><caption class=\"table-caption\">\n<h2 class=\"table-title\">Language Proficiency</h2>\n</caption>\n<tbody>\n<tr class=\"table-header-row\">\n<th class=\"table-column-header\" scope=\"col\">Skill</th>\n<th class=\"table-column-header\" scope=\"col\">Ability</th>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td>d4</td>\n<td>The character can read, write and speak common words and phrases.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>d6</td>\n<td>The speaker can carry on a prolonged but occasionally halting conversation.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>d8</td>\n<td>The character can speak fluently.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>d10</td>\n<td>The hero can mimic other dialects within the language.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>d12</td>\n<td>The speaker can masterfully recite important literary or oral works.</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>\n</div>\n<p><strong>Limited: </strong>Use whichever skill is lowest when performing an action that requires knowledge of a foreign language. @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Intimidation]{Intimidation} (if verbal), @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Persuasion]{Persuasion}, @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Research]{Research}, @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Taunt]{Taunt}, etc., are all limited by the character&rsquo;s Language skill.</p>\n<p>This limitation never applies to a character&rsquo;s native tongue.</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"attribute":"smarts","isCoreSkill":false,"die":{"sides":8,"modifier":0},"wild-die":{"sides":6}},"effects":[],"folder":"kFghWjY7gP7MEqav","sort":1,"permission":{"default":0,"3HvtK4sMp7flYKmT":3,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_nsugutrpau","path":"Skills","color":"#8c160f"},"journal-links":{},"core":{"sourceId":"Item.B8Z0BJ0B2ULcZFmw"}}},{"_id":"iy0z38oOByQSlz3U","name":"Language (Halfling)","type":"skill","img":"icons/sundries/documents/document-letter-formal-tan.webp","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p>In some settings, such as those that focus on pulp action or &ldquo;planetary romance&rdquo; (where characters frequently travel among many strange civilizations), speaking various languages can simply be roleplayed with halting dialogue and campy accents that start out a little difficult and are quickly forgotten. The GM may ignore this skill altogether in these settings, or use the @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Multiple Languages]{Multiple Languages}&nbsp;&shy;option in the @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Setting Rules]{Setting Rules}.</p>\n<p>In more realistic settings, communication can be a major barrier that requires characters to put skill points into additional languages. In a 1980s World War Three game, for example, a group of United Nations paratroopers won&rsquo;t be able to speak with their foes unless they take Russian, Polish, or other languages common to the Warsaw Pact.</p>\n<p>If the Language skill is in use, it should be listed as Language (Spanish), Language (American Sign Language), etc. A character&rsquo;s die type also notes how fluent he is in it. (Characters start with a d8 in their own Language.)</p>\n<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<table class=\"table value-table\"><caption class=\"table-caption\">\n<h2 class=\"table-title\">Language Proficiency</h2>\n</caption>\n<tbody>\n<tr class=\"table-header-row\">\n<th class=\"table-column-header\" scope=\"col\">Skill</th>\n<th class=\"table-column-header\" scope=\"col\">Ability</th>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td>d4</td>\n<td>The character can read, write and speak common words and phrases.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>d6</td>\n<td>The speaker can carry on a prolonged but occasionally halting conversation.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>d8</td>\n<td>The character can speak fluently.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>d10</td>\n<td>The hero can mimic other dialects within the language.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>d12</td>\n<td>The speaker can masterfully recite important literary or oral works.</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>\n</div>\n<p><strong>Limited: </strong>Use whichever skill is lowest when performing an action that requires knowledge of a foreign language. @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Intimidation]{Intimidation} (if verbal), @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Persuasion]{Persuasion}, @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Research]{Research}, @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Taunt]{Taunt}, etc., are all limited by the character&rsquo;s Language skill.</p>\n<p>This limitation never applies to a character&rsquo;s native tongue.</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"attribute":"smarts","isCoreSkill":false,"die":{"sides":8,"modifier":0},"wild-die":{"sides":6}},"effects":[],"folder":"kFghWjY7gP7MEqav","sort":1,"permission":{"default":0,"3HvtK4sMp7flYKmT":3,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_nsugutrpau","path":"Skills","color":"#8c160f"},"journal-links":{},"core":{"sourceId":"Item.B8Z0BJ0B2ULcZFmw"}}},{"_id":"gQRQHq3VChuwmSzV","name":"Language (Elvish)","type":"skill","img":"icons/sundries/documents/document-letter-formal-tan.webp","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p>In some settings, such as those that focus on pulp action or &ldquo;planetary romance&rdquo; (where characters frequently travel among many strange civilizations), speaking various languages can simply be roleplayed with halting dialogue and campy accents that start out a little difficult and are quickly forgotten. The GM may ignore this skill altogether in these settings, or use the @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Multiple Languages]{Multiple Languages}&nbsp;&shy;option in the @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Setting Rules]{Setting Rules}.</p>\n<p>In more realistic settings, communication can be a major barrier that requires characters to put skill points into additional languages. In a 1980s World War Three game, for example, a group of United Nations paratroopers won&rsquo;t be able to speak with their foes unless they take Russian, Polish, or other languages common to the Warsaw Pact.</p>\n<p>If the Language skill is in use, it should be listed as Language (Spanish), Language (American Sign Language), etc. A character&rsquo;s die type also notes how fluent he is in it. (Characters start with a d8 in their own Language.)</p>\n<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<table class=\"table value-table\"><caption class=\"table-caption\">\n<h2 class=\"table-title\">Language Proficiency</h2>\n</caption>\n<tbody>\n<tr class=\"table-header-row\">\n<th class=\"table-column-header\" scope=\"col\">Skill</th>\n<th class=\"table-column-header\" scope=\"col\">Ability</th>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td>d4</td>\n<td>The character can read, write and speak common words and phrases.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>d6</td>\n<td>The speaker can carry on a prolonged but occasionally halting conversation.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>d8</td>\n<td>The character can speak fluently.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>d10</td>\n<td>The hero can mimic other dialects within the language.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>d12</td>\n<td>The speaker can masterfully recite important literary or oral works.</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>\n</div>\n<p><strong>Limited: </strong>Use whichever skill is lowest when performing an action that requires knowledge of a foreign language. @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Intimidation]{Intimidation} (if verbal), @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Persuasion]{Persuasion}, @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Research]{Research}, @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Taunt]{Taunt}, etc., are all limited by the character&rsquo;s Language skill.</p>\n<p>This limitation never applies to a character&rsquo;s native tongue.</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"attribute":"smarts","isCoreSkill":false,"die":{"sides":6,"modifier":0},"wild-die":{"sides":6}},"effects":[],"folder":"kFghWjY7gP7MEqav","sort":1,"permission":{"default":0,"3HvtK4sMp7flYKmT":3,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_nsugutrpau","path":"Skills","color":"#8c160f"},"journal-links":{},"core":{"sourceId":"Item.B8Z0BJ0B2ULcZFmw"}}},{"_id":"7jA8CuOvL4lMsLbg","name":"Performance","type":"skill","img":"icons/tools/instruments/lute-gold-brown.webp","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p>A good entertainer can lift the spirits, rally a crowd to action, or simply earn a few bucks from the locals. Specifics depend on the situation, setting, and how well the character is known in the area.</p>\n<p>Performance covers singing, acting, playing an instrument, or similar tasks that require an audience to appreciate.</p>\n<p><strong>Raising Funds:</strong> The amount of money a character can raise by performing is extremely subjective, but as a general rule a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{successful} performance raises 20% of the setting's @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Characters]{Starting Funds} with a success and 30% with a raise. The GM can multiply this amount by the performer's @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Advancement]{Rank} if she feels it's appropriate. These numbers work for typical performers who might be known in a small establishment or area. Larger performances can greatly boost the performer's fee, but also require more time, energy, and setup.</p>\n<p><strong>Deception: </strong>Performance can be used instead of @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Persuasion]{Persuasion} if the character is attempting to deceive, bluff, or disguise herself and the GM agrees it makes sense in the context of the situation.</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"attribute":"spirit","isCoreSkill":false,"die":{"sides":6,"modifier":0},"wild-die":{"sides":6}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"3HvtK4sMp7flYKmT":3,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_qals24wpyph","path":"Skills","color":"#8c160f"},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.swade-core-rules.swade-skills.SJ1nN0CmOHNQhfOQ"}}},{"_id":"pQV9TN9sKQnrMqBA","name":"Combat Training","type":"edge","img":"icons/environment/people/infantry.webp","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p>The fighter are trained and adept at feints and deception in combat to unbalance their opponent. They add +1 to the all rolls for @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Test]{Tests} in combat that use any of the following skills: @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Athletics]{Athletics}, @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Battle]{Battle}, @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Fighting]{Fighting}, @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Intimidation]{Intimidation}, or @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Shooting]{Shooting} rolls.</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Novice, Fighter"}},"effects":[],"folder":"i5aNd30ywxpcOuxy","sort":200000,"permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"flags":{"journal-links":{},"core":{"sourceId":"Item.iAxlS6GhMXNoZpnI"}}},{"_id":"MHgAVQFq1kJqhxbG","name":"Fighter","type":"edge","img":"icons/environment/people/infantry.webp","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p>Some take up arms for glory, wealth, or revenge. Others do battle to prove themselves, to protect others, or because they know nothing else. Still others learn the ways of weaponcraft to hone their bodies in battle and prove their mettle in the forge of war.</p>\n<p>Lords of the battlefield, fighters are a disparate lot. Some train with many weapons; some prefer just one. Whatever their tactics, fighters excel at combat. They protect their own and defeat their enemies, rarely shying away from battle. They often lead the charge, a role they relish even if they don&rsquo;t insist on it.</p>\n<p>These skilled warriors turn hunks of metal into arms capable of taming kingdoms, slaughtering monsters, and rousing the hearts of armies. Woe to those who dare stand against them.</p>\n<p>Fighters gain the following abilities:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Combat Training]{Combat Training}</li>\n<li>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Martial Flexibility]{Martial Flexibility}</li>\n</ul>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Novice, Strength d6+, Fighting d6+"}},"effects":[],"folder":"i5aNd30ywxpcOuxy","sort":100000,"permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"flags":{"journal-links":{},"core":{"sourceId":"Item.JSFKscBmodf3b9qX"}}},{"_id":"znEgpQ5w8lTh7YJ4","name":"Martial Flexibility","type":"edge","img":"icons/environment/people/infantry.webp","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p>Once per encounter, as a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Actions]{free action}, a fighter can choose to gain the benefits of a single Combat Edge. He must have the same Rank or higher as the Edge's Requirements, and the benefits of the chosen Edge end when the encounter ends.</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Fighter"}},"effects":[],"folder":"i5aNd30ywxpcOuxy","sort":200000,"permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"flags":{"journal-links":{},"core":{"sourceId":"Item.xWLvdULZeijuxwnc"}}},{"_id":"HVCL8zHMcKYH2leW","name":"Fleet-Footed","type":"edge","img":"icons/environment/people/group.webp","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p>The hero&rsquo;s @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Movement]{Pace} is increased by +2 and his @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Movement]{running die} increases one step (from d6 to d8, for example)</span></p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Novice, Agility d6+"}},"effects":[],"folder":"EnpCvbp1xbBRZIf1","sort":1300000,"permission":{"default":0,"3HvtK4sMp7flYKmT":3,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"flags":{"cf":null,"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.swade-core-rules.swade-edges.PTPwOeAxgwnjCiIv"}}},{"_id":"bn3zEKpaewDoyKzQ","name":"Quick","type":"edge","img":"icons/environment/people/group.webp","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p>Quick characters have lightning-fast reflexes and a cool head. Whenever you are dealt an @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Action Cards (Initiative)]{Action Card} of Five or lower, you may discard it and draw again until you get a card higher than Five.</span></p>\n<p>@Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Characters]{Characters} with both the @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Level Headed]{Level Headed} and Quick Edges first draw their additional card and choose which to take. If that card is a Five or less, the Quick Edge may be used to draw a replacement until it&rsquo;s Six or higher.</span></p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Novice, Agility d8+"}},"effects":[],"folder":"EnpCvbp1xbBRZIf1","sort":1800000,"permission":{"default":0,"3HvtK4sMp7flYKmT":3,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"flags":{"cf":null,"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.swade-core-rules.swade-edges.XHguf9iQ3N9yHN4Z"}}},{"_id":"5s6yDCmY9lOlhBlf","name":"Frenzy","type":"edge","img":"icons/environment/people/charge.webp","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p>A character with Frenzy&nbsp;rolls a second @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-skills.Fighting]{Fighting} die with any one of his Fighting attacks for the turn. The extra die may be allocated to the same or different targets as he sees fit. Resolve each separately</span></p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Seasoned, Fighting d8+"}},"effects":[],"folder":"hsEO07bFB8oM1LJo","sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"3HvtK4sMp7flYKmT":3,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"flags":{"cf":null,"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.swade-core-rules.swade-edges.DugtMFQnsmkUnQiv"}}},{"_id":"rLd6OYr6j2OSWfGD","name":"Mean","type":"hindrance","img":"icons/magic/holy/yin-yang-balance-symbol.webp","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p>This curmudgeon is ill-tempered and disagreeable. He has trouble doing anything kind for anyone else, must be paid for his troubles, and doesn&rsquo;t accept awards or favors graciously. Besides the obvious roleplaying issues, Mean characters subtract 1 from @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-skills.Persuasion]{Persuasion} @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{rolls}.</span></p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"major":false},"effects":[],"folder":"1updrtPaYhKD0fRY","sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"3HvtK4sMp7flYKmT":3,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"flags":{"cf":null,"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.swade-core-rules.swade-hindrances.sNgSwqh2fGyM6i14"}}},{"_id":"7XiebKl6VQRApcQ6","name":"Thin Skinned","type":"hindrance","img":"icons/magic/holy/yin-yang-balance-symbol.webp","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p>Personal attacks really get under this individual&rsquo;s skin. As a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Characters]{Minor} @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Hindrances]{Hindrance}, he subtracts 2 when resisting @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Intimidation]{Intimidation} attacks or insults directed towards him. As a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Characters]{Major}, he subtracts 4.</span></p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"major":false},"effects":[],"folder":"1updrtPaYhKD0fRY","sort":1100000,"permission":{"default":0,"3HvtK4sMp7flYKmT":3,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_paujlrjlvl","path":"Hindrances","color":"#8c160f"},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.swade-core-rules.swade-hindrances.7uHyQqqlYJRZoxUp"}}},{"_id":"ApxjgFdUiM2p4Y9v","name":"Axe, Hand (mwk)","type":"weapon","img":"icons/weapons/axes/axe-broad-engraved.webp","data":{"description":"","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"quantity":1,"weight":2,"price":310,"equippable":false,"equipped":true,"isVehicular":false,"mods":1,"actions":{"skill":"Fighting","skillMod":"","dmgMod":"","additional":{"czf29uz2s1":{"name":"Athletics (throwing)","type":"skill","rof":null,"skillMod":"","skillOverride":"Athletics","shotsUsed":null}}},"damage":"@str+d6","range":"3/6/12","rof":"1","ap":"1","minStr":"d6","shots":"0","currentShots":"0","ammo":"","autoReload":false},"effects":[],"folder":"ofLOMYgHLqfG1MyP","sort":800001,"permission":{"default":0,"ZvqefCj0L7TxJS56":3,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"flags":{"journal-links":{},"core":{"sourceId":"Item.F2JNgD0SfESTyCZ6"}}},{"_id":"KGDArywrleBpgKmK","name":"Resilient","type":"ability","img":"icons/creatures/fish/fish-fangtooth-skeletal-green.webp","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p>Elite Extras are tougher than usual. This might include specially bred orcs in a fantasy setting, particularly tough thugs or agents in the modern world, or even mutant animals created in the lab of some mad scientist.</p>\n<p>Resilient @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Wild Cards and Extras]{Extras} can take one @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Damage Effects]{Wound} before they're @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Damage Effects]{incapacitated}. @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Wild Cards and Extras]{Wild Cards} can't be Resilient. The ability exist to bring select Extras a little closer to the heroes and villains who lead them.</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"subtype":"special","grantsPowers":false},"effects":[],"folder":"vNo3WMiRK9jNtjZL","sort":2900000,"permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"flags":{"journal-links":{},"core":{"sourceId":"Item.qw10GaZFXFDuNQcm"}}},{"_id":"YTfaBIJCrm5QYRFv","name":"Brawler","type":"edge","img":"icons/environment/people/charge.webp","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p>His fists hit like hammers or his talons cut like scythes. His body feels like it&rsquo;s made of stone. Brawlers increase their @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Characters]{Toughness} by 1 and roll @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Traits]{Strength} +d4 when hitting with their fists or feet (or claws if they have them). If they already have a damage die from&nbsp;</span><strong>@Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Special Ability (Claws)]{Claws}</strong>, the @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Martial Artist]{Martial Artist} Edge, etc., increase the damage die type by one instead. </span></p>\n<p>The Brawler Edge doesn&rsquo;t make the character&rsquo;s fists </span><strong>@Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Natural Weapons]{Natural Weapons}</span></strong></p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Novice, Strength d8+, Vigor d8+"}},"effects":[{"_id":"kjzlcYkuLXL4NwhC","changes":[{"key":"data.stats.toughness.value","mode":2,"value":"1"}],"disabled":false,"duration":{"startTime":null},"icon":"icons/environment/people/charge.webp","label":"Brawler","transfer":true,"flags":{},"tint":null}],"folder":"hsEO07bFB8oM1LJo","sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"3HvtK4sMp7flYKmT":3,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"flags":{"cf":null,"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.swade-core-rules.swade-edges.q5NKwGPeK9PKQdIb"}}},{"_id":"kX2e3UbprC1SDnII","name":"Brave","type":"edge","img":"icons/skills/social/peace-luck-insult.webp","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p>Those with this Edge have learned to master their fear, or have dealt with so many horrors they&rsquo;ve become jaded. These valiant explorers add +2 to @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Fear]{Fear} checks and subtract 2 from </span><strong>@Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-tables.Fear Table]{Fear Table} </span></strong>results.</span></p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Novice, Spirit d6+"}},"effects":[],"folder":"RXzRwNmHRkixYrfR","sort":500000,"permission":{"default":0,"3HvtK4sMp7flYKmT":3,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_9dc4ijzy8uh","path":"Edges#/CF_SEP/Background Edges","color":"#000000"},"journal-links":{},"core":{"sourceId":"Item.WJbfV0MEvQBjHEaE"}}},{"_id":"fxWX3PiDspiVbDas","name":"Luck","type":"edge","img":"icons/skills/social/peace-luck-insult.webp","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p>The adventurer seems to be blessed by fate, karma, the gods, or whatever external forces he believes in (or believe in him!). </span></p>\n<p>He draws one extra @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Bennies]{Benny} at the beginning of each game session, allowing him to succeed at important tasks more often than most, and survive incredible dangers.</span></p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Novice"}},"effects":[{"_id":"ypFj4ugwOSUtjOLm","changes":[{"key":"data.bennies.max","mode":2,"value":"1"}],"disabled":false,"duration":{"startTime":null},"icon":"icons/skills/social/peace-luck-insult.webp","label":"Luck","transfer":true,"flags":{},"tint":null}],"folder":"RXzRwNmHRkixYrfR","sort":400000,"permission":{"default":0,"3HvtK4sMp7flYKmT":3,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_9dc4ijzy8uh","path":"Edges#/CF_SEP/Background Edges","color":"#000000"},"journal-links":{},"core":{"sourceId":"Item.a5BHUWx93nGoO2mo"}}}],"effects":[{"_id":"PfqXp0vlhAqmaicN","changes":[{"key":"data.stats.toughness.value","mode":2,"value":"1"}],"disabled":false,"duration":{"startTime":28973116800},"icon":"icons/environment/people/charge.webp","label":"Brawler","origin":"Actor.WN58p23HYeWyTQXL.Item.YTfaBIJCrm5QYRFv","tint":null,"transfer":false,"flags":{}},{"_id":"as7pjFynmnQL6H4G","changes":[{"key":"data.bennies.max","mode":2,"value":"1"}],"disabled":false,"duration":{"startTime":28973116800},"icon":"icons/skills/social/peace-luck-insult.webp","label":"Luck","origin":"Actor.WN58p23HYeWyTQXL.Item.fxWX3PiDspiVbDas","tint":null,"transfer":false,"flags":{}}],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"flags":{"journal-links":{"references":{}},"cf":{"id":"temp_3a04s0jrz4j","path":"Pirates of Cyre Bestiary#/CF_SEP/NPC's","color":"#000000"}},"_id":"NI8DuzUr5xNAOcht"}
{"name":"Krornik Kragshard","type":"npc","img":"https://assets.forge-vtt.com/5f43f8ea1a91d63438d13159/artwork-adventures/pirates-of-cyre/characters/krornik-kragshard.webp","data":{"attributes":{"agility":{"die":{"sides":6,"modifier":0},"wild-die":{"sides":6}},"smarts":{"die":{"sides":8,"modifier":0},"wild-die":{"sides":6},"animal":false},"spirit":{"die":{"sides":6,"modifier":0},"wild-die":{"sides":6},"unShakeBonus":0},"strength":{"die":{"sides":6,"modifier":0},"wild-die":{"sides":6},"encumbranceSteps":0},"vigor":{"die":{"sides":8,"modifier":0},"wild-die":{"sides":6}}},"stats":{"speed":{"runningDie":4,"runningMod":0,"value":5},"toughness":{"value":0,"armor":0,"modifier":0},"parry":{"value":5,"modifier":0},"size":0},"details":{"biography":{"value":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p>xxxxx</p>\n</div>"},"species":{"name":""},"currency":500,"wealth":{"die":6,"modifier":0,"wild-die":6},"conviction":{"value":0,"active":false},"autoCalcToughness":true,"autoCalcParry":true},"powerPoints":{},"fatigue":{"value":0,"min":0,"max":2},"wounds":{"value":0,"min":0,"max":0,"ignored":0},"advances":{"value":0,"rank":"Novice","details":""},"bennies":{"value":2,"max":2},"status":{"isShaken":false,"isDistracted":false,"isVulnerable":false,"isStunned":false,"isEntangled":false,"isBound":false},"initiative":{"hasHesitant":false,"hasLevelHeaded":false,"hasImpLevelHeaded":false,"hasQuick":false},"additionalStats":{},"wildcard":false},"token":{"flags":{},"name":"Blank","displayName":30,"img":"modules/etu-rules/assets/bestiary_tokens/sonya-alvarez-min.png","tint":null,"width":1,"height":1,"scale":1,"mirrorX":false,"mirrorY":false,"lockRotation":false,"rotation":0,"vision":true,"dimSight":0,"brightSight":0,"dimLight":0,"brightLight":0,"sightAngle":0,"lightAngle":0,"lightColor":null,"lightAlpha":1,"lightAnimation":{"speed":5,"intensity":5},"actorId":null,"actorLink":true,"disposition":0,"displayBars":0,"bar1":{"attribute":""},"bar2":{"attribute":""},"randomImg":false,"alpha":1},"items":[{"_id":"UZW0tLJicg0VZOp4","name":"Athletics","type":"skill","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p>Athletics combines an individual&rsquo;s coordin&shy;ation with learned skills such as climbing, jumping, balancing, biking, wrestling, skiing, swimming, throwing, or catching. Characters who rely on physical power more than coordination can take the @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Brute]{Brute} Edge to link this skill to @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Traits]{Strength} instead of @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Traits]{Agility}.</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"attribute":"agility","isCoreSkill":false,"die":{"sides":6,"modifier":0},"wild-die":{"sides":6}},"sort":100000,"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_nsugutrpau","path":"Skills","color":"#8c160f"},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.swade-core-rules.swade-skills.Athletics"}},"img":"icons/magic/control/buff-strength-muscle-damage.webp","effects":[],"folder":null,"permission":{"default":0}},{"_id":"W5lfcCNjirSPUH42","name":"Common Knowledge","type":"skill","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\"><p>Characters roll Common Knowledge to know people, places, and things of their world, including etiquette, geography, culture, popular technology, contacts, and customs.</p></div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"attribute":"smarts","isCoreSkill":false,"die":{"sides":8,"modifier":0},"wild-die":{"sides":6}},"sort":200000,"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_nsugutrpau","path":"Skills","color":"#8c160f"},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.swade-core-rules.swade-skills.Common Knowledge"}},"img":"icons/sundries/documents/document-official-capital.webp","effects":[],"folder":null,"permission":{"default":0}},{"_id":"quj5jF3vNls1j5E3","name":"Notice","type":"skill","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p>Notice is a hero&rsquo;s general awareness and alertness. It&rsquo;s used to sense sights, sounds, tastes, and smells, spot clues, detect ambushes, spot hidden weapons on a foe, or tell if a rival is lying, frightened, happy, etc.</p>\n<p>@Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{Success} conveys basic information&mdash;the character hears movement in the forest, smells distant smoke, or senses someone isn&rsquo;t being completely truthful.</p>\n<p>A @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{raise} grants more detail, such as the direction of a sound or odor or what topic a person is avoiding or lying about.</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"attribute":"smarts","isCoreSkill":false,"die":{"sides":6,"modifier":0},"wild-die":{"sides":6}},"sort":300000,"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_nsugutrpau","path":"Skills","color":"#8c160f"},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.swade-core-rules.swade-skills.ZvwjzMLxsneptV4T"}},"img":"icons/creatures/eyes/human-single-blue.webp","effects":[],"folder":null,"permission":{"default":0}},{"_id":"TOEzoo2Lf4A5JXOF","name":"Persuasion","type":"skill","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p>Persuasion is the ability to convince others to do what you want through reason, cajoling, deception, rewards, or other friendly means. Persuasion isn&rsquo;t mind control. It can change someone&rsquo;s attitude but not their goals. A bandit may let you keep a sentimental piece of jewelry with a good Persuasion roll but still takes all your other goods.</p>\n<p>When used to @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Support]{Support} allies it&rsquo;s an unopposed roll. If the target is resistant, it&rsquo;s an @JournalEntry[JBxsGv2wAoAmoCDe]{opposed} roll vs. the target&rsquo;s @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Traits]{Spirit}. The GM should modify the roll as she sees fit based on roleplaying, any pertinent @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Edges]{Edges} or @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Hindrances]{Hindrances} that affect the conversation, and the circumstances.</p>\n<p><strong>Reaction Level:</strong> How much a person is willing to cooperate depends largely on their attitude toward whoever&rsquo;s talking to them. The Game Master can decide how nonplayer characters feel based on the setting, or roll on the @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-tables.Reaction Table]{Reaction Table} if she has no preconceived notions.</p>\n<p>@Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{Success} improves the target&rsquo;s attitude one level and a raise improves it two. Further increases aren&rsquo;t generally possible in the same encounter&mdash;it takes individuals a little time to adjust their biases.</p>\n<p>@Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{Failure} means the target won&rsquo;t change his mind this scene or until the situation changes in some important way. A @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{Critical Failure} also <em>reduces</em> the target&rsquo;s attitude two levels.</p>\n<p>Only one roll should generally be allowed per interaction unless new information is revealed, a substantial reward is offered, etc.</p>\n<p><strong>Networking: </strong>Characters can also use Persuasion as a &ldquo;macro skill,&rdquo; simulating a few hours or an evening&rsquo;s time hobnobbing and socializing to gain favors or information. See @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Networking]{Networking}.</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"attribute":"spirit","isCoreSkill":false,"die":{"sides":6,"modifier":0},"wild-die":{"sides":6}},"sort":400000,"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_nsugutrpau","path":"Skills","color":"#8c160f"},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.swade-core-rules.swade-skills.Persuasion"}},"img":"icons/skills/social/diplomacy-handshake.webp","effects":[],"folder":null,"permission":{"default":0}},{"_id":"8VzaSa3EEDrMz6PR","name":"Stealth","type":"skill","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p>Stealth is the ability to hide and move quietly. A simple @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{success} on a Stealth roll means the character avoids detection if enemies aren&rsquo;t particularly alert. If the character @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{fails} the roll, the enemy realizes something is amiss and begins actively searching for whatever roused them.</p>\n<p>Once foes are alerted and active, Stealth is opposed by @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Notice]{Notice} (a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{group roll} if there are many foes.</p>\n<p>The GM should apply any circumstantial penalties to @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Notice]{Notice} rolls for @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Illumination]{darkness}, @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Cover and Obstacles]{cover}, noise, distractions, and any difference in the target&rsquo;s @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Size and Scale]{Scale} (just like when attacking). Sneaking through dry leaves might subtract 2 from the Stealth roll, for example, while spotting someone in the dark uses the @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Illumination]{Illumination} penalty (&minus;4). Don&rsquo;t apply the same modifier to both rolls, however. If Stealth is at &minus;2 for the leaves, don&rsquo;t give Notice a +2 for them as well.</p>\n<p><strong>Sneak Attack: </strong> Sneaking up close enough to make a melee attack <em>always</em> requires an @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{opposed} Stealth roll versus the target&rsquo;s @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Notice]{Notice}, whether the guard is actively looking for trouble or not. If successful, the victim is @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Distracted and Vulnerable]{Vulnerable} to the attacker, but only until the attacker&rsquo;s turn ends. With a raise, the attacker has @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.The Drop]{The Drop} instead.</p>\n<p><strong>Movement:</strong> In combat, characters roll Stealth each turn as a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Actions]{free action} at the end of their move or any action the GM thinks might draw attention.</p>\n<p>Out of combat, the distance moved depends entirely on the situation. The GM might want a roll every minute if the group is sneaking around the perimeter of a defensive position, or every few miles if they&rsquo;re trying to quietly walk the path through a dark forest without alerting the creatures that live there.</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"attribute":"agility","isCoreSkill":false,"die":{"sides":4,"modifier":"0"},"wild-die":{"sides":6}},"sort":500000,"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_nsugutrpau","path":"Skills","color":"#8c160f"},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.swade-core-rules.swade-skills.Stealth"}},"img":"icons/magic/nature/stealth-hide-eyes-green.webp","effects":[],"folder":null,"permission":{"default":0}},{"_id":"BQ3OOQlkZvCl1Lfb","name":"Unskilled Attempt","type":"skill","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p>If a character doesn&rsquo;t have a skill for an action he&rsquo;s attempting, he rolls a d4 for his skill die (and a Wild Die if a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Wild Cards and Extras]{Wild Card}) and subtracts 2 from the total.</p>\n<p>The GM may decide certain tasks cannot be attempted unskilled, such as performing complex surgery or flying a commercial jet.</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"attribute":"agility","isCoreSkill":false,"die":{"sides":4,"modifier":"-2"},"wild-die":{"sides":6}},"sort":1100000,"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_nsugutrpau","path":"Skills","color":"#8c160f"},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.swade-core-rules.swade-skills.zcn1epcU4FEJGGyI"}},"img":"icons/magic/symbols/question-stone-yellow.webp","effects":[],"folder":null,"permission":{"default":0}},{"_id":"uaVAhwDnUDLFZFXm","name":"Unarmed strike","type":"weapon","data":{"description":"","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"quantity":1,"weight":0,"price":0,"equippable":false,"equipped":true,"isVehicular":false,"mods":1,"actions":{"skill":"","skillMod":"","dmgMod":"","additional":{}},"damage":"@str","range":"","rof":"1","ap":"0","minStr":"","shots":"0","currentShots":"0","ammo":"","autoReload":false},"sort":1400000,"flags":{},"img":"icons/skills/melee/unarmed-punch-fist.webp","effects":[],"folder":null,"permission":{"default":0}},{"_id":"GjcL17dCtOeFUvbu","name":"Fighting","type":"skill","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p>Fighting covers all hand-to-hand (melee) attacks, whether it&rsquo;s with fists, axes, laser swords, or martial arts. See @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Combat]{Chapter Three} for the combat rules and the various maneuvers a warrior might attempt.</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"attribute":"agility","isCoreSkill":false,"die":{"sides":6,"modifier":0},"wild-die":{"sides":6}},"sort":1500000,"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_qals24wpyph","path":"Skills","color":"#8c160f"},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.swade-core-rules.swade-skills.wWiwjPlzAQU3TN9l"}},"img":"icons/skills/melee/hand-grip-sword-white-brown.webp","effects":[],"folder":null,"permission":{"default":0}},{"_id":"lOUi2JoByDSV740w","name":"Habit (Alcoholic)","type":"hindrance","img":"icons/magic/holy/yin-yang-balance-symbol.webp","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p>Your warrior has an annoying or dangerous compulsion. A @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Characters]{Minor} Habit irritates those around her but isn&rsquo;t dangerous. Maybe she picks her nose, can&rsquo;t stop fiddling with her phone, says &ldquo;y&rsquo;know&rdquo; in the middle of every sentence, or chews and smacks her gum loudly and often. Allies avoid her if possible.</p>\n<p>A @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Characters]{Major} Habit is a physical or mental addiction of some sort that is debilitating or possibly even deadly. This includes drug use, chronic drinking, or perhaps even an addiction to virtual reality in a hightech setting.</p>\n<p>An addict who doesn&rsquo;t get his fix must make a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Traits]{Vigor}&nbsp;roll every 24 hours he goes without or take a level of @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Fatigue]{Fatigue}.</p>\n<p>Once every 24 hours, a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-skills.Healing]{Healing} roll with some sort of appropriate medicine removes one level of @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Fatigue]{Fatigue}&nbsp;for four hours. After that the Fatigue returns and can only be recovered with the addicting substance.</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"major":true},"effects":[],"folder":"1updrtPaYhKD0fRY","sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"3HvtK4sMp7flYKmT":3,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"flags":{"cf":null,"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.swade-core-rules.swade-hindrances.DvgwzTd4xsaPE77h"}}},{"_id":"FXkjNgX70HUd4vMp","name":"Obese","type":"hindrance","img":"icons/magic/holy/yin-yang-balance-symbol.webp","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p>Those who carry their weight well have the @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Brawny]{Brawny} Edge. Those who don&rsquo;t are Obese. A character cannot be both @Compendium[swade.edges.Brawny]{Brawny} and Obese, and this @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Hindrances]{Hindrance} can&rsquo;t increase your @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Size and Scale]{Size} above +3. </span></p>\n<p>An Obese hero&rsquo;s @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Size and Scale]{Size} (and therefore @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Characters]{Toughness}) increase by +1. His @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Movement]{Pace} is reduced by 1, and his @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Movement]{running die} by one die type (minimum d4). @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Traits]{Strength} is considered one die type less (minimum d4) for armor and worn gear (not weapons). They may also have difficulty finding armor or @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Common Gear Table]{clothing} that fits or entering confined spaces.</span></p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"major":true},"effects":[{"_id":"GC2tkR9tmhi1ganW","changes":[{"key":"data.stats.size","mode":2,"value":"1"},{"key":"data.stats.speed.value","mode":2,"value":"-1"},{"key":"data.stats.speed.runningDie","mode":2,"value":"-2"},{"key":"data.attributes.strength.die.sides","mode":2,"value":"-2"}],"disabled":false,"duration":{"startTime":null},"icon":"icons/magic/holy/yin-yang-balance-symbol.webp","label":"Obese","transfer":true,"flags":{},"tint":null}],"folder":"1updrtPaYhKD0fRY","sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"3HvtK4sMp7flYKmT":3,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"flags":{"cf":null,"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.swade-core-rules.swade-hindrances.W7sBGVEV7SxVJ5LY"}}},{"_id":"gcbqDP4ePVf2kg4O","name":"Kitchen Knife","type":"weapon","img":"icons/weapons/daggers/knife-engraved-black.webp","data":{"description":"","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"quantity":1,"weight":1,"price":2,"equippable":false,"equipped":true,"isVehicular":false,"mods":1,"actions":{"skill":"Fighting","skillMod":"","dmgMod":"","additional":{"oyxuzdjora":{"name":"Athletics (throwing)","type":"skill","rof":null,"skillMod":"","skillOverride":"Athletics","shotsUsed":null}}},"damage":"@str+d4","range":"3/6/12","rof":"1","ap":"0","minStr":"d4","shots":"0","currentShots":"0","ammo":"","autoReload":false},"effects":[],"folder":"ofLOMYgHLqfG1MyP","sort":400001,"permission":{"default":0,"ZvqefCj0L7TxJS56":3,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"flags":{"journal-links":{},"core":{"sourceId":"Item.GxVNY83rIxMpxCqB"}}},{"_id":"V4o3jDNEfg9JdmfP","name":"Boating","type":"skill","img":"icons/environment/settlement/ship.webp","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\"><p>Characters with this skill can handle most any boat or ship common to their setting. They also know how to handle common tasks associated with their vessel such as tying knots, rigging sails, or following currents.</p></div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"attribute":"agility","isCoreSkill":false,"die":{"sides":6,"modifier":0},"wild-die":{"sides":6}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_azxylmvr7yo","path":"Skills","color":"#008000"},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.swade-core-rules.swade-skills.WMWgIVDuAW4cHxj2"}}},{"_id":"hgqtHmh5rVEZXQRp","name":"Language (Common)","type":"skill","img":"icons/sundries/documents/document-letter-formal-tan.webp","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p>In some settings, such as those that focus on pulp action or &ldquo;planetary romance&rdquo; (where characters frequently travel among many strange civilizations), speaking various languages can simply be roleplayed with halting dialogue and campy accents that start out a little difficult and are quickly forgotten. The GM may ignore this skill altogether in these settings, or use the @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Multiple Languages]{Multiple Languages}&nbsp;&shy;option in the @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Setting Rules]{Setting Rules}.</p>\n<p>In more realistic settings, communication can be a major barrier that requires characters to put skill points into additional languages. In a 1980s World War Three game, for example, a group of United Nations paratroopers won&rsquo;t be able to speak with their foes unless they take Russian, Polish, or other languages common to the Warsaw Pact.</p>\n<p>If the Language skill is in use, it should be listed as Language (Spanish), Language (American Sign Language), etc. A character&rsquo;s die type also notes how fluent he is in it. (Characters start with a d8 in their own Language.)</p>\n<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<table class=\"table value-table\"><caption class=\"table-caption\">\n<h2 class=\"table-title\">Language Proficiency</h2>\n</caption>\n<tbody>\n<tr class=\"table-header-row\">\n<th class=\"table-column-header\" scope=\"col\">Skill</th>\n<th class=\"table-column-header\" scope=\"col\">Ability</th>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td>d4</td>\n<td>The character can read, write and speak common words and phrases.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>d6</td>\n<td>The speaker can carry on a prolonged but occasionally halting conversation.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>d8</td>\n<td>The character can speak fluently.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>d10</td>\n<td>The hero can mimic other dialects within the language.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>d12</td>\n<td>The speaker can masterfully recite important literary or oral works.</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>\n</div>\n<p><strong>Limited: </strong>Use whichever skill is lowest when performing an action that requires knowledge of a foreign language. @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Intimidation]{Intimidation} (if verbal), @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Persuasion]{Persuasion}, @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Research]{Research}, @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Taunt]{Taunt}, etc., are all limited by the character&rsquo;s Language skill.</p>\n<p>This limitation never applies to a character&rsquo;s native tongue.</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"attribute":"smarts","isCoreSkill":false,"die":{"sides":8,"modifier":0},"wild-die":{"sides":6}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_azxylmvr7yo","path":"Skills","color":"#008000"},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.swade-core-rules.swade-skills.XIuR2IyQtewm5BZP"}}},{"_id":"ENKI20IumFFXneOR","name":"Language (Dwarvish)","type":"skill","img":"icons/sundries/documents/document-letter-formal-tan.webp","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p>In some settings, such as those that focus on pulp action or &ldquo;planetary romance&rdquo; (where characters frequently travel among many strange civilizations), speaking various languages can simply be roleplayed with halting dialogue and campy accents that start out a little difficult and are quickly forgotten. The GM may ignore this skill altogether in these settings, or use the @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Multiple Languages]{Multiple Languages}&nbsp;&shy;option in the @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Setting Rules]{Setting Rules}.</p>\n<p>In more realistic settings, communication can be a major barrier that requires characters to put skill points into additional languages. In a 1980s World War Three game, for example, a group of United Nations paratroopers won&rsquo;t be able to speak with their foes unless they take Russian, Polish, or other languages common to the Warsaw Pact.</p>\n<p>If the Language skill is in use, it should be listed as Language (Spanish), Language (American Sign Language), etc. A character&rsquo;s die type also notes how fluent he is in it. (Characters start with a d8 in their own Language.)</p>\n<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<table class=\"table value-table\"><caption class=\"table-caption\">\n<h2 class=\"table-title\">Language Proficiency</h2>\n</caption>\n<tbody>\n<tr class=\"table-header-row\">\n<th class=\"table-column-header\" scope=\"col\">Skill</th>\n<th class=\"table-column-header\" scope=\"col\">Ability</th>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td>d4</td>\n<td>The character can read, write and speak common words and phrases.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>d6</td>\n<td>The speaker can carry on a prolonged but occasionally halting conversation.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>d8</td>\n<td>The character can speak fluently.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>d10</td>\n<td>The hero can mimic other dialects within the language.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>d12</td>\n<td>The speaker can masterfully recite important literary or oral works.</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>\n</div>\n<p><strong>Limited: </strong>Use whichever skill is lowest when performing an action that requires knowledge of a foreign language. @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Intimidation]{Intimidation} (if verbal), @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Persuasion]{Persuasion}, @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Research]{Research}, @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Taunt]{Taunt}, etc., are all limited by the character&rsquo;s Language skill.</p>\n<p>This limitation never applies to a character&rsquo;s native tongue.</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"attribute":"smarts","isCoreSkill":false,"die":{"sides":8,"modifier":0},"wild-die":{"sides":6}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_azxylmvr7yo","path":"Skills","color":"#008000"},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.swade-core-rules.swade-skills.XIuR2IyQtewm5BZP"}}},{"_id":"o4zkG0eHpwbmz0ie","name":"Language (Goblin)","type":"skill","img":"icons/sundries/documents/document-letter-formal-tan.webp","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p>In some settings, such as those that focus on pulp action or &ldquo;planetary romance&rdquo; (where characters frequently travel among many strange civilizations), speaking various languages can simply be roleplayed with halting dialogue and campy accents that start out a little difficult and are quickly forgotten. The GM may ignore this skill altogether in these settings, or use the @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Multiple Languages]{Multiple Languages}&nbsp;&shy;option in the @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Setting Rules]{Setting Rules}.</p>\n<p>In more realistic settings, communication can be a major barrier that requires characters to put skill points into additional languages. In a 1980s World War Three game, for example, a group of United Nations paratroopers won&rsquo;t be able to speak with their foes unless they take Russian, Polish, or other languages common to the Warsaw Pact.</p>\n<p>If the Language skill is in use, it should be listed as Language (Spanish), Language (American Sign Language), etc. A character&rsquo;s die type also notes how fluent he is in it. (Characters start with a d8 in their own Language.)</p>\n<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<table class=\"table value-table\"><caption class=\"table-caption\">\n<h2 class=\"table-title\">Language Proficiency</h2>\n</caption>\n<tbody>\n<tr class=\"table-header-row\">\n<th class=\"table-column-header\" scope=\"col\">Skill</th>\n<th class=\"table-column-header\" scope=\"col\">Ability</th>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td>d4</td>\n<td>The character can read, write and speak common words and phrases.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>d6</td>\n<td>The speaker can carry on a prolonged but occasionally halting conversation.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>d8</td>\n<td>The character can speak fluently.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>d10</td>\n<td>The hero can mimic other dialects within the language.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>d12</td>\n<td>The speaker can masterfully recite important literary or oral works.</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>\n</div>\n<p><strong>Limited: </strong>Use whichever skill is lowest when performing an action that requires knowledge of a foreign language. @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Intimidation]{Intimidation} (if verbal), @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Persuasion]{Persuasion}, @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Research]{Research}, @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Taunt]{Taunt}, etc., are all limited by the character&rsquo;s Language skill.</p>\n<p>This limitation never applies to a character&rsquo;s native tongue.</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"attribute":"smarts","isCoreSkill":false,"die":{"sides":6,"modifier":0},"wild-die":{"sides":6}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_azxylmvr7yo","path":"Skills","color":"#008000"},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.swade-core-rules.swade-skills.XIuR2IyQtewm5BZP"}}},{"_id":"dIlOnbuBe7q8UlNB","name":"Performance","type":"skill","img":"icons/tools/instruments/lute-gold-brown.webp","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p>A good entertainer can lift the spirits, rally a crowd to action, or simply earn a few bucks from the locals. Specifics depend on the situation, setting, and how well the character is known in the area.</p>\n<p>Performance covers singing, acting, playing an instrument, or similar tasks that require an audience to appreciate.</p>\n<p><strong>Raising Funds:</strong> The amount of money a character can raise by performing is extremely subjective, but as a general rule a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{successful} performance raises 20% of the setting's @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Characters]{Starting Funds} with a success and 30% with a raise. The GM can multiply this amount by the performer's @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Advancement]{Rank} if she feels it's appropriate. These numbers work for typical performers who might be known in a small establishment or area. Larger performances can greatly boost the performer's fee, but also require more time, energy, and setup.</p>\n<p><strong>Deception: </strong>Performance can be used instead of @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Persuasion]{Persuasion} if the character is attempting to deceive, bluff, or disguise herself and the GM agrees it makes sense in the context of the situation.</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"attribute":"spirit","isCoreSkill":false,"die":{"sides":4,"modifier":0},"wild-die":{"sides":6}},"effects":[],"folder":"cgfmurTJRwbCvmCc","sort":2400001,"permission":{"default":0,"3HvtK4sMp7flYKmT":3,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_qals24wpyph","path":"Skills","color":"#8c160f"},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.swade-core-rules.swade-skills.SJ1nN0CmOHNQhfOQ"}}},{"_id":"e2DoL9jjQmdLcPHg","name":"Survival","type":"skill","img":"icons/environment/settlement/tent.webp","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p>Survival allows a character to find food, water, or shelter in hostile environments. It can also be used to navigate wilderness environments, figure out which plants are good to eat and which aren&rsquo;t, and so on.</p>\n<p>A @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{successful} Survival roll provides enough food and water for one person for one day; or five people with a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{raise}.</p>\n<p>More detailed information on @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Hunger]{Hunger} and @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Thirst]{Thirst} can be found under @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Hazards]{Hazards} section.</p>\n<p><strong>Tracking: </strong>Survival can also be used to detect and follow tracks. Each roll generally covers following the tracks for one mile, but the GM should adjust this as needed for specific circumstances.</p>\n<p>The Game Master should assign a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{bonus or penalty} based on the target, environment, and time. Tracking a large group that recently passed through a snow-covered area might grant a bonus of +4, while following a single person over rocks and streams after more than a day incurs a &minus;4 penalty.</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"attribute":"smarts","isCoreSkill":false,"die":{"sides":4,"modifier":0},"wild-die":{"sides":6}},"effects":[],"folder":"cgfmurTJRwbCvmCc","sort":1075001,"permission":{"default":0,"3HvtK4sMp7flYKmT":3,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_qals24wpyph","path":"Skills","color":"#8c160f"},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.swade-core-rules.swade-skills.15aEAJjDEjQy4fHF"}}}],"effects":[{"_id":"kBSy9tQ1wpNG3IH9","changes":[{"key":"data.stats.size","mode":2,"value":"1"},{"key":"data.stats.speed.value","mode":2,"value":"-1"},{"key":"data.stats.speed.runningDie","mode":2,"value":"-2"},{"key":"data.attributes.strength.die.sides","mode":2,"value":"-2"}],"disabled":false,"duration":{"startTime":28973116800},"icon":"icons/magic/holy/yin-yang-balance-symbol.webp","label":"Obese","origin":"Actor.gjZ3MYnC5l4iKY6y.Item.FXkjNgX70HUd4vMp","tint":null,"transfer":false,"flags":{}}],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"flags":{"journal-links":{"references":{}},"cf":{"id":"temp_3a04s0jrz4j","path":"Pirates of Cyre Bestiary#/CF_SEP/NPC's","color":"#000000"}},"_id":"Q5asnYfjlp4vQD7W"}
{"name":"#[CF_tempEntity]","type":"character","img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","data":{"attributes":{"agility":{"die":{"sides":4,"modifier":0},"wild-die":{"sides":6}},"smarts":{"die":{"sides":4,"modifier":0},"wild-die":{"sides":6},"animal":false},"spirit":{"die":{"sides":4,"modifier":0},"wild-die":{"sides":6},"unShakeBonus":0},"strength":{"die":{"sides":4,"modifier":0},"wild-die":{"sides":6},"encumbranceSteps":0},"vigor":{"die":{"sides":4,"modifier":0},"wild-die":{"sides":6}}},"stats":{"speed":{"runningDie":6,"runningMod":0,"value":6},"toughness":{"value":0,"armor":0,"modifier":0},"parry":{"value":0,"modifier":0},"size":0},"details":{"biography":{"value":""},"species":{"name":""},"currency":500,"wealth":{"die":6,"modifier":0,"wild-die":6},"conviction":{"value":0,"active":false},"autoCalcToughness":true,"autoCalcParry":true},"powerPoints":{},"fatigue":{"value":0,"min":0,"max":2},"wounds":{"value":0,"min":0,"max":3,"ignored":0},"advances":{"value":0,"rank":"Novice","details":""},"bennies":{"value":3,"max":3},"status":{"isShaken":false,"isDistracted":false,"isVulnerable":false,"isStunned":false,"isEntangled":false,"isBound":false},"initiative":{"hasHesitant":false,"hasLevelHeaded":false,"hasImpLevelHeaded":false,"hasQuick":false},"additionalStats":{},"wildcard":true},"token":{"name":"#[CF_tempEntity]","img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","displayName":0,"actorLink":false,"width":1,"height":1,"scale":1,"mirrorX":false,"mirrorY":false,"lockRotation":false,"rotation":0,"alpha":1,"vision":false,"dimSight":0,"brightSight":0,"dimLight":0,"brightLight":0,"sightAngle":0,"lightAngle":0,"lightAlpha":0.25,"lightAnimation":{"speed":5,"intensity":5},"disposition":-1,"displayBars":0,"bar1":{"attribute":null},"bar2":{"attribute":null},"flags":{},"randomImg":false,"actorId":null},"items":[{"_id":"BAaFJq4Ss7Bgmt8w","name":"Persuasion","type":"skill","img":"icons/skills/social/diplomacy-handshake.webp","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p>Persuasion is the ability to convince others to do what you want through reason, cajoling, deception, rewards, or other friendly means. Persuasion isn&rsquo;t mind control. It can change someone&rsquo;s attitude but not their goals. A bandit may let you keep a sentimental piece of jewelry with a good Persuasion roll but still takes all your other goods.</p>\n<p>When used to @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Support]{Support} allies it&rsquo;s an unopposed roll. If the target is resistant, it&rsquo;s an @JournalEntry[JBxsGv2wAoAmoCDe]{opposed} roll vs. the target&rsquo;s @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Traits]{Spirit}. The GM should modify the roll as she sees fit based on roleplaying, any pertinent @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Edges]{Edges} or @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Hindrances]{Hindrances} that affect the conversation, and the circumstances.</p>\n<p><strong>Reaction Level:</strong> How much a person is willing to cooperate depends largely on their attitude toward whoever&rsquo;s talking to them. The Game Master can decide how nonplayer characters feel based on the setting, or roll on the @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-tables.Reaction Table]{Reaction Table} if she has no preconceived notions.</p>\n<p>@Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{Success} improves the target&rsquo;s attitude one level and a raise improves it two. Further increases aren&rsquo;t generally possible in the same encounter&mdash;it takes individuals a little time to adjust their biases.</p>\n<p>@Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{Failure} means the target won&rsquo;t change his mind this scene or until the situation changes in some important way. A @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{Critical Failure} also <em>reduces</em> the target&rsquo;s attitude two levels.</p>\n<p>Only one roll should generally be allowed per interaction unless new information is revealed, a substantial reward is offered, etc.</p>\n<p><strong>Networking: </strong>Characters can also use Persuasion as a &ldquo;macro skill,&rdquo; simulating a few hours or an evening&rsquo;s time hobnobbing and socializing to gain favors or information. See @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Networking]{Networking}.</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"attribute":"spirit","isCoreSkill":true,"die":{"sides":4,"modifier":0},"wild-die":{"sides":6}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_azxylmvr7yo","path":"Skills","color":"#008000"},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.swade-core-rules.swade-skills.xOmuCR92Ys9jD5vg"}}},{"_id":"Dk7MTEB8I6MuoNKP","name":"Notice","type":"skill","img":"icons/creatures/eyes/human-single-blue.webp","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p>Notice is a hero&rsquo;s general awareness and alertness. It&rsquo;s used to sense sights, sounds, tastes, and smells, spot clues, detect ambushes, spot hidden weapons on a foe, or tell if a rival is lying, frightened, happy, etc.</p>\n<p>@Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{Success} conveys basic information&mdash;the character hears movement in the forest, smells distant smoke, or senses someone isn&rsquo;t being completely truthful.</p>\n<p>A @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{raise} grants more detail, such as the direction of a sound or odor or what topic a person is avoiding or lying about.</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"attribute":"smarts","isCoreSkill":true,"die":{"sides":4,"modifier":0},"wild-die":{"sides":6}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_azxylmvr7yo","path":"Skills","color":"#008000"},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.swade-core-rules.swade-skills.yvw9bMgsrWQXuZN2"}}},{"_id":"X0BYJUZclN1vQeaV","name":"Athletics","type":"skill","img":"icons/magic/control/buff-strength-muscle-damage.webp","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p>Athletics combines an individual&rsquo;s coordin&shy;ation with learned skills such as climbing, jumping, balancing, biking, wrestling, skiing, swimming, throwing, or catching. Characters who rely on physical power more than coordination can take the @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Brute]{Brute} Edge to link this skill to @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Traits]{Strength} instead of @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Traits]{Agility}.</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"attribute":"agility","isCoreSkill":true,"die":{"sides":4,"modifier":0},"wild-die":{"sides":6}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_azxylmvr7yo","path":"Skills","color":"#008000"},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.swade-core-rules.swade-skills.sAig03GZiFKqBX7p"}}},{"_id":"d8bbwVTHdQpb5AFb","name":"Stealth","type":"skill","img":"icons/magic/nature/stealth-hide-eyes-green.webp","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p>Stealth is the ability to hide and move quietly. A simple @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{success} on a Stealth roll means the character avoids detection if enemies aren&rsquo;t particularly alert. If the character @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{fails} the roll, the enemy realizes something is amiss and begins actively searching for whatever roused them.</p>\n<p>Once foes are alerted and active, Stealth is opposed by @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Notice]{Notice} (a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{group roll} if there are many foes.</p>\n<p>The GM should apply any circumstantial penalties to @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Notice]{Notice} rolls for @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Illumination]{darkness}, @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Cover and Obstacles]{cover}, noise, distractions, and any difference in the target&rsquo;s @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Size and Scale]{Scale} (just like when attacking). Sneaking through dry leaves might subtract 2 from the Stealth roll, for example, while spotting someone in the dark uses the @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Illumination]{Illumination} penalty (&minus;4). Don&rsquo;t apply the same modifier to both rolls, however. If Stealth is at &minus;2 for the leaves, don&rsquo;t give Notice a +2 for them as well.</p>\n<p><strong>Sneak Attack: </strong> Sneaking up close enough to make a melee attack <em>always</em> requires an @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{opposed} Stealth roll versus the target&rsquo;s @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Notice]{Notice}, whether the guard is actively looking for trouble or not. If successful, the victim is @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Distracted and Vulnerable]{Vulnerable} to the attacker, but only until the attacker&rsquo;s turn ends. With a raise, the attacker has @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.The Drop]{The Drop} instead.</p>\n<p><strong>Movement:</strong> In combat, characters roll Stealth each turn as a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Actions]{free action} at the end of their move or any action the GM thinks might draw attention.</p>\n<p>Out of combat, the distance moved depends entirely on the situation. The GM might want a roll every minute if the group is sneaking around the perimeter of a defensive position, or every few miles if they&rsquo;re trying to quietly walk the path through a dark forest without alerting the creatures that live there.</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"attribute":"agility","isCoreSkill":true,"die":{"sides":4,"modifier":0},"wild-die":{"sides":6}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_azxylmvr7yo","path":"Skills","color":"#008000"},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.swade-core-rules.swade-skills.z9FmdFVGOOW2kufm"}}},{"_id":"wT9Ir2pYgNXXi5iA","name":"Common Knowledge","type":"skill","img":"icons/sundries/documents/document-official-capital.webp","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\"><p>Characters roll Common Knowledge to know people, places, and things of their world, including etiquette, geography, culture, popular technology, contacts, and customs.</p></div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"attribute":"smarts","isCoreSkill":true,"die":{"sides":4,"modifier":0},"wild-die":{"sides":6}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_azxylmvr7yo","path":"Skills","color":"#008000"},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.swade-core-rules.swade-skills.8N1uMThntsjaUPem"}}},{"name":"Untrained","type":"skill","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/skill.svg","data":{"description":"","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"attribute":"","isCoreSkill":false,"die":{"sides":4,"modifier":-2},"wild-die":{"sides":6}},"_id":"zg149xozs1a7wpb6","effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0},"flags":{}}],"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_3a04s0jrz4j","path":"Pirates of Cyre Bestiary#/CF_SEP/NPC's","color":"#000000","name":"NPC's","children":["2OH6BHW2dWwq8OFH","56twwTP4lR2skY8E","CDp0gPIh75K20LjT","z2qkrFSshkwFRNra","Q5asnYfjlp4vQD7W","JdZmTO2mCUBMDTaY","gytbnCnNuCBAS9FR","raZYvUdO4Op0Mc0t","NI8DuzUr5xNAOcht","7lLpzNGV5uDjF3qL"],"folderPath":["temp_pw543v57cu"]}},"_id":"VVQDwlLpBEkpiBnV"}
{"name":"Mister Lagraa","type":"npc","img":"https://assets.forge-vtt.com/5f43f8ea1a91d63438d13159/artwork-adventures/pirates-of-cyre/characters/mister-lagraa.webp","data":{"attributes":{"agility":{"die":{"sides":8,"modifier":0},"wild-die":{"sides":6}},"smarts":{"die":{"sides":8,"modifier":0},"wild-die":{"sides":6},"animal":false},"spirit":{"die":{"sides":6,"modifier":0},"wild-die":{"sides":6},"unShakeBonus":0},"strength":{"die":{"sides":10,"modifier":0},"wild-die":{"sides":6},"encumbranceSteps":0},"vigor":{"die":{"sides":8,"modifier":0},"wild-die":{"sides":6}}},"stats":{"speed":{"runningDie":"6","runningMod":0,"value":6},"toughness":{"value":0,"armor":0,"modifier":0},"parry":{"value":7,"modifier":0},"size":1},"details":{"biography":{"value":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p>Mister Lagraa is Black Red's bullying and sadistic first mate. She is an angry young orc that is a huge, hulking muscled orc. At over 8' in height and over 400 lbs of pure muscle. Her face is fixed in an almost constant grimace, and her teeth are gray and yellow. She dresses in more traditional trible orcs clothes, but clearly takes great pride in herself. With everything well kept, well groomed, and shining.</p>\n</div>"},"species":{"name":""},"currency":500,"wealth":{"die":6,"modifier":0,"wild-die":6},"conviction":{"value":0,"active":false},"autoCalcToughness":true,"autoCalcParry":true},"powerPoints":{},"fatigue":{"value":0,"min":0,"max":2},"wounds":{"value":0,"min":0,"max":3,"ignored":0},"advances":{"value":0,"rank":"Novice","details":""},"bennies":{"value":2,"max":2},"status":{"isShaken":false,"isDistracted":false,"isVulnerable":false,"isStunned":false,"isEntangled":false,"isBound":false},"initiative":{"hasHesitant":false,"hasLevelHeaded":false,"hasImpLevelHeaded":false,"hasQuick":false},"additionalStats":{},"wildcard":true},"token":{"flags":{},"name":"Blank","displayName":30,"img":"modules/etu-rules/assets/bestiary_tokens/sonya-alvarez-min.png","tint":null,"width":1,"height":1,"scale":1,"mirrorX":false,"mirrorY":false,"lockRotation":false,"rotation":0,"vision":true,"dimSight":0,"brightSight":0,"dimLight":0,"brightLight":0,"sightAngle":0,"lightAngle":0,"lightColor":null,"lightAlpha":1,"lightAnimation":{"speed":5,"intensity":5},"actorId":null,"actorLink":true,"disposition":0,"displayBars":0,"bar1":{"attribute":""},"bar2":{"attribute":""},"randomImg":false,"alpha":1},"items":[{"_id":"UZW0tLJicg0VZOp4","name":"Athletics","type":"skill","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p>Athletics combines an individual&rsquo;s coordin&shy;ation with learned skills such as climbing, jumping, balancing, biking, wrestling, skiing, swimming, throwing, or catching. Characters who rely on physical power more than coordination can take the @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Brute]{Brute} Edge to link this skill to @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Traits]{Strength} instead of @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Traits]{Agility}.</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"attribute":"agility","isCoreSkill":false,"die":{"sides":8,"modifier":0},"wild-die":{"sides":6}},"sort":100000,"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_nsugutrpau","path":"Skills","color":"#8c160f"},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.swade-core-rules.swade-skills.Athletics"}},"img":"icons/magic/control/buff-strength-muscle-damage.webp","effects":[],"folder":null,"permission":{"default":0}},{"_id":"W5lfcCNjirSPUH42","name":"Common Knowledge","type":"skill","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\"><p>Characters roll Common Knowledge to know people, places, and things of their world, including etiquette, geography, culture, popular technology, contacts, and customs.</p></div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"attribute":"smarts","isCoreSkill":false,"die":{"sides":6,"modifier":0},"wild-die":{"sides":6}},"sort":200000,"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_nsugutrpau","path":"Skills","color":"#8c160f"},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.swade-core-rules.swade-skills.Common Knowledge"}},"img":"icons/sundries/documents/document-official-capital.webp","effects":[],"folder":null,"permission":{"default":0}},{"_id":"quj5jF3vNls1j5E3","name":"Notice","type":"skill","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p>Notice is a hero&rsquo;s general awareness and alertness. It&rsquo;s used to sense sights, sounds, tastes, and smells, spot clues, detect ambushes, spot hidden weapons on a foe, or tell if a rival is lying, frightened, happy, etc.</p>\n<p>@Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{Success} conveys basic information&mdash;the character hears movement in the forest, smells distant smoke, or senses someone isn&rsquo;t being completely truthful.</p>\n<p>A @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{raise} grants more detail, such as the direction of a sound or odor or what topic a person is avoiding or lying about.</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"attribute":"smarts","isCoreSkill":false,"die":{"sides":6,"modifier":0},"wild-die":{"sides":6}},"sort":300000,"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_nsugutrpau","path":"Skills","color":"#8c160f"},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.swade-core-rules.swade-skills.ZvwjzMLxsneptV4T"}},"img":"icons/creatures/eyes/human-single-blue.webp","effects":[],"folder":null,"permission":{"default":0}},{"_id":"TOEzoo2Lf4A5JXOF","name":"Persuasion","type":"skill","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p>Persuasion is the ability to convince others to do what you want through reason, cajoling, deception, rewards, or other friendly means. Persuasion isn&rsquo;t mind control. It can change someone&rsquo;s attitude but not their goals. A bandit may let you keep a sentimental piece of jewelry with a good Persuasion roll but still takes all your other goods.</p>\n<p>When used to @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Support]{Support} allies it&rsquo;s an unopposed roll. If the target is resistant, it&rsquo;s an @JournalEntry[JBxsGv2wAoAmoCDe]{opposed} roll vs. the target&rsquo;s @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Traits]{Spirit}. The GM should modify the roll as she sees fit based on roleplaying, any pertinent @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Edges]{Edges} or @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Hindrances]{Hindrances} that affect the conversation, and the circumstances.</p>\n<p><strong>Reaction Level:</strong> How much a person is willing to cooperate depends largely on their attitude toward whoever&rsquo;s talking to them. The Game Master can decide how nonplayer characters feel based on the setting, or roll on the @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-tables.Reaction Table]{Reaction Table} if she has no preconceived notions.</p>\n<p>@Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{Success} improves the target&rsquo;s attitude one level and a raise improves it two. Further increases aren&rsquo;t generally possible in the same encounter&mdash;it takes individuals a little time to adjust their biases.</p>\n<p>@Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{Failure} means the target won&rsquo;t change his mind this scene or until the situation changes in some important way. A @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{Critical Failure} also <em>reduces</em> the target&rsquo;s attitude two levels.</p>\n<p>Only one roll should generally be allowed per interaction unless new information is revealed, a substantial reward is offered, etc.</p>\n<p><strong>Networking: </strong>Characters can also use Persuasion as a &ldquo;macro skill,&rdquo; simulating a few hours or an evening&rsquo;s time hobnobbing and socializing to gain favors or information. See @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Networking]{Networking}.</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"attribute":"spirit","isCoreSkill":false,"die":{"sides":4,"modifier":0},"wild-die":{"sides":6}},"sort":400000,"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_nsugutrpau","path":"Skills","color":"#8c160f"},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.swade-core-rules.swade-skills.Persuasion"}},"img":"icons/skills/social/diplomacy-handshake.webp","effects":[],"folder":null,"permission":{"default":0}},{"_id":"8VzaSa3EEDrMz6PR","name":"Stealth","type":"skill","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p>Stealth is the ability to hide and move quietly. A simple @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{success} on a Stealth roll means the character avoids detection if enemies aren&rsquo;t particularly alert. If the character @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{fails} the roll, the enemy realizes something is amiss and begins actively searching for whatever roused them.</p>\n<p>Once foes are alerted and active, Stealth is opposed by @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Notice]{Notice} (a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{group roll} if there are many foes.</p>\n<p>The GM should apply any circumstantial penalties to @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Notice]{Notice} rolls for @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Illumination]{darkness}, @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Cover and Obstacles]{cover}, noise, distractions, and any difference in the target&rsquo;s @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Size and Scale]{Scale} (just like when attacking). Sneaking through dry leaves might subtract 2 from the Stealth roll, for example, while spotting someone in the dark uses the @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Illumination]{Illumination} penalty (&minus;4). Don&rsquo;t apply the same modifier to both rolls, however. If Stealth is at &minus;2 for the leaves, don&rsquo;t give Notice a +2 for them as well.</p>\n<p><strong>Sneak Attack: </strong> Sneaking up close enough to make a melee attack <em>always</em> requires an @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{opposed} Stealth roll versus the target&rsquo;s @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Notice]{Notice}, whether the guard is actively looking for trouble or not. If successful, the victim is @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Distracted and Vulnerable]{Vulnerable} to the attacker, but only until the attacker&rsquo;s turn ends. With a raise, the attacker has @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.The Drop]{The Drop} instead.</p>\n<p><strong>Movement:</strong> In combat, characters roll Stealth each turn as a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Actions]{free action} at the end of their move or any action the GM thinks might draw attention.</p>\n<p>Out of combat, the distance moved depends entirely on the situation. The GM might want a roll every minute if the group is sneaking around the perimeter of a defensive position, or every few miles if they&rsquo;re trying to quietly walk the path through a dark forest without alerting the creatures that live there.</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"attribute":"agility","isCoreSkill":false,"die":{"sides":6,"modifier":0},"wild-die":{"sides":6}},"sort":500000,"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_nsugutrpau","path":"Skills","color":"#8c160f"},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.swade-core-rules.swade-skills.Stealth"}},"img":"icons/magic/nature/stealth-hide-eyes-green.webp","effects":[],"folder":null,"permission":{"default":0}},{"_id":"BQ3OOQlkZvCl1Lfb","name":"Unskilled Attempt","type":"skill","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p>If a character doesn&rsquo;t have a skill for an action he&rsquo;s attempting, he rolls a d4 for his skill die (and a Wild Die if a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Wild Cards and Extras]{Wild Card}) and subtracts 2 from the total.</p>\n<p>The GM may decide certain tasks cannot be attempted unskilled, such as performing complex surgery or flying a commercial jet.</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"attribute":"agility","isCoreSkill":false,"die":{"sides":4,"modifier":"-2"},"wild-die":{"sides":6}},"sort":1100000,"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_nsugutrpau","path":"Skills","color":"#8c160f"},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.swade-core-rules.swade-skills.zcn1epcU4FEJGGyI"}},"img":"icons/magic/symbols/question-stone-yellow.webp","effects":[],"folder":null,"permission":{"default":0}},{"_id":"uaVAhwDnUDLFZFXm","name":"Unarmed strike","type":"weapon","data":{"description":"","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"quantity":1,"weight":0,"price":0,"equippable":false,"equipped":true,"isVehicular":false,"mods":1,"actions":{"skill":"","skillMod":"","dmgMod":"","additional":{}},"damage":"@str","range":"","rof":"1","ap":"0","minStr":"","shots":"0","currentShots":"0","ammo":"","autoReload":false},"sort":1400000,"flags":{},"img":"icons/skills/melee/unarmed-punch-fist.webp","effects":[],"folder":null,"permission":{"default":0}},{"_id":"GjcL17dCtOeFUvbu","name":"Fighting","type":"skill","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p>Fighting covers all hand-to-hand (melee) attacks, whether it&rsquo;s with fists, axes, laser swords, or martial arts. See @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Combat]{Chapter Three} for the combat rules and the various maneuvers a warrior might attempt.</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"attribute":"agility","isCoreSkill":false,"die":{"sides":10,"modifier":0},"wild-die":{"sides":6}},"sort":1500000,"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_qals24wpyph","path":"Skills","color":"#8c160f"},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.swade-core-rules.swade-skills.wWiwjPlzAQU3TN9l"}},"img":"icons/skills/melee/hand-grip-sword-white-brown.webp","effects":[],"folder":null,"permission":{"default":0}},{"_id":"s8YLnRMZBKFrbqXe","name":"Intimidation","type":"skill","img":"icons/skills/wounds/injury-face-impact-orange.webp","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p>Intimidation is the art of frightening an opponent so that he backs down, reveals information, or flees.</p>\n<p>Intimidation is an @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{opposed roll} resisted by the opponent&rsquo;s @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Traits]{Spirit}. In combat, this is a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Test]{Test}. Out of combat, a successful roll means the foe backs down for the most part, reveals some information, or slinks away when the opportunity presents itself.</p>\n<p>A @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{raise} might mean he backs down for the remainder of the scene, spills all the beans, or runs away as fast as he can.</p>\n<p>In or out of combat, a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{Critical Failure} means the target is immune to this character&rsquo;s Intimidation attempts for the remainder of this encounter!</p>\n<p><strong>Networking:</strong> Intimidation can also be used as a &ldquo;macro&rdquo; skill to simulate several hours of working the streets. See&nbsp;@Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Networking]{Networking}&nbsp;to see how to crack some heads for favors or information.</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"attribute":"spirit","isCoreSkill":false,"die":{"sides":10,"modifier":2},"wild-die":{"sides":6}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"3HvtK4sMp7flYKmT":3,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_qals24wpyph","path":"Skills","color":"#8c160f"},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.swade-core-rules.swade-skills.RrgAZp50CgQyyY6w"}}},{"_id":"DZaUSUgNMyMTaS6e","name":"Language (Common)","type":"skill","img":"icons/sundries/documents/document-letter-formal-tan.webp","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p>In some settings, such as those that focus on pulp action or &ldquo;planetary romance&rdquo; (where characters frequently travel among many strange civilizations), speaking various languages can simply be roleplayed with halting dialogue and campy accents that start out a little difficult and are quickly forgotten. The GM may ignore this skill altogether in these settings, or use the @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Multiple Languages]{Multiple Languages}&nbsp;&shy;option in the @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Setting Rules]{Setting Rules}.</p>\n<p>In more realistic settings, communication can be a major barrier that requires characters to put skill points into additional languages. In a 1980s World War Three game, for example, a group of United Nations paratroopers won&rsquo;t be able to speak with their foes unless they take Russian, Polish, or other languages common to the Warsaw Pact.</p>\n<p>If the Language skill is in use, it should be listed as Language (Spanish), Language (American Sign Language), etc. A character&rsquo;s die type also notes how fluent he is in it. (Characters start with a d8 in their own Language.)</p>\n<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<table class=\"table value-table\"><caption class=\"table-caption\">\n<h2 class=\"table-title\">Language Proficiency</h2>\n</caption>\n<tbody>\n<tr class=\"table-header-row\">\n<th class=\"table-column-header\" scope=\"col\">Skill</th>\n<th class=\"table-column-header\" scope=\"col\">Ability</th>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td>d4</td>\n<td>The character can read, write and speak common words and phrases.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>d6</td>\n<td>The speaker can carry on a prolonged but occasionally halting conversation.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>d8</td>\n<td>The character can speak fluently.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>d10</td>\n<td>The hero can mimic other dialects within the language.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>d12</td>\n<td>The speaker can masterfully recite important literary or oral works.</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>\n</div>\n<p><strong>Limited: </strong>Use whichever skill is lowest when performing an action that requires knowledge of a foreign language. @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Intimidation]{Intimidation} (if verbal), @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Persuasion]{Persuasion}, @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Research]{Research}, @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Taunt]{Taunt}, etc., are all limited by the character&rsquo;s Language skill.</p>\n<p>This limitation never applies to a character&rsquo;s native tongue.</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"attribute":"smarts","isCoreSkill":false,"die":{"sides":8,"modifier":0},"wild-die":{"sides":6}},"effects":[],"folder":"kFghWjY7gP7MEqav","sort":1,"permission":{"default":0,"3HvtK4sMp7flYKmT":3,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_nsugutrpau","path":"Skills","color":"#8c160f"},"journal-links":{},"core":{"sourceId":"Item.B8Z0BJ0B2ULcZFmw"}}},{"_id":"vtb0HNEXmdC9DPXO","name":"Language (Dwarvish)","type":"skill","img":"icons/sundries/documents/document-letter-formal-tan.webp","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p>In some settings, such as those that focus on pulp action or &ldquo;planetary romance&rdquo; (where characters frequently travel among many strange civilizations), speaking various languages can simply be roleplayed with halting dialogue and campy accents that start out a little difficult and are quickly forgotten. The GM may ignore this skill altogether in these settings, or use the @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Multiple Languages]{Multiple Languages}&nbsp;&shy;option in the @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Setting Rules]{Setting Rules}.</p>\n<p>In more realistic settings, communication can be a major barrier that requires characters to put skill points into additional languages. In a 1980s World War Three game, for example, a group of United Nations paratroopers won&rsquo;t be able to speak with their foes unless they take Russian, Polish, or other languages common to the Warsaw Pact.</p>\n<p>If the Language skill is in use, it should be listed as Language (Spanish), Language (American Sign Language), etc. A character&rsquo;s die type also notes how fluent he is in it. (Characters start with a d8 in their own Language.)</p>\n<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<table class=\"table value-table\"><caption class=\"table-caption\">\n<h2 class=\"table-title\">Language Proficiency</h2>\n</caption>\n<tbody>\n<tr class=\"table-header-row\">\n<th class=\"table-column-header\" scope=\"col\">Skill</th>\n<th class=\"table-column-header\" scope=\"col\">Ability</th>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td>d4</td>\n<td>The character can read, write and speak common words and phrases.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>d6</td>\n<td>The speaker can carry on a prolonged but occasionally halting conversation.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>d8</td>\n<td>The character can speak fluently.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>d10</td>\n<td>The hero can mimic other dialects within the language.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>d12</td>\n<td>The speaker can masterfully recite important literary or oral works.</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>\n</div>\n<p><strong>Limited: </strong>Use whichever skill is lowest when performing an action that requires knowledge of a foreign language. @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Intimidation]{Intimidation} (if verbal), @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Persuasion]{Persuasion}, @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Research]{Research}, @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Taunt]{Taunt}, etc., are all limited by the character&rsquo;s Language skill.</p>\n<p>This limitation never applies to a character&rsquo;s native tongue.</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"attribute":"smarts","isCoreSkill":false,"die":{"sides":8,"modifier":0},"wild-die":{"sides":6}},"effects":[],"folder":"kFghWjY7gP7MEqav","sort":1,"permission":{"default":0,"3HvtK4sMp7flYKmT":3,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_nsugutrpau","path":"Skills","color":"#8c160f"},"journal-links":{},"core":{"sourceId":"Item.B8Z0BJ0B2ULcZFmw"}}},{"_id":"IJQAmJPJ7wDpJN7B","name":"Shooting","type":"skill","img":"icons/skills/ranged/target-bullseye-arrow-glowing.webp","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p>Shooting covers all attempts to hit a target with a ranged weapon such as a bow, pistol, or rocket launcher (thrown weapons use @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Athletics]{Athletics}). See @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Combat]{Chapter Three} for details on ranged combat.</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"attribute":"agility","isCoreSkill":false,"die":{"sides":6,"modifier":0},"wild-die":{"sides":6}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"3HvtK4sMp7flYKmT":3,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_qals24wpyph","path":"Skills","color":"#8c160f"},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.swade-core-rules.swade-skills.sOHfVvBDhe3Oy3r1"}}},{"_id":"9izbwRBef2TPadUL","name":"Boating","type":"skill","img":"icons/environment/settlement/ship.webp","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\"><p>Characters with this skill can handle most any boat or ship common to their setting. They also know how to handle common tasks associated with their vessel such as tying knots, rigging sails, or following currents.</p></div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"attribute":"agility","isCoreSkill":false,"die":{"sides":8,"modifier":0},"wild-die":{"sides":6}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"3HvtK4sMp7flYKmT":3,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_qals24wpyph","path":"Skills","color":"#8c160f"},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.swade-core-rules.swade-skills.WMWgIVDuAW4cHxj2"}}},{"_id":"2HNpJlUkXn8aDKq8","name":"Mean","type":"hindrance","img":"icons/magic/holy/yin-yang-balance-symbol.webp","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p>This curmudgeon is ill-tempered and disagreeable. He has trouble doing anything kind for anyone else, must be paid for his troubles, and doesn&rsquo;t accept awards or favors graciously. Besides the obvious roleplaying issues, Mean characters subtract 1 from @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-skills.Persuasion]{Persuasion} @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{rolls}.</span></p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"major":false},"effects":[],"folder":"1updrtPaYhKD0fRY","sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"3HvtK4sMp7flYKmT":3,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"flags":{"cf":null,"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.swade-core-rules.swade-hindrances.sNgSwqh2fGyM6i14"}}},{"_id":"zhbz3wrBr6XLhACp","name":"Suspicious","type":"hindrance","img":"icons/magic/holy/yin-yang-balance-symbol.webp","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p>Your character is suspicious of everyone. As a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Characters]{Minor} @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Hindrances]{Hindrance}, his paranoia causes frequent trust issues. He might demand full payment before doing a task, want every agreement in writing, or believe even his friends are out to get him.</p>\n<p>As a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Characters]{Major} @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Hindrances]{Hindrance}, @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Support]{Support} @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{rolls} to aid the distrustful individual are made at -2.</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"major":false},"effects":[],"folder":"1updrtPaYhKD0fRY","sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"3HvtK4sMp7flYKmT":3,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"flags":{"cf":null,"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.swade-core-rules.swade-hindrances.OKRpEOPTwa1gX5c9"}}},{"_id":"TxH0M4E7JugBO5HP","name":"Driven (Captain her own ship)","type":"hindrance","img":"icons/magic/holy/yin-yang-balance-symbol.webp","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p>A vow is a commitment to others. Driven characters want something for themselves. It may be to protect the realm, become a decorated officer, prove you&rsquo;re the best gladiator in Rome, or the best pilot in the galactic fleet.</p>\n<p>The @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Characters]{Minor} version shapes the character and pushes his decisions but either happens rarely or is fairly harmless. As a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Characters]{Major} @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Hindrances]{Hindrance} it&rsquo;s an overriding desire that comes up frequently or causes peril for the heroine and those around her.</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"major":false},"effects":[],"folder":"1updrtPaYhKD0fRY","sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"3HvtK4sMp7flYKmT":3,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"flags":{"cf":null,"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.swade-core-rules.swade-hindrances.I7XFI1uVE9xqx8gu"}}},{"_id":"nFA5TtK7rZl54VD6","name":"Language (Orcish)","type":"skill","img":"icons/sundries/documents/document-letter-formal-tan.webp","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p>In some settings, such as those that focus on pulp action or &ldquo;planetary romance&rdquo; (where characters frequently travel among many strange civilizations), speaking various languages can simply be roleplayed with halting dialogue and campy accents that start out a little difficult and are quickly forgotten. The GM may ignore this skill altogether in these settings, or use the @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Multiple Languages]{Multiple Languages}&nbsp;&shy;option in the @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Setting Rules]{Setting Rules}.</p>\n<p>In more realistic settings, communication can be a major barrier that requires characters to put skill points into additional languages. In a 1980s World War Three game, for example, a group of United Nations paratroopers won&rsquo;t be able to speak with their foes unless they take Russian, Polish, or other languages common to the Warsaw Pact.</p>\n<p>If the Language skill is in use, it should be listed as Language (Spanish), Language (American Sign Language), etc. A 