_id":"R2EXexl18VPrLgtv","name":"Primal Brute","type":"ability","img":"icons/creatures/eyes/humanoid-single-red-brown.webp","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Orc]{Orcs} focus on core strength and fitness over coordination and flexibility. They treat @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Athletics]{Athletics} as linked to @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Traits]{Strength} instead of @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Traits]{Agility} for purposes of @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Advancement]{Advancement}. The character may also resist @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Athletics]{Athletics} @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Test]{Tests} with @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Traits]{Strength} if she chooses.</p>\n<p>Finally, @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Orc]{orcs} increase the @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Range]{Short Range} of any thrown item by +1. Double that for the adjusted @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Range]{Medium Range} , and double again for @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Range]{Long Range}. If a thrown item&rsquo;s @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Range]{Range} is 3/6/12, for example, an @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Orc]{orc's} @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Range]{Range}&nbsp;is 4/8/16.</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"subtype":"special","grantsPowers":false},"effects":[],"folder":"onRNTIr80exOb3zL","sort":500000,"permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"flags":{"journal-links":{},"core":{"sourceId":"Item.NvIGTQvwpA2rek6y"}}},{"_id":"EOOaKgZNfrdnNJGi","name":"Primal Passion","type":"hindrance","img":"icons/creatures/eyes/humanoid-single-red-brown.webp","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Orc]{Orcs} are reactive and driven by a primal passion. They often take action without thinking things through.</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"major":true},"effects":[],"folder":"onRNTIr80exOb3zL","sort":300000,"permission":{"default":0,"ZvqefCj0L7TxJS56":3,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"flags":{"journal-links":{},"core":{"sourceId":"Item.lTwGLJJQ4OHToNdH"}}},{"_id":"HMxTvVxVWIYaTyU1","name":"Language (Elvish)","type":"skill","img":"icons/sundries/documents/document-letter-formal-tan.webp","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p>In some settings, such as those that focus on pulp action or &ldquo;planetary romance&rdquo; (where characters frequently travel among many strange civilizations), speaking various languages can simply be roleplayed with halting dialogue and campy accents that start out a little difficult and are quickly forgotten. The GM may ignore this skill altogether in these settings, or use the @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Multiple Languages]{Multiple Languages}&nbsp;&shy;option in the @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Setting Rules]{Setting Rules}.</p>\n<p>In more realistic settings, communication can be a major barrier that requires characters to put skill points into additional languages. In a 1980s World War Three game, for example, a group of United Nations paratroopers won&rsquo;t be able to speak with their foes unless they take Russian, Polish, or other languages common to the Warsaw Pact.</p>\n<p>If the Language skill is in use, it should be listed as Language (Spanish), Language (American Sign Language), etc. A character&rsquo;s die type also notes how fluent he is in it. (Characters start with a d8 in their own Language.)</p>\n<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<table class=\"table value-table\"><caption class=\"table-caption\">\n<h2 class=\"table-title\">Language Proficiency</h2>\n</caption>\n<tbody>\n<tr class=\"table-header-row\">\n<th class=\"table-column-header\" scope=\"col\">Skill</th>\n<th class=\"table-column-header\" scope=\"col\">Ability</th>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td>d4</td>\n<td>The character can read, write and speak common words and phrases.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>d6</td>\n<td>The speaker can carry on a prolonged but occasionally halting conversation.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>d8</td>\n<td>The character can speak fluently.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>d10</td>\n<td>The hero can mimic other dialects within the language.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>d12</td>\n<td>The speaker can masterfully recite important literary or oral works.</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>\n</div>\n<p><strong>Limited: </strong>Use whichever skill is lowest when performing an action that requires knowledge of a foreign language. @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Intimidation]{Intimidation} (if verbal), @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Persuasion]{Persuasion}, @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Research]{Research}, @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Taunt]{Taunt}, etc., are all limited by the character&rsquo;s Language skill.</p>\n<p>This limitation never applies to a character&rsquo;s native tongue.</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"attribute":"smarts","isCoreSkill":false,"die":{"sides":6,"modifier":0},"wild-die":{"sides":6}},"effects":[],"folder":"kFghWjY7gP7MEqav","sort":1,"permission":{"default":0,"3HvtK4sMp7flYKmT":3,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_nsugutrpau","path":"Skills","color":"#8c160f"},"journal-links":{},"core":{"sourceId":"Item.B8Z0BJ0B2ULcZFmw"}}},{"_id":"9RBt7voVmiV81ZVl","name":"Strong Willed","type":"edge","img":"icons/skills/social/diplomacy-unity-alliance.webp","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p>Self-confidence is powerful armor against those who attempt to attack this individual&rsquo;s will. He adds +2 to his total when resisting @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Test]{Tests} with @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Traits]{Smarts} or @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Traits]{Spirit}.</span></p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Novice, Spirit d8+"}},"effects":[],"folder":"4qgDgsPe5IZFyuwd","sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"3HvtK4sMp7flYKmT":3,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"flags":{"cf":null,"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.swade-core-rules.swade-edges.LXKTnJkZTAKTl9hs"}}},{"_id":"wRjFwQakSQhW2HDq","name":"Trademark Weapon (Cutlass)","type":"edge","img":"icons/environment/people/charge.webp","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p>The hero knows one unique weapon (Excalibur, Old Betsy, Sting) like the back of his hand. When using it, he adds +1 to his @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-skills.Athletics]{Athletics} (throwing), @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-skills.Fighting]{Fighting}, or @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-skills.Shooting]{Shooting} rolls, and +1 to @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Characters]{Parry} when readied (even if it&rsquo;s a ranged weapon).</span></p>\n<p>A fighter can take this Edge multiple times, applying it to a different weapon each time. If a Trademark Weapon is lost, he can replace it but the benefits don&rsquo;t kick in for a few days (however long the GM feels is dramatically appropriate).</span></p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Novice, skill with chosen weapon of d8+"}},"effects":[{"_id":"viA65GSpKV0IFwsX","changes":[{"key":"data.stats.parry.value","mode":2,"value":"1"}],"disabled":false,"duration":{"startTime":null},"icon":"icons/environment/people/charge.webp","label":"Trademark Readied Weapon","transfer":true,"flags":{},"tint":null}],"folder":"hsEO07bFB8oM1LJo","sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"3HvtK4sMp7flYKmT":3,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"flags":{"cf":null,"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.swade-core-rules.swade-edges.QHBtO0jmIzfl8TDE"}}},{"_id":"9OvmPgMkvLo0N6gw","name":"Menacing","type":"edge","img":"icons/skills/social/diplomacy-unity-alliance.webp","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p>Being a brutish lout isn&rsquo;t always a drawback if you know how to use it. Menacing allows a character to put her bad looks or worse attitude to good use. The goon adds +2 to her @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-skills.Intimidation]{Intimidation} rolls.</span></p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Novice, any one of Bloodthirsty, Mean, Ruthless, or Ugly"}},"effects":[],"folder":"4qgDgsPe5IZFyuwd","sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"3HvtK4sMp7flYKmT":3,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"flags":{"cf":null,"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.swade-core-rules.swade-edges.WRpK5JTq57sLcfOq"}}},{"_id":"LNpii9QGtw623CEf","name":"Two-Weapon Fighting","type":"edge","img":"icons/environment/people/charge.webp","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p>If a character battles with a weapon in each hand, the hero can attack with the &ldquo;good hand&rdquo; on one action and the other hand in a later action.</p>\n<p>The second attack doesn&rsquo;t inflict a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Multi-Actions]{Multi-Action} penalty. The @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Off-Hand Attacks]{off-hand} penalty still applies unless he&rsquo;s @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Ambidextrous]{Ambidextrous}, however.</p>\n<p>The character can choose to make a @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Fighting]{Fighting} attack with each hand, a throwing (@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Athletics]{Athletics}) attack with each hand, or one of each, depending on the readied weapons.</p>\n<p class=\"embedded-example\"><strong>Example: </strong>A fighter wields a longsword in one hand and a dagger in the other. He has Two-Weapon Fighting so he rolls @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Fighting]{Fighting} on one action with the sword, and then makes a second @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Fighting]{Fighting} roll&mdash;or a throwing roll (@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Athletics]{Athletics})&mdash; with the dagger, with no @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Multi-Actions]{Multi-Action}&nbsp;penalty to either.</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Novice, Agility d8+"}},"effects":[],"folder":"hsEO07bFB8oM1LJo","sort":1100000,"permission":{"default":2,"ZvqefCj0L7TxJS56":3,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"flags":{"journal-links":{},"core":{"sourceId":"Item.Fk7h9WOsyy1eaVlo"}}},{"_id":"QNQQquHtFVhcj6F1","name":"Low Light Vision","type":"ability","img":"icons/creatures/eyes/human-single-brown.webp","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p>Low Light Vision ignores up &ndash;2 penalties for @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Illumination]{Dim and Dark Illumination}. @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Illumination]{Pitch Darkness} remains unaffected.</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"subtype":"special","grantsPowers":false},"effects":[],"folder":"cZShSnwTPtovR6Ah","sort":500000,"permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"flags":{"journal-links":{},"core":{"sourceId":"Item.E6a9fFWIn3Dzqo9Q"}}},{"_id":"yc348ic3KkNEo69r","name":"Killer Instinct","type":"edge","img":"icons/environment/people/charge.webp","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\"><p>This hero hates losing. He gets a free reroll in any opposed @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Test]{Test} he initiates</span> </p></div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Seasoned"}},"effects":[],"folder":"hsEO07bFB8oM1LJo","sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"3HvtK4sMp7flYKmT":3,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"flags":{"cf":null,"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.swade-core-rules.swade-edges.QomybVyELXkYseoC"}}},{"_id":"8y0ZMqrIIapH2Nyw","name":"Tidewater Cutlass","type":"weapon","img":"icons/weapons/swords/scimitar-guard-brown.webp","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p>The blade of this cutlass is spotted with rust, and its basket hilt is cast in the likeness of a grinning skull. It is @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Masterwork]{Masterwork} and has the @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Accurate]{Accurate} enchantment.</p>\n<p>The wielder of this cutlass can cause it blast forth a tidal wave of water as an action once per day. This is as per the <em>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Havoc]{havoc}</em> power using a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Blast Templates]{Cone Template} and @Item[Fighting]{Fighting} as the casting roll.</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"quantity":1,"weight":2,"price":12310,"equippable":false,"equipped":true,"isVehicular":false,"mods":1,"actions":{"skill":"Fighting","skillMod":"+2","dmgMod":"","additional":{}},"damage":"@str+d6","range":"","rof":"1","ap":"1","minStr":"d6","shots":"0","currentShots":"0","ammo":"","autoReload":false},"effects":[],"folder":"IV0OqLxQENP62AG9","sort":100000,"permission":{"default":0,"ZvqefCj0L7TxJS56":3,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"flags":{"journal-links":{},"core":{"sourceId":"Item.BzFluL4CPr0x3oDS"}}},{"_id":"LxyXA1uoyiSUtZsD","name":"Cat-o-nine Tails","type":"weapon","img":"icons/weapons/misc/whip-red-yellow.webp","data":{"description":null,"notes":"","additionalStats":{},"quantity":1,"weight":1,"price":7,"equippable":true,"equipped":true,"isVehicular":false,"mods":1,"actions":{"skill":"Fighting","skillMod":"","dmgMod":"","additional":{}},"damage":"@str+d4","range":"","rof":"0","ap":"0","minStr":"d4","shots":"0","currentShots":"0","ammo":"","autoReload":false},"effects":[],"folder":"tnIhNgfhxgoXoVDh","sort":1300001,"permission":{"default":0,"3HvtK4sMp7flYKmT":3,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_rz46r8sengj","path":"Equipment#/CF_SEP/Personal Weapons#/CF_SEP/Melee Weapons, Medieval","color":"#000000"},"journal-links":{},"core":{"sourceId":"Item.GBIV4MIh57FGTxWB"}}},{"_id":"kHLocbr1Q8kK0Hhk","name":"Shackles of Compliance","type":"gear","img":"icons/sundries/survival/cuffs-shackles-steel.webp","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p>These battered iron manacles magically adjust themselves to fit around the wrists or ankles of any creature from Small to Large @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Size and Scale]{Size} and automatically lock. The lock can be picked with @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Thievery]{Thievery} roll &ndash;3.</p>\n<p>Once per day, the holder of the key to the manacles may make an @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Intimidation]{Intimidation} roll to cast the minor <em>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Puppet]{puppet}</em> power on the wearer of the shackles.</p>\n<p><strong>Craft:</strong> <em>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Puppet]{Puppet}</em>, 1,500 gp</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"quantity":1,"weight":5,"price":3000,"equippable":false,"equipped":true,"isVehicular":false,"mods":1},"effects":[],"folder":"A5d3oIg9sVmXEgI1","sort":400000,"permission":{"default":0,"ZvqefCj0L7TxJS56":3,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"flags":{"journal-links":{},"core":{"sourceId":"Item.VpLp24aWHGyVEXPA"}}},{"_id":"HJdTNOqGKS5xoJBC","name":"Brawny","type":"edge","img":"icons/environment/people/group.webp","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p>Your bruiser is very large or very fit. Her @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Size and Scale]{Size} increases by +1 (and therefore @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Characters]{Toughness} by 1) and she treats her @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Traits]{Strength} as one die type higher when determining <strong>@Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Gear Notes]{Encumbrance}</strong><strong>&nbsp;</strong>and <strong>@Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Minimum Strength]{Minimum Strength} </strong>to use armor, weapons, and equipment without a penalty.</p>\n<p>Brawny can&rsquo;t increase a character&rsquo;s Size above +3.</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Novice, Strength d6+, Vigor d6+"}},"effects":[{"_id":"xD9SM5eqeRZvcjF6","changes":[{"key":"data.stats.size","mode":2,"value":"1"},{"key":"data.attributes.strength.encumbranceSteps","mode":2,"value":"2"}],"disabled":false,"duration":{"startTime":null},"icon":"icons/environment/people/group.webp","label":"Brawny","transfer":true,"flags":{},"tint":null}],"folder":"EnpCvbp1xbBRZIf1","sort":600000,"permission":{"default":0,"3HvtK4sMp7flYKmT":3,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"flags":{"cf":null,"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.swade-core-rules.swade-edges.LYYfJsMEFfJVmelT"}}},{"_id":"tQyM4YhYaTa1N3Lv","name":"Deception","type":"skill","img":"icons/skills/toxins/poison-skull-herbs-bottle-pink.webp","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p>Deception determines whether the hero can convincingly hide the truth, either verbally or through her actions. This deception can encompass everything from misleading others through ambiguity to telling outright lies.</p>\n<p>Typical situations include trying to fast-talk a guard, con a merchant, dull someone's suspicions with false assurances, or maintain a straight face while telling a blatant lie.</p>\n<p>Usually, a character successfully passing herself off in a disguise, or trying to impersonate the sound of someone else's voice would be a @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Performance]{Performance} check rather than a deception check.&nbsp;</p>\n<p><em><strong>Source: Savage Eberron</strong></em></p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"attribute":"spirit","isCoreSkill":false,"die":{"sides":6,"modifier":0},"wild-die":{"sides":6}},"effects":[],"folder":"cgfmurTJRwbCvmCc","sort":700001,"permission":{"default":0,"ZvqefCj0L7TxJS56":3,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"flags":{"journal-links":{},"core":{"sourceId":"Item.E0BVumGwbaczoPjD"}}}],"effects":[{"_id":"we0WXaPtHycNu15h","changes":[{"key":"data.stats.parry.value","mode":2,"value":"1"}],"disabled":false,"duration":{"startTime":28973116800},"icon":"icons/environment/people/charge.webp","label":"Trademark Readied Weapon","origin":"Actor.DzgkbRMhHmwXuAiA.Item.wRjFwQakSQhW2HDq","tint":null,"transfer":false,"flags":{}},{"_id":"ewEGk2IXZmqDPJQ3","changes":[{"key":"data.stats.size","mode":2,"value":"1"},{"key":"data.attributes.strength.encumbranceSteps","mode":2,"value":"2"}],"disabled":false,"duration":{"startTime":28973116800},"icon":"icons/environment/people/group.webp","label":"Brawny","origin":"Actor.DzgkbRMhHmwXuAiA.Item.HJdTNOqGKS5xoJBC","tint":null,"transfer":false,"flags":{}}],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"flags":{"journal-links":{"references":{}},"cf":{"id":"temp_3a04s0jrz4j","path":"Pirates of Cyre Bestiary#/CF_SEP/NPC's","color":"#000000"}},"_id":"gytbnCnNuCBAS9FR"}
{"name":"Owlbear Hartshorn","type":"npc","img":"https://assets.forge-vtt.com/5f43f8ea1a91d63438d13159/tokens/bestiary/monstrous%20humanoid/harpy-10.png","data":{"attributes":{"agility":{"die":{"sides":6,"modifier":0},"wild-die":{"sides":6}},"smarts":{"die":{"sides":4,"modifier":0},"wild-die":{"sides":6},"animal":false},"spirit":{"die":{"sides":6,"modifier":0},"wild-die":{"sides":6},"unShakeBonus":0},"strength":{"die":{"sides":6,"modifier":0},"wild-die":{"sides":6},"encumbranceSteps":0},"vigor":{"die":{"sides":6,"modifier":0},"wild-die":{"sides":6}}},"stats":{"speed":{"runningDie":6,"runningMod":0,"value":6},"toughness":{"value":0,"armor":0,"modifier":0},"parry":{"value":5,"modifier":0},"size":0},"details":{"biography":{"value":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p>xxxxxx</p>"},"species":{"name":""},"currency":500,"wealth":{"die":6,"modifier":0,"wild-die":6},"conviction":{"value":0,"active":false},"autoCalcToughness":true,"autoCalcParry":true},"powerPoints":{},"fatigue":{"value":0,"min":0,"max":2},"wounds":{"value":0,"min":0,"max":0,"ignored":0},"advances":{"value":0,"rank":"Novice","details":""},"bennies":{"value":2,"max":2},"status":{"isShaken":false,"isDistracted":false,"isVulnerable":false,"isStunned":false,"isEntangled":false,"isBound":false},"initiative":{"hasHesitant":false,"hasLevelHeaded":false,"hasImpLevelHeaded":false,"hasQuick":false},"additionalStats":{},"wildcard":false},"token":{"name":"Blank NPC","img":"https://assets.forge-vtt.com/5f43f8ea1a91d63438d13159/tokens/bestiary/monstrous%20humanoid/harpy-*.png","displayName":30,"actorLink":false,"width":1,"height":1,"scale":1,"mirrorX":false,"mirrorY":false,"lockRotation":false,"rotation":0,"alpha":1,"vision":true,"dimSight":0,"brightSight":0,"dimLight":0,"brightLight":0,"sightAngle":0,"lightAngle":0,"lightAlpha":0.25,"lightAnimation":{"speed":5,"intensity":5},"disposition":-1,"displayBars":20,"bar1":{"attribute":""},"bar2":{"attribute":""},"flags":{"perfect-vision":{"visionRules":"default","monoVisionColor":"","sightLimit":null}},"randomImg":true,"actorId":null,"tint":null,"lightColor":null,"x":null,"y":null,"elevation":null},"items":[{"_id":"Bf0NpaRHtHmfrLb3","name":"Athletics","type":"skill","img":"icons/magic/control/buff-strength-muscle-damage.webp","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p>Athletics combines an individual&rsquo;s coordin&shy;ation with learned skills such as climbing, jumping, balancing, biking, wrestling, skiing, swimming, throwing, or catching. Characters who rely on physical power more than coordination can take the @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Brute]{Brute} Edge to link this skill to @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Traits]{Strength} instead of @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Traits]{Agility}.</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"attribute":"agility","isCoreSkill":false,"die":{"sides":6,"modifier":0},"wild-die":{"sides":6}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_azxylmvr7yo","path":"Skills","color":"#008000"},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.swade-core-rules.swade-skills.sAig03GZiFKqBX7p"}}},{"_id":"bJxCFLP4a8BEU0Qm","name":"Common Knowledge","type":"skill","img":"icons/sundries/documents/document-official-capital.webp","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\"><p>Characters roll Common Knowledge to know people, places, and things of their world, including etiquette, geography, culture, popular technology, contacts, and customs.</p></div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"attribute":"smarts","isCoreSkill":false,"die":{"sides":4,"modifier":0},"wild-die":{"sides":6}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_azxylmvr7yo","path":"Skills","color":"#008000"},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.swade-core-rules.swade-skills.8N1uMThntsjaUPem"}}},{"_id":"gMAJFeCm5e3Oporq","name":"Fighting","type":"skill","img":"icons/skills/melee/hand-grip-sword-white-brown.webp","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p>Fighting covers all hand-to-hand (melee) attacks, whether it&rsquo;s with fists, axes, laser swords, or martial arts. See @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Combat]{Chapter Three} for the combat rules and the various maneuvers a warrior might attempt.</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"attribute":"agility","isCoreSkill":false,"die":{"sides":6,"modifier":0},"wild-die":{"sides":6}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_azxylmvr7yo","path":"Skills","color":"#008000"},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.swade-core-rules.swade-skills.wWiwjPlzAQU3TN9l"}}},{"_id":"9coycVPgGdTGpbmh","name":"Language (Common)","type":"skill","img":"icons/sundries/documents/document-letter-formal-tan.webp","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p>In some settings, such as those that focus on pulp action or &ldquo;planetary romance&rdquo; (where characters frequently travel among many strange civilizations), speaking various languages can simply be roleplayed with halting dialogue and campy accents that start out a little difficult and are quickly forgotten. The GM may ignore this skill altogether in these settings, or use the @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Multiple Languages]{Multiple Languages}&nbsp;&shy;option in the @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Setting Rules]{Setting Rules}.</p>\n<p>In more realistic settings, communication can be a major barrier that requires characters to put skill points into additional languages. In a 1980s World War Three game, for example, a group of United Nations paratroopers won&rsquo;t be able to speak with their foes unless they take Russian, Polish, or other languages common to the Warsaw Pact.</p>\n<p>If the Language skill is in use, it should be listed as Language (Spanish), Language (American Sign Language), etc. A character&rsquo;s die type also notes how fluent he is in it. (Characters start with a d8 in their own Language.)</p>\n<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<table class=\"table value-table\"><caption class=\"table-caption\">\n<h2 class=\"table-title\">Language Proficiency</h2>\n</caption>\n<tbody>\n<tr class=\"table-header-row\">\n<th class=\"table-column-header\" scope=\"col\">Skill</th>\n<th class=\"table-column-header\" scope=\"col\">Ability</th>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td>d4</td>\n<td>The character can read, write and speak common words and phrases.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>d6</td>\n<td>The speaker can carry on a prolonged but occasionally halting conversation.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>d8</td>\n<td>The character can speak fluently.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>d10</td>\n<td>The hero can mimic other dialects within the language.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>d12</td>\n<td>The speaker can masterfully recite important literary or oral works.</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>\n</div>\n<p><strong>Limited: </strong>Use whichever skill is lowest when performing an action that requires knowledge of a foreign language. @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Intimidation]{Intimidation} (if verbal), @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Persuasion]{Persuasion}, @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Research]{Research}, @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Taunt]{Taunt}, etc., are all limited by the character&rsquo;s Language skill.</p>\n<p>This limitation never applies to a character&rsquo;s native tongue.</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"attribute":"smarts","isCoreSkill":false,"die":{"sides":8,"modifier":0},"wild-die":{"sides":6}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_azxylmvr7yo","path":"Skills","color":"#008000"},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.swade-core-rules.swade-skills.XIuR2IyQtewm5BZP"}}},{"_id":"TWqtRMnChmXvwXvN","name":"Notice","type":"skill","img":"icons/creatures/eyes/human-single-blue.webp","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p>Notice is a hero&rsquo;s general awareness and alertness. It&rsquo;s used to sense sights, sounds, tastes, and smells, spot clues, detect ambushes, spot hidden weapons on a foe, or tell if a rival is lying, frightened, happy, etc.</p>\n<p>@Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{Success} conveys basic information&mdash;the character hears movement in the forest, smells distant smoke, or senses someone isn&rsquo;t being completely truthful.</p>\n<p>A @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{raise} grants more detail, such as the direction of a sound or odor or what topic a person is avoiding or lying about.</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"attribute":"smarts","isCoreSkill":false,"die":{"sides":6,"modifier":0},"wild-die":{"sides":6}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_azxylmvr7yo","path":"Skills","color":"#008000"},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.swade-core-rules.swade-skills.yvw9bMgsrWQXuZN2"}}},{"_id":"rk3ft5Cc4sHxF5ay","name":"Stealth","type":"skill","img":"icons/magic/nature/stealth-hide-eyes-green.webp","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p>Stealth is the ability to hide and move quietly. A simple @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{success} on a Stealth roll means the character avoids detection if enemies aren&rsquo;t particularly alert. If the character @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{fails} the roll, the enemy realizes something is amiss and begins actively searching for whatever roused them.</p>\n<p>Once foes are alerted and active, Stealth is opposed by @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Notice]{Notice} (a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{group roll} if there are many foes.</p>\n<p>The GM should apply any circumstantial penalties to @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Notice]{Notice} rolls for @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Illumination]{darkness}, @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Cover and Obstacles]{cover}, noise, distractions, and any difference in the target&rsquo;s @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Size and Scale]{Scale} (just like when attacking). Sneaking through dry leaves might subtract 2 from the Stealth roll, for example, while spotting someone in the dark uses the @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Illumination]{Illumination} penalty (&minus;4). Don&rsquo;t apply the same modifier to both rolls, however. If Stealth is at &minus;2 for the leaves, don&rsquo;t give Notice a +2 for them as well.</p>\n<p><strong>Sneak Attack: </strong> Sneaking up close enough to make a melee attack <em>always</em> requires an @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{opposed} Stealth roll versus the target&rsquo;s @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Notice]{Notice}, whether the guard is actively looking for trouble or not. If successful, the victim is @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Distracted and Vulnerable]{Vulnerable} to the attacker, but only until the attacker&rsquo;s turn ends. With a raise, the attacker has @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.The Drop]{The Drop} instead.</p>\n<p><strong>Movement:</strong> In combat, characters roll Stealth each turn as a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Actions]{free action} at the end of their move or any action the GM thinks might draw attention.</p>\n<p>Out of combat, the distance moved depends entirely on the situation. The GM might want a roll every minute if the group is sneaking around the perimeter of a defensive position, or every few miles if they&rsquo;re trying to quietly walk the path through a dark forest without alerting the creatures that live there.</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"attribute":"agility","isCoreSkill":false,"die":{"sides":6,"modifier":0},"wild-die":{"sides":6}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_azxylmvr7yo","path":"Skills","color":"#008000"},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.swade-core-rules.swade-skills.z9FmdFVGOOW2kufm"}}},{"_id":"6BeiHr2FDzQaAZll","name":"Unskilled Attempt","type":"skill","img":"icons/magic/symbols/question-stone-yellow.webp","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p>If a character doesn&rsquo;t have a skill for an action he&rsquo;s attempting, he rolls a d4 for his skill die (and a Wild Die if a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Wild Cards and Extras]{Wild Card}) and subtracts 2 from the total.</p>\n<p>The GM may decide certain tasks cannot be attempted unskilled, such as performing complex surgery or flying a commercial jet.</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"attribute":"agility","isCoreSkill":false,"die":{"sides":4,"modifier":-2},"wild-die":{"sides":6}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_azxylmvr7yo","path":"Skills","color":"#008000"},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.swade-core-rules.swade-skills.1Pl2ZL8MPyKnaVEg"}}},{"_id":"N1OCwZvFIDN4gSVH","name":"Unarmed Strike","type":"weapon","img":"icons/skills/melee/unarmed-punch-fist.webp","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p>See @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Unarmed Defender]{Unarmed Defender}.</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"quantity":1,"weight":0,"price":0,"equippable":false,"equipped":true,"isVehicular":false,"mods":1,"actions":{"skill":"Fighting","skillMod":"","dmgMod":"","additional":{}},"damage":"@str+d4","range":"","rof":"1","ap":"0","minStr":"","shots":"0","currentShots":"0","ammo":"","autoReload":false},"effects":[],"folder":"651LNce8no6HR9rY","sort":100000,"permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"flags":{"journal-links":{},"core":{"sourceId":"Item.X31v8asHtqhgiaM2"}}},{"_id":"4F8Q5B0P7tADAaGa","name":"Brawler","type":"edge","img":"icons/environment/people/charge.webp","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p>His fists hit like hammers or his talons cut like scythes. His body feels like it&rsquo;s made of stone. Brawlers increase their @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Characters]{Toughness} by 1 and roll @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Traits]{Strength} +d4 when hitting with their fists or feet (or claws if they have them). If they already have a damage die from&nbsp;</span><strong>@Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Special Ability (Claws)]{Claws}</strong>, the @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Martial Artist]{Martial Artist} Edge, etc., increase the damage die type by one instead. </span></p>\n<p>The Brawler Edge doesn&rsquo;t make the character&rsquo;s fists </span><strong>@Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Natural Weapons]{Natural Weapons}</span></strong></p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Novice, Strength d8+, Vigor d8+"}},"effects":[{"_id":"kjzlcYkuLXL4NwhC","changes":[{"key":"data.stats.toughness.value","mode":2,"value":"1"}],"disabled":false,"duration":{"startTime":null},"icon":"icons/environment/people/charge.webp","label":"Brawler","transfer":true,"flags":{},"tint":null}],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_7529swwanpd","path":"Edges#/CF_SEP/Combat Edges","color":"#000000"},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.swade-core-rules.swade-edges.q5NKwGPeK9PKQdIb"}}}],"effects":[{"_id":"9ByhnGOJiAHNuQZZ","changes":[{"key":"data.stats.toughness.value","mode":2,"value":"1"}],"disabled":false,"duration":{"startTime":28973116800},"icon":"icons/environment/people/charge.webp","label":"Brawler","origin":"Actor.ctrOErn6sfvnn1xC.Item.4F8Q5B0P7tADAaGa","tint":null,"transfer":false,"flags":{}}],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_3a04s0jrz4j","path":"Pirates of Cyre Bestiary#/CF_SEP/NPC's","color":"#000000"}},"_id":"raZYvUdO4Op0Mc0t"}
{"name":"#[CF_tempEntity]","type":"character","img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","data":{"attributes":{"agility":{"die":{"sides":4,"modifier":0},"wild-die":{"sides":6}},"smarts":{"die":{"sides":4,"modifier":0},"wild-die":{"sides":6},"animal":false},"spirit":{"die":{"sides":4,"modifier":0},"wild-die":{"sides":6},"unShakeBonus":0},"strength":{"die":{"sides":4,"modifier":0},"wild-die":{"sides":6},"encumbranceSteps":0},"vigor":{"die":{"sides":4,"modifier":0},"wild-die":{"sides":6}}},"stats":{"speed":{"runningDie":6,"runningMod":0,"value":6},"toughness":{"value":0,"armor":0,"modifier":0},"parry":{"value":0,"modifier":0},"size":0},"details":{"biography":{"value":""},"species":{"name":""},"currency":500,"wealth":{"die":6,"modifier":0,"wild-die":6},"conviction":{"value":0,"active":false},"autoCalcToughness":true,"autoCalcParry":true},"powerPoints":{},"fatigue":{"value":0,"min":0,"max":2},"wounds":{"value":0,"min":0,"max":3,"ignored":0},"advances":{"value":0,"rank":"Novice","details":""},"bennies":{"value":3,"max":3},"status":{"isShaken":false,"isDistracted":false,"isVulnerable":false,"isStunned":false,"isEntangled":false,"isBound":false},"initiative":{"hasHesitant":false,"hasLevelHeaded":false,"hasImpLevelHeaded":false,"hasQuick":false},"additionalStats":{},"wildcard":true},"token":{"name":"#[CF_tempEntity]","img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","displayName":0,"actorLink":false,"width":1,"height":1,"scale":1,"mirrorX":false,"mirrorY":false,"lockRotation":false,"rotation":0,"alpha":1,"vision":false,"dimSight":0,"brightSight":0,"dimLight":0,"brightLight":0,"sightAngle":0,"lightAngle":0,"lightAlpha":0.25,"lightAnimation":{"speed":5,"intensity":5},"disposition":-1,"displayBars":0,"bar1":{"attribute":null},"bar2":{"attribute":null},"flags":{},"randomImg":false,"actorId":null},"items":[{"_id":"BAaFJq4Ss7Bgmt8w","name":"Persuasion","type":"skill","img":"icons/skills/social/diplomacy-handshake.webp","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p>Persuasion is the ability to convince others to do what you want through reason, cajoling, deception, rewards, or other friendly means. Persuasion isn&rsquo;t mind control. It can change someone&rsquo;s attitude but not their goals. A bandit may let you keep a sentimental piece of jewelry with a good Persuasion roll but still takes all your other goods.</p>\n<p>When used to @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Support]{Support} allies it&rsquo;s an unopposed roll. If the target is resistant, it&rsquo;s an @JournalEntry[JBxsGv2wAoAmoCDe]{opposed} roll vs. the target&rsquo;s @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Traits]{Spirit}. The GM should modify the roll as she sees fit based on roleplaying, any pertinent @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Edges]{Edges} or @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Hindrances]{Hindrances} that affect the conversation, and the circumstances.</p>\n<p><strong>Reaction Level:</strong> How much a person is willing to cooperate depends largely on their attitude toward whoever&rsquo;s talking to them. The Game Master can decide how nonplayer characters feel based on the setting, or roll on the @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-tables.Reaction Table]{Reaction Table} if she has no preconceived notions.</p>\n<p>@Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{Success} improves the target&rsquo;s attitude one level and a raise improves it two. Further increases aren&rsquo;t generally possible in the same encounter&mdash;it takes individuals a little time to adjust their biases.</p>\n<p>@Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{Failure} means the target won&rsquo;t change his mind this scene or until the situation changes in some important way. A @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{Critical Failure} also <em>reduces</em> the target&rsquo;s attitude two levels.</p>\n<p>Only one roll should generally be allowed per interaction unless new information is revealed, a substantial reward is offered, etc.</p>\n<p><strong>Networking: </strong>Characters can also use Persuasion as a &ldquo;macro skill,&rdquo; simulating a few hours or an evening&rsquo;s time hobnobbing and socializing to gain favors or information. See @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Networking]{Networking}.</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"attribute":"spirit","isCoreSkill":true,"die":{"sides":4,"modifier":0},"wild-die":{"sides":6}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_azxylmvr7yo","path":"Skills","color":"#008000"},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.swade-core-rules.swade-skills.xOmuCR92Ys9jD5vg"}}},{"_id":"Dk7MTEB8I6MuoNKP","name":"Notice","type":"skill","img":"icons/creatures/eyes/human-single-blue.webp","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p>Notice is a hero&rsquo;s general awareness and alertness. It&rsquo;s used to sense sights, sounds, tastes, and smells, spot clues, detect ambushes, spot hidden weapons on a foe, or tell if a rival is lying, frightened, happy, etc.</p>\n<p>@Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{Success} conveys basic information&mdash;the character hears movement in the forest, smells distant smoke, or senses someone isn&rsquo;t being completely truthful.</p>\n<p>A @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{raise} grants more detail, such as the direction of a sound or odor or what topic a person is avoiding or lying about.</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"attribute":"smarts","isCoreSkill":true,"die":{"sides":4,"modifier":0},"wild-die":{"sides":6}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_azxylmvr7yo","path":"Skills","color":"#008000"},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.swade-core-rules.swade-skills.yvw9bMgsrWQXuZN2"}}},{"_id":"X0BYJUZclN1vQeaV","name":"Athletics","type":"skill","img":"icons/magic/control/buff-strength-muscle-damage.webp","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p>Athletics combines an individual&rsquo;s coordin&shy;ation with learned skills such as climbing, jumping, balancing, biking, wrestling, skiing, swimming, throwing, or catching. Characters who rely on physical power more than coordination can take the @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Brute]{Brute} Edge to link this skill to @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Traits]{Strength} instead of @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Traits]{Agility}.</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"attribute":"agility","isCoreSkill":true,"die":{"sides":4,"modifier":0},"wild-die":{"sides":6}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_azxylmvr7yo","path":"Skills","color":"#008000"},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.swade-core-rules.swade-skills.sAig03GZiFKqBX7p"}}},{"_id":"d8bbwVTHdQpb5AFb","name":"Stealth","type":"skill","img":"icons/magic/nature/stealth-hide-eyes-green.webp","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p>Stealth is the ability to hide and move quietly. A simple @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{success} on a Stealth roll means the character avoids detection if enemies aren&rsquo;t particularly alert. If the character @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{fails} the roll, the enemy realizes something is amiss and begins actively searching for whatever roused them.</p>\n<p>Once foes are alerted and active, Stealth is opposed by @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Notice]{Notice} (a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{group roll} if there are many foes.</p>\n<p>The GM should apply any circumstantial penalties to @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Notice]{Notice} rolls for @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Illumination]{darkness}, @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Cover and Obstacles]{cover}, noise, distractions, and any difference in the target&rsquo;s @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Size and Scale]{Scale} (just like when attacking). Sneaking through dry leaves might subtract 2 from the Stealth roll, for example, while spotting someone in the dark uses the @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Illumination]{Illumination} penalty (&minus;4). Don&rsquo;t apply the same modifier to both rolls, however. If Stealth is at &minus;2 for the leaves, don&rsquo;t give Notice a +2 for them as well.</p>\n<p><strong>Sneak Attack: </strong> Sneaking up close enough to make a melee attack <em>always</em> requires an @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{opposed} Stealth roll versus the target&rsquo;s @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Notice]{Notice}, whether the guard is actively looking for trouble or not. If successful, the victim is @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Distracted and Vulnerable]{Vulnerable} to the attacker, but only until the attacker&rsquo;s turn ends. With a raise, the attacker has @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.The Drop]{The Drop} instead.</p>\n<p><strong>Movement:</strong> In combat, characters roll Stealth each turn as a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Actions]{free action} at the end of their move or any action the GM thinks might draw attention.</p>\n<p>Out of combat, the distance moved depends entirely on the situation. The GM might want a roll every minute if the group is sneaking around the perimeter of a defensive position, or every few miles if they&rsquo;re trying to quietly walk the path through a dark forest without alerting the creatures that live there.</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"attribute":"agility","isCoreSkill":true,"die":{"sides":4,"modifier":0},"wild-die":{"sides":6}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_azxylmvr7yo","path":"Skills","color":"#008000"},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.swade-core-rules.swade-skills.z9FmdFVGOOW2kufm"}}},{"_id":"wT9Ir2pYgNXXi5iA","name":"Common Knowledge","type":"skill","img":"icons/sundries/documents/document-official-capital.webp","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\"><p>Characters roll Common Knowledge to know people, places, and things of their world, including etiquette, geography, culture, popular technology, contacts, and customs.</p></div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"attribute":"smarts","isCoreSkill":true,"die":{"sides":4,"modifier":0},"wild-die":{"sides":6}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_azxylmvr7yo","path":"Skills","color":"#008000"},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.swade-core-rules.swade-skills.8N1uMThntsjaUPem"}}},{"name":"Untrained","type":"skill","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/skill.svg","data":{"description":"","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"attribute":"","isCoreSkill":false,"die":{"sides":4,"modifier":-2},"wild-die":{"sides":6}},"_id":"33b00za9pruiom2g","effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0},"flags":{}}],"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_z59ej144gfl","path":"Pirates of Cyre Bestiary#/CF_SEP/Vehicles","color":"#000000","name":"Vehicles","children":["HaEE59Dzh7i0zZov"],"folderPath":["temp_pw543v57cu"]}},"_id":"xg2XDD84JzvWBg9M"}
{"name":"Cut-Throat Grok","type":"npc","img":"https://assets.forge-vtt.com/5f43f8ea1a91d63438d13159/artwork-adventures/pirates-of-cyre/characters/cut-throat-grok.webp","data":{"attributes":{"agility":{"die":{"sides":6,"modifier":0},"wild-die":{"sides":6}},"smarts":{"die":{"sides":6,"modifier":0},"wild-die":{"sides":6},"animal":false},"spirit":{"die":{"sides":8,"modifier":0},"wild-die":{"sides":6},"unShakeBonus":0},"strength":{"die":{"sides":6,"modifier":0},"wild-die":{"sides":6},"encumbranceSteps":0},"vigor":{"die":{"sides":8,"modifier":0},"wild-die":{"sides":6}}},"stats":{"speed":{"runningDie":6,"runningMod":0,"value":6},"toughness":{"value":0,"armor":0,"modifier":0},"parry":{"value":6,"modifier":0},"size":0},"details":{"biography":{"value":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p>Cut-Throat Grok is the <em>Storm Reaver's </em></span>quartermaster, a no-nonsense character with a huge scar across her neck. Grok is a reedy half-orc who favors dark clothing. She carries a notched greataxe and an array of throwing axes hangs from her belt. Grok frequently grins toothily, and uses appalling curse words, particularly when drunk. </span> <br style=\"font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; font-weight: normal; letter-spacing: normal; line-height: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: -webkit-auto; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-size-adjust: auto; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px;\" /><br /></p>\n</div>"},"species":{"name":""},"currency":500,"wealth":{"die":6,"modifier":0,"wild-die":6},"conviction":{"value":0,"active":false},"autoCalcToughness":true,"autoCalcParry":true},"powerPoints":{},"fatigue":{"value":0,"min":0,"max":2},"wounds":{"value":0,"min":0,"max":0,"ignored":0},"advances":{"value":0,"rank":"Novice","details":""},"bennies":{"value":2,"max":2},"status":{"isShaken":false,"isDistracted":false,"isVulnerable":false,"isStunned":false,"isEntangled":false,"isBound":false},"initiative":{"hasHesitant":false,"hasLevelHeaded":false,"hasImpLevelHeaded":false,"hasQuick":false},"additionalStats":{},"wildcard":false},"token":{"flags":{"perfect-vision":{"visionRules":"default","monoVisionColor":"","sightLimit":null}},"name":"Cut-Thraot Grok","displayName":30,"img":"modules/etu-rules/assets/bestiary_tokens/sonya-alvarez-min.png","tint":null,"width":1,"height":1,"scale":1,"mirrorX":false,"mirrorY":false,"lockRotation":false,"rotation":0,"vision":true,"dimSight":30,"brightSight":0,"dimLight":0,"brightLight":0,"sightAngle":0,"lightAngle":0,"lightColor":null,"lightAlpha":1,"lightAnimation":{"speed":5,"intensity":5},"actorId":null,"actorLink":true,"disposition":0,"displayBars":0,"bar1":{"attribute":""},"bar2":{"attribute":""},"randomImg":false,"alpha":1,"x":null,"y":null,"elevation":null},"items":[{"_id":"UZW0tLJicg0VZOp4","name":"Athletics","type":"skill","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p>Athletics combines an individual&rsquo;s coordin&shy;ation with learned skills such as climbing, jumping, balancing, biking, wrestling, skiing, swimming, throwing, or catching. Characters who rely on physical power more than coordination can take the @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Brute]{Brute} Edge to link this skill to @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Traits]{Strength} instead of @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Traits]{Agility}.</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"attribute":"agility","isCoreSkill":false,"die":{"sides":6,"modifier":0},"wild-die":{"sides":6}},"sort":100000,"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_nsugutrpau","path":"Skills","color":"#8c160f"},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.swade-core-rules.swade-skills.Athletics"}},"img":"icons/magic/control/buff-strength-muscle-damage.webp","effects":[],"folder":null,"permission":{"default":0}},{"_id":"W5lfcCNjirSPUH42","name":"Common Knowledge","type":"skill","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\"><p>Characters roll Common Knowledge to know people, places, and things of their world, including etiquette, geography, culture, popular technology, contacts, and customs.</p></div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"attribute":"smarts","isCoreSkill":false,"die":{"sides":6,"modifier":-1},"wild-die":{"sides":6}},"sort":200000,"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_nsugutrpau","path":"Skills","color":"#8c160f"},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.swade-core-rules.swade-skills.Common Knowledge"}},"img":"icons/sundries/documents/document-official-capital.webp","effects":[],"folder":null,"permission":{"default":0}},{"_id":"quj5jF3vNls1j5E3","name":"Notice","type":"skill","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p>Notice is a hero&rsquo;s general awareness and alertness. It&rsquo;s used to sense sights, sounds, tastes, and smells, spot clues, detect ambushes, spot hidden weapons on a foe, or tell if a rival is lying, frightened, happy, etc.</p>\n<p>@Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{Success} conveys basic information&mdash;the character hears movement in the forest, smells distant smoke, or senses someone isn&rsquo;t being completely truthful.</p>\n<p>A @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{raise} grants more detail, such as the direction of a sound or odor or what topic a person is avoiding or lying about.</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"attribute":"smarts","isCoreSkill":false,"die":{"sides":6,"modifier":-1},"wild-die":{"sides":6}},"sort":300000,"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_nsugutrpau","path":"Skills","color":"#8c160f"},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.swade-core-rules.swade-skills.ZvwjzMLxsneptV4T"}},"img":"icons/creatures/eyes/human-single-blue.webp","effects":[],"folder":null,"permission":{"default":0}},{"_id":"TOEzoo2Lf4A5JXOF","name":"Persuasion","type":"skill","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p>Persuasion is the ability to convince others to do what you want through reason, cajoling, deception, rewards, or other friendly means. Persuasion isn&rsquo;t mind control. It can change someone&rsquo;s attitude but not their goals. A bandit may let you keep a sentimental piece of jewelry with a good Persuasion roll but still takes all your other goods.</p>\n<p>When used to @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Support]{Support} allies it&rsquo;s an unopposed roll. If the target is resistant, it&rsquo;s an @JournalEntry[JBxsGv2wAoAmoCDe]{opposed} roll vs. the target&rsquo;s @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Traits]{Spirit}. The GM should modify the roll as she sees fit based on roleplaying, any pertinent @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Edges]{Edges} or @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Hindrances]{Hindrances} that affect the conversation, and the circumstances.</p>\n<p><strong>Reaction Level:</strong> How much a person is willing to cooperate depends largely on their attitude toward whoever&rsquo;s talking to them. The Game Master can decide how nonplayer characters feel based on the setting, or roll on the @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-tables.Reaction Table]{Reaction Table} if she has no preconceived notions.</p>\n<p>@Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{Success} improves the target&rsquo;s attitude one level and a raise improves it two. Further increases aren&rsquo;t generally possible in the same encounter&mdash;it takes individuals a little time to adjust their biases.</p>\n<p>@Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{Failure} means the target won&rsquo;t change his mind this scene or until the situation changes in some important way. A @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{Critical Failure} also <em>reduces</em> the target&rsquo;s attitude two levels.</p>\n<p>Only one roll should generally be allowed per interaction unless new information is revealed, a substantial reward is offered, etc.</p>\n<p><strong>Networking: </strong>Characters can also use Persuasion as a &ldquo;macro skill,&rdquo; simulating a few hours or an evening&rsquo;s time hobnobbing and socializing to gain favors or information. See @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Networking]{Networking}.</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"attribute":"spirit","isCoreSkill":false,"die":{"sides":8,"modifier":-1},"wild-die":{"sides":6}},"sort":400000,"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_nsugutrpau","path":"Skills","color":"#8c160f"},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.swade-core-rules.swade-skills.Persuasion"}},"img":"icons/skills/social/diplomacy-handshake.webp","effects":[],"folder":null,"permission":{"default":0}},{"_id":"8VzaSa3EEDrMz6PR","name":"Stealth","type":"skill","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p>Stealth is the ability to hide and move quietly. A simple @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{success} on a Stealth roll means the character avoids detection if enemies aren&rsquo;t particularly alert. If the character @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{fails} the roll, the enemy realizes something is amiss and begins actively searching for whatever roused them.</p>\n<p>Once foes are alerted and active, Stealth is opposed by @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Notice]{Notice} (a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{group roll} if there are many foes.</p>\n<p>The GM should apply any circumstantial penalties to @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Notice]{Notice} rolls for @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Illumination]{darkness}, @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Cover and Obstacles]{cover}, noise, distractions, and any difference in the target&rsquo;s @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Size and Scale]{Scale} (just like when attacking). Sneaking through dry leaves might subtract 2 from the Stealth roll, for example, while spotting someone in the dark uses the @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Illumination]{Illumination} penalty (&minus;4). Don&rsquo;t apply the same modifier to both rolls, however. If Stealth is at &minus;2 for the leaves, don&rsquo;t give Notice a +2 for them as well.</p>\n<p><strong>Sneak Attack: </strong> Sneaking up close enough to make a melee attack <em>always</em> requires an @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{opposed} Stealth roll versus the target&rsquo;s @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Notice]{Notice}, whether the guard is actively looking for trouble or not. If successful, the victim is @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Distracted and Vulnerable]{Vulnerable} to the attacker, but only until the attacker&rsquo;s turn ends. With a raise, the attacker has @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.The Drop]{The Drop} instead.</p>\n<p><strong>Movement:</strong> In combat, characters roll Stealth each turn as a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Actions]{free action} at the end of their move or any action the GM thinks might draw attention.</p>\n<p>Out of combat, the distance moved depends entirely on the situation. The GM might want a roll every minute if the group is sneaking around the perimeter of a defensive position, or every few miles if they&rsquo;re trying to quietly walk the path through a dark forest without alerting the creatures that live there.</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"attribute":"agility","isCoreSkill":false,"die":{"sides":4,"modifier":"0"},"wild-die":{"sides":6}},"sort":500000,"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_nsugutrpau","path":"Skills","color":"#8c160f"},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.swade-core-rules.swade-skills.Stealth"}},"img":"icons/magic/nature/stealth-hide-eyes-green.webp","effects":[],"folder":null,"permission":{"default":0}},{"_id":"BQ3OOQlkZvCl1Lfb","name":"Unskilled Attempt","type":"skill","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p>If a character doesn&rsquo;t have a skill for an action he&rsquo;s attempting, he rolls a d4 for his skill die (and a Wild Die if a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Wild Cards and Extras]{Wild Card}) and subtracts 2 from the total.</p>\n<p>The GM may decide certain tasks cannot be attempted unskilled, such as performing complex surgery or flying a commercial jet.</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"attribute":"agility","isCoreSkill":false,"die":{"sides":4,"modifier":"-2"},"wild-die":{"sides":6}},"sort":1100000,"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_nsugutrpau","path":"Skills","color":"#8c160f"},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.swade-core-rules.swade-skills.zcn1epcU4FEJGGyI"}},"img":"icons/magic/symbols/question-stone-yellow.webp","effects":[],"folder":null,"permission":{"default":0}},{"_id":"uaVAhwDnUDLFZFXm","name":"Unarmed strike","type":"weapon","data":{"description":"","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"quantity":1,"weight":0,"price":0,"equippable":false,"equipped":true,"isVehicular":false,"mods":1,"actions":{"skill":"","skillMod":"","dmgMod":"","additional":{}},"damage":"@str","range":"","rof":"1","ap":"0","minStr":"","shots":"0","currentShots":"0","ammo":"","autoReload":false},"sort":1400000,"flags":{},"img":"icons/skills/melee/unarmed-punch-fist.webp","effects":[],"folder":null,"permission":{"default":0}},{"_id":"GjcL17dCtOeFUvbu","name":"Fighting","type":"skill","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p>Fighting covers all hand-to-hand (melee) attacks, whether it&rsquo;s with fists, axes, laser swords, or martial arts. See @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Combat]{Chapter Three} for the combat rules and the various maneuvers a warrior might attempt.</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"attribute":"agility","isCoreSkill":false,"die":{"sides":8,"modifier":0},"wild-die":{"sides":6}},"sort":1500000,"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_qals24wpyph","path":"Skills","color":"#8c160f"},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.swade-core-rules.swade-skills.wWiwjPlzAQU3TN9l"}},"img":"icons/skills/melee/hand-grip-sword-white-brown.webp","effects":[],"folder":null,"permission":{"default":0}},{"_id":"TLp2vEe194RjRVYB","name":"Fighter","type":"edge","img":"icons/environment/people/infantry.webp","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p>Some take up arms for glory, wealth, or revenge. Others do battle to prove themselves, to protect others, or because they know nothing else. Still others learn the ways of weaponcraft to hone their bodies in battle and prove their mettle in the forge of war.</p>\n<p>Lords of the battlefield, fighters are a disparate lot. Some train with many weapons; some prefer just one. Whatever their tactics, fighters excel at combat. They protect their own and defeat their enemies, rarely shying away from battle. They often lead the charge, a role they relish even if they don&rsquo;t insist on it.</p>\n<p>These skilled warriors turn hunks of metal into arms capable of taming kingdoms, slaughtering monsters, and rousing the hearts of armies. Woe to those who dare stand against them.</p>\n<p>Fighters gain the following abilities:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Combat Training]{Combat Training}</li>\n<li>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Martial Flexibility]{Martial Flexibility}</li>\n</ul>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Novice, Strength d6+, Fighting d6+"}},"effects":[],"folder":"i5aNd30ywxpcOuxy","sort":100000,"permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"flags":{"journal-links":{},"core":{"sourceId":"Item.JSFKscBmodf3b9qX"}}},{"_id":"AmMcLJktnYTO3cZt","name":"Combat Training","type":"edge","img":"icons/environment/people/infantry.webp","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p>The fighter are trained and adept at feints and deception in combat to unbalance their opponent. They add +1 to the all rolls for @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Test]{Tests} in combat that use any of the following skills: @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Athletics]{Athletics}, @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Battle]{Battle}, @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Fighting]{Fighting}, @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Intimidation]{Intimidation}, or @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Shooting]{Shooting} rolls.</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Novice, Fighter"}},"effects":[],"folder":"i5aNd30ywxpcOuxy","sort":200000,"permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"flags":{"journal-links":{},"core":{"sourceId":"Item.iAxlS6GhMXNoZpnI"}}},{"_id":"jDPQ3HNSu0yVYt2d","name":"Language (Orcish)","type":"skill","img":"icons/sundries/documents/document-letter-formal-tan.webp","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p>In some settings, such as those that focus on pulp action or &ldquo;planetary romance&rdquo; (where characters frequently travel among many strange civilizations), speaking various languages can simply be roleplayed with halting dialogue and campy accents that start out a little difficult and are quickly forgotten. The GM may ignore this skill altogether in these settings, or use the @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Multiple Languages]{Multiple Languages}&nbsp;&shy;option in the @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Setting Rules]{Setting Rules}.</p>\n<p>In more realistic settings, communication can be a major barrier that requires characters to put skill points into additional languages. In a 1980s World War Three game, for example, a group of United Nations paratroopers won&rsquo;t be able to speak with their foes unless they take Russian, Polish, or other languages common to the Warsaw Pact.</p>\n<p>If the Language skill is in use, it should be listed as Language (Spanish), Language (American Sign Language), etc. A character&rsquo;s die type also notes how fluent he is in it. (Characters start with a d8 in their own Language.)</p>\n<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<table class=\"table value-table\"><caption class=\"table-caption\">\n<h2 class=\"table-title\">Language Proficiency</h2>\n</caption>\n<tbody>\n<tr class=\"table-header-row\">\n<th class=\"table-column-header\" scope=\"col\">Skill</th>\n<th class=\"table-column-header\" scope=\"col\">Ability</th>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td>d4</td>\n<td>The character can read, write and speak common words and phrases.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>d6</td>\n<td>The speaker can carry on a prolonged but occasionally halting conversation.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>d8</td>\n<td>The character can speak fluently.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>d10</td>\n<td>The hero can mimic other dialects within the language.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>d12</td>\n<td>The speaker can masterfully recite important literary or oral works.</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>\n</div>\n<p><strong>Limited: </strong>Use whichever skill is lowest when performing an action that requires knowledge of a foreign language. @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Intimidation]{Intimidation} (if verbal), @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Persuasion]{Persuasion}, @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Research]{Research}, @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Taunt]{Taunt}, etc., are all limited by the character&rsquo;s Language skill.</p>\n<p>This limitation never applies to a character&rsquo;s native tongue.</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"attribute":"smarts","isCoreSkill":false,"die":{"sides":6,"modifier":0},"wild-die":{"sides":6}},"effects":[],"folder":"NGCHRRLs7ShzfqpB","sort":200000,"permission":{"default":0,"3HvtK4sMp7flYKmT":3,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_nsugutrpau","path":"Skills","color":"#8c160f"},"journal-links":{},"core":{"sourceId":"Item.r0POISsnudlhTqsf"}}},{"_id":"fZwcFZGcNVXSHUch","name":"Primal Intuition","type":"ability","img":"icons/magic/nature/leaf-rune-glow-green.webp","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p>Half-orcs start with a d4 in one of the following skills:&nbsp;<em>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Athletics]{athletics}, @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Healing]{healing}, @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Intimidation]{intimidation}, @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Notice]{notice},&nbsp;</em>or&nbsp;<em>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Survival]{survival}</em>. If the chosen skill is a core skill, it starts at d6 and the skill's maximum increases to d12+1.</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"subtype":"special","grantsPowers":false},"effects":[],"folder":"NGCHRRLs7ShzfqpB","sort":300000,"permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"flags":{"journal-links":{},"core":{"sourceId":"Item.eK4ugnzc1XArIZA6"}}},{"_id":"HaDfxXcTkGpGXyve","name":"Low Light Vision","type":"ability","img":"icons/creatures/eyes/human-single-brown.webp","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p>Low Light Vision ignores up &ndash;2 penalties for @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Illumination]{Dim and Dark Illumination}. @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Illumination]{Pitch Darkness} remains unaffected.</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"subtype":"special","grantsPowers":false},"effects":[],"folder":"kFghWjY7gP7MEqav","sort":100001,"permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"flags":{"journal-links":{},"core":{"sourceId":"Item.OL3T8otZVCkOoir3"}}},{"_id":"bo7crv0cGG78T9UP","name":"Liquid Courage","type":"edge","img":"icons/environment/people/cleric-orange.webp","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p>This gregarious individual processes alcohol far differently than most. The round after consuming a stiff drink (about eight ounces of hard liquor or equivalent), her @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Traits]{Vigor} increases one die type (increasing @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Characters]{Toughness} as well). The drinker can also ignore one level of @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Damage Effects]{Wound} penalties (which stacks with other abilities that do the same).</p>\n<p>@Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Traits]{Smarts}, @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Traits]{Agility}, and all linked skills suffer a &minus;1 penalty for the duration, however.</p>\n<p>The effect lasts for one hour after it begins, at which point the boozer suffers a level of @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Fatigue]{Fatigue} for the next four hours.</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Novice, Vigor d8+"}},"effects":[{"_id":"5f5punVk9GcL8wd6","changes":[{"key":"data.attributes.vigor.die.sides","mode":2,"value":"2"},{"key":"data.wounds.ignored","mode":2,"value":"1"},{"key":"data.attributes.smarts.die.modifier","mode":2,"value":"-1"},{"key":"data.attributes.agility.die.modifier","mode":2,"value":"-1"}],"disabled":false,"duration":{"startTime":null},"icon":"icons/environment/people/cleric-orange.webp","label":"Liquid Courage","transfer":true,"flags":{},"tint":null}],"folder":"OeyARkjjHG8YltWb","sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"3HvtK4sMp7flYKmT":3,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"flags":{"cf":null,"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.swade-core-rules.swade-edges.MkvhQtL8RUJrsGj9"}}},{"_id":"JYGgxWOSbOlSQZ8k","name":"Streetwise","type":"edge","img":"icons/skills/social/diplomacy-unity-alliance.webp","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p>Streetwise characters know how to find the local black market, fence stolen goods, avoid the local law (or criminal element!), lay low when the heat&rsquo;s on, obtain illegal weapons, find out which &ldquo;boss&rdquo; is hiring muscle, or similar shady activities.<br /></span></p>\n<p>Streetwise characters add +2 to @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-skills.Intimidation]{Intimidation} or @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-skills.Persuasion]{Persuasion} rolls made to </span>@Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Networking]{Networking}</span>&nbsp;with shady or criminal elements.<br /></span></p>\n<p>They also add +2 to @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-skills.Common Knowledge]{Common Knowledge} rolls pertaining to the types of disreputable activities listed above</span></p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Novice, Smarts d6+"}},"effects":[],"folder":"4qgDgsPe5IZFyuwd","sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"3HvtK4sMp7flYKmT":3,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"flags":{"cf":null,"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.swade-core-rules.swade-edges.9dkUUjYdfSoYx10K"}}},{"_id":"uILmewT5YLFZoSiV","name":"Boating","type":"skill","img":"icons/environment/settlement/ship.webp","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\"><p>Characters with this skill can handle most any boat or ship common to their setting. They also know how to handle common tasks associated with their vessel such as tying knots, rigging sails, or following currents.</p></div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"attribute":"agility","isCoreSkill":false,"die":{"sides":6,"modifier":0},"wild-die":{"sides":6}},"effects":[],"folder":"cgfmurTJRwbCvmCc","sort":1400001,"permission":{"default":0,"3HvtK4sMp7flYKmT":3,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_qals24wpyph","path":"Skills","color":"#8c160f"},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.swade-core-rules.swade-skills.WMWgIVDuAW4cHxj2"}}},{"_id":"9iTPpx0fmkQVJA8R","name":"Language (Common)","type":"skill","img":"icons/sundries/documents/document-letter-formal-tan.webp","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p>In some settings, such as those that focus on pulp action or &ldquo;planetary romance&rdquo; (where characters frequently travel among many strange civilizations), speaking various languages can simply be roleplayed with halting dialogue and campy accents that start out a little difficult and are quickly forgotten. The GM may ignore this skill altogether in these settings, or use the @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Multiple Languages]{Multiple Languages}&nbsp;&shy;option in the @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Setting Rules]{Setting Rules}.</p>\n<p>In more realistic settings, communication can be a major barrier that requires characters to put skill points into additional languages. In a 1980s World War Three game, for example, a group of United Nations paratroopers won&rsquo;t be able to speak with their foes unless they take Russian, Polish, or other languages common to the Warsaw Pact.</p>\n<p>If the Language skill is in use, it should be listed as Language (Spanish), Language (American Sign Language), etc. A character&rsquo;s die type also notes how fluent he is in it. (Characters start with a d8 in their own Language.)</p>\n<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<table class=\"table value-table\"><caption class=\"table-caption\">\n<h2 class=\"table-title\">Language Proficiency</h2>\n</caption>\n<tbody>\n<tr class=\"table-header-row\">\n<th class=\"table-column-header\" scope=\"col\">Skill</th>\n<th class=\"table-column-header\" scope=\"col\">Ability</th>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td>d4</td>\n<td>The character can read, write and speak common words and phrases.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>d6</td>\n<td>The speaker can carry on a prolonged but occasionally halting conversation.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>d8</td>\n<td>The character can speak fluently.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>d10</td>\n<td>The hero can mimic other dialects within the language.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>d12</td>\n<td>The speaker can masterfully recite important literary or oral works.</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>\n</div>\n<p><strong>Limited: </strong>Use whichever skill is lowest when performing an action that requires knowledge of a foreign l