startTime":28973116800},"icon":"modules/swade-core-rules/assets/art/equipment/weapons/melee-medieval-greataxe.webp","label":"Great Axe Parry Penalty","origin":"Actor.HqdOgzzsCeFolctC.Item.ukORcNhJ26q2KQsc","tint":null,"transfer":false,"flags":{}}],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"flags":{"journal-links":{"references":{}},"cf":{"id":"temp_3a04s0jrz4j","path":"Pirates of Cyre Bestiary#/CF_SEP/NPC's","color":"#000000"}},"_id":"z2qkrFSshkwFRNra"}
{"_id":"2OH6BHW2dWwq8OFH","name":"Conchobhar","type":"npc","img":"https://assets.forge-vtt.com/5f43f8ea1a91d63438d13159/artwork-adventures/pirates-of-cyre/characters/conchobhar-turlach-tomraan.webp","data":{"attributes":{"agility":{"die":{"sides":8,"modifier":0},"wild-die":{"sides":6}},"smarts":{"die":{"sides":6,"modifier":0},"wild-die":{"sides":6},"animal":false},"spirit":{"die":{"sides":8,"modifier":0},"wild-die":{"sides":6},"unShakeBonus":0},"strength":{"die":{"sides":6,"modifier":0},"wild-die":{"sides":6},"encumbranceSteps":0},"vigor":{"die":{"sides":6,"modifier":0},"wild-die":{"sides":6}}},"stats":{"speed":{"runningDie":4,"runningMod":0,"value":5},"toughness":{"value":0,"armor":0,"modifier":0},"parry":{"value":5,"modifier":0},"size":-1},"details":{"biography":{"value":"<div class=\"sweb-core\">\n<p>Conchobhar Shortstone is a handsome, honey-tongued gnome who wears a foppish purple hat, an eye patch, and a white silk shirt, and carries a dandyish cane. His appearance is that of someone pretending to be a pirate, rather than a true buccaneer. </p>"},"species":{"name":""},"currency":500,"wealth":{"die":6,"modifier":0,"wild-die":6},"conviction":{"value":0,"active":false},"autoCalcToughness":true,"autoCalcParry":true},"powerPoints":{"value":11,"max":11,"Gnome Magic":{"value":0,"max":0},"Bard":{"value":0,"max":0}},"fatigue":{"value":0,"min":0,"max":2},"wounds":{"value":0,"min":0,"max":3,"ignored":0},"advances":{"value":0,"rank":"Novice","details":""},"bennies":{"value":2,"max":2},"status":{"isShaken":false,"isDistracted":false,"isVulnerable":false,"isStunned":false,"isEntangled":false,"isBound":false},"initiative":{"hasHesitant":false,"hasLevelHeaded":false,"hasImpLevelHeaded":false,"hasQuick":false},"additionalStats":{},"wildcard":true},"token":{"name":"Blank NPC","img":"https://assets.forge-vtt.com/5f43f8ea1a91d63438d13159/tokens/bestiary/monstrous%20humanoid/harpy-*.png","displayName":30,"actorLink":false,"width":1,"height":1,"scale":1,"mirrorX":false,"mirrorY":false,"lockRotation":false,"rotation":0,"alpha":1,"vision":false,"dimSight":0,"brightSight":0,"dimLight":0,"brightLight":0,"sightAngle":0,"lightAngle":0,"lightAlpha":0.25,"lightAnimation":{"speed":5,"intensity":5},"disposition":-1,"displayBars":0,"bar1":{"attribute":""},"bar2":{"attribute":""},"flags":{},"randomImg":true,"actorId":null,"tint":null,"lightColor":null,"x":null,"y":null,"elevation":null},"items":[{"_id":"Bf0NpaRHtHmfrLb3","name":"Athletics","type":"skill","img":"icons/magic/control/buff-strength-muscle-damage.webp","data":{"description":"<div class=\"sweb-core\">\n<p>Athletics combines an individual&rsquo;s coordin&shy;ation with learned skills such as climbing, jumping, balancing, biking, wrestling, skiing, swimming, throwing, or catching. Characters who rely on physical power more than coordination can take the @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Brute]{Brute} Edge to link this skill to @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Traits]{Strength} instead of @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Traits]{Agility}.</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"attribute":"agility","isCoreSkill":false,"die":{"sides":6,"modifier":0},"wild-die":{"sides":6}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_azxylmvr7yo","path":"Skills","color":"#008000"},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.swade-core-rules.swade-skills.sAig03GZiFKqBX7p"}}},{"_id":"bJxCFLP4a8BEU0Qm","name":"Common Knowledge","type":"skill","img":"icons/sundries/documents/document-official-capital.webp","data":{"description":"<div class=\"sweb-core\"><p>Characters roll Common Knowledge to know people, places, and things of their world, including etiquette, geography, culture, popular technology, contacts, and customs.</p></div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"attribute":"smarts","isCoreSkill":false,"die":{"sides":6,"modifier":0},"wild-die":{"sides":6}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_azxylmvr7yo","path":"Skills","color":"#008000"},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.swade-core-rules.swade-skills.8N1uMThntsjaUPem"}}},{"_id":"gMAJFeCm5e3Oporq","name":"Fighting","type":"skill","img":"icons/skills/melee/hand-grip-sword-white-brown.webp","data":{"description":"<div class=\"sweb-core\">\n<p>Fighting covers all hand-to-hand (melee) attacks, whether it&rsquo;s with fists, axes, laser swords, or martial arts. See @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Combat]{Chapter Three} for the combat rules and the various maneuvers a warrior might attempt.</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"attribute":"agility","isCoreSkill":false,"die":{"sides":6,"modifier":0},"wild-die":{"sides":6}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_azxylmvr7yo","path":"Skills","color":"#008000"},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.swade-core-rules.swade-skills.wWiwjPlzAQU3TN9l"}}},{"_id":"9coycVPgGdTGpbmh","name":"Language (Common)","type":"skill","img":"icons/sundries/documents/document-letter-formal-tan.webp","data":{"description":"<div class=\"sweb-core\">\n<p>In some settings, such as those that focus on pulp action or &ldquo;planetary romance&rdquo; (where characters frequently travel among many strange civilizations), speaking various languages can simply be roleplayed with halting dialogue and campy accents that start out a little difficult and are quickly forgotten. The GM may ignore this skill altogether in these settings, or use the @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Multiple Languages]{Multiple Languages} &shy;option in the @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Setting Rules]{Setting Rules}.</p>\n<p>In more realistic settings, communication can be a major barrier that requires characters to put skill points into additional languages. In a 1980s World War Three game, for example, a group of United Nations paratroopers won&rsquo;t be able to speak with their foes unless they take Russian, Polish, or other languages common to the Warsaw Pact.</p>\n<p>If the Language skill is in use, it should be listed as Language (Spanish), Language (American Sign Language), etc. A character&rsquo;s die type also notes how fluent he is in it. (Characters start with a d8 in their own Language.)</p>\n<div class=\"sweb-core\">\n<table class=\"table value-table\"><caption class=\"table-caption\">\n<h2 class=\"table-title\">Language Proficiency</h2>\n</caption>\n<tbody>\n<tr class=\"table-header-row\">\n<th class=\"table-column-header\" scope=\"col\">Skill</th>\n<th class=\"table-column-header\" scope=\"col\">Ability</th>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td>d4</td>\n<td>The character can read, write and speak common words and phrases.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>d6</td>\n<td>The speaker can carry on a prolonged but occasionally halting conversation.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>d8</td>\n<td>The character can speak fluently.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>d10</td>\n<td>The hero can mimic other dialects within the language.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>d12</td>\n<td>The speaker can masterfully recite important literary or oral works.</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>\n</div>\n<p><strong>Limited: </strong>Use whichever skill is lowest when performing an action that requires knowledge of a foreign language. @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Intimidation]{Intimidation} (if verbal), @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Persuasion]{Persuasion}, @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Research]{Research}, @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Taunt]{Taunt}, etc., are all limited by the character&rsquo;s Language skill.</p>\n<p>This limitation never applies to a character&rsquo;s native tongue.</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"attribute":"smarts","isCoreSkill":false,"die":{"sides":8,"modifier":0},"wild-die":{"sides":6}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_azxylmvr7yo","path":"Skills","color":"#008000"},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.swade-core-rules.swade-skills.XIuR2IyQtewm5BZP"}}},{"_id":"TWqtRMnChmXvwXvN","name":"Notice","type":"skill","img":"icons/creatures/eyes/human-single-blue.webp","data":{"description":"<div class=\"sweb-core\">\n<p>Notice is a hero&rsquo;s general awareness and alertness. It&rsquo;s used to sense sights, sounds, tastes, and smells, spot clues, detect ambushes, spot hidden weapons on a foe, or tell if a rival is lying, frightened, happy, etc.</p>\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Trait Rolls]{Success} conveys basic information&mdash;the character hears movement in the forest, smells distant smoke, or senses someone isn&rsquo;t being completely truthful.</p>\n<p>A @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Raises]{raise} grants more detail, such as the direction of a sound or odor or what topic a person is avoiding or lying about.</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"attribute":"smarts","isCoreSkill":false,"die":{"sides":6,"modifier":0},"wild-die":{"sides":6}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_azxylmvr7yo","path":"Skills","color":"#008000"},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.swade-core-rules.swade-skills.yvw9bMgsrWQXuZN2"}}},{"_id":"rk3ft5Cc4sHxF5ay","name":"Stealth","type":"skill","img":"icons/magic/nature/stealth-hide-eyes-green.webp","data":{"description":"<div class=\"sweb-core\">\n<p>Stealth is the ability to hide and move quietly. A simple @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Trait Rolls]{success} on a Stealth roll means the character avoids detection if enemies aren&rsquo;t particularly alert. If the character @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Trait Rolls]{fails} the roll, the enemy realizes something is amiss and begins actively searching for whatever roused them.</p>\n<p>Once foes are alerted and active, Stealth is opposed by @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Notice]{Notice} (a @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Trait Rolls]{group roll} if there are many foes.</p>\n<p>The GM should apply any circumstantial penalties to @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Notice]{Notice} rolls for @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Illumination]{darkness}, @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Cover and Obstacles]{cover}, noise, distractions, and any difference in the target&rsquo;s @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Size and Scale]{Scale} (just like when attacking). Sneaking through dry leaves might subtract 2 from the Stealth roll, for example, while spotting someone in the dark uses the @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Illumination]{Illumination} penalty (&minus;4). Don&rsquo;t apply the same modifier to both rolls, however. If Stealth is at &minus;2 for the leaves, don&rsquo;t give Notice a +2 for them as well.</p>\n<p><strong>Sneak Attack: </strong> Sneaking up close enough to make a melee attack <em>always</em> requires an @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Trait Rolls]{opposed} Stealth roll versus the target&rsquo;s @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Notice]{Notice}, whether the guard is actively looking for trouble or not. If successful, the victim is @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Distracted and Vulnerable]{Vulnerable} to the attacker, but only until the attacker&rsquo;s turn ends. With a raise, the attacker has @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.The Drop]{The Drop} instead.</p>\n<p><strong>Movement:</strong> In combat, characters roll Stealth each turn as a @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Actions]{free action} at the end of their move or any action the GM thinks might draw attention.</p>\n<p>Out of combat, the distance moved depends entirely on the situation. The GM might want a roll every minute if the group is sneaking around the perimeter of a defensive position, or every few miles if they&rsquo;re trying to quietly walk the path through a dark forest without alerting the creatures that live there.</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"attribute":"agility","isCoreSkill":false,"die":{"sides":8,"modifier":0},"wild-die":{"sides":6}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_azxylmvr7yo","path":"Skills","color":"#008000"},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.swade-core-rules.swade-skills.z9FmdFVGOOW2kufm"}}},{"_id":"6BeiHr2FDzQaAZll","name":"Untrained","type":"skill","img":"icons/magic/symbols/question-stone-yellow.webp","data":{"description":"<div class=\"sweb-core\">\n<p>If a character doesn&rsquo;t have a skill for an action he&rsquo;s attempting, he rolls a d4 for his skill die (and a Wild Die if a @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Wild Cards and Extras]{Wild Card}) and subtracts 2 from the total.</p>\n<p>The GM may decide certain tasks cannot be attempted unskilled, such as performing complex surgery or flying a commercial jet.</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"attribute":"agility","isCoreSkill":false,"die":{"sides":4,"modifier":-2},"wild-die":{"sides":6}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_azxylmvr7yo","path":"Skills","color":"#008000"},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.swade-core-rules.swade-skills.1Pl2ZL8MPyKnaVEg"}}},{"_id":"dKrkxQ780O1QyNfq","name":"Unarmed Strike","type":"weapon","img":"icons/skills/melee/unarmed-punch-fist.webp","data":{"description":"<div class=\"sweb-core\">\n<p>See @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Unarmed Defender]{Unarmed Defender}.</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"quantity":1,"weight":0,"price":0,"equippable":false,"equipped":true,"isVehicular":false,"mods":1,"actions":{"skill":"Fighting","skillMod":"","dmgMod":"","additional":{}},"damage":"@str","range":"","rof":"1","ap":"0","minStr":"","shots":"0","currentShots":"0","ammo":"","autoReload":false},"effects":[],"folder":"651LNce8no6HR9rY","sort":100000,"permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"flags":{"journal-links":{},"core":{"sourceId":"Item.X31v8asHtqhgiaM2"}}},{"_id":"cUCXNAyC28lHwJ1j","name":"Obsessive (Lore)","type":"ability","img":"icons/magic/nature/plant-sproud-hands-dirt-green.webp","data":{"description":"<div class=\"sweb-core\">\n<p>Gnomes start with a d4 in any one Smarts-related skill.</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"subtype":"special","grantsPowers":false},"effects":[],"folder":"UUZJk5Z5jpjqw5rC","sort":400000,"permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"flags":{"journal-links":{},"core":{"sourceId":"Item.5NAJSxm6K1Vya1aZ"}}},{"_id":"r14ToNyzKEQE0zho","name":"Bard","type":"edge","img":"icons/skills/trades/music-singing-voice-blue.webp","data":{"description":"<div class=\"sweb-core\">\n<p>The bards of Eberron bring epic tales of heroism and tragedy to the people. Many are renowned far and wide for their talents, but few realize how crucial they are to parties of brave adventurers. They bolster their allies in dire circumstances, beguile their enemies, and often battle evil with a sword in one hand and a lute in the other.</p>\n<p>Bards cast spells by singing, playing an instrument, reciting poetry, or reciting epic tales. They are usually erudite individuals, traveling the land to learn bawdy songs, great histories, and epic legends.</p>\n<p>Allies must be able to hear the bard to benefit from his various abilities.</p>\n<p>Bards gain the following abilities:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Arcane Background (Bard)]{Arcane Background (Bard)}</li>\n<li>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Bard Armor Interference (Light)]{Bard Armor Interference (Light)}</li>\n<li>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Lore Keeper]{Lore Keeper}</li>\n<li>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Sharp Tongued]{Sharp Tongued}</li>\n</ul>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Novice, Spirit d6+, Common Knowledge d6+"}},"effects":[],"folder":"YstCBrpWUVlhJwXz","sort":100000,"permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"flags":{"journal-links":{},"core":{"sourceId":"Item.zphGBAJ4gdUCFIqa"}}},{"_id":"Ufqcrdnfi8AiACko","name":"Arcane Background (Bard)","type":"edge","img":"icons/skills/trades/music-singing-voice-blue.webp","data":{"description":"<div class=\"sweb-core\">\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Arcane Background (Bard)]{Arcane Background (Bard)}</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"isArcaneBackground":true,"requirements":{"value":"Novice"}},"effects":[],"folder":"YstCBrpWUVlhJwXz","sort":500000,"permission":{"default":2,"ZvqefCj0L7TxJS56":3,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"flags":{"journal-links":{},"core":{"sourceId":"Item.zVLHayWmSMnBSupy"}}},{"_id":"XaMmQdQvRi2YKPR4","name":"Lore Keeper","type":"edge","img":"icons/skills/trades/music-singing-voice-blue.webp","data":{"description":"<div class=\"sweb-core\">\n<p>A bard learns special techniques for memorizing things he has heard or read, and he is well versed in many topics as part of his training. They have +1 to all @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Common Knowledge]{Common Knowledge} rolls, as well as rolls relating to riddles, history, folklore, and such like. Bards are also particularly popular with nobility and commoners alike and receive +1 @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Persuasion]{Persuasion} checks to @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Networking]{Networking} if they are known as a bard.</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Bard"}},"effects":[],"folder":"YstCBrpWUVlhJwXz","sort":300000,"permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"flags":{"journal-links":{},"core":{"sourceId":"Item.Yg6gxH0XZX9gc1gm"}}},{"_id":"9XMrHtpMcPksl1iM","name":"Sharp Tongued","type":"edge","img":"icons/skills/trades/music-singing-voice-blue.webp","data":{"description":"<div class=\"sweb-core\">\n<p>Bards may use @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Performance]{Performance} to @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Test]{Test} a foe. They may also ignore the Repetition advice given under @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Test]{Tests}, as long as they recite different verses, stanzas, lyrics, etc. Bards may also substitute @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Performance]{Performance} for @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Intimidation]{Intimidation} to meet Edge Requirements.</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Bard"}},"effects":[],"folder":"YstCBrpWUVlhJwXz","sort":300000,"permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"flags":{"journal-links":{},"core":{"sourceId":"Item.pD0DjyWGZctqf2qX"}}},{"_id":"zZSwUDYGQpshnUdl","name":"Gambling","type":"skill","img":"icons/sundries/gaming/dice-pair-white-green.webp","data":{"description":"<div class=\"sweb-core\"><p>Gambling is common in the saloons of the Old West, the back rooms of criminal organizations, the barracks of most armies, or the flight decks of scifi spaceships.</p>\n<p>To simulate an hour of gambling without having to roll for every single toss of the dice or hand of cards, have everyone agree on the stakes, such as $10, 10 gold coins, etc. Everyone in the game then makes a Gambling roll. The lowest total pays the highest total the difference times the stake. The next lowest pays the second highest the difference times the stake, and so on. If there&rsquo;s an odd man left in the middle, he breaks even.</p>\n<p class=\"embedded-example\"><strong>Example:</strong> Red rolls highest with a 10 and Gabe rolls lowest with a 4. The difference is 6, so Gabe pays Red 6 &times; the stake of $10, or $60.</p>\n<p><strong>Cheating: </strong>A character who cheats adds +2 to his roll. The GM may raise or lower this modifier depending on the particulars of the game or the method of cheating. If a cheater rolls a @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Trait Rolls]{Critical Failure}, however, he&rsquo;s caught. The consequences depend on the circumstances and who noticed, but are usually unpleasant!</p></div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"attribute":"smarts","isCoreSkill":false,"die":{"sides":8,"modifier":0},"wild-die":{"sides":6}},"effects":[],"folder":"cgfmurTJRwbCvmCc","sort":1900001,"permission":{"default":0,"3HvtK4sMp7flYKmT":3,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_qals24wpyph","path":"Skills","color":"#8c160f"},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.swade-core-rules.swade-skills.zPegv65RzQXUbQIz"}}},{"_id":"QBpBKVYkadCy2IOC","name":"Thievery","type":"skill","img":"icons/skills/social/theft-pickpocket-bribery-brown.webp","data":{"description":"<div class=\"sweb-core\">\n<p>Lockpicking, safecracking, picking pockets, sleight of hand, setting and disabling traps and similar acts of misdirection, sabotage, subterfuge, and manipulation are called Thievery.</p>\n<p>If used to pick a lock, crack a safe, disable a trap, or perform a simple unopposed action, @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Trait Rolls]{success} opens or disables the device, and a @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Raises]{raise} does it in less time, without tripping alarms, or whatever else the GM feels is appropriate.</p>\n<p>Sleight of hand, hiding or planting an item, or picking a pocket require a simple @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Trait Rolls]{success}. If foes are actively watching the character, Thievery is @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Trait Rolls]{opposed} by @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Notice]{Notice}.</p>\n<p>The Game Master should assign @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Trait Rolls]{penalties} for particularly difficult circumstances. Picking a heavy padlock might have a &minus;4 penalty, while hiding a revolver in bulky winter clothing might grant a +1 bonus. @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Trait Rolls]{Failure} typically means the character is spotted or it takes too much time (after which the character can try again). A @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Trait Rolls]{Critical Failure} typically sets off the trap, alerts the victim, or jams the device so that it must be opened or interacted with in a different way.</p>\n<p><strong>Limited: </strong>Using Thievery on an electronic device, such as a keypad, is limited by the thief&rsquo;s @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Electronics]{Electronics} skill. Use the lowest of the two skills.</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"attribute":"agility","isCoreSkill":false,"die":{"sides":6,"modifier":0},"wild-die":{"sides":6}},"effects":[],"folder":"cgfmurTJRwbCvmCc","sort":1087501,"permission":{"default":0,"3HvtK4sMp7flYKmT":3,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_qals24wpyph","path":"Skills","color":"#8c160f"},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.swade-core-rules.swade-skills.wZbyJkisWIfmcZNt"}}},{"_id":"JqoohAdH7GrGar6d","name":"Performance","type":"skill","img":"icons/tools/instruments/lute-gold-brown.webp","data":{"description":"<div class=\"sweb-core\">\n<p>A good entertainer can lift the spirits, rally a crowd to action, or simply earn a few bucks from the locals. Specifics depend on the situation, setting, and how well the character is known in the area.</p>\n<p>Performance covers singing, acting, playing an instrument, or similar tasks that require an audience to appreciate.</p>\n<p><strong>Raising Funds:</strong> The amount of money a character can raise by performing is extremely subjective, but as a general rule a @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Trait Rolls]{successful} performance raises 20% of the setting's @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Characters]{Starting Funds} with a success and 30% with a raise. The GM can multiply this amount by the performer's @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Advancement]{Rank} if she feels it's appropriate. These numbers work for typical performers who might be known in a small establishment or area. Larger performances can greatly boost the performer's fee, but also require more time, energy, and setup.</p>\n<p><strong>Deception: </strong>Performance can be used instead of @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Persuasion]{Persuasion} if the character is attempting to deceive, bluff, or disguise herself and the GM agrees it makes sense in the context of the situation.</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"attribute":"spirit","isCoreSkill":false,"die":{"sides":8,"modifier":0},"wild-die":{"sides":6}},"effects":[],"folder":"cgfmurTJRwbCvmCc","sort":2400001,"permission":{"default":0,"3HvtK4sMp7flYKmT":3,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_qals24wpyph","path":"Skills","color":"#8c160f"},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.swade-core-rules.swade-skills.SJ1nN0CmOHNQhfOQ"}}},{"_id":"LKSgjqNeDhS4PsEx","name":"Gnome Magic","type":"ability","img":"icons/magic/nature/plant-sproud-hands-dirt-green.webp","data":{"description":"<div class=\"sweb-core\">\n<p>Gnomes are inherently magical creatures. They can cast cantrips as if they knew each of the following powers: <em>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Light/Darkness]{light}</em>, <em>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Sound/Silence]{sound}</em>, <em>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Telekinesis]{telekinesis}</em>, and <em>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Beast Friend]{beast friend}</em> using their @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Traits]{Smarts} (or @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Arcane Backgrounds]{arcane skill} if they have one). They have 1 @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Arcane Backgrounds]{Power Point} for activating these cantrips, regained as usual. Gnomes with an Arcane Background or Mystic Power  or Dragonmark add their bonus @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Arcane Backgrounds]{Power Point} to their pool but must still learn the spells if they wish to cast them normally.</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"subtype":"special","grantsPowers":true},"effects":[],"folder":"UUZJk5Z5jpjqw5rC","sort":400000,"permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"flags":{"journal-links":{},"core":{"sourceId":"Item.wgvTOJ8MnESHB6rQ"}}},{"_id":"1IK9S7J34ibAK8G4","name":"Light (Cantrips Only)","type":"power","img":"icons/magic/light/torch-fire-orange.webp","data":{"description":"<div class=\"sweb-core\">\n<p><strong>School: </strong>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Schools of Magic]{Evocation}</p>\n<p><em>Light </em>creates bright @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Illumination]{illumination} in a @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Area Effect Attacks]{Large Blast Template}. With a raise, the light can be focused into a 5&Prime; (10 yard) beam as well.</p>\n<p><em>Darkness </em>blocks @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Illumination]{illumination} in an area the size of a @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Area Effect Attacks]{Large Blast Template}, making the area Dark, or Pitch Darkness with a raise (see @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Illumination]{Illumination}).</p>\n<p>If <em>light </em>and <em>darkness </em>overlap, they create a patch of @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Illumination]{Dim light} (&minus;2).</p>\n<p><strong>Helpful Links:</strong> @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Using Magic]{Using Magic} - <h3 class=\"red-label\">@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.4 Power Modifiers]{Modifiers}</p>\n<h3>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Power Modifiers]{Modifiers}</h3>\n<ul class=\"red-bullet-list\">\n<li class=\"star\"><strong>Area Effect (+2): </strong>The <em>light</em> expands to the caster&rsquo;s @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Traits]{Smarts} in radius, with a Range of @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Traits]{Smarts} &times;2. The light is sunlight and has the same effect on certain creatures (such as vampires) as natural sunlight.</li>\n<li class=\"star\"><strong>True Darkness (+2):</strong> The <em>darkness</em> blocks @Compendium[savage-eberron-bestiary.savage-eberron-bestiary-abilities.Infravision]{Infravision}, @Compendium[savage-eberron-bestiary.savage-eberron-bestiary-abilities.Low Light Vision]{Low Light Vision}, and @Compendium[savage-eberron-bestiary.savage-eberron-bestiary-abilities.Darkvision]{Darkvision}. It has no effect on magical sight such as <em>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Detect/Conceal Arcana]{detect arcana}</em>.</li>\n<li><strong>Mobile (+1):</strong> The caster can move the area of effect up to his @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Arcane Backgrounds]{arcane skill} die type each @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Actions]{round} after casting, or attach it to an inanimate object when first cast. </li>\n</ul>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"equippable":false,"equipped":true,"actions":{"skill":"Performance","skillMod":"","dmgMod":"","additional":{}},"rank":"Novice","pp":"2","damage":"","range":"Smarts","duration":"10 minutes","trapping":"Illusionary torch, sunlight, darkness, thick fogs","arcane":"Gnome Magic","skill":"","modifiers":[]},"effects":[],"folder":"8NyF3ZLDhkqHw0IP","sort":2300000,"permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"flags":{"cf":null,"journal-links":{},"core":{"sourceId":"Item.gEg0cmKVXZN0LEYt"}}},{"_id":"LOOuzkdblxBCfEXu","name":"Sound (Cantrips Only)","type":"power","img":"icons/magic/sonic/scream-wail-shout-teal.webp","data":{"description":"<div class=\"sweb-core\">\n<p><strong>School: </strong>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Schools of Magic]{Illusion}</p>\n<p><em>Sound </em>mimics any known sound or voice, emanating from a point of origin within @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Range]{Range} at a volume up to the sound of a loud shout. If used as a @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Test]{Test}, the defender @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Trait Rolls]{opposes} the casting roll with @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Traits]{Smarts}.</p>\n<p><em>Silence </em>does the opposite, muting all sound up to a loud shout within a @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Area Effect Attacks]{Large Blast Template}. This subtracts 4 from @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Notice]{Notice} rolls made by those inside the area of effect, as well as anyone trying to hear sounds made from within. A @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Raises]{raise} completely mutes all sound inside the template&mdash;such @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Notice]{Notice} rolls automatically fail.</p>\n<p><strong>Helpful Links:</strong> @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Using Magic]{Using Magic} - <h3 class=\"red-label\">@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.4 Power Modifiers]{Modifiers}</p>\n<h3>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Power Modifiers]{Modifiers}</h3>\n<ul class=\"red-bullet-list\">\n<li><strong>Greater Sound/Silence</strong><strong> (+1):</strong> The @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Traits]{Smarts} roll made to resist a @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Test]{Test} (or Targeted modifier) is made at &minus;2.</li>\n<li><strong>Mobile (+1):</strong> The caster can move the area of effect up to his @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Arcane Backgrounds]{arcane skill} die type each @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Actions]{round}.</li>\n<li><strong>Targeted (+0):</strong> Instead of casting <em>silence </em>in an @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Area Effect Attacks]{area of effect}, the caster may instead target individuals in @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Range]{Range} for 1 @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Arcane Backgrounds]{Power Point} each. Unwilling targets resist with @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Traits]{Spirit} (at &minus;2 if the caster gets a @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Raises]{raise}).</li>\n</ul>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"equippable":false,"equipped":true,"actions":{"skill":"Performance","skillMod":"","dmgMod":"","additional":{}},"rank":"Novice","pp":"1","damage":"","range":"Smarts ×5 (sound); Smarts (silence)","duration":"Instant (sound); 5 (silence)","trapping":"Magical effects, a brief ripple in the air, a bell or chime that starts or stops ringing","arcane":"Gnome Magic","skill":"","modifiers":[]},"effects":[],"folder":"8NyF3ZLDhkqHw0IP","sort":3500000,"permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"flags":{"cf":null,"journal-links":{},"core":{"sourceId":"Item.2XWZLvwndmibm5gP"}}},{"_id":"6LgnGbY7UalTaPqv","name":"Mage Hand (Cantrips Only)","type":"power","img":"icons/magic/light/hand-sparks-smoke-green.webp","data":{"description":"<div class=\"sweb-core\">\n<p><strong>School: </strong>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Schools of Magic]{Transmutation}</p>\n<p><em>Telekinesis </em>is the ability to move objects or creatures (including oneself) with arcane will. It has a @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Traits]{Strength} of d10, or d12 with a raise.</p>\n<p>Unwilling opponents resist the caster&rsquo;s @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Arcane Backgrounds]{arcane skill} with an @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Trait Rolls]{opposed} @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Traits]{Spirit} roll when targeted and at the start of each of their @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Actions]{turns} afterward until they&rsquo;re released. They can be moved up to the caster&rsquo; @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Traits]{Smarts} per turn in any direction, and can be bashed into walls, ceilings, or other obstacles for Str+d6 @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Dealing Damage]{damage}.</p>\n<p>Dropped creatures suffer @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Falling]{falling damage} as usual.</p>\n<p><strong>Telekinetic Tools</strong>: A caster can wield tools (including weapons) with <em>telekinesis </em>as an action. Use the caster&rsquo;s relevant @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Traits]{skill} when attacking in this way (not his @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Arcane Backgrounds]{arcane skill}).</p>\n<p><strong>Helpful Links:</strong> @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Using Magic]{Using Magic} - <h3 class=\"red-label\">@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.4 Power Modifiers]{Modifiers}</p>\n<h3>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Power Modifiers]{Modifiers}</h3>\n<ul class=\"red-bullet-list\">\n<li class=\"star\"><strong>Power (+3): </strong>The Strength of telekinesis is d12, or d12 + 2 with a @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Raises]{raise}. Objects weighing 1,000 pounds or more automatically deal @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Heavy Weapon (HW)]{Heavy} @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Dealing Damage]{Damage} when used as weapons.</li>\n</ul>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"equippable":false,"equipped":true,"actions":{"skill":"Performance","skillMod":"","dmgMod":"","additional":{}},"rank":"Seasoned","pp":"5","damage":"","range":"Smarts x2","duration":"5","trapping":"A wave of the hand, magic wand, steely gaze","arcane":"Gnome Magic","skill":"","modifiers":[]},"effects":[],"folder":"ISCYYNpA2xp2iRN8","sort":100001,"permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"flags":{"cf":null,"journal-links":{},"core":{"sourceId":"Item.KLsRF4Gf0QBakUZu"}}},{"_id":"JQ5qQ1ibkZZqIIEf","name":"Beast Friend (Cantrips Only)","type":"power","img":"icons/environment/creatures/horses.webp","data":{"description":"<div class=\"sweb-core\">\n<p><strong>School: </strong>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Schools of Magic]{Enchantment}</p>\n<p>This spell allows an individual to speak with and guide the actions of nature&rsquo;s beasts. The cost to cast is equal to the sum of their @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Size and Scale]{Size} (minimum 1 per creature). Controlling five @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-bestiary.Dog / Wolf]{wolves} (Size &minus;1) costs 5 points (remember the minimum cost of 1), for example. Controlling a rhino (Size 5) costs 5 points.</p>\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Trait Rolls]{Success} means the creatures obey simple commands, like a well-trained dog. They attack foes and endanger their lives for their master. A @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Raises]{raise} on the arcane skill roll means the beasts are more obedient. They won&rsquo;t kill themselves but overcome their natural fears to follow their orders.</p>\n<p>@Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-bestiary.Swarm]{Swarms} can also be controlled. Small Swarms cost 1 point, Medium Swarms cost 2, and Large Swarms cost 3.</p>\n<p><em> Beast friend</em> works only on natural creatures with animal intelligence, not humanoids, and has no effect on conjured, magical, or otherwise &ldquo;unnatural&rdquo; animals.</p>\n<p><strong>Helpful Links:</strong> @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Using Magic]{Using Magic} - <h3 class=\"red-label\">@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.4 Power Modifiers]{Modifiers}</p>\n<h3>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Power Modifiers]{Modifiers}</h3>\n<ul class=\"red-bullet-list\">\n<li class=\"star\"><strong>Bestiarium (+2):</strong> The caster may affect magical and mythical beasts with animal intelligence.</li>\n<li><strong>Duration (+1):</strong> The base Duration increases to 30 minutes per rank.</li>\n<li><strong>Mind Rider (+1):</strong> The caster can communicate and sense through any of the beasts they've befriended.</li>\n</ul>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"equippable":false,"equipped":true,"actions":{"skill":"Performance","skillMod":"","dmgMod":"","additional":{}},"rank":"Novice","pp":"Special","damage":"","range":"Smarts","duration":"10 minutes","trapping":"The caster concentrates and gestures with his hands.","arcane":"Gnome Magic","skill":"","modifiers":[]},"effects":[],"folder":"8NyF3ZLDhkqHw0IP","sort":400000,"permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"flags":{"cf":null,"journal-links":{},"core":{"sourceId":"Item.YL9RGHSkkkLJEF2f"}}},{"_id":"xYBLzjuJIOtAZQFx","name":"Dirge of Haunting","type":"power","img":"icons/creatures/magical/spirit-fear-energy-pink.webp","data":{"description":"<div class=\"sweb-core\">\n<p><strong>School: </strong>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Schools of Magic]{Necromancy}</p>\n<p>This power causes overwhelming dread and horror. The target makes a @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Fear]{Fear} roll. @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Wild Cards and Extras]{Extras} who fail are @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-tables.Fear Table]{Panicked} and @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Wild Cards and Extras]{Wild Cards} roll on the @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-macros.Fear Table]{Fear Table}. If the power is cast with a raise, the Fear roll is at &minus;2 and Wild Cards add +2 to @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-macros.Fear Table]{Fear Table} results.</p>\n<p><strong>Helpful Links:</strong> @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Using Magic]{Using Magic} - <h3 class=\"red-label\">@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.4 Power Modifiers]{Modifiers}</p>\n<h3>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Power Modifiers]{Modifiers}</h3>\n<ul class=\"red-bullet-list\">\n<li><strong>Area of Effect (+2/+3):</strong> For +2 @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Arcane Backgrounds]{Power Points} the power affects everyone in a @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Area Effect Attacks]{Small} or @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Area Effect Attacks]{Medium Blast Template}. For +3 points the area of effect is increased to a @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Area Effect Attacks]{Large Blast Template}.</li>\n<li class=\"star\"><strong>Greater Fear (+2): </strong>Fear rolls are made at&minus;2, or &minus;4 if cast with a @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Raises]{raise}.</li>\n</ul>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"equippable":false,"equipped":true,"actions":{"skill":"Performance","skillMod":"","dmgMod":"","additional":{}},"rank":"Novice","pp":"2","damage":"","range":"Smarts","duration":"Instant","trapping":"Haunting, grating song.","arcane":"Bard","skill":"","modifiers":[]},"effects":[],"folder":"8NyF3ZLDhkqHw0IP","sort":1800000,"permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"flags":{"cf":null,"journal-links":{},"core":{"sourceId":"Item.RkKW0hhkT9E7bK1C"}}},{"_id":"1YgjVPecCPKIlsRR","name":"Hideous Laughter","type":"power","img":"icons/magic/symbols/question-stone-yellow.webp","data":{"description":"<div class=\"sweb-core\">\n<p><strong>School: </strong>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Schools of Magic]{Enchantment}</p>\n<p><em>Confusion </em>confounds all targets in a @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Area Effect Attacks]{Medium Blast Template}, making them either @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Distracted and Vulnerable]{Distracted or Vulnerable}, or both with a @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Raises]{raise}. The same effect applies to all those affected. These states are removed at the end of the victims&rsquo; next turn as usual.</p>\n<p><strong>Helpful Links:</strong> @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Using Magic]{Using Magic} - <h3 class=\"red-label\">@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.4 Power Modifiers]{Modifiers}</p>\n<h3>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Power Modifiers]{Modifiers}</h3>\n<ul class=\"red-bullet-list\">\n<li><strong>Area of Effect (+0/+1):</strong>The caster can focus the <em>confusion </em>to a @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Area Effect Attacks]{Small Blast Template} for no extra cost, or a @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Area Effect Attacks]{Large Blast Template} for +1.</li>\n<li><strong>★ Greater Confusion (+2):</strong> On a success, targets are @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Damage Effects]{Shaken} in addition to being @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Distracted and Vulnerable]{Distracted} or @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Distracted and Vulnerable]{Vulnerable} (or both with a @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Raises]{raise}). <em>Confusion </em>is a non-damaging effect and cannot cause a @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Damage Effects]{Wound} on an already @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Damage Effects]{Shaken} target.</li>\n</ul>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"equippable":false,"equipped":true,"actions":{"skill":"Performance","skillMod":"","dmgMod":"","additional":{}},"rank":"Novice","pp":"2","damage":"","range":"Smarts","duration":"Instant","trapping":"Upbeat song that causes laughter.","arcane":"Bard","skill":"","modifiers":[]},"effects":[],"folder":"8NyF3ZLDhkqHw0IP","sort":1000000,"permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"flags":{"cf":null,"journal-links":{},"core":{"sourceId":"Item.fffVpphTGKxBvT6q"}}},{"_id":"nZR8GLqsdKIALaN6","name":"Sleep","type":"power","img":"icons/magic/control/sleep-bubble-purple.webp","data":{"description":"<div class=\"sweb-core\">\n<p><strong>School: </strong>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Schools of Magic]{Enchantment}</p>\n<p>Those who favor stealth or want to avoid harming their foes are drawn to this spell, which puts its victims into a deep and restful sleep.</p>\n<p>Anyone affected by <em>slumber </em>must make a @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Traits]{Spirit} roll (at &minus;2 if the caster got a raise on her @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Arcane Backgrounds]{arcane skill} roll). Those who fail fall asleep for the @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Powers]{Duration} of the spell. Very loud noises or attempts to physically wake a sleeper (by shaking him, for example), grant another @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Traits]{Spirit} roll.</p>\n<p><strong>Helpful Links:</strong> @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Using Magic]{Using Magic} - <h3 class=\"red-label\">@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.4 Power Modifiers]{Modifiers}</p>\n<h3>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Power Modifiers]{Modifiers}</h3>\n<ul class=\"red-bullet-list\">\n<li><strong>Area of Effect (+2/+3):</strong> For +2 points the power affects everyone in a @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Area Effect Attacks]{Medium Blast Template}. For +3 points the area of effect is increased to a @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Area Effect Attacks]{Large Blast Template}.</li>\n</ul>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"equippable":false,"equipped":true,"actions":{"skill":"Performance","skillMod":"","dmgMod":"","additional":{}},"rank":"Seasoned","pp":"2","damage":"","range":"Smarts","duration":"One hour","trapping":"A lullaby","arcane":"Bard","skill":"","modifiers":[]},"effects":[],"folder":"ISCYYNpA2xp2iRN8","sort":100001,"permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"flags":{"cf":null,"journal-links":{},"core":{"sourceId":"Item.5bw0RKYgOReACsnM"}}},{"_id":"NOdveTlTfgwoTRRT","name":"Cane, Sword","type":"weapon","img":"icons/weapons/staves/staff-orb-feather.webp","data":{"description":"<div class=\"sweb-core\">\n<p>At first glance, a sword cane looks like an ordinary walking cane often decorated and carved.</p>\n<p>It is difficult to tell that a sword cane is a weapon. An observer has to study the cane's owner carefully, making a successful @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Notice]{Notice} roll at &ndash;2 (or at no penalty if the observer has the @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Danger Sense]{Danger Sense} Edge) to discern that the cane is dangerous in his hands. The wielder can make a @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Persuasion]{Persuasion} roll or @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Stealth]{Stealth} roll to avoid giving away his proficiency.</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"quantity":1,"weight":1,"price":15,"equippable":false,"equipped":true,"isVehicular":false,"mods":1,"actions":{"skill":"Fighting","skillMod":"+1","dmgMod":"","additional":{}},"damage":"@str+d6","range":"","rof":"1","ap":"0","minStr":"d6","shots":"0","currentShots":"0","ammo":"","autoReload":false},"effects":[],"folder":"tnIhNgfhxgoXoVDh","sort":200001,"permission":{"default":0,"ZvqefCj0L7TxJS56":3,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"flags":{"journal-links":{},"core":{"sourceId":"Item.QLPZVwdHPYs6Arx6"}}},{"_id":"K17UQBuvOJAiHwnd","name":"Trademark Weapon (Sword Cane)","type":"edge","img":"icons/environment/people/charge.webp","data":{"description":"<div class=\"sweb-core\">\n<p>The hero knows one unique weapon (Excalibur, Old Betsy, Sting) like the back of his hand. When using it, he adds +1 to his @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Athletics]{Athletics} (throwing), @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Fighting]{Fighting}, or @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Shooting]{Shooting} rolls, and +1 to @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Characters]{Parry} when readied (even if it&rsquo;s a ranged weapon).</span></p>\n<p>A fighter can take this Edge multiple times, applying it to a different weapon each time. If a Trademark Weapon is lost, he can replace it but the benefits don&rsquo;t kick in for a few days (however long the GM feels is dramatically appropriate).</span></p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Novice, skill with chosen weapon of d8+"}},"effects":[{"_id":"viA65GSpKV0IFwsX","changes":[{"key":"data.stats.parry.value","mode":2,"value":"1"}],"disabled":false,"duration":{"startTime":null},"icon":"icons/environment/people/charge.webp","label":"Trademark Readied Weapon","transfer":true,"flags":{},"tint":null}],"folder":"hsEO07bFB8oM1LJo","sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"3HvtK4sMp7flYKmT":3,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"flags":{"cf":null,"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.swade-core-rules.swade-edges.QHBtO0jmIzfl8TDE"}}},{"_id":"dsCHatrzLODMx6Fg","name":"Low Light Vision","type":"ability","img":"icons/creatures/eyes/human-single-brown.webp","data":{"description":"<div class=\"sweb-core\">\n<p>Low Light Vision ignores up &ndash;2 penalties for @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Illumination]{Dim and Dark Illumination}. @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Illumination]{Pitch Darkness} remains unaffected.</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"subtype":"special","grantsPowers":false},"effects":[],"folder":"kFghWjY7gP7MEqav","sort":100001,"permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"flags":{"journal-links":{},"core":{"sourceId":"Item.OL3T8otZVCkOoir3"}}},{"_id":"C84DIQsyGijZCyHU","name":"Language (Gnomish)","type":"skill","img":"icons/sundries/documents/document-letter-formal-tan.webp","data":{"description":"<div class=\"sweb-core\">\n<p>In some settings, such as those that focus on pulp action or &ldquo;planetary romance&rdquo; (where characters frequently travel among many strange civilizations), speaking various languages can simply be roleplayed with halting dialogue and campy accents that start out a little difficult and are quickly forgotten. The GM may ignore this skill altogether in these settings, or use the @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Multiple Languages]{Multiple Languages} &shy;option in the @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Setting Rules]{Setting Rules}.</p>\n<p>In more realistic settings, communication can be a major barrier that requires characters to put skill points into additional languages. In a 1980s World War Three game, for example, a group of United Nations paratroopers won&rsquo;t be able to speak with their foes unless they take Russian, Polish, or other languages common to the Warsaw Pact.</p>\n<p>If the Language skill is in use, it should be listed as Language (Spanish), Language (American Sign Language), etc. A character&rsquo;s die type also notes how fluent he is in it. (Characters start with a d8 in their own Language.)</p>\n<div class=\"sweb-core\">\n<table class=\"table value-table\"><caption class=\"table-caption\">\n<h2 class=\"table-title\">Language Proficiency</h2>\n</caption>\n<tbody>\n<tr class=\"table-header-row\">\n<th class=\"table-column-header\" scope=\"col\">Skill</th>\n<th class=\"table-column-header\" scope=\"col\">Ability</th>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td>d4</td>\n<td>The character can read, write and speak common words and phrases.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>d6</td>\n<td>The speaker can carry on a prolonged but occasionally halting conversation.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>d8</td>\n<td>The character can speak fluently.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>d10</td>\n<td>The hero can mimic other dialects within the language.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>d12</td>\n<td>The speaker can masterfully recite important literary or oral works.</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>\n</div>\n<p><strong>Limited: </strong>Use whichever skill is lowest when performing an action that requires knowledge of a foreign language. @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Intimidation]{Intimidation} (if verbal), @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Persuasion]{Persuasion}, @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Research]{Research}, @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Taunt]{Taunt}, etc., are all limited by the character&rsquo;s Language skill.</p>\n<p>This limitation never applies to a character&rsquo;s native tongue.</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"attribute":"smarts","isCoreSkill":false,"die":{"sides":8,"modifier":0},"wild-die":{"sides":6}},"effects":[],"folder":"UUZJk5Z5jpjqw5rC","sort":300000,"permission":{"default":0,"3HvtK4sMp7flYKmT":3,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_nsugutrpau","path":"Skills","color":"#8c160f"},"journal-links":{},"core":{"sourceId":"Item.udHxlHKPSrGG5QjZ"}}},{"_id":"lKqp3CXbisb5umX6","name":"Language (Halfling)","type":"skill","img":"icons/sundries/documents/document-letter-formal-tan.webp","data":{"description":"<div class=\"sweb-core\">\n<p>In some settings, such as those that focus on pulp action or &ldquo;planetary romance&rdquo; (where characters frequently travel among many strange civilizations), speaking various languages can simply be roleplayed with halting dialogue and campy accents that start out a little difficult and are quickly forgotten. The GM may ignore this skill altogether in these settings, or use the @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Multiple Languages]{Multiple Languages} &shy;option in the @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Setting Rules]{Setting Rules}.</p>\n<p>In more realistic settings, communication can be a major barrier that requires characters to put skill points into additional languages. In a 1980s World War Three game, for example, a group of United Nations paratroopers won&rsquo;t be able to speak with their foes unless they take Russian, Polish, or other languages common to the Warsaw Pact.</p>\n<p>If the Language skill is in use, it should be listed as Language (Spanish), Language (American Sign Language), etc. A character&rsquo;s die type also notes how fluent he is in it. (Characters start with a d8 in their own Language.)</p>\n<div class=\"sweb-core\">\n<table class=\"table value-table\"><caption class=\"table-caption\">\n<h2 class=\"table-title\">Language Proficiency</h2>\n</caption>\n<tbody>\n<tr class=\"table-header-row\">\n<th class=\"table-column-header\" scope=\"col\">Skill</th>\n<th class=\"table-column-header\" scope=\"col\">Ability</th>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td>d4</td>\n<td>The character can read, write and speak common words and phrases.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>d6</td>\n<td>The speaker can carry on a prolonged but occasionally halting conversation.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>d8</td>\n<td>The character can speak fluently.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>d10</td>\n<td>The hero can mimic other dialects within the language.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>d12</td>\n<td>The speaker can masterfully recite important literary or oral works.</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>\n</div>\n<p><strong>Limited: </strong>Use whichever skill is lowest when performing an action that requires knowledge of a foreign language. @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Intimidation]{Intimidation} (if verbal), @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Persuasion]{Persuasion}, @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Research]{Research}, @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Taunt]{Taunt}, etc., are all limited by the character&rsquo;s Language skill.</p>\n<p>This limitation never applies to a character&rsquo;s native tongue.</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"attribute":"smarts","isCoreSkill":false,"die":{"sides":6,"modifier":0},"wild-die":{"sides":6}},"effects":[],"folder":"RXzRwNmHRkixYrfR","sort":300000,"permission":{"default":0,"3HvtK4sMp7flYKmT":3,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_nsugutrpau","path":"Skills","color":"#8c160f"},"journal-links":{},"core":{"sourceId":"Item.EYk5HsLk3sstMnmu"}}},{"_id":"Zf7bj6kuiPjdeUyO","name":"Language (Sylvan)","type":"skill","img":"icons/sundries/documents/document-letter-formal-tan.webp","data":{"description":"<div class=\"sweb-core\">\n<p>In some settings, such as those that focus on pulp action or &ldquo;planetary romance&rdquo; (where characters frequently travel among many strange civilizations), speaking various languages can simply be roleplayed with halting dialogue and campy accents that start out a little difficult and are quickly forgotten. The GM may ignore this skill altogether in these settings, or use the @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Multiple Languages]{Multiple Languages} &shy;option in the @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Setting Rules]{Setting Rules}.</p>\n<p>In more realistic settings, communication can be a major barrier that requires characters to put skill points into additional languages. In a 1980s World War Three game, for example, a group of United Nations paratroopers won&rsquo;t be able to speak with their foes unless they take Russian, Polish, or other languages common to the Warsaw Pact.</p>\n<p>If the Language skill is in use, it should be listed as Language (Spanish), Language (American Sign Language), etc. A character&rsquo;s die type also notes how fluent he is in it. (Characters start with a d8 in their own Language.)</p>\n<div class=\"sweb-core\">\n<table class=\"table value-table\"><caption class=\"table-caption\">\n<h2 class=\"table-title\">Language Proficiency</h2>\n</caption>\n<tbody>\n<tr class=\"table-header-row\">\n<th class=\"table-column-header\" scope=\"col\">Skill</th>\n<th class=\"table-column-header\" scope=\"col\">Ability</th>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td>d4</td>\n<td>The character can read, write and speak common words and phrases.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>d6</td>\n<td>The speaker can carry on a prolonged but occasionally halting conversation.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>d8</td>\n<td>The character can speak fluently.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>d10</td>\n<td>The hero can mimic other dialects within the language.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>d12</td>\n<td>The speaker can masterfully recite important literary or oral works.</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>\n</div>\n<p><strong>Limited: </strong>Use whichever skill is lowest when performing an action that requires knowledge of a foreign language. @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Intimidation]{Intimidation} (if verbal), @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Persuasion]{Persuasion}, @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Research]{Research}, @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Taunt]{Taunt}, etc., are all limited by the character&rsquo;s Language skill.</p>\n<p>This limitation never applies to a character&rsquo;s native tongue.</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"attribute":"smarts","isCoreSkill":false,"die":{"sides":6,"modifier":0},"wild-die":{"sides":6}},"effects":[],"folder":"cgfmurTJRwbCvmCc","sort":2200001,"permission":{"default":0,"3HvtK4sMp7flYKmT":3,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_qals24wpyph","path":"Skills","color":"#8c160f"},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.swade-core-rules.swade-skills.XIuR2IyQtewm5BZP"}}},{"_id":"sMQJqYunmrAYzP5A","name":"Lore","type":"skill","img":"icons/sundries/books/book-stack.webp","data":{"description":"<div class=\"sweb-core\">\n<p>Lore reflects knowledge and your ability to recall bits of information about history, archaeology, different Ages, legends, other continents, literature, song, poetry, and similar fields. This would also include knowledge about the more common races of the worlds.</p>\n<p>If an explorer wants to remember when the Dhakaani empire collapsed or know when the Qualabrin were destroyed on Xen'drik, this is the skill to have.</p>\n<p>A successful Lore roll reveals basic information about a topic, and a raise grants more details.</p>\n<p><em><strong>Source: Savage Eberron replaces Academics</strong></em></p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"attribute":"smarts","isCoreSkill":false,"die":{"sides":6,"modifier":0},"wild-die":{"sides":6}},"effects":[],"folder":"cgfmurTJRwbCvmCc","sort":700001,"permission":{"default":0,"ZvqefCj0L7TxJS56":3,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"flags":{"journal-links":{},"core":{"sourceId":"Item.E0BVumGwbaczoPjD"}}},{"_id":"dYfnkLV74q9n4eVu","name":"Arrogant","type":"hindrance","img":"icons/magic/holy/yin-yang-balance-symbol.webp","data":{"description":"<div class=\"sweb-core\"><p>Your hero doesn&rsquo;t think he&rsquo;s the best&mdash;he knows he is. Whether it&rsquo;s swordsmanship, kung fu, or painting, few compare to his skills and he flaunts it every chance he gets. Winning isn&rsquo;t enough for this champion. He wants to dominate his opponent and prove there&rsquo;s no one better. He&rsquo;s the kind of fighter who disarms an opponent in a duel just to pick the sword up and hand it back with a smirk. Arrogant individuals look for the greatest threat in battle, hacking their way through lesser minions only because they&rsquo;re in the way.</span></p></div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"major":true},"effects":[],"folder":"1updrtPaYhKD0fRY","sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"3HvtK4sMp7flYKmT":3,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"flags":{"cf":null,"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.swade-core-rules.swade-hindrances.YpLBVlqcaIEy8oYq"}}},{"_id":"4NfflUuJjZQ7zehu","name":"Quirk (Womanizer)","type":"hindrance","img":"icons/magic/holy/yin-yang-balance-symbol.webp","data":{"description":"<div class=\"sweb-core\"><p>This individual has some minor foible that is usually humorous but can occasionally cause him real trouble. A swashbuckler may always try to slash his initials on his foes, a dwarf may brag constantly about his culture, or a snobby d&eacute;butante might not eat, drink, or socialize with the lower class, for example.</span></p></div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"major":false},"effects":[],"folder":"1updrtPaYhKD0fRY","sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"3HvtK4sMp7flYKmT":3,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"flags":{"cf":null,"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.swade-core-rules.swade-hindrances.y0lUBhYHhl2LdjZZ"}}},{"_id":"qT0juD8PKGanAQyc","name":"Deception","type":"skill","img":"icons/skills/toxins/poison-skull-herbs-bottle-pink.webp","data":{"description":"<div class=\"sweb-core\">\n<p>Deception determines whether the hero can convincingly hide the truth, either verbally or through her actions. This deception can encompass everything from misleading others through ambiguity to telling outright lies.</p>\n<p>Typical situations include trying to fast-talk a guard, con a merchant, dull someone's suspicions with false assurances, or maintain a straight face while telling a blatant lie.</p>\n<p>Usually, a character successfully passing herself off in a disguise, or trying to impersonate the sound of someone else's voice would be a @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Performance]{Performance} check rather than a deception check. </p>\n<p><em><strong>Source: Savage Eberron</strong></em></p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"attribute":"spirit","isCoreSkill":false,"die":{"sides":6,"modifier":0},"wild-die":{"sides":6}},"effects":[],"folder":"cgfmurTJRwbCvmCc","sort":700001,"permission":{"default":0,"ZvqefCj0L7TxJS56":3,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"flags":{"journal-links":{},"core":{"sourceId":"Item.E0BVumGwbaczoPjD"}}}],"effects":[{"_id":"JWzHw9SU5Y4zNRJV","changes":[{"key":"data.stats.parry.value","mode":2,"value":"1"}],"disabled":true,"duration":{"startTime":28973116800},"icon":"icons/environment/people/charge.webp","label":"Trademark Readied Weapon","origin":"Actor.sLKblh4aPfMgTnut.Item.K17UQBuvOJAiHwnd","tint":null,"transfer":false,"flags":{}}],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_3a04s0jrz4j","path":"Pirates of Cyre Bestiary#/CF_SEP/NPC's","color":"#000000"}}}
{"_id":"56twwTP4lR2skY8E","name":"Crewmember","type":"npc","img":"https://assets.forge-vtt.com/5f43f8ea1a91d63438d13159/tokens/characters/nautical/token_2218.png","data":{"attributes":{"agility":{"die":{"sides":6,"modifier":0},"wild-die":{"sides":6}},"smarts":{"die":{"sides":4,"modifier":0},"wild-die":{"sides":6},"animal":false},"spirit":{"die":{"sides":6,"modifier":0},"wild-die":{"sides":6},"unShakeBonus":0},"strength":{"die":{"sides":6,"modifier":0},"wild-die":{"sides":6},"encumbranceSteps":0},"vigor":{"die":{"sides":6,"modifier":0},"wild-die":{"sides":6}}},"stats":{"speed":{"runningDie":6,"runningMod":0,"value":6},"toughness":{"value":0,"armor":0,"modifier":0},"parry":{"value":5,"modifier":0},"size":0},"details":{"biography":{"value":"<div class=\"sweb-core\">\n<p>Shipmates are ordinary sailors, the rank-and-file deckhands who keep any vessel, great or small, afloat and moving. They are alert for danger and quick on their feet, weathered by wind and wave and sun, but always with an eye for what waits beyond the horizon.</p>\n<p>Shipmates can be used as low-level marines, rivermen, bargefolk, or even swamp rats living in stilt-houses.</p>\n</div>"},"species":{"name":""},"currency":500,"wealth":{"die":6,"modifier":0,"wild-die":6},"conviction":{"value":0,"active":false},"autoCalcToughness":true,"autoCalcParry":true},"powerPoints":{},"fatigue":{"value":0,"min":0,"max":2},"wounds":{"value":0,"min":0,"max":0,"ignored":0},"advances":{"value":0,"rank":"Novice","details":""},"bennies":{"value":2,"max":2},"status":{"isShaken":false,"isDistracted":false,"isVulnerable":false,"isStunned":false,"isEntangled":false,"isBound":false},"initiative":{"hasHesitant":false,"hasLevelHeaded":false,"hasImpLevelHeaded":false,"hasQuick":false},"additionalStats":{},"wildcard":false},"token":{"flags":{"perfect-vision":{"visionRules":"default","monoVisionColor":"","sightLimit":null}},"name":"Pirate","displayName":30,"img":"https://assets.forge-vtt.com/5f43f8ea1a91d63438d13159/tokens/characters/nautical/token_*.png","tint":null,"width":1,"height":1,"scale":1,"mirrorX":false,"mirrorY":false,"lockRotation":false,"rotation":0,"vision":true,"dimSight":0,"brightSight":0,"dimLight":0,"brightLight":0,"sightAngle":0,"lightAngle":0,"lightColor":null,"lightAlpha":1,"lightAnimation":{"speed":5,"intensity":5},"actorId":null,"actorLink":false,"disposition":0,"displayBars":0,"bar1":{"attribute":""},"bar2":{"attribute":""},"randomImg":true,"alpha":1,"x":null,"y":null,"elevation":null},"items":[{"_id":"g51OdceqBLOvsYIZ","name":"Untrained","type":"skill","data":{"description":"<div class=\"sweb-core\">\n<p>If a character doesn&rsquo;t have a skill for an action he&rsquo;s attempting, he rolls a d4 for his skill die (and a Wild Die if a @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Wild Cards and Extras]{Wild Card}) and subtracts 2 from the total.</p>\n<p>The GM may decide certain tasks cannot be attempted unskilled, such as performing complex surgery or flying a commercial jet.</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"attribute":"agility","isCoreSkill":false,"die":{"sides":4,"modifier":"-2"},"wild-die":{"sides":6}},"sort":100000,"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_nsugutrpau","path":"Skills","color":"#8c160f"},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.swade-core-rules.swade-skills.zcn1epcU4FEJGGyI"}},"img":"icons/magic/symbols/question-stone-yellow.webp","effects":[],"folder":null,"permission":{"default":0}},{"_id":"LAGjXeGIlviM5MXX","name":"Athletics","type":"skill","data":{"description":"<div class=\"sweb-core\">\n<p>Athletics combines an individual&rsquo;s coordin&shy;ation with learned skills such as climbing, jumping, balancing, biking, wrestling, skiing, swimming, throwing, or catching. Characters who rely on physical power more than coordination can take the @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Brute]{Brute} Edge to link this skill to @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Traits]{Strength} instead of @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Traits]{Agility}.</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"attribute":"agility","isCoreSkill":false,"die":{"sides":6,"modifier":0},"wild-die":{"sides":6}},"sort":200000,"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_nsugutrpau","path":"Skills","color":"#8c160f"},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.swade-core-rules.swade-skills.Athletics"}},"img":"icons/magic/control/buff-strength-muscle-damage.webp","effects":[],"folder":null,"permission":{"default":0}},{"_id":"SHK9HItDWPN7ZPJN","name":"Notice","type":"skill","data":{"description":"<div class=\"sweb-core\">\n<p>Notice is a hero&rsquo;s general awareness and alertness. It&rsquo;s used to sense sights, sounds, tastes, and smells, spot clues, detect ambushes, spot hidden weapons on a foe, or tell if a rival is lying, frightened, happy, etc.</p>\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Trait Rolls]{Success} conveys basic information&mdash;the character hears movement in the forest, smells distant smoke, or senses someone isn&rsquo;t being completely truthful.</p>\n<p>A @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Raises]{raise} grants more detail, such as the direction of a sound or odor or what topic a person is avoiding or lying about.</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"attribute":"smarts","isCoreSkill":false,"die":{"sides":6,"modifier":0},"wild-die":{"sides":6}},"sort":300000,"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_nsugutrpau","path":"Skills","color":"#8c160f"},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.swade-core-rules.swade-skills.ZvwjzMLxsneptV4T"}},"img":"icons/creatures/eyes/human-single-blue.webp","effects":[],"folder":null,"permission":{"default":0}},{"_id":"sRNLdF1QqG36IxQ8","name":"Stealth","type":"skill","data":{"description":"<div class=\"sweb-core\">\n<p>Stealth is the ability to hide and move quietly. A simple @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Trait Rolls]{success} on a Stealth roll means the character avoids detection if enemies aren&rsquo;t particularly alert. If the character @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Trait Rolls]{fails} the roll, the enemy realizes something is amiss and begins actively searching for whatever roused them.</p>\n<p>Once foes are alerted and active, Stealth is opposed by @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Notice]{Notice} (a @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Trait Rolls]{group roll} if there are many foes.</p>\n<p>The GM should apply any circumstantial penalties to @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Notice]{Notice} rolls for @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Illumination]{darkness}, @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Cover and Obstacles]{cover}, noise, distractions, and any difference in the target&rsquo;s @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Size and Scale]{Scale} (just like when attacking). Sneaking through dry leaves might subtract 2 from the Stealth roll, for example, while spotting someone in the dark uses the @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Illumination]{Illumination} penalty (&minus;4). Don&rsquo;t apply the same modifier to both rolls, however. If Stealth is at &minus;2 for the leaves, don&rsquo;t give Notice a +2 for them as well.</p>\n<p><strong>Sneak Attack: </strong> Sneaking up close enough to make a melee attack <em>always</em> requires an @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Trait Rolls]{opposed} Stealth roll versus the target&rsquo;s @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Notice]{Notice}, whether the guard is actively looking for trouble or not. If successful, the victim is @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Distracted and Vulnerable]{Vulnerable} to the attacker, but only until the attacker&rsquo;s turn ends. With a raise, the attacker has @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.The Drop]{The Drop} instead.</p>\n<p><strong>Movement:</strong> In combat, characters roll Stealth each turn as a @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Actions]{free action} at the end of their move or any action the GM thinks might draw attention.</p>\n<p>Out of combat, the distance moved depends entirely on the situation. The GM might want a roll every minute if the group is sneaking around the perimeter of a defensive position, or every few miles if they&rsquo;re trying to quietly walk the path through a dark forest without alerting the creatures that live there.</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"attribute":"agility","isCoreSkill":false,"die":{"sides":4,"modifier":0},"wild-die":{"sides":6}},"sort":400000,"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_nsugutrpau","path":"Skills","color":"#8c160f"},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.swade-core-rules.swade-skills.Stealth"}},"img":"icons/magic/nature/stealth-hide-eyes-green.webp","effects":[],"folder":null,"permission":{"default":0}},{"_id":"ZSTpfYVuyj30bPk4","name":"Fighting","type":"skill","data":{"description":"<div class=\"sweb-core\">\n<p>Fighting covers all hand-to-hand (melee) attacks, whether it&rsquo;s with fists, axes, laser swords, or martial arts. See @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Combat]{Chapter Three} for the combat rules and the various maneuvers a warrior might attempt.</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"attribute":"agility","isCoreSkill":false,"die":{"sides":6,"modifier":0},"wild-die":{"sides":6}},"sort":600000,"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_nsugutrpau","path":"Skills","color":"#8c160f"},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.swade-core-rules.swade-skills.Fighting"}},"img":"icons/skills/melee/hand-grip-sword-white-brown.webp","effects":[],"folder":null,"permission":{"default":0}},{"_id":"SFe8t0TKOWMe1koT","name":"Language (Common)","type":"skill","data":{"description":"<div class=\"sweb-core\">\n<p>In some settings, such as those that focus on pulp action or &ldquo;planetary romance&rdquo; (where characters frequently travel among many strange civilizations), speaking various languages can simply be roleplayed with halting dialogue and campy accents that start out a little difficult and are quickly forgotten. The GM may ignore this skill altogether in these settings, or use the @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Multiple Languages]{Multiple Languages} &shy;option in the @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Setting Rules]{Setting Rules}.</p>\n<p>In more realistic settings, communication can be a major barrier that requires characters to put skill points into additional languages. In a 1980s World War Three game, for example, a group of United Nations paratroopers won&rsquo;t be able to speak with their foes unless they take Russian, Polish, or other languages common to the Warsaw Pact.</p>\n<p>If the Language skill is in use, it should be listed as Language (Spanish), Language (American Sign Language), etc. A character&rsquo;s die type also notes how fluent he is in it. (Characters start with a d8 in their own Language.)</p>\n<div class=\"sweb-core\">\n<table class=\"table value-table\"><caption class=\"table-caption\">\n<h2 class=\"table-title\">Language Proficiency</h2>\n</caption>\n<tbody>\n<tr class=\"table-header-row\">\n<th class=\"table-column-header\" scope=\"col\">Skill</th>\n<th class=\"table-column-header\" scope=\"col\">Ability</th>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td>d4</td>\n<td>The character can read, write and speak common words and phrases.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>d6</td>\n<td>The speaker can carry on a prolonged but occasionally halting conversation.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>d8</td>\n<td>The character can speak fluently.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>d10</td>\n<td>The hero can mimic other dialects within the language.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>d12</td>\n<td>The speaker can masterfully recite important literary or oral works.</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>\n</div>\n<p><strong>Limited: </strong>Use whichever skill is lowest when performing an action that requires knowledge of a foreign language. @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Intimidation]{Intimidation} (if verbal), @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Persuasion]{Persuasion}, @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Research]{Research}, @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Taunt]{Taunt}, etc., are all limited by the character&rsquo;s Language skill.</p>\n<p>This limitation never applies to a character&rsquo;s native tongue.</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"attribute":"smarts","isCoreSkill":false,"die":{"sides":8,"modifier":"0"},"wild-die":{"sides":6}},"sort":700000,"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_nsugutrpau","path":"Skills","color":"#8c160f"},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.swade-core-rules.swade-skills.IoNMK5MtKODpwVjP"}},"img":"icons/sundries/documents/document-letter-formal-tan.webp","effects":[],"folder":null,"permission":{"default":0}},{"_id":"2wGuS0Zl5FyLJtOa","name":"Common Knowledge","type":"skill","data":{"description":"<div class=\"sweb-core\"><p>Characters roll Common Knowledge to know people, places, and things of their world, including etiquette, geography, culture, popular technology, contacts, and customs.</p></div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"attribute":"smarts","isCoreSkill":false,"die":{"sides":4,"modifier":0},"wild-die":{"sides":6}},"sort":800000,"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_nsugutrpau","path":"Skills","color":"#8c160f"},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.swade-core-rules.swade-skills.Common Knowledge"}},"img":"icons/sundries/documents/document-official-capital.webp","effects":[],"folder":null,"permission":{"default":0}},{"_id":"RBsOqQKi50j2VM4Q","name":"Persuasion","type":"skill","data":{"description":"<div class=\"sweb-core\">\n<p>Persuasion is the ability to convince others to do what you want through reason, cajoling, deception, rewards, or other friendly means. Persuasion isn&rsquo;t mind control. It can change someone&rsquo;s attitude but not their goals. A bandit may let you keep a sentimental piece of jewelry with a good Persuasion roll but still takes all your other goods.</p>\n<p>When used to @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Support]{Support} allies it&rsquo;s an unopposed roll. If the target is resistant, it&rsquo;s an @JournalEntry[JBxsGv2wAoAmoCDe]{opposed} roll vs. the target&rsquo;s @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Traits]{Spirit}. The GM should modify the roll as she sees fit based on roleplaying, any pertinent @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Edges]{Edges} or @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Hindrances]{Hindrances} that affect the conversation, and the circumstances.</p>\n<p><strong>Reaction Level:</strong> How much a person is willing to cooperate depends largely on their attitude toward whoever&rsquo;s talking to them. The Game Master can decide how nonplayer characters feel based on the setting, or roll on the @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-tables.Reaction Table]{Reaction Table} if she has no preconceived notions.</p>\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Trait Rolls]{Success} improves the target&rsquo;s attitude one level and a raise improves it two. Further increases aren&rsquo;t generally possible in the same encounter&mdash;it takes individuals a little time to adjust their biases.</p>\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Trait Rolls]{Failure} means the target won&rsquo;t change his mind this scene or until the situation changes in some important way. A @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Trait Rolls]{Critical Failure} also <em>reduces</em> the target&rsquo;s attitude two levels.</p>\n<p>Only one roll should generally be allowed per interaction unless new information is revealed, a substantial reward is offered, etc.</p>\n<p><strong>Networking: </strong>Characters can also use Persuasion as a &ldquo;macro skill,&rdquo; simulating a few hours or an evening&rsquo;s time hobnobbing and socializing to gain favors or information. See @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Networking]{Networking}.</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"attribute":"spirit","isCoreSkill":false,"die":{"sides":4,"modifier":0},"wild-die":{"sides":6}},"sort":1000000,"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_nsugutrpau","path":"Skills","color":"#8c160f"},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.swade-core-rules.swade-skills.Persuasion"}},"img":"icons/skills/social/diplomacy-handshake.webp","effects":[],"folder":null,"permission":{"default":0}},{"_id":"cwPBxwLZzL3RjNfi","name":"Shooting","type":"skill","data":{"description":"<div class=\"sweb-core\">\n<p>Shooting covers all attempts to hit a target with a ranged weapon such as a bow, pistol, or rocket launcher (thrown weapons use @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Athletics]{Athletics}). See @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Combat]{Chapter Three} for details on ranged combat.</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"attribute":"agility","isCoreSkill":false,"die":{"sides":4,"modifier":0},"wild-die":{"sides":6}},"sort":1100000,"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_nsugutrpau","path":"Skills","color":"#8c160f"},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.swade-core-rules.swade-skills.Shooting"}},"img":"icons/skills/ranged/target-bullseye-arrow-glowing.webp","effects":[],"folder":null,"permission":{"default":0}},{"_id":"RAsB5RnqXChEqKyD","name":"Boating","type":"skill","data":{"description":"<div class=\"sweb-core\"><p>Characters with this skill can handle most any boat or ship common to their setting. They also know how to handle common tasks associated with their vessel such as tying knots, rigging sails, or following currents.</p></div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"attribute":"agility","isCoreSkill":false,"die":{"sides":6,"modifier":0},"wild-die":{"sides":6}},"sort":2500000,"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_qals24wpyph","path":"Skills","color":"#8c160f"},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.swade-core-rules.swade-skills.WMWgIVDuAW4cHxj2"}},"img":"icons/environment/settlement/ship.webp","effects":[],"folder":null,"permission":{"default":0}},{"_id":"GFn2A0OT8af3Miye","name":"Repair","type":"skill","data":{"description":"<div class=\"sweb-core\">\n<p>Repair is the ability to craft, take apart and/or fix mechanical gadgets, vehicles, weapons, and constructs including warforged.</p>\n<p>How long a Repair roll takes is up to the DM and the complexity of the task. Success means the item is functional. A @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Raises]{raise} on the Repair roll halves the time required.</p>\n<p><strong>Constructs: </strong>Repair can be used in the @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Healing]{Healing} of warforged and other constructs @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Damage Effects]{Wounds}.</p>\n<p><strong>Crafting: </strong>Adventurers sometimes take time to create items from raw materials using appropriate tools. Creating an item requires appropriate raw materials costing half the item's total cost. Making something is usually resolved as an extended skill check, with each skill roll representing roughly a day's work, though this may be smaller for particularly simple jobs.</p>\n<p>The number of successes required and modifiers depend on the complexity, size, and cost of the item to be created, as well as the availability of suitable plans and tools. A critical failure on a skill roll means the work has been ruined and the raw materials wasted.</p>\n<p><strong>Tools:</strong> Characters suffer a minor penalty (&ndash;1 to &ndash;2) to their roll if they don't have access to basic tools, or a major penalty (&ndash;3 to &ndash;4) if the device requires specialized equipment.</p>\n<p><em><strong>Source: Modified for Savage Eberron</strong></em></p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"attribute":"smarts","isCoreSkill":false,"die":{"sides":4,"modifier":0},"wild-die":{"sides":6}},"sort":2600000,"flags":{"journal-links":{},"core":{"sourceId":"Item.VBAYsBHznEUKcaNv"},"cf":{"id":"temp_v8ypmxc2q0l","path":"Skills","color":"#008000"}},"img":"icons/skills/trades/smithing-tongs-metal-red.webp","effects":[],"folder":null,"permission":{"default":0}},{"_id":"iB16vP0AtkDyWqIF","name":"Baley Pin","type":"weapon","img":"icons/weapons/clubs/club-baton-blue.webp","data":{"description":"","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"quantity":1,"weight":2,"price":0.2,"equippable":false,"equipped":true,"isVehicular":false,"mods":1,"actions":{"skill":"Fighting","skillMod":"","dmgMod":"","additional":{}},"damage":"@str+d4","range":"","rof":"1","ap":"0","minStr":"d4","shots":"0","currentShots":"0","ammo":"","autoReload":false},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"flags":{"journal-links":{},"core":{"sourceId":"Item.VZDUG0uVURTjmhW2"},"cf":{"id":"temp_5rp00xv6vmg","path":"Savage Eberron Equipment#/CF_SEP/2.1. Meleee Weapons#/CF_SEP/Simple Weapons","color":"#000000"}}},{"_id":"KiKLSWJNDe5CFvKd","name":"Dagger","type":"weapon","img":"icons/weapons/daggers/dagger-double-red.webp","data":{"description":"","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"quantity":1,"weight":1,"price":2,"equippable":false,"equipped":true,"isVehicular":false,"mods":1,"actions":{"skill":"Fighting","skillMod":"","dmgMod":"","additional":{"oyxuzdjora":{"name":"Athletics (throwing)","type":"skill","rof":null,"skillMod":"","skillOverride":"Athletics","shotsUsed":null}}},"damage":"@str+d4","range":"3/6/12","rof":"1","ap":"0","minStr":"d4","shots":"0","currentShots":"0","ammo":"","autoReload":false},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"flags":{"journal-links":{},"core":{"sourceId":"Item.GxVNY83rIxMpxCqB"},"cf":{"id":"temp_5rp00xv6vmg","path":"Savage Eberron Equipment#/CF_SEP/2.1. Meleee Weapons#/CF_SEP/Simple Weapons","color":"#000000"}}},{"_id":"VgAAzRSdMK0pkmSW","name":"Unarmed Strike","type":"weapon","img":"icons/skills/melee/unarmed-punch-fist.webp","data":{"description":"<div class=\"sweb-core\">\n<p>See @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Unarmed Defender]{Unarmed Defender}.</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"quantity":1,"weight":0,"price":0,"equippable":false,"equipped":true,"isVehicular":false,"mods":1,"actions":{"skill":"Fighting","skillMod":"","dmgMod":"","additional":{}},"damage":"@str","range":"","rof":"1","ap":"0","minStr":"","shots":"0","currentShots":"0","ammo":"","autoReload":false},"effects":[],"folder":"651LNce8no6HR9rY","sort":100000,"permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"flags":{"journal-links":{},"core":{"sourceId":"Item.X31v8asHtqhgiaM2"}}},{"_id":"84hQCzTgYZqNFvEV","name":"Gambling","type":"skill","img":"icons/sundries/gaming/dice-pair-white-green.webp","data":{"description":"<div class=\"sweb-core\"><p>Gambling is common in the saloons of the Old West, the back rooms of criminal organizations, the barracks of most armies, or the flight decks of scifi spaceships.</p>\n<p>To simulate an hour of gambling without having to roll for every single toss of the dice or hand of cards, have everyone agree on the stakes, such as $10, 10 gold coins, etc. Everyone in the game then makes a Gambling roll. The lowest total pays the highest total the difference times the stake. The next lowest pays the second highest the difference times the stake, and so on. If there&rsquo;s an odd man left in the middle, he breaks even.</p>\n<p class=\"embedded-example\"><strong>Example:</strong> Red rolls highest with a 10 and Gabe rolls lowest with a 4. The difference is 6, so Gabe pays Red 6 &times; the stake of $10, or $60.</p>\n<p><strong>Cheating: </strong>A character who cheats adds +2 to his roll. The GM may raise or lower this modifier depending on the particulars of the game or the method of cheating. If a cheater rolls a @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Trait Rolls]{Critical Failure}, however, he&rsquo;s caught. The consequences depend on the circumstances and who noticed, but are usually unpleasant!</p></div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"attribute":"smarts","isCoreSkill":false,"die":{"sides":4,"modifier":0},"wild-die":{"sides":6}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_azxylmvr7yo","path":"Skills","color":"#008000"},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.swade-core-rules.swade-skills.zPegv65RzQXUbQIz"}}},{"_id":"4IhUco89Om1pE4qe","name":"Intimidation","type":"skill","img":"icons/skills/wounds/injury-face-impact-orange.webp","data":{"description":"<div class=\"sweb-core\">\n<p>Intimidation is the art of frightening an opponent so that he backs down, reveals information, or flees.</p>\n<p>Intimidation is an @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Trait Rolls]{opposed roll} resisted by the opponent&rsquo;s @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Traits]{Spirit}. In combat, this is a @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Test]{Test}. Out of combat, a successful roll means the foe backs down for the most part, reveals some information, or slinks away when the opportunity presents itself.</p>\n<p>A @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Raises]{raise} might mean he backs down for the remainder of the scene, spills all the beans, or runs away as fast as he can.</p>\n<p>In or out of combat, a @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Trait Rolls]{Critical Failure} means the target is immune to this character&rsquo;s Intimidation attempts for the remainder of this encounter!</p>\n<p><strong>Networking:</strong> Intimidation can also be used as a &ldquo;macro&rdquo; skill to simulate several hours of working the streets. See @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Networking]{Networking} to see how to crack some heads for favors or information.</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"attribute":"spirit","isCoreSkill":false,"die":{"sides":4,"modifier":0},"wild-die":{"sides":6}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_azxylmvr7yo","path":"Skills","color":"#008000"},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.swade-core-rules.swade-skills.RrgAZp50CgQyyY6w"}}}],"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"flags":{"journal-links":{"references":{}},"cf":{"id":"temp_3a04s0jrz4j","path":"Pirates of Cyre Bestiary#/CF_SEP/NPC's","color":"#000000"}}}
{"_id":"CDp0gPIh75K20LjT","name":"Crimson Cogward","type":"npc","img":"https://assets.forge-vtt.com/5f43f8ea1a91d63438d13159/artwork-adventures/pirates-of-cyre/characters/crimson-cogward.webp","data":{"attributes":{"agility":{"die":{"sides":6,"modifier":0},"wild-die":{"sides":6}},"smarts":{"die":{"sides":6,"modifier":0},"wild-die":{"sides":6},"animal":false},"spirit":{"die":{"sides":6,"modifier":0},"wild-die":{"sides":6},"unShakeBonus":0},"strength":{"die":{"sides":8,"modifier":0},"wild-die":{"sides":6},"encumbranceSteps":0},"vigor":{"die":{"sides":6,"modifier":0},"wild-die":{"sides":6}}},"stats":{"speed":{"runningDie":6,"runningMod":0,"value":6},"toughness":{"value":0,"armor":0,"modifier":0},"parry":{"value":6,"modifier":0},"size":0},"details":{"biography":{"value":"<div class=\"sweb-core\">\n<p>Crimson Cogward so called after the color his neck turns when he&rsquo;s angry.</p>\n<p>He wears a blue Vistani scarf tied tight around his shaven head to hide the scar left when his ear when bitten off in a bar fight.</p>\n<p> </p>"},"species":{"name":""},"currency":500,"wealth":{"die":6,"modifier":0,"wild-die":6},"conviction":{"value":0,"active":false},"autoCalcToughness":true,"autoCalcParry":true},"powerPoints":{},"fatigue":{"value":0,"min":0,"max":2},"wounds":{"value":0,"min":0,"max":0,"ignored":0},"advances":{"value":0,"rank":"Novice","details":""},"bennies":{"value":2,"max":2},"status":{"isShaken":false,"isDistracted":false,"isVulnerable":false,"isStunned":false,"isEntangled":false,"isBound":false},"initiative":{"hasHesitant":false,"hasLevelHeaded":false,"hasImpLevelHeaded":false,"hasQuick":false},"additionalStats":{},"wildcard":false},"token":{"name":"Blank NPC","img":"https://assets.forge-vtt.com/5f43f8ea1a91d63438d13159/tokens/bestiary/monstrous%20humanoid/harpy-*.png","displayName":30,"actorLink":false,"width":1,"height":1,"scale":1,"mirrorX":false,"mirrorY":false,"lockRotation":false,"rotation":0,"alpha":1,"vision":true,"dimSight":0,"brightSight":0,"dimLight":0,"brightLight":0,"sightAngle":0,"lightAngle":0,"lightAlpha":0.25,"lightAnimation":{"speed":5,"intensity":5},"disposition":-1,"displayBars":20,"bar1":{"attribute":""},"bar2":{"attribute":""},"flags":{"perfect-vision":{"visionRules":"default","monoVisionColor":"","sightLimit":null}},"randomImg":true,"actorId":null,"tint":null,"lightColor":null,"x":null,"y":null,"elevation":null},"items":[{"_id":"Bf0NpaRHtHmfrLb3","name":"Athletics","type":"skill","img":"icons/magic/control/buff-strength-muscle-damage.webp","data":{"description":"<div class=\"sweb-core\">\n<p>Athletics combines an individual&rsquo;s coordin&shy;ation with learned skills such as climbing, jumping, balancing, biking, wrestling, skiing, swimming, throwing, or catching. Characters who rely on physical power more than coordination can take the @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Brute]{Brute} Edge to link this skill to @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Traits]{Strength} instead of @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Traits]{Agility}.</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"attribute":"agility","isCoreSkill":false,"die":{"sides":6,"modifier":0},"wild-die":{"sides":6}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_azxylmvr7yo","path":"Skills","color":"#008000"},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.swade-core-rules.swade-skills.sAig03GZiFKqBX7p"}}},{"_id":"bJxCFLP4a8BEU0Qm","name":"Common Knowledge","type":"skill","img":"icons/sundries/documents/document-official-capital.webp","data":{"description":"<div class=\"sweb-core\"><p>Characters roll Common Knowledge to know people, places, and things of their world, including etiquette, geography, culture, popular technology, contacts, and customs.</p></div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"attribute":"smarts","isCoreSkill":false,"die":{"sides":6,"modifier":0},"wild-die":{"sides":6}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_azxylmvr7yo","path":"Skills","color":"#008000"},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.swade-core-rules.swade-skills.8N1uMThntsjaUPem"}}},{"_id":"gMAJFeCm5e3Oporq","name":"Fighting","type":"skill","img":"icons/skills/melee/hand-grip-sword-white-brown.webp","data":{"description":"<div class=\"sweb-core\">\n<p>Fighting covers all hand-to-hand (melee) attacks, whether it&rsquo;s with fists, axes, laser swords, or martial arts. See @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Combat]{Chapter Three} for the combat rules and the various maneuvers a warrior might attempt.</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"attribute":"agility","isCoreSkill":false,"die":{"sides":8,"modifier":0},"wild-die":{"sides":6}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_azxylmvr7yo","path":"Skills","color":"#008000"},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.swade-core-rules.swade-skills.wWiwjPlzAQU3TN9l"}}},{"_id":"9coycVPgGdTGpbmh","name":"Language (Common)","type":"skill","img":"icons/sundries/documents/document-letter-formal-tan.webp","data":{"description":"<div class=\"sweb-core\">\n<p>In some settings, such as those that focus on pulp action or &ldquo;planetary romance&rdquo; (where characters frequently travel among many strange civilizations), speaking various languages can simply be roleplayed with halting dialogue and campy accents that start out a little difficult and are quickly forgotten. The GM may ignore this skill altogether in these settings, or use the @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Multiple Languages]{Multiple Languages} &shy;option in the @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Setting Rules]{Setting Rules}.</p>\n<p>In more realistic settings, communication can be a major barrier that requires characters to put skill points into additional languages. In a 1980s World War Three game, for example, a group of United Nations paratroopers won&rsquo;t be able to speak with their foes unless they take Russian, Polish, or other languages common to the Warsaw Pact.</p>\n<p>If the Language skill is in use, it should be listed as Language (Spanish), Language (American Sign Language), etc. A character&rsquo;s die type also notes how fluent he is in it. (Characters start with a d8 in their own Language.)</p>\n<div class=\"sweb-core\">\n<table class=\"table value-table\"><caption class=\"table-caption\">\n<h2 class=\"table-title\">Language Proficiency</h2>\n</caption>\n<tbody>\n<tr class=\"table-header-row\">\n<th class=\"table-column-header\" scope=\"col\">Skill</th>\n<th class=\"table-column-header\" scope=\"col\">Ability</th>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td>d4</td>\n<td>The character can read, write and speak common words and phrases.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>d6</td>\n<td>The speaker can carry on a prolonged but occasionally halting conversation.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>d8</td>\n<td>The character can speak fluently.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>d10</td>\n<td>The hero can mimic other dialects within the language.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>d12</td>\n<td>The speaker can masterfully recite important literary or oral works.</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>\n</div>\n<p><strong>Limited: </strong>Use whichever skill is lowest when performing an action that requires knowledge of a foreign language. @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Intimidation]{Intimidation} (if verbal), @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Persuasion]{Persuasion}, @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Research]{Research}, @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Taunt]{Taunt}, etc., are all limited by the character&rsquo;s Language skill.</p>\n<p>This limitation never applies to a character&rsquo;s native tongue.</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"attribute":"smarts","isCoreSkill":false,"die":{"sides":8,"modifier":0},"wild-die":{"sides":6}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_azxylmvr7yo","path":"Skills","color":"#008000"},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.swade-core-rules.swade-skills.XIuR2IyQtewm5BZP"}}},{"_id":"TWqtRMnChmXvwXvN","name":"Notice","type":"skill","img":"icons/creatures/eyes/human-single-blue.webp","data":{"description":"<div class=\"sweb-core\">\n<p>Notice is a hero&rsquo;s general awareness and alertness. It&rsquo;s used to sense sights, sounds, tastes, and smells, spot clues, detect ambushes, spot hidden weapons on a foe, or tell if a rival is lying, frightened, happy, etc.</p>\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Trait Rolls]{Success} conveys basic information&mdash;the character hears movement in the forest, smells distant smoke, or senses someone isn&rsquo;t being completely truthful.</p>\n<p>A @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Raises]{raise} grants more detail, such as the direction of a sound or odor or what topic a person is avoiding or lying about.</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"attribute":"smarts","isCoreSkill":false,"die":{"sides":6,"modifier":0},"wild-die":{"sides":6}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_azxylmvr7yo","path":"Skills","color":"#008000"},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.swade-core-rules.swade-skills.yvw9bMgsrWQXuZN2"}}},{"_id":"rk3ft5Cc4sHxF5ay","name":"Stealth","type":"skill","img":"icons/magic/nature/stealth-hide-eyes-green.webp","data":{"description":"<div class=\"sweb-core\">\n<p>Stealth is the ability to hide and move quietly. A simple @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Trait Rolls]{success} on a Stealth roll means the character avoids detection if enemies aren&rsquo;t particularly alert. If the character @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Trait Rolls]{fails} the roll, the enemy realizes something is amiss and begins actively searching for whatever roused them.</p>\n<p>Once foes are alerted and active, Stealth is opposed by @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Notice]{Notice} (a @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Trait Rolls]{group roll} if there are many foes.</p>\n<p>The GM should apply any circumstantial penalties to @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Notice]{Notice} rolls for @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Illumination]{darkness}, @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Cover and Obstacles]{cover}, noise, distractions, and any difference in the target&rsquo;s @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Size and Scale]{Scale} (just like when attacking). Sneaking through dry leaves might subtract 2 from the Stealth roll, for example, while spotting someone in the dark uses the @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Illumination]{Illumination} penalty (&minus;4). Don&rsquo;t apply the same modifier to both rolls, however. If Stealth is at &minus;2 for the leaves, don&rsquo;t give Notice a +2 for them as well.</p>\n<p><strong>Sneak Attack: </strong> Sneaking up close enough to make a melee attack <em>always</em> requires an @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Trait Rolls]{opposed} Stealth roll versus the target&rsquo;s @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Notice]{Notice}, whether the guard is actively looking for trouble or not. If successful, the victim is @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Distracted and Vulnerable]{Vulnerable} to the attacker, but only until the attacker&rsquo;s turn ends. With a raise, the attacker has @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.The Drop]{The Drop} instead.</p>\n<p><strong>Movement:</strong> In combat, characters roll Stealth each turn as a @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Actions]{free action} at the end of their move or any action the GM thinks might draw attention.</p>\n<p>Out of combat, the distance moved depends entirely on the situation. The GM might want a roll every minute if the group is sneaking around the perimeter of a defensive position, or every few miles if they&rsquo;re trying to quietly walk the path through a dark forest without alerting the creatures that live there.</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"attribute":"agility","isCoreSkill":false,"die":{"sides":6,"modifier":0},"wild-die":{"sides":6}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_azxylmvr7yo","path":"Skills","color":"#008000"},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.swade-core-rules.swade-skills.z9FmdFVGOOW2kufm"}}},{"_id":"6BeiHr2FDzQaAZll","name":"Untrained","type":"skill","img":"icons/magic/symbols/question-stone-yellow.webp","data":{"description":"<div class=\"sweb-core\">\n<p>If a character doesn&rsquo;t have a skill for an action he&rsquo;s attempting, he rolls a d4 for his skill die (and a Wild Die if a @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Wild Cards and Extras]{Wild Card}) and subtracts 2 from the total.</p>\n<p>The GM may decide certain tasks cannot be attempted unskilled, such as performing complex surgery or flying a commercial jet.</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"attribute":"agility","isCoreSkill":false,"die":{"sides":4,"modifier":-2},"wild-die":{"sides":6}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_azxylmvr7yo","path":"Skills","color":"#008000"},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.swade-core-rules.swade-skills.1Pl2ZL8MPyKnaVEg"}}},{"_id":"N1OCwZvFIDN4gSVH","name":"Unarmed Strike","type":"weapon","img":"icons/skills/melee/unarmed-punch-fist.webp","data":{"description":"<div class=\"sweb-core\">\n<p>See @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Unarmed Defender]{Unarmed Defender}.</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"quantity":1,"weight":0,"price":0,"equippable":false,"equipped":true,"isVehicular":false,"mods":1,"actions":{"skill":"Fighting","skillMod":"","dmgMod":"","additional":{}},"damage":"@str","range":"","rof":"1","ap":"0","minStr":"","shots":"0","currentShots":"0","ammo":"","autoReload":false},"effects":[],"folder":"651LNce8no6HR9rY","sort":100000,"permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"flags":{"journal-links":{},"core":{"sourceId":"Item.X31v8asHtqhgiaM2"}}},{"_id":"2rgJhHIyr0HMWJAC","name":"Mean","type":"hindrance","img":"icons/magic/holy/yin-yang-balance-symbol.webp","data":{"description":"<div class=\"sweb-core\">\n<p>This curmudgeon is ill-tempered and disagreeable. He has trouble doing anything kind for anyone else, must be paid for his troubles, and doesn&rsquo;t accept awards or favors graciously. Besides the obvious roleplaying issues, Mean characters subtract 1 from @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Persuasion]{Persuasion} @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Trait Rolls]{rolls}.</span></p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"major":false},"effects":[],"folder":"1updrtPaYhKD0fRY","sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"3HvtK4sMp7flYKmT":3,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"flags":{"cf":null,"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.swade-core-rules.swade-hindrances.sNgSwqh2fGyM6i14"}}},{"_id":"sMzRq2ERvcGPZnIA","name":"Quirk (loner, dark moods, rages)","type":"hindrance","img":"icons/magic/holy/yin-yang-balance-symbol.webp","data":{"description":"<div class=\"sweb-core\"><p>This individual has some minor foible that is usually humorous but can occasionally cause him real trouble. A swashbuckler may always try to slash his initials on his foes, a dwarf may brag constantly about his culture, or a snobby d&eacute;butante might not eat, drink, or socialize with the lower class, for example.</span></p></div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"major":false},"effects":[],"folder":"1updrtPaYhKD0fRY","sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"3HvtK4sMp7flYKmT":3,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"flags":{"cf":null,"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.swade-core-rules.swade-hindrances.y0lUBhYHhl2LdjZZ"}}},{"_id":"u6SIBWGiu10iNsTO","name":"Brawler","type":"edge","img":"icons/environment/people/charge.webp","data":{"description":"<div class=\"sweb-core\">\n<p>His fists hit like hammers or his talons cut like scythes. His body feels like it&rsquo;s made of stone. Brawlers increase their @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Characters]{Toughness} by 1 and roll @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Traits]{Strength} +d4 when hitting with their fists or feet (or claws if they have them). If they already have a damage die from </span><strong>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Special Ability (Claws)]{Claws}</strong>, the @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Martial Artist]{Martial Artist} Edge, etc., increase the damage die type by one instead. </span></p>\n<p>The Brawler Edge doesn&rsquo;t make the character&rsquo;s fists </span><strong>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Natural Weapons]{Natural Weapons}</span></strong></p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Novice, Strength d8+, Vigor d8+"}},"effects":[{"_id":"kjzlcYkuLXL4NwhC","changes":[{"key":"data.stats.toughness.value","mode":2,"value":"1"}],"disabled":false,"duration":{"startTime":null},"icon":"icons/environment/people/charge.webp","label":"Brawler","transfer":true,"flags":{},"tint":null}],"folder":"hsEO07bFB8oM1LJo","sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"3HvtK4sMp7flYKmT":3,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"flags":{"cf":null,"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.swade-core-rules.swade-edges.q5NKwGPeK9PKQdIb"}}},{"_id":"fFhVO9nuyyeWW5ub","name":"Shooting","type":"skill","img":"icons/skills/ranged/target-bullseye-arrow-glowing.webp","data":{"description":"<div class=\"sweb-core\">\n<p>Shooting covers all attempts to hit a target with a ranged weapon such as a bow, pistol, or rocket launcher (thrown weapons use @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Athletics]{Athletics}). See @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Combat]{Chapter Three} for details on ranged combat.</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"attribute":"agility","isCoreSkill":false,"die":{"sides":6,"modifier":0},"wild-die":{"sides":6}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_azxylmvr7yo","path":"Skills","color":"#008000"},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.swade-core-rules.swade-skills.sOHfVvBDhe3Oy3r1"}}},{"_id":"m4SZ6IfmO651jKbx","name":"Religion","type":"skill","img":"icons/environment/settlement/gazebo.webp","data":{"description":"<div class=\"sweb-core\">\n<p>Religion reflects knowledge about ancient religions, mythic history, eccelsiastic tradition, holy symbols, undead, as well as details about all the religions of Eberron.</p>\n<p>A successful Religion roll reveals basic information about a topic, and a raise grants more details.</p>\n<p><em><strong>Source: Savage Eberron</strong></em></p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"attribute":"smarts","isCoreSkill":false,"die":{"sides":6,"modifier":0},"wild-die":{"sides":6}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"flags":{"journal-links":{},"core":{"sourceId":"Item.HdShAatiWIBLgv8z"},"cf":{"id":"temp_azxylmvr7yo","path":"Skills","color":"#008000"}}},{"_id":"cnhn5TPjRhzOi1lz","name":"Intimidation","type":"skill","img":"icons/skills/wounds/injury-face-impact-orange.webp","data":{"description":"<div class=\"sweb-core\">\n<p>Intimidation is the art of frightening an opponent so that he backs down, reveals information, or flees.</p>\n<p>Intimidation is an @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Trait Rolls]{opposed roll} resisted by the opponent&rsquo;s @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Traits]{Spirit}. In combat, this is a @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Test]{Test}. Out of combat, a successful roll means the foe backs down for the most part, reveals some information, or slinks away when the opportunity presents itself.</p>\n<p>A @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Raises]{raise} might mean he backs down for the remainder of the scene, spills all the beans, or runs away as fast as he can.</p>\n<p>In or out of combat, a @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Trait Rolls]{Critical Failure} means the target is immune to this character&rsquo;s Intimidation attempts for the remainder of this encounter!</p>\n<p><strong>Networking:</strong> Intimidation can also be used as a &ldquo;macro&rdquo; skill to simulate several hours of working the streets. See @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Networking]{Networking} to see how to crack some heads for favors or information.</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"attribute":"spirit","isCoreSkill":false,"die":{"sides":8,"modifier":0},"wild-die":{"sides":6}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_azxylmvr7yo","path":"Skills","color":"#008000"},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.swade-core-rules.swade-skills.RrgAZp50CgQyyY6w"}}},{"_id":"9O1VN6EyKI1oBOXu","name":"Boating","type":"skill","img":"icons/environment/settlement/ship.webp","data":{"description":"<div class=\"sweb-core\"><p>Characters with this skill can handle most any boat or ship common to their setting. They also know how to handle common tasks associated with their vessel such as tying knots, rigging sails, or following currents.</p></div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"attribute":"agility","isCoreSkill":false,"die":{"sides":6,"modifier":0},"wild-die":{"sides":6}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_azxylmvr7yo","path":"Skills","color":"#008000"},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.swade-core-rules.swade-skills.WMWgIVDuAW4cHxj2"}}},{"_id":"VRabazJG4QkAhaTl","name":"Rogue","type":"edge","img":"icons/skills/melee/strike-dagger-skull-white.webp","data":{"description":"<div class=\"sweb-core\">\n<p>Life is an endless adventure for those who live by their wits. Ever just one step ahead of danger, rogues bank on their cunning, skill, and charm to bend fate to their favor. Never knowing what to expect, they tend to prepare for everything. Out of necessity, they become adept manipulators, agile acrobats, or shadowy stalkers. They are thieves and gamblers, fast talkers and diplomats, bandits and bounty hunters, or explorers and investigators.</p>\n<p>Although many rogues favor the opportunities of towns and cities, some embrace life on the road. They wander from place to place, meeting exotic people and facing fantastic danger in pursuit of endless riches. In the end, all rogues desire to shape their fates and live life on their own terms.</p>\n<p>Rogues gain the following abilities:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Rogue Armor Restriction (Light)]{Rogue Armor Restriction (Light)}</li>\n<li>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Skill Monkey]{Skill Monkey}</li>\n<li>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Trap Sense]{Trap Sense}</li>\n</ul>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Novice, Agility d6+, Notice d6+, Stealth d6+, Thievery d6+"}},"effects":[],"folder":"zzeiXM6YEGI9jNRc","sort":500000,"permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"flags":{"journal-links":{},"core":{"sourceId":"Item.UBXzgLMsycquNmh2"}}},{"_id":"YPZuh0XYnbGtpJP0","name":"Rogue Armor Restriction (Light)","type":"hindrance","img":"icons/skills/melee/strike-dagger-skull-white.webp","data":{"description":"<div class=\"sweb-core\">\n<p>Rogues are nimble and deadly acrobats. Bulky armor interferes with their abilities, so they subtract 4 from @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Traits]{Agility} and @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Traits]{Agility-based} skill rolls when wearing medium or heavy armor, or using medium or heavy shields.</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"major":false},"effects":[],"folder":"zzeiXM6YEGI9jNRc","sort":100000,"permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"flags":{"journal-links":{},"core":{"sourceId":"Item.B1jMHG6GDPNV0kYU"}}},{"_id":"qc62tiNMro0EeQiS","name":"Skill Monkey","type":"edge","img":"icons/skills/melee/strike-dagger-skull-white.webp","data":{"description":"<div class=\"sweb-core\">\n<p>To survive, rogues have become adept at learning all sorts of skills and trades, both to survive and to con people. Whether trained by a mentor, a guild member, a house, or the streets, rogues have picked up additional skills and training.</p>\n<p>Rogues gain two skill points they can put into increasing the die type of two of the following skills: @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Athletics]{Athletics}, @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Common Knowledge]{Common Knowledge}, @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Deception]{Deception}, @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Gambling]{Gambling}, @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Intimidation]{Intimidation}, @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Notice]{Notice}, @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Performance]{Performance}, @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Persuasion]{Persuasion}, @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Stealth]{Stealth}, or @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Thievery]{Thievery}.</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Novice, Rogue"}},"effects":[],"folder":"zzeiXM6YEGI9jNRc","sort":400000,"permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"flags":{"journal-links":{},"core":{"sourceId":"Item.Voq7KPCbPVjrEjZP"}}},{"_id":"gd6OYmWMR4a28phH","name":"Deception","type":"skill","img":"icons/skills/toxins/poison-skull-herbs-bottle-pink.webp","data":{"description":"<div class=\"sweb-core\">\n<p>Deception determines whether the hero can convincingly hide the truth, either verbally or through her actions. This deception can encompass everything from misleading others through ambiguity to telling outright lies.</p>\n<p>Typical situations include trying to fast-talk a guard, con a merchant, dull someone's suspicions with false assurances, or maintain a straight face while telling a blatant lie.</p>\n<p>Usually, a character successfully passing herself off in a disguise, or trying to impersonate the sound of someone else's voice would be a @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Performance]{Performance} check rather than a deception check. </p>\n<p><em><strong>Source: Savage Eberron</strong></em></p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"attribute":"spirit","isCoreSkill":false,"die":{"sides":4,"modifier":0},"wild-die":{"sides":6}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"flags":{"journal-links":{},"core":{"sourceId":"Item.E0BVumGwbaczoPjD"},"cf":{"id":"temp_azxylmvr7yo","path":"Skills","color":"#008000"}}},{"_id":"44v1BPzLmQyLvyZt","name":"Gambling","type":"skill","img":"icons/sundries/gaming/dice-pair-white-green.webp","data":{"description":"<div class=\"sweb-core\"><p>Gambling is common in the saloons of the Old West, the back rooms of criminal organizations, the barracks of most armies, or the flight decks of scifi spaceships.</p>\n<p>To simulate an hour of gambling without having to roll for every single toss of the dice or hand of cards, have everyone agree on the stakes, such as $10, 10 gold coins, etc. Everyone in the game then makes a Gambling roll. The lowest total pays the highest total the difference times the stake. The next lowest pays the second highest the difference times the stake, and so on. If there&rsquo;s an odd man left in the middle, he breaks even.</p>\n<p class=\"embedded-example\"><strong>Example:</strong> Red rolls highest with a 10 and Gabe rolls lowest with a 4. The difference is 6, so Gabe pays Red 6 &times; the stake of $10, or $60.</p>\n<p><strong>Cheating: </strong>A character who cheats adds +2 to his roll. The GM may raise or lower this modifier depending on the particulars of the game or the method of cheating. If a cheater rolls a @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Trait Rolls]{Critical Failure}, however, he&rsquo;s caught. The consequences depend on the circumstances and who noticed, but are usually unpleasant!</p></div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"attribute":"smarts","isCoreSkill":false,"die":{"sides":6,"modifier":0},"wild-die":{"sides":6}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_azxylmvr7yo","path":"Skills","color":"#008000"},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.swade-core-rules.swade-skills.zPegv65RzQXUbQIz"}}},{"_id":"8NlgE5Cpj4zyjrzl","name":"Trap Sense","type":"edge","img":"icons/skills/melee/strike-dagger-skull-white.webp","data":{"description":"<div class=\"sweb-core\">\n<p>Rogues are adept at spotting and defeating all but the most clever snares and traps. They get a @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Notice]{Notice} roll anytime a detectable trap is about to be sprung within 5&rdquo; (10 yards). They must have line of sight to the trap and can&rsquo;t be @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Damage Effects]{Shaken} or @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Stunned]{Stunned}. This works generally like @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Danger Sense]{Danger Sense} but applies only to mechanical and magical traps.</p>\n<p>If the trap is detected and may be @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Evasion]{Evaded}, the rogue and anyone she warns ignores 2 points of @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Evasion]{Evasion} penalties to do so. If the trap can&rsquo;t normally be @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Evasion]{Evaded}, anyone warned may @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Evasion]{Evade} at the usual &minus;2 penalty.</p>\n<p><strong>Disarming Traps:</strong> Rogues with Trap Sense ignore up 2 points of @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Thievery]{Thievery} penalties when attempting to disarm traps.</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Novice, Rogue"}},"effects":[],"folder":"zzeiXM6YEGI9jNRc","sort":400000,"permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"flags":{"journal-links":{},"core":{"sourceId":"Item.gMhsswekqyI1hslR"}}},{"_id":"ms9RvVzdF5cz5gwP","name":"Thievery","type":"skill","img":"icons/skills/social/theft-pickpocket-bribery-brown.webp","data":{"description":"<div class=\"sweb-core\">\n<p>Lockpicking, safecracking, picking pockets, sleight of hand, setting and disabling traps and similar acts of misdirection, sabotage, subterfuge, and manipulation are called Thievery.</p>\n<p>If used to pick a lock, crack a safe, disable a trap, or perform a simple unopposed action, @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Trait Rolls]{success} opens or disables the device, and a @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Raises]{raise} does it in less time, without tripping alarms, or whatever else the GM feels is appropriate.</p>\n<p>Sleight of hand, hiding or planting an item, or picking a pocket require a simple @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Trait Rolls]{success}. If foes are actively watching the character, Thievery is @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Trait Rolls]{opposed} by @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Notice]{Notice}.</p>\n<p>The Game Master should assign @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Trait Rolls]{penalties} for particularly difficult circumstances. Picking a heavy padlock might have a &minus;4 penalty, while hiding a revolver in bulky winter clothing might grant a +1 bonus. @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Trait Rolls]{Failure} typically means the character is spotted or it takes too much time (after which the character can try again). A @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Trait Rolls]{Critical Failure} typically sets off the trap, alerts the victim, or jams the device so that it must be opened or interacted with in a different way.</p>\n<p><strong>Limited: </strong>Using Thievery on an electronic device, such as a keypad, is limited by the thief&rsquo;s @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Electronics]{Electronics} skill. Use the lowest of the two skills.</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"attribute":"agility","isCoreSkill":false,"die":{"sides":8,"modifier":0},"wild-die":{"sides":6}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_azxylmvr7yo","path":"Skills","color":"#008000"},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.swade-core-rules.swade-skills.wZbyJkisWIfmcZNt"}}},{"_id":"9tSxcdi6UUTG1Fab","name":"Cutlass","type":"weapon","img":"icons/weapons/swords/greatsword-blue.webp","data":{"description":"","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"quantity":1,"weight":2,"price":10,"equippable":false,"equipped":true,"isVehicular":false,"mods":1,"actions":{"skill":"Fighting","skillMod":"","dmgMod":"","additional":{}},"damage":"@str+d6","range":"","rof":"1","ap":"0","minStr":"d8","shots":"0","currentShots":"0","ammo":"","autoReload":false},"effects":[],"folder":"wKOO5vrTtLr5gJsf","sort":1000001,"permission":{"default":0,"ZvqefCj0L7TxJS56":3,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"flags":{"journal-links":{},"core":{"sourceId":"Item.bxg2xSSoDL9ZUkSk"}}},{"_id":"9PgSnkOzBjXa1s3y","name":"Leather Armor","type":"armor","img":"icons/equipment/chest/breastplate-layered-grey.webp","data":{"description":"","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"quantity":1,"weight":3,"price":5,"equippable":false,"equipped":true,"minStr":"d4","armor":1,"isNaturalArmor":false,"locations":{"head":false,"torso":true,"arms":true,"legs":false}},"effects":[],"folder":"XQoSmfkzvuK8FNo1","sort":100000,"permission":{"default":0,"ZvqefCj0L7TxJS56":3,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"flags":{"journal-links":{},"core":{"sourceId":"Item.PRPRsNmJyfvoy6hH"}}},{"_id":"MEOep7SQghsREc2S","name":"Dagger","type":"weapon","img":"icons/weapons/daggers/dagger-double-red.webp","data":{"description":"","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"quantity":1,"weight":1,"price":2,"equippable":false,"equipped":true,"isVehicular":false,"mods":1,"actions":{"skill":"Fighting","skillMod":"","dmgMod":"","additional":{"oyxuzdjora":{"name":"Athletics (throwing)","type":"skill","rof":null,"skillMod":"","skillOverride":"Athletics","shotsUsed":null}}},"damage":"@str+d4","range":"3/6/12","rof":"1","ap":"0","minStr":"d4","shots":"0","currentShots":"0","ammo":"","autoReload":false},"effects":[],"folder":"ofLOMYgHLqfG1MyP","sort":400001,"permission":{"default":0,"ZvqefCj0L7TxJS56":3,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"flags":{"journal-links":{},"core":{"sourceId":"Item.GxVNY83rIxMpxCqB"}}}],"effects":[{"_id":"uMqh6VsX8QTKAQbD","changes":[{"key":"data.stats.toughness.value","mode":2,"value":"1"}],"disabled":false,"duration":{"startTime":28973116800},"icon":"icons/environment/people/charge.webp","label":"Brawler","origin":"Actor.V1CNhfR8X7IKjik4.Item.u6SIBWGiu10iNsTO","tint":null,"transfer":false,"flags":{}}],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_3a04s0jrz4j","path":"Pirates of Cyre Bestiary#/CF_SEP/NPC's","color":"#000000"}}}
{"_id":"z2qkrFSshkwFRNra","name":"Cut-Throat Grok","type":"npc","img":"https://assets.forge-vtt.com/5f43f8ea1a91d63438d13159/artwork-adventures/pirates-of-cyre/characters/cut-throat-grok.webp","data":{"attributes":{"agility":{"die":{"sides":6,"modifier":0},"wild-die":{"sides":6}},"smarts":{"die":{"sides":6,"modifier":0},"wild-die":{"sides":6},"animal":false},"spirit":{"die":{"sides":8,"modifier":0},"wild-die":{"sides":6},"unShakeBonus":0},"strength":{"die":{"sides":6,"modifier":0},"wild-die":{"sides":6},"encumbranceSteps":0},"vigor":{"die":{"sides":8,"modifier":0},"wild-die":{"sides":6}}},"stats":{"speed":{"runningDie":6,"runningMod":0,"value":6},"toughness":{"value":0,"armor":0,"modifier":0},"parry":{"value":6,"modifier":0},"size":0},"details":{"biography":{"value":"<div class=\"sweb-core\">\n<p>Cut-Throat Grok is the <em>Storm Reaver's </em></span>quartermaster, a no-nonsense character with a huge scar across her neck. Grok is a reedy half-orc who favors dark clothing. She carries a notched greataxe and an array of throwing axes hangs from her belt. Grok frequently grins toothily, and uses appalling curse words, particularly when drunk. </span> <br style=\"font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; font-weight: normal; letter-spacing: normal; line-height: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: -webkit-auto; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-size-adjust: auto; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px;\" /><br /></p>\n</div>"},"species":{"name":""},"currency":500,"wealth":{"die":6,"modifier":0,"wild-die":6},"conviction":{"value":0,"active":false},"autoCalcToughness":true,"autoCalcParry":true},"powerPoints":{},"fatigue":{"value":0,"min":0,"max":2},"wounds":{"value":0,"min":0,"max":0,"ignored":0},"advances":{"value":0,"rank":"Novice","details":""},"bennies":{"value":2,"max":2},"status":{"isShaken":false,"isDistracted":false,"isVulnerable":false,"isStunned":false,"isEntangled":false,"isBound":false},"initiative":{"hasHesitant":false,"hasLevelHeaded":false,"hasImpLevelHeaded":false,"hasQuick":false},"additionalStats":{},"wildcard":false},"token":{"flags":{"perfect-vision":{"visionRules":"default","monoVisionColor":"","sightLimit":null}},"name":"Cut-Thraot Grok","displayName":30,"img":"modules/etu-rules/assets/bestiary_tokens/sonya-alvarez-min.png","tint":null,"width":1,"height":1,"scale":1,"mirrorX":false,"mirrorY":false,"lockRotation":false,"rotation":0,"vision":true,"dimSight":30,"brightSight":0,"dimLight":0,"brightLight":0,"sightAngle":0,"lightAngle":0,"lightColor":null,"lightAlpha":1,"lightAnimation":{"speed":5,"intensity":5},"actorId":null,"actorLink":true,"disposition":0,"displayBars":0,"bar1":{"attribute":""},"bar2":{"attribute":""},"randomImg":false,"alpha":1,"x":null,"y":null,"elevation":null},"items":[{"_id":"UZW0tLJicg0VZOp4","name":"Athletics","type":"skill","data":{"description":"<div class=\"sweb-core\">\n<p>Athletics combines an individual&rsquo;s coordin&shy;ation with learned skills such as climbing, jumping, balancing, biking, wrestling, skiing, swimming, throwing, or catching. Characters who rely on physical power more than coordination can take the @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Brute]{Brute} Edge to link this skill to @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Traits]{Strength} instead of @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Traits]{Agility}.</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"attribute":"agility","isCoreSkill":false,"die":{"sides":6,"modifier":0},"wild-die":{"sides":6}},"sort":100000,"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_nsugutrpau","path":"Skills","color":"#8c160f"},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.swade-core-rules.swade-skills.Athletics"}},"img":"icons/magic/control/buff-strength-muscle-damage.webp","effects":[],"folder":null,"permission":{"default":0}},{"_id":"W5lfcCNjirSPUH42","name":"Common Knowledge","type":"skill","data":{"description":"<div class=\"sweb-core\"><p>Characters roll Common Knowledge to know people, places, and things of their world, including etiquette, geography, culture, popular technology, contacts, and customs.</p></div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"attribute":"smarts","isCoreSkill":false,"die":{"sides":6,"modifier":-1},"wild-die":{"sides":6}},"sort":200000,"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_nsugutrpau","path":"Skills","color":"#8c160f"},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.swade-core-rules.swade-skills.Common Knowledge"}},"img":"icons/sundries/documents/document-official-capital.webp","effects":[],"folder":null,"permission":{"default":0}},{"_id":"quj5jF3vNls1j5E3","name":"Notice","type":"skill","data":{"description":"<div class=\"sweb-core\">\n<p>Notice is a hero&rsquo;s general awareness and alertness. It&rsquo;s used to sense sights, sounds, tastes, and smells, spot clues, detect ambushes, spot hidden weapons on a foe, or tell if a rival is lying, frightened, happy, etc.</p>\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Trait Rolls]{Success} conveys basic information&mdash;the character hears movement in the forest, smells distant smoke, or senses someone isn&rsquo;t being completely truthful.</p>\n<p>A @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Raises]{raise} grants more detail, such as the direction of a sound or odor or what topic a person is avoiding or lying about.</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"attribute":"smarts","isCoreSkill":false,"die":{"sides":6,"modifier":-1},"wild-die":{"sides":6}},"sort":300000,"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_nsugutrpau","path":"Skills","color":"#8c160f"},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.swade-core-rules.swade-skills.ZvwjzMLxsneptV4T"}},"img":"icons/creatures/eyes/human-single-blue.webp","effects":[],"folder":null,"permission":{"default":0}},{"_id":"TOEzoo2Lf4A5JXOF","name":"Persuasion","type":"skill","data":{"description":"<div class=\"sweb-core\">\n<p>Persuasion is the ability to convince others to do what you want through reason, cajoling, deception, rewards, or other friendly means. Persuasion isn&rsquo;t mind control. It can change someone&rsquo;s attitude but not their goals. A bandit may let you keep a sentimental piece of jewelry with a good Persuasion roll but still takes all your other goods.</p>\n<p>When used to @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Support]{Support} allies it&rsquo;s an unopposed roll. If the target is resistant, it&rsquo;s an @JournalEntry[JBxsGv2wAoAmoCDe]{opposed} roll vs. the target&rsquo;s @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Traits]{Spirit}. The GM should modify the roll as she sees fit based on roleplaying, any pertinent @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Edges]{Edges} or @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Hindrances]{Hindrances} that affect the conversation, and the circumstances.</p>\n<p><strong>Reaction Level:</strong> How much a person is willing to cooperate depends largely on their attitude toward whoever&rsquo;s talking to them. The Game Master can decide how nonplayer characters feel based on the setting, or roll on the @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-tables.Reaction Table]{Reaction Table} if she has no preconceived notions.</p>\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Trait Rolls]{Success} improves the target&rsquo;s attitude one level and a raise improves it two. Further increases aren&rsquo;t generally possible in the same encounter&mdash;it takes individuals a little time to adjust their biases.</p>\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Trait Rolls]{Failure} means the target won&rsquo;t change his mind this scene or until the situation changes in some important way. A @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Trait Rolls]{Critical Failure} also <em>reduces</em> the target&rsquo;s attitude two levels.</p>\n<p>Only one roll should generally be allowed per interaction unless new information is revealed, a substantial reward is offered, etc.</p>\n<p><strong>Networking: </strong>Characters can also use Persuasion as a &ldquo;macro skill,&rdquo; simulating a few hours or an evening&rsquo;s time hobnobbing and socializing to gain favors or information. See @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Networking]{Networking}.</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"attribute":"spirit","isCoreSkill":false,"die":{"sides":8,"modifier":-1},"wild-die":{"sides":6}},"sort":400000,"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_nsugutrpau","path":"Skills","color":"#8c160f"},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.swade-core-rules.swade-skills.Persuasion"}},"img":"icons/skills/social/diplomacy-handshake.webp","effects":[],"folder":null,"permission":{"default":0}},{"_id":"8VzaSa3EEDrMz6PR","name":"Stealth","type":"skill","data":{"description":"<div class=\"sweb-core\">\n<p>Stealth is the ability to hide and move quietly. A simple @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Trait Rolls]{success} on a Stealth roll means the character avoids detection if enemies aren&rsquo;t particularly alert. If the character @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Trait Rolls]{fails} the roll, the enemy realizes something is amiss and begins actively searching for whatever roused them.</p>\n<p>Once foes are alerted and active, Stealth is opposed by @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Notice]{Notice} (a @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Trait Rolls]{group roll} if there are many foes.</p>\n<p>The GM should apply any circumstantial penalties to @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Notice]{Notice} rolls for @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Illumination]{darkness}, @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Cover and Obstacles]{cover}, noise, distractions, and any difference in the target&rsquo;s @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Size and Scale]{Scale} (just like when attacking). Sneaking through dry leaves might subtract 2 from the Stealth roll, for example, while spotting someone in the dark uses the @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Illumination]{Illumination} penalty (&minus;4). Don&rsquo;t apply the same modifier to both rolls, however. If Stealth is at &minus;2 for the leaves, don&rsquo;t give Notice a +2 for them as well.</p>\n<p><strong>Sneak Attack: </strong> Sneaking up close enough to make a melee attack <em>always</em> requires an @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Trait Rolls]{opposed} Stealth roll versus the target&rsquo;s @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Notice]{Notice}, whether the guard is actively looking for trouble or not. If successful, the victim is @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Distracted and Vulnerable]{Vulnerable} to the attacker, but only until the attacker&rsquo;s turn ends. With a raise, the attacker has @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.The Drop]{The Drop} instead.</p>\n<p><strong>Movement:</strong> In combat, characters roll Stealth each turn as a @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Actions]{free action} at the end of their move or any action the GM thinks might draw attention.</p>\n<p>Out of combat, the distance moved depends entirely on the situation. The GM might want a roll every minute if the group is sneaking around the perimeter of a defensive position, or every few miles if they&rsquo;re trying to quietly walk the path through a dark forest without alerting the creatures that live there.</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"attribute":"agility","isCoreSkill":false,"die":{"sides":4,"modifier":"0"},"wild-die":{"sides":6}},"sort":500000,"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_nsugutrpau","path":"Skills","color":"#8c160f"},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.swade-core-rules.swade-skills.Stealth"}},"img":"icons/magic/nature/stealth-hide-eyes-green.webp","effects":[],"folder":null,"permission":{"default":0}},{"_id":"BQ3OOQlkZvCl1Lfb","name":"Untrained","type":"skill","data":{"description":"<div class=\"sweb-core\">\n<p>If a character doesn&rsquo;t have a skill for an action he&rsquo;s attempting, he rolls a d4 for his skill die (and a Wild Die if a @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Wild Cards and Extras]{Wild Card}) and subtracts 2 from the total.</p>\n<p>The GM may decide certain tasks cannot be attempted unskilled, such as performing complex surgery or flying a commercial jet.</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"attribute":"agility","isCoreSkill":false,"die":{"sides":4,"modifier":"-2"},"wild-die":{"sides":6}},"sort":1100000,"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_nsugutrpau","path":"Skills","color":"#8c160f"},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.swade-core-rules.swade-skills.zcn1epcU4FEJGGyI"}},"img":"icons/magic/symbols/question-stone-yellow.webp","effects":[],"folder":null,"permission":{"default":0}},{"_id":"uaVAhwDnUDLFZFXm","name":"Unarmed strike","type":"weapon","data":{"description":"","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"quantity":1,"weight":0,"price":0,"equippable":false,"equipped":true,"isVehicular":false,"mods":1,"actions":{"skill":"","skillMod":"","dmgMod":"","additional":{}},"damage":"@str","range":"","rof":"1","ap":"0","minStr":"","shots":"0","currentShots":"0","ammo":"","autoReload":false},"sort":1400000,"flags":{},"img":"icons/skills/melee/unarmed-punch-fist.webp","effects":[],"folder":null,"permission":{"default":0}},{"_id":"GjcL17dCtOeFUvbu","name":"Fighting","type":"skill","data":{"description":"<div class=\"sweb-core\">\n<p>Fighting covers all hand-to-hand (melee) attacks, whether it&rsquo;s with fists, axes, laser swords, or martial arts. See @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Combat]{Chapter Three} for the combat rules and the various maneuvers a warrior might attempt.</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"attribute":"agility","isCoreSkill":false,"die":{"sides":8,"modifier":0},"wild-die":{"sides":6}},"sort":1500000,"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_qals24wpyph","path":"Skills","color":"#8c160f"},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.swade-core-rules.swade-skills.wWiwjPlzAQU3TN9l"}},"img":"icons/skills/melee/hand-grip-sword-white-brown.webp","effects":[],"folder":null,"permission":{"default":0}},{"_id":"TLp2vEe194RjRVYB","name":"Fighter","type":"edge","img":"icons/environment/people/infantry.webp","data":{"description":"<div class=\"sweb-core\">\n<p>Some take up arms for glory, wealth, or revenge. Others do battle to prove themselves, to protect others, or because they know nothing else. Still others learn the ways of weaponcraft to hone their bodies in battle and prove their mettle in the forge of war.</p>\n<p>Lords of the battlefield, fighters are a disparate lot. Some train with many weapons; some prefer just one. Whatever their tactics, fighters excel at combat. They protect their own and defeat their enemies, rarely shying away from battle. They often lead the charge, a role they relish even if they don&rsquo;t insist on it.</p>\n<p>These skilled warriors turn hunks of metal into arms capable of taming kingdoms, slaughtering monsters, and rousing the hearts of armies. Woe to those who dare stand against them.</p>\n<p>Fighters gain the following abilities:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Combat Training]{Combat Training}</li>\n<li>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Martial Flexibility]{Martial Flexibility}</li>\n</ul>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Novice, Strength d6+, Fighting d6+"}},"effects":[],"folder":"i5aNd30ywxpcOuxy","sort":100000,"permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"flags":{"journal-links":{},"core":{"sourceId":"Item.JSFKscBmodf3b9qX"}}},{"_id":"AmMcLJktnYTO3cZt","name":"Combat Training","type":"edge","img":"icons/environment/people/infantry.webp","data":{"description":"<div class=\"sweb-core\">\n<p>The fighter are trained and adept at feints and deception in combat to unbalance their opponent. They add +1 to the all rolls for @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Test]{Tests} in combat that use any of the following skills: @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Athletics]{Athletics}, @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Battle]{Battle}, @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Fighting]{Fighting}, @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Intimidation]{Intimidation}, or @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Shooting]{Shooting} rolls.</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Novice, Fighter"}},"effects":[],"folder":"i5aNd30ywxpcOuxy","sort":200000,"permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"flags":{"journal-links":{},"core":{"sourceId":"Item.iAxlS6GhMXNoZpnI"}}},{"_id":"jDPQ3HNSu0yVYt2d","name":"Language (Orcish)","type":"skill","img":"icons/sundries/documents/document-letter-formal-tan.webp","data":{"description":"<div class=\"sweb-core\">\n<p>In some settings, such as those that focus on pulp action or &ldquo;planetary romance&rdquo; (where characters frequently travel among many strange civilizations), speaking various languages can simply be roleplayed with halting dialogue and campy accents that start out a little difficult and are quickly forgotten. The GM may ignore this skill altogether in these settings, or use the @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Multiple Languages]{Multiple Languages} &shy;option in the @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Setting Rules]{Setting Rules}.</p>\n<p>In more realistic settings, communication can be a major barrier that requires characters to put skill points into additional languages. In a 1980s World War Three game, for example, a group of United Nations paratroopers won&rsquo;t be able to speak with their foes unless they take Russian, Polish, or other languages common to the Warsaw Pact.</p>\n<p>If the Language skill is in use, it should be listed as Language (Spanish), Language (American Sign Language), etc. A character&rsquo;s die type also notes how fluent he is in it. (Characters start with a d8 in their own Language.)</p>\n<div class=\"sweb-core\">\n<table class=\"table value-table\"><caption class=\"table-caption\">\n<h2 class=\"table-title\">Language Proficiency</h2>\n</caption>\n<tbody>\n<tr class=\"table-header-row\">\n<th class=\"table-column-header\" scope=\"col\">Skill</th>\n<th class=\"table-column-header\" scope=\"col\">Ability</th>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td>d4</td>\n<td>The character can read, write and speak common words and phrases.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>d6</td>\n<td>The speaker can carry on a prolonged but occasionally halting conversation.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>d8</td>\n<td>The character can speak fluently.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>d10</td>\n<td>The hero can mimic other dialects within the language.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>d12</td>\n<td>The speaker can masterfully recite important literary or oral works.</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>\n</div>\n<p><strong>Limited: </strong>Use whichever skill is lowest when performing an action that requires knowledge of a foreign language. @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Intimidation]{Intimidation} (if verbal), @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Persuasion]{Persuasion}, @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Research]{Research}, @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Taunt]{Taunt}, etc., are all limited by the character&rsquo;s Language skill.</p>\n<p>This limitation never applies to a character&rsquo;s native tongue.</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"attribute":"smarts","isCoreSkill":false,"die":{"sides":6,"modifier":0},"wild-die":{"sides":6}},"effects":[],"folder":"NGCHRRLs7ShzfqpB","sort":200000,"permission":{"default":0,"3HvtK4sMp7flYKmT":3,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_nsugutrpau","path":"Skills","color":"#8c160f"},"journal-links":{},"core":{"sourceId":"Item.r0POISsnudlhTqsf"}}},{"_id":"fZwcFZGcNVXSHUch","name":"Primal Intuition","type":"ability","img":"icons/magic/nature/leaf-rune-glow-green.webp","data":{"description":"<div class=\"sweb-core\">\n<p>Half-orcs start with a d4 in one of the following skills: <em>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Athletics]{athletics}, @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Healing]{healing}, @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Intimidation]{intimidation}, @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Notice]{notice}, </em>or <em>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Survival]{survival}</em>. If the chosen skill is a core skill, it starts at d6 and the skill's maximum increases to d12+1.</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"subtype":"special","grantsPowers":false},"effects":[],"folder":"NGCHRRLs7ShzfqpB","sort":300000,"permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"flags":{"journal-links":{},"core":{"sourceId":"Item.eK4ugnzc1XArIZA6"}}},{"_id":"HaDfxXcTkGpGXyve","name":"Low Light Vision","type":"ability","img":"icons/creatures/eyes/human-single-brown.webp","data":{"description":"<div class=\"sweb-core\">\n<p>Low Light Vision ignores up &ndash;2 penalties for @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Illumination]{Dim and Dark Illumination}. @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Illumination]{Pitch Darkness} remains unaffected.</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"subtype":"special","grantsPowers":false},"effects":[],"folder":"kFghWjY7gP7MEqav","sort":100001,"permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"flags":{"journal-links":{},"core":{"sourceId":"Item.OL3T8otZVCkOoir3"}}},{"_id":"bo7crv0cGG78T9UP","name":"Liquid Courage","type":"edge","img":"icons/environment/people/cleric-orange.webp","data":{"description":"<div class=\"sweb-core\">\n<p>This gregarious individual processes alcohol far differently than most. The round after consuming a stiff drink (about eight ounces of hard liquor or equivalent), her @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Traits]{Vigor} increases one die type (increasing @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Characters]{Toughness} as well). The drinker can also ignore one level of @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Damage Effects]{Wound} penalties (which stacks with other abilities that do the same).</p>\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Traits]{Smarts}, @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Traits]{Agility}, and all linked skills suffer a &minus;1 penalty for the duration, however.</p>\n<p>The effect lasts for one hour after it begins, at which point the boozer suffers a level of @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Fatigue]{Fatigue} for the next four hours.</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Novice, Vigor d8+"}},"effects":[{"_id":"5f5punVk9GcL8wd6","changes":[{"key":"data.attributes.vigor.die.sides","mode":2,"value":"2"},{"key":"data.wounds.ignored","mode":2,"value":"1"},{"key":"data.attributes.smarts.die.modifier","mode":2,"value":"-1"},{"key":"data.attributes.agility.die.modifier","mode":2,"value":"-1"}],"disabled":false,"duration":{"startTime":null},"icon":"icons/environment/people/cleric-orange.webp","label":"Liquid Courage","transfer":true,"flags":{},"tint":null}],"folder":"OeyARkjjHG8YltWb","sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"3HvtK4sMp7flYKmT":3,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"flags":{"cf":null,"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.swade-core-rules.swade-edges.MkvhQtL8RUJrsGj9"}}},{"_id":"JYGgxWOSbOlSQZ8k","name":"Streetwise","type":"edge","img":"icons/skills/social/diplomacy-unity-alliance.webp","data":{"description":"<div class=\"sweb-core\">\n<p>Streetwise characters know how to find the local black market, fence stolen goods, avoid the local law (or criminal element!), lay low when the heat&rsquo;s on, obtain illegal weapons, find out which &ldquo;boss&rdquo; is hiring muscle, or similar shady activities.<br /></span></p>\n<p>Streetwise characters add +2 to @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Intimidation]{Intimidation} or @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Persuasion]{Persuasion} rolls made to </span>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Networking]{Networking}</span> with shady or criminal elements.<br /></span></p>\n<p>They also add +2 to @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Common Knowledge]{Common Knowledge} rolls pertaining to the types of disreputable activities listed above</span></p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Novice, Smarts d6+"}},"effects":[],"folder":"4qgDgsPe5IZFyuwd","sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"3HvtK4sMp7flYKmT":3,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"flags":{"cf":null,"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.swade-core-rules.swade-edges.9dkUUjYdfSoYx10K"}}},{"_id":"uILmewT5YLFZoSiV","name":"Boating","type":"skill","img":"icons/environment/settlement/ship.webp","data":{"description":"<div class=\"sweb-core\"><p>Characters with this skill can handle most any boat or ship common to their setting. They also know how to handle common tasks associated with their vessel such as tying knots, rigging sails, or following currents.</p></div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"attribute":"agility","isCoreSkill":false,"die":{"sides":6,"modifier":0},"wild-die":{"sides":6}},"effects":[],"folder":"cgfmurTJRwbCvmCc","sort":1400001,"permission":{"default":0,"3HvtK4sMp7flYKmT":3,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_qals24wpyph","path":"Skills","color":"#8c160f"},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.swade-core-rules.swade-skills.WMWgIVDuAW4cHxj2"}}},{"_id":"9iTPpx0fmkQVJA8R","name":"Language (Common)","type":"skill","img":"icons/sundries/documents/document-letter-formal-tan.webp","data":{"description":"<div class=\"sweb-core\">\n<p>In some settings, such as those that focu