-eberron-rules.Trait Rolls]{penalty} to @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Common Knowledge]{Common Knowledge} and @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Notice]{Notice} rolls.</span></p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"major":true},"effects":[],"folder":"1updrtPaYhKD0fRY","sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"3HvtK4sMp7flYKmT":3,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"flags":{"cf":null,"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.swade-core-rules.swade-hindrances.ms1x4JRCRLLEBI6c"}}},{"_id":"e9sbxvAeuzfd5WmG","name":"Ugly (Huge scar on neck)","type":"hindrance","img":"icons/magic/holy/yin-yang-balance-symbol.webp","data":{"description":"<div class=\"sweb-core\">\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Attractive]{Attractive} people get all the breaks. This unfortunate individual isn&rsquo;t one of them. He subtracts 1 from his @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Persuasion]{Persuasion} @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Trait Rolls]{rolls}, or 2 if taken as a @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Characters]{Major} @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Hindrances]{Hindrance}.</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"major":false},"effects":[],"folder":"1updrtPaYhKD0fRY","sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"3HvtK4sMp7flYKmT":3,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"flags":{"cf":null,"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.swade-core-rules.swade-hindrances.YOpdOTiA5Q1Rnq2X"}}}],"effects":[{"_id":"MgwN3VT828eXYNJE","changes":[{"key":"data.attributes.vigor.die.sides","mode":2,"value":"2"},{"key":"data.wounds.ignored","mode":2,"value":"1"},{"key":"data.attributes.smarts.die.modifier","mode":2,"value":"-1"},{"key":"data.attributes.agility.die.modifier","mode":2,"value":"-1"}],"disabled":true,"duration":{"startTime":28973116800},"icon":"icons/environment/people/cleric-orange.webp","label":"Liquid Courage","origin":"Actor.HqdOgzzsCeFolctC.Item.bo7crv0cGG78T9UP","tint":null,"transfer":false,"flags":{}},{"_id":"bvUYKJJLDqmVuzj1","changes":[{"key":"data.stats.parry.modifier","value":"-1","mode":2}],"disabled":true,"duration":{"startTime":28973116800},"icon":"modules/swade-core-rules/assets/art/equipment/weapons/melee-medieval-greataxe.webp","label":"Great Axe Parry Penalty","origin":"Actor.HqdOgzzsCeFolctC.Item.ukORcNhJ26q2KQsc","tint":null,"transfer":false,"flags":{}}],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"flags":{"journal-links":{"references":{}},"cf":{"id":"temp_3a04s0jrz4j","path":"Pirates of Cyre Bestiary#/CF_SEP/NPC's","color":"#000000"}}}
{"_id":"Q5asnYfjlp4vQD7W","name":"Krornik Kragshard","type":"npc","img":"https://assets.forge-vtt.com/5f43f8ea1a91d63438d13159/artwork-adventures/pirates-of-cyre/characters/krornik-kragshard.webp","data":{"attributes":{"agility":{"die":{"sides":6,"modifier":0},"wild-die":{"sides":6}},"smarts":{"die":{"sides":8,"modifier":0},"wild-die":{"sides":6},"animal":false},"spirit":{"die":{"sides":6,"modifier":0},"wild-die":{"sides":6},"unShakeBonus":0},"strength":{"die":{"sides":6,"modifier":0},"wild-die":{"sides":6},"encumbranceSteps":0},"vigor":{"die":{"sides":8,"modifier":0},"wild-die":{"sides":6}}},"stats":{"speed":{"runningDie":4,"runningMod":0,"value":5},"toughness":{"value":0,"armor":0,"modifier":0},"parry":{"value":5,"modifier":0},"size":0},"details":{"biography":{"value":"<div class=\"sweb-core\">\n<p>xxxxx</p>\n</div>"},"species":{"name":""},"currency":500,"wealth":{"die":6,"modifier":0,"wild-die":6},"conviction":{"value":0,"active":false},"autoCalcToughness":true,"autoCalcParry":true},"powerPoints":{},"fatigue":{"value":0,"min":0,"max":2},"wounds":{"value":0,"min":0,"max":0,"ignored":0},"advances":{"value":0,"rank":"Novice","details":""},"bennies":{"value":2,"max":2},"status":{"isShaken":false,"isDistracted":false,"isVulnerable":false,"isStunned":false,"isEntangled":false,"isBound":false},"initiative":{"hasHesitant":false,"hasLevelHeaded":false,"hasImpLevelHeaded":false,"hasQuick":false},"additionalStats":{},"wildcard":false},"token":{"flags":{},"name":"Blank","displayName":30,"img":"modules/etu-rules/assets/bestiary_tokens/sonya-alvarez-min.png","tint":null,"width":1,"height":1,"scale":1,"mirrorX":false,"mirrorY":false,"lockRotation":false,"rotation":0,"vision":true,"dimSight":0,"brightSight":0,"dimLight":0,"brightLight":0,"sightAngle":0,"lightAngle":0,"lightColor":null,"lightAlpha":1,"lightAnimation":{"speed":5,"intensity":5},"actorId":null,"actorLink":true,"disposition":0,"displayBars":0,"bar1":{"attribute":""},"bar2":{"attribute":""},"randomImg":false,"alpha":1},"items":[{"_id":"UZW0tLJicg0VZOp4","name":"Athletics","type":"skill","data":{"description":"<div class=\"sweb-core\">\n<p>Athletics combines an individual&rsquo;s coordin&shy;ation with learned skills such as climbing, jumping, balancing, biking, wrestling, skiing, swimming, throwing, or catching. Characters who rely on physical power more than coordination can take the @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Brute]{Brute} Edge to link this skill to @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Traits]{Strength} instead of @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Traits]{Agility}.</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"attribute":"agility","isCoreSkill":false,"die":{"sides":6,"modifier":0},"wild-die":{"sides":6}},"sort":100000,"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_nsugutrpau","path":"Skills","color":"#8c160f"},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.swade-core-rules.swade-skills.Athletics"}},"img":"icons/magic/control/buff-strength-muscle-damage.webp","effects":[],"folder":null,"permission":{"default":0}},{"_id":"W5lfcCNjirSPUH42","name":"Common Knowledge","type":"skill","data":{"description":"<div class=\"sweb-core\"><p>Characters roll Common Knowledge to know people, places, and things of their world, including etiquette, geography, culture, popular technology, contacts, and customs.</p></div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"attribute":"smarts","isCoreSkill":false,"die":{"sides":8,"modifier":0},"wild-die":{"sides":6}},"sort":200000,"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_nsugutrpau","path":"Skills","color":"#8c160f"},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.swade-core-rules.swade-skills.Common Knowledge"}},"img":"icons/sundries/documents/document-official-capital.webp","effects":[],"folder":null,"permission":{"default":0}},{"_id":"quj5jF3vNls1j5E3","name":"Notice","type":"skill","data":{"description":"<div class=\"sweb-core\">\n<p>Notice is a hero&rsquo;s general awareness and alertness. It&rsquo;s used to sense sights, sounds, tastes, and smells, spot clues, detect ambushes, spot hidden weapons on a foe, or tell if a rival is lying, frightened, happy, etc.</p>\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Trait Rolls]{Success} conveys basic information&mdash;the character hears movement in the forest, smells distant smoke, or senses someone isn&rsquo;t being completely truthful.</p>\n<p>A @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Raises]{raise} grants more detail, such as the direction of a sound or odor or what topic a person is avoiding or lying about.</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"attribute":"smarts","isCoreSkill":false,"die":{"sides":6,"modifier":0},"wild-die":{"sides":6}},"sort":300000,"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_nsugutrpau","path":"Skills","color":"#8c160f"},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.swade-core-rules.swade-skills.ZvwjzMLxsneptV4T"}},"img":"icons/creatures/eyes/human-single-blue.webp","effects":[],"folder":null,"permission":{"default":0}},{"_id":"TOEzoo2Lf4A5JXOF","name":"Persuasion","type":"skill","data":{"description":"<div class=\"sweb-core\">\n<p>Persuasion is the ability to convince others to do what you want through reason, cajoling, deception, rewards, or other friendly means. Persuasion isn&rsquo;t mind control. It can change someone&rsquo;s attitude but not their goals. A bandit may let you keep a sentimental piece of jewelry with a good Persuasion roll but still takes all your other goods.</p>\n<p>When used to @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Support]{Support} allies it&rsquo;s an unopposed roll. If the target is resistant, it&rsquo;s an @JournalEntry[JBxsGv2wAoAmoCDe]{opposed} roll vs. the target&rsquo;s @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Traits]{Spirit}. The GM should modify the roll as she sees fit based on roleplaying, any pertinent @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Edges]{Edges} or @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Hindrances]{Hindrances} that affect the conversation, and the circumstances.</p>\n<p><strong>Reaction Level:</strong> How much a person is willing to cooperate depends largely on their attitude toward whoever&rsquo;s talking to them. The Game Master can decide how nonplayer characters feel based on the setting, or roll on the @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-tables.Reaction Table]{Reaction Table} if she has no preconceived notions.</p>\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Trait Rolls]{Success} improves the target&rsquo;s attitude one level and a raise improves it two. Further increases aren&rsquo;t generally possible in the same encounter&mdash;it takes individuals a little time to adjust their biases.</p>\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Trait Rolls]{Failure} means the target won&rsquo;t change his mind this scene or until the situation changes in some important way. A @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Trait Rolls]{Critical Failure} also <em>reduces</em> the target&rsquo;s attitude two levels.</p>\n<p>Only one roll should generally be allowed per interaction unless new information is revealed, a substantial reward is offered, etc.</p>\n<p><strong>Networking: </strong>Characters can also use Persuasion as a &ldquo;macro skill,&rdquo; simulating a few hours or an evening&rsquo;s time hobnobbing and socializing to gain favors or information. See @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Networking]{Networking}.</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"attribute":"spirit","isCoreSkill":false,"die":{"sides":6,"modifier":0},"wild-die":{"sides":6}},"sort":400000,"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_nsugutrpau","path":"Skills","color":"#8c160f"},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.swade-core-rules.swade-skills.Persuasion"}},"img":"icons/skills/social/diplomacy-handshake.webp","effects":[],"folder":null,"permission":{"default":0}},{"_id":"8VzaSa3EEDrMz6PR","name":"Stealth","type":"skill","data":{"description":"<div class=\"sweb-core\">\n<p>Stealth is the ability to hide and move quietly. A simple @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Trait Rolls]{success} on a Stealth roll means the character avoids detection if enemies aren&rsquo;t particularly alert. If the character @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Trait Rolls]{fails} the roll, the enemy realizes something is amiss and begins actively searching for whatever roused them.</p>\n<p>Once foes are alerted and active, Stealth is opposed by @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Notice]{Notice} (a @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Trait Rolls]{group roll} if there are many foes.</p>\n<p>The GM should apply any circumstantial penalties to @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Notice]{Notice} rolls for @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Illumination]{darkness}, @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Cover and Obstacles]{cover}, noise, distractions, and any difference in the target&rsquo;s @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Size and Scale]{Scale} (just like when attacking). Sneaking through dry leaves might subtract 2 from the Stealth roll, for example, while spotting someone in the dark uses the @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Illumination]{Illumination} penalty (&minus;4). Don&rsquo;t apply the same modifier to both rolls, however. If Stealth is at &minus;2 for the leaves, don&rsquo;t give Notice a +2 for them as well.</p>\n<p><strong>Sneak Attack: </strong> Sneaking up close enough to make a melee attack <em>always</em> requires an @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Trait Rolls]{opposed} Stealth roll versus the target&rsquo;s @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Notice]{Notice}, whether the guard is actively looking for trouble or not. If successful, the victim is @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Distracted and Vulnerable]{Vulnerable} to the attacker, but only until the attacker&rsquo;s turn ends. With a raise, the attacker has @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.The Drop]{The Drop} instead.</p>\n<p><strong>Movement:</strong> In combat, characters roll Stealth each turn as a @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Actions]{free action} at the end of their move or any action the GM thinks might draw attention.</p>\n<p>Out of combat, the distance moved depends entirely on the situation. The GM might want a roll every minute if the group is sneaking around the perimeter of a defensive position, or every few miles if they&rsquo;re trying to quietly walk the path through a dark forest without alerting the creatures that live there.</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"attribute":"agility","isCoreSkill":false,"die":{"sides":4,"modifier":"0"},"wild-die":{"sides":6}},"sort":500000,"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_nsugutrpau","path":"Skills","color":"#8c160f"},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.swade-core-rules.swade-skills.Stealth"}},"img":"icons/magic/nature/stealth-hide-eyes-green.webp","effects":[],"folder":null,"permission":{"default":0}},{"_id":"BQ3OOQlkZvCl1Lfb","name":"Untrained","type":"skill","data":{"description":"<div class=\"sweb-core\">\n<p>If a character doesn&rsquo;t have a skill for an action he&rsquo;s attempting, he rolls a d4 for his skill die (and a Wild Die if a @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Wild Cards and Extras]{Wild Card}) and subtracts 2 from the total.</p>\n<p>The GM may decide certain tasks cannot be attempted unskilled, such as performing complex surgery or flying a commercial jet.</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"attribute":"agility","isCoreSkill":false,"die":{"sides":4,"modifier":"-2"},"wild-die":{"sides":6}},"sort":1100000,"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_nsugutrpau","path":"Skills","color":"#8c160f"},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.swade-core-rules.swade-skills.zcn1epcU4FEJGGyI"}},"img":"icons/magic/symbols/question-stone-yellow.webp","effects":[],"folder":null,"permission":{"default":0}},{"_id":"uaVAhwDnUDLFZFXm","name":"Unarmed strike","type":"weapon","data":{"description":"","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"quantity":1,"weight":0,"price":0,"equippable":false,"equipped":true,"isVehicular":false,"mods":1,"actions":{"skill":"","skillMod":"","dmgMod":"","additional":{}},"damage":"@str","range":"","rof":"1","ap":"0","minStr":"","shots":"0","currentShots":"0","ammo":"","autoReload":false},"sort":1400000,"flags":{},"img":"icons/skills/melee/unarmed-punch-fist.webp","effects":[],"folder":null,"permission":{"default":0}},{"_id":"GjcL17dCtOeFUvbu","name":"Fighting","type":"skill","data":{"description":"<div class=\"sweb-core\">\n<p>Fighting covers all hand-to-hand (melee) attacks, whether it&rsquo;s with fists, axes, laser swords, or martial arts. See @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Combat]{Chapter Three} for the combat rules and the various maneuvers a warrior might attempt.</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"attribute":"agility","isCoreSkill":false,"die":{"sides":6,"modifier":0},"wild-die":{"sides":6}},"sort":1500000,"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_qals24wpyph","path":"Skills","color":"#8c160f"},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.swade-core-rules.swade-skills.wWiwjPlzAQU3TN9l"}},"img":"icons/skills/melee/hand-grip-sword-white-brown.webp","effects":[],"folder":null,"permission":{"default":0}},{"_id":"lOUi2JoByDSV740w","name":"Habit (Alcoholic)","type":"hindrance","img":"icons/magic/holy/yin-yang-balance-symbol.webp","data":{"description":"<div class=\"sweb-core\">\n<p>Your warrior has an annoying or dangerous compulsion. A @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Characters]{Minor} Habit irritates those around her but isn&rsquo;t dangerous. Maybe she picks her nose, can&rsquo;t stop fiddling with her phone, says &ldquo;y&rsquo;know&rdquo; in the middle of every sentence, or chews and smacks her gum loudly and often. Allies avoid her if possible.</p>\n<p>A @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Characters]{Major} Habit is a physical or mental addiction of some sort that is debilitating or possibly even deadly. This includes drug use, chronic drinking, or perhaps even an addiction to virtual reality in a hightech setting.</p>\n<p>An addict who doesn&rsquo;t get his fix must make a @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Traits]{Vigor} roll every 24 hours he goes without or take a level of @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Fatigue]{Fatigue}.</p>\n<p>Once every 24 hours, a @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Healing]{Healing} roll with some sort of appropriate medicine removes one level of @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Fatigue]{Fatigue} for four hours. After that the Fatigue returns and can only be recovered with the addicting substance.</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"major":true},"effects":[],"folder":"1updrtPaYhKD0fRY","sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"3HvtK4sMp7flYKmT":3,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"flags":{"cf":null,"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.swade-core-rules.swade-hindrances.DvgwzTd4xsaPE77h"}}},{"_id":"FXkjNgX70HUd4vMp","name":"Obese","type":"hindrance","img":"icons/magic/holy/yin-yang-balance-symbol.webp","data":{"description":"<div class=\"sweb-core\">\n<p>Those who carry their weight well have the @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Brawny]{Brawny} Edge. Those who don&rsquo;t are Obese. A character cannot be both @Compendium[swade.edges.Brawny]{Brawny} and Obese, and this @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Hindrances]{Hindrance} can&rsquo;t increase your @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Size and Scale]{Size} above +3. </span></p>\n<p>An Obese hero&rsquo;s @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Size and Scale]{Size} (and therefore @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Characters]{Toughness}) increase by +1. His @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Movement]{Pace} is reduced by 1, and his @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Movement]{running die} by one die type (minimum d4). @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Traits]{Strength} is considered one die type less (minimum d4) for armor and worn gear (not weapons). They may also have difficulty finding armor or @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Common Gear Table]{clothing} that fits or entering confined spaces.</span></p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"major":true},"effects":[{"_id":"GC2tkR9tmhi1ganW","changes":[{"key":"data.stats.size","mode":2,"value":"1"},{"key":"data.stats.speed.value","mode":2,"value":"-1"},{"key":"data.stats.speed.runningDie","mode":2,"value":"-2"},{"key":"data.attributes.strength.die.sides","mode":2,"value":"-2"}],"disabled":false,"duration":{"startTime":null},"icon":"icons/magic/holy/yin-yang-balance-symbol.webp","label":"Obese","transfer":true,"flags":{},"tint":null}],"folder":"1updrtPaYhKD0fRY","sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"3HvtK4sMp7flYKmT":3,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"flags":{"cf":null,"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.swade-core-rules.swade-hindrances.W7sBGVEV7SxVJ5LY"}}},{"_id":"gcbqDP4ePVf2kg4O","name":"Kitchen Knife","type":"weapon","img":"icons/weapons/daggers/knife-engraved-black.webp","data":{"description":"","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"quantity":1,"weight":1,"price":2,"equippable":false,"equipped":true,"isVehicular":false,"mods":1,"actions":{"skill":"Fighting","skillMod":"","dmgMod":"","additional":{"oyxuzdjora":{"name":"Athletics (throwing)","type":"skill","rof":null,"skillMod":"","skillOverride":"Athletics","shotsUsed":null}}},"damage":"@str+d4","range":"3/6/12","rof":"1","ap":"0","minStr":"d4","shots":"0","currentShots":"0","ammo":"","autoReload":false},"effects":[],"folder":"ofLOMYgHLqfG1MyP","sort":400001,"permission":{"default":0,"ZvqefCj0L7TxJS56":3,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"flags":{"journal-links":{},"core":{"sourceId":"Item.GxVNY83rIxMpxCqB"}}},{"_id":"V4o3jDNEfg9JdmfP","name":"Boating","type":"skill","img":"icons/environment/settlement/ship.webp","data":{"description":"<div class=\"sweb-core\"><p>Characters with this skill can handle most any boat or ship common to their setting. They also know how to handle common tasks associated with their vessel such as tying knots, rigging sails, or following currents.</p></div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"attribute":"agility","isCoreSkill":false,"die":{"sides":6,"modifier":0},"wild-die":{"sides":6}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_azxylmvr7yo","path":"Skills","color":"#008000"},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.swade-core-rules.swade-skills.WMWgIVDuAW4cHxj2"}}},{"_id":"hgqtHmh5rVEZXQRp","name":"Language (Common)","type":"skill","img":"icons/sundries/documents/document-letter-formal-tan.webp","data":{"description":"<div class=\"sweb-core\">\n<p>In some settings, such as those that focus on pulp action or &ldquo;planetary romance&rdquo; (where characters frequently travel among many strange civilizations), speaking various languages can simply be roleplayed with halting dialogue and campy accents that start out a little difficult and are quickly forgotten. The GM may ignore this skill altogether in these settings, or use the @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Multiple Languages]{Multiple Languages} &shy;option in the @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Setting Rules]{Setting Rules}.</p>\n<p>In more realistic settings, communication can be a major barrier that requires characters to put skill points into additional languages. In a 1980s World War Three game, for example, a group of United Nations paratroopers won&rsquo;t be able to speak with their foes unless they take Russian, Polish, or other languages common to the Warsaw Pact.</p>\n<p>If the Language skill is in use, it should be listed as Language (Spanish), Language (American Sign Language), etc. A character&rsquo;s die type also notes how fluent he is in it. (Characters start with a d8 in their own Language.)</p>\n<div class=\"sweb-core\">\n<table class=\"table value-table\"><caption class=\"table-caption\">\n<h2 class=\"table-title\">Language Proficiency</h2>\n</caption>\n<tbody>\n<tr class=\"table-header-row\">\n<th class=\"table-column-header\" scope=\"col\">Skill</th>\n<th class=\"table-column-header\" scope=\"col\">Ability</th>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td>d4</td>\n<td>The character can read, write and speak common words and phrases.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>d6</td>\n<td>The speaker can carry on a prolonged but occasionally halting conversation.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>d8</td>\n<td>The character can speak fluently.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>d10</td>\n<td>The hero can mimic other dialects within the language.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>d12</td>\n<td>The speaker can masterfully recite important literary or oral works.</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>\n</div>\n<p><strong>Limited: </strong>Use whichever skill is lowest when performing an action that requires knowledge of a foreign language. @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Intimidation]{Intimidation} (if verbal), @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Persuasion]{Persuasion}, @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Research]{Research}, @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Taunt]{Taunt}, etc., are all limited by the character&rsquo;s Language skill.</p>\n<p>This limitation never applies to a character&rsquo;s native tongue.</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"attribute":"smarts","isCoreSkill":false,"die":{"sides":8,"modifier":0},"wild-die":{"sides":6}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_azxylmvr7yo","path":"Skills","color":"#008000"},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.swade-core-rules.swade-skills.XIuR2IyQtewm5BZP"}}},{"_id":"ENKI20IumFFXneOR","name":"Language (Dwarvish)","type":"skill","img":"icons/sundries/documents/document-letter-formal-tan.webp","data":{"description":"<div class=\"sweb-core\">\n<p>In some settings, such as those that focus on pulp action or &ldquo;planetary romance&rdquo; (where characters frequently travel among many strange civilizations), speaking various languages can simply be roleplayed with halting dialogue and campy accents that start out a little difficult and are quickly forgotten. The GM may ignore this skill altogether in these settings, or use the @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Multiple Languages]{Multiple Languages} &shy;option in the @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Setting Rules]{Setting Rules}.</p>\n<p>In more realistic settings, communication can be a major barrier that requires characters to put skill points into additional languages. In a 1980s World War Three game, for example, a group of United Nations paratroopers won&rsquo;t be able to speak with their foes unless they take Russian, Polish, or other languages common to the Warsaw Pact.</p>\n<p>If the Language skill is in use, it should be listed as Language (Spanish), Language (American Sign Language), etc. A character&rsquo;s die type also notes how fluent he is in it. (Characters start with a d8 in their own Language.)</p>\n<div class=\"sweb-core\">\n<table class=\"table value-table\"><caption class=\"table-caption\">\n<h2 class=\"table-title\">Language Proficiency</h2>\n</caption>\n<tbody>\n<tr class=\"table-header-row\">\n<th class=\"table-column-header\" scope=\"col\">Skill</th>\n<th class=\"table-column-header\" scope=\"col\">Ability</th>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td>d4</td>\n<td>The character can read, write and speak common words and phrases.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>d6</td>\n<td>The speaker can carry on a prolonged but occasionally halting conversation.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>d8</td>\n<td>The character can speak fluently.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>d10</td>\n<td>The hero can mimic other dialects within the language.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>d12</td>\n<td>The speaker can masterfully recite important literary or oral works.</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>\n</div>\n<p><strong>Limited: </strong>Use whichever skill is lowest when performing an action that requires knowledge of a foreign language. @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Intimidation]{Intimidation} (if verbal), @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Persuasion]{Persuasion}, @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Research]{Research}, @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Taunt]{Taunt}, etc., are all limited by the character&rsquo;s Language skill.</p>\n<p>This limitation never applies to a character&rsquo;s native tongue.</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"attribute":"smarts","isCoreSkill":false,"die":{"sides":8,"modifier":0},"wild-die":{"sides":6}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_azxylmvr7yo","path":"Skills","color":"#008000"},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.swade-core-rules.swade-skills.XIuR2IyQtewm5BZP"}}},{"_id":"o4zkG0eHpwbmz0ie","name":"Language (Goblin)","type":"skill","img":"icons/sundries/documents/document-letter-formal-tan.webp","data":{"description":"<div class=\"sweb-core\">\n<p>In some settings, such as those that focus on pulp action or &ldquo;planetary romance&rdquo; (where characters frequently travel among many strange civilizations), speaking various languages can simply be roleplayed with halting dialogue and campy accents that start out a little difficult and are quickly forgotten. The GM may ignore this skill altogether in these settings, or use the @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Multiple Languages]{Multiple Languages} &shy;option in the @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Setting Rules]{Setting Rules}.</p>\n<p>In more realistic settings, communication can be a major barrier that requires characters to put skill points into additional languages. In a 1980s World War Three game, for example, a group of United Nations paratroopers won&rsquo;t be able to speak with their foes unless they take Russian, Polish, or other languages common to the Warsaw Pact.</p>\n<p>If the Language skill is in use, it should be listed as Language (Spanish), Language (American Sign Language), etc. A character&rsquo;s die type also notes how fluent he is in it. (Characters start with a d8 in their own Language.)</p>\n<div class=\"sweb-core\">\n<table class=\"table value-table\"><caption class=\"table-caption\">\n<h2 class=\"table-title\">Language Proficiency</h2>\n</caption>\n<tbody>\n<tr class=\"table-header-row\">\n<th class=\"table-column-header\" scope=\"col\">Skill</th>\n<th class=\"table-column-header\" scope=\"col\">Ability</th>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td>d4</td>\n<td>The character can read, write and speak common words and phrases.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>d6</td>\n<td>The speaker can carry on a prolonged but occasionally halting conversation.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>d8</td>\n<td>The character can speak fluently.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>d10</td>\n<td>The hero can mimic other dialects within the language.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>d12</td>\n<td>The speaker can masterfully recite important literary or oral works.</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>\n</div>\n<p><strong>Limited: </strong>Use whichever skill is lowest when performing an action that requires knowledge of a foreign language. @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Intimidation]{Intimidation} (if verbal), @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Persuasion]{Persuasion}, @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Research]{Research}, @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Taunt]{Taunt}, etc., are all limited by the character&rsquo;s Language skill.</p>\n<p>This limitation never applies to a character&rsquo;s native tongue.</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"attribute":"smarts","isCoreSkill":false,"die":{"sides":6,"modifier":0},"wild-die":{"sides":6}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_azxylmvr7yo","path":"Skills","color":"#008000"},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.swade-core-rules.swade-skills.XIuR2IyQtewm5BZP"}}},{"_id":"dIlOnbuBe7q8UlNB","name":"Performance","type":"skill","img":"icons/tools/instruments/lute-gold-brown.webp","data":{"description":"<div class=\"sweb-core\">\n<p>A good entertainer can lift the spirits, rally a crowd to action, or simply earn a few bucks from the locals. Specifics depend on the situation, setting, and how well the character is known in the area.</p>\n<p>Performance covers singing, acting, playing an instrument, or similar tasks that require an audience to appreciate.</p>\n<p><strong>Raising Funds:</strong> The amount of money a character can raise by performing is extremely subjective, but as a general rule a @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Trait Rolls]{successful} performance raises 20% of the setting's @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Characters]{Starting Funds} with a success and 30% with a raise. The GM can multiply this amount by the performer's @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Advancement]{Rank} if she feels it's appropriate. These numbers work for typical performers who might be known in a small establishment or area. Larger performances can greatly boost the performer's fee, but also require more time, energy, and setup.</p>\n<p><strong>Deception: </strong>Performance can be used instead of @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Persuasion]{Persuasion} if the character is attempting to deceive, bluff, or disguise herself and the GM agrees it makes sense in the context of the situation.</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"attribute":"spirit","isCoreSkill":false,"die":{"sides":4,"modifier":0},"wild-die":{"sides":6}},"effects":[],"folder":"cgfmurTJRwbCvmCc","sort":2400001,"permission":{"default":0,"3HvtK4sMp7flYKmT":3,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_qals24wpyph","path":"Skills","color":"#8c160f"},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.swade-core-rules.swade-skills.SJ1nN0CmOHNQhfOQ"}}},{"_id":"e2DoL9jjQmdLcPHg","name":"Survival","type":"skill","img":"icons/environment/settlement/tent.webp","data":{"description":"<div class=\"sweb-core\">\n<p>Survival allows a character to find food, water, or shelter in hostile environments. It can also be used to navigate wilderness environments, figure out which plants are good to eat and which aren&rsquo;t, and so on.</p>\n<p>A @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Trait Rolls]{successful} Survival roll provides enough food and water for one person for one day; or five people with a @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Raises]{raise}.</p>\n<p>More detailed information on @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Hunger]{Hunger} and @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Thirst]{Thirst} can be found under @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Hazards]{Hazards} section.</p>\n<p><strong>Tracking: </strong>Survival can also be used to detect and follow tracks. Each roll generally covers following the tracks for one mile, but the GM should adjust this as needed for specific circumstances.</p>\n<p>The Game Master should assign a @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Trait Rolls]{bonus or penalty} based on the target, environment, and time. Tracking a large group that recently passed through a snow-covered area might grant a bonus of +4, while following a single person over rocks and streams after more than a day incurs a &minus;4 penalty.</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"attribute":"smarts","isCoreSkill":false,"die":{"sides":4,"modifier":0},"wild-die":{"sides":6}},"effects":[],"folder":"cgfmurTJRwbCvmCc","sort":1075001,"permission":{"default":0,"3HvtK4sMp7flYKmT":3,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_qals24wpyph","path":"Skills","color":"#8c160f"},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.swade-core-rules.swade-skills.15aEAJjDEjQy4fHF"}}}],"effects":[{"_id":"kBSy9tQ1wpNG3IH9","changes":[{"key":"data.stats.size","mode":2,"value":"1"},{"key":"data.stats.speed.value","mode":2,"value":"-1"},{"key":"data.stats.speed.runningDie","mode":2,"value":"-2"},{"key":"data.attributes.strength.die.sides","mode":2,"value":"-2"}],"disabled":false,"duration":{"startTime":28973116800},"icon":"icons/magic/holy/yin-yang-balance-symbol.webp","label":"Obese","origin":"Actor.gjZ3MYnC5l4iKY6y.Item.FXkjNgX70HUd4vMp","tint":null,"transfer":false,"flags":{}}],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"flags":{"journal-links":{"references":{}},"cf":{"id":"temp_3a04s0jrz4j","path":"Pirates of Cyre Bestiary#/CF_SEP/NPC's","color":"#000000"}}}
{"_id":"JdZmTO2mCUBMDTaY","name":"Master Scourge","type":"npc","img":"https://assets.forge-vtt.com/5f43f8ea1a91d63438d13159/artwork-adventures/pirates-of-cyre/characters/master-scourge.webp","data":{"attributes":{"agility":{"die":{"sides":8,"modifier":0},"wild-die":{"sides":6}},"smarts":{"die":{"sides":6,"modifier":0},"wild-die":{"sides":6},"animal":false},"spirit":{"die":{"sides":6,"modifier":0},"wild-die":{"sides":6},"unShakeBonus":0},"strength":{"die":{"sides":6,"modifier":0},"wild-die":{"sides":6},"encumbranceSteps":0},"vigor":{"die":{"sides":8,"modifier":0},"wild-die":{"sides":6}}},"stats":{"speed":{"runningDie":6,"runningMod":0,"value":6},"toughness":{"value":0,"armor":0,"modifier":0},"parry":{"value":6,"modifier":0},"size":0},"details":{"biography":{"value":"<div>\n<p>Master Scourge is a sneering man with a braided beard and a mouth full of gold teeth. His body is tall and thin, and even his long coat and heavy boots fail to give any impression of strength or bulk.</p>\n</div>"},"species":{"name":""},"currency":500,"wealth":{"die":6,"modifier":0,"wild-die":6},"conviction":{"value":0,"active":false},"autoCalcToughness":true,"autoCalcParry":true},"powerPoints":{},"fatigue":{"value":0,"min":0,"max":2},"wounds":{"value":0,"min":0,"max":3,"ignored":0},"advances":{"value":0,"rank":"Novice","details":""},"bennies":{"value":2,"max":2},"status":{"isShaken":false,"isDistracted":false,"isVulnerable":false,"isStunned":false,"isEntangled":false,"isBound":false},"initiative":{"hasHesitant":false,"hasLevelHeaded":false,"hasImpLevelHeaded":false,"hasQuick":true},"additionalStats":{},"wildcard":true},"token":{"flags":{},"name":"Blank","displayName":30,"img":"modules/etu-rules/assets/bestiary_tokens/sonya-alvarez-min.png","tint":null,"width":1,"height":1,"scale":1,"mirrorX":false,"mirrorY":false,"lockRotation":false,"rotation":0,"vision":true,"dimSight":0,"brightSight":0,"dimLight":0,"brightLight":0,"sightAngle":0,"lightAngle":0,"lightColor":null,"lightAlpha":1,"lightAnimation":{"speed":5,"intensity":5},"actorId":null,"actorLink":true,"disposition":0,"displayBars":0,"bar1":{"attribute":""},"bar2":{"attribute":""},"randomImg":false,"alpha":1},"items":[{"_id":"UZW0tLJicg0VZOp4","name":"Athletics","type":"skill","data":{"description":"<div class=\"sweb-core\">\n<p>Athletics combines an individual&rsquo;s coordin&shy;ation with learned skills such as climbing, jumping, balancing, biking, wrestling, skiing, swimming, throwing, or catching. Characters who rely on physical power more than coordination can take the @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Brute]{Brute} Edge to link this skill to @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Traits]{Strength} instead of @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Traits]{Agility}.</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"attribute":"agility","isCoreSkill":false,"die":{"sides":8,"modifier":0},"wild-die":{"sides":6}},"sort":100000,"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_nsugutrpau","path":"Skills","color":"#8c160f"},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.swade-core-rules.swade-skills.Athletics"}},"img":"icons/magic/control/buff-strength-muscle-damage.webp","effects":[],"folder":null,"permission":{"default":0}},{"_id":"W5lfcCNjirSPUH42","name":"Common Knowledge","type":"skill","data":{"description":"<div class=\"sweb-core\"><p>Characters roll Common Knowledge to know people, places, and things of their world, including etiquette, geography, culture, popular technology, contacts, and customs.</p></div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"attribute":"smarts","isCoreSkill":false,"die":{"sides":4,"modifier":0},"wild-die":{"sides":6}},"sort":200000,"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_nsugutrpau","path":"Skills","color":"#8c160f"},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.swade-core-rules.swade-skills.Common Knowledge"}},"img":"icons/sundries/documents/document-official-capital.webp","effects":[],"folder":null,"permission":{"default":0}},{"_id":"quj5jF3vNls1j5E3","name":"Notice","type":"skill","data":{"description":"<div class=\"sweb-core\">\n<p>Notice is a hero&rsquo;s general awareness and alertness. It&rsquo;s used to sense sights, sounds, tastes, and smells, spot clues, detect ambushes, spot hidden weapons on a foe, or tell if a rival is lying, frightened, happy, etc.</p>\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Trait Rolls]{Success} conveys basic information&mdash;the character hears movement in the forest, smells distant smoke, or senses someone isn&rsquo;t being completely truthful.</p>\n<p>A @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Raises]{raise} grants more detail, such as the direction of a sound or odor or what topic a person is avoiding or lying about.</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"attribute":"smarts","isCoreSkill":false,"die":{"sides":8,"modifier":0},"wild-die":{"sides":6}},"sort":300000,"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_nsugutrpau","path":"Skills","color":"#8c160f"},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.swade-core-rules.swade-skills.ZvwjzMLxsneptV4T"}},"img":"icons/creatures/eyes/human-single-blue.webp","effects":[],"folder":null,"permission":{"default":0}},{"_id":"TOEzoo2Lf4A5JXOF","name":"Persuasion","type":"skill","data":{"description":"<div class=\"sweb-core\">\n<p>Persuasion is the ability to convince others to do what you want through reason, cajoling, deception, rewards, or other friendly means. Persuasion isn&rsquo;t mind control. It can change someone&rsquo;s attitude but not their goals. A bandit may let you keep a sentimental piece of jewelry with a good Persuasion roll but still takes all your other goods.</p>\n<p>When used to @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Support]{Support} allies it&rsquo;s an unopposed roll. If the target is resistant, it&rsquo;s an @JournalEntry[JBxsGv2wAoAmoCDe]{opposed} roll vs. the target&rsquo;s @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Traits]{Spirit}. The GM should modify the roll as she sees fit based on roleplaying, any pertinent @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Edges]{Edges} or @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Hindrances]{Hindrances} that affect the conversation, and the circumstances.</p>\n<p><strong>Reaction Level:</strong> How much a person is willing to cooperate depends largely on their attitude toward whoever&rsquo;s talking to them. The Game Master can decide how nonplayer characters feel based on the setting, or roll on the @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-tables.Reaction Table]{Reaction Table} if she has no preconceived notions.</p>\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Trait Rolls]{Success} improves the target&rsquo;s attitude one level and a raise improves it two. Further increases aren&rsquo;t generally possible in the same encounter&mdash;it takes individuals a little time to adjust their biases.</p>\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Trait Rolls]{Failure} means the target won&rsquo;t change his mind this scene or until the situation changes in some important way. A @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Trait Rolls]{Critical Failure} also <em>reduces</em> the target&rsquo;s attitude two levels.</p>\n<p>Only one roll should generally be allowed per interaction unless new information is revealed, a substantial reward is offered, etc.</p>\n<p><strong>Networking: </strong>Characters can also use Persuasion as a &ldquo;macro skill,&rdquo; simulating a few hours or an evening&rsquo;s time hobnobbing and socializing to gain favors or information. See @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Networking]{Networking}.</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"attribute":"spirit","isCoreSkill":false,"die":{"sides":6,"modifier":0},"wild-die":{"sides":6}},"sort":400000,"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_nsugutrpau","path":"Skills","color":"#8c160f"},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.swade-core-rules.swade-skills.Persuasion"}},"img":"icons/skills/social/diplomacy-handshake.webp","effects":[],"folder":null,"permission":{"default":0}},{"_id":"8VzaSa3EEDrMz6PR","name":"Stealth","type":"skill","data":{"description":"<div class=\"sweb-core\">\n<p>Stealth is the ability to hide and move quietly. A simple @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Trait Rolls]{success} on a Stealth roll means the character avoids detection if enemies aren&rsquo;t particularly alert. If the character @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Trait Rolls]{fails} the roll, the enemy realizes something is amiss and begins actively searching for whatever roused them.</p>\n<p>Once foes are alerted and active, Stealth is opposed by @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Notice]{Notice} (a @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Trait Rolls]{group roll} if there are many foes.</p>\n<p>The GM should apply any circumstantial penalties to @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Notice]{Notice} rolls for @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Illumination]{darkness}, @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Cover and Obstacles]{cover}, noise, distractions, and any difference in the target&rsquo;s @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Size and Scale]{Scale} (just like when attacking). Sneaking through dry leaves might subtract 2 from the Stealth roll, for example, while spotting someone in the dark uses the @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Illumination]{Illumination} penalty (&minus;4). Don&rsquo;t apply the same modifier to both rolls, however. If Stealth is at &minus;2 for the leaves, don&rsquo;t give Notice a +2 for them as well.</p>\n<p><strong>Sneak Attack: </strong> Sneaking up close enough to make a melee attack <em>always</em> requires an @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Trait Rolls]{opposed} Stealth roll versus the target&rsquo;s @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Notice]{Notice}, whether the guard is actively looking for trouble or not. If successful, the victim is @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Distracted and Vulnerable]{Vulnerable} to the attacker, but only until the attacker&rsquo;s turn ends. With a raise, the attacker has @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.The Drop]{The Drop} instead.</p>\n<p><strong>Movement:</strong> In combat, characters roll Stealth each turn as a @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Actions]{free action} at the end of their move or any action the GM thinks might draw attention.</p>\n<p>Out of combat, the distance moved depends entirely on the situation. The GM might want a roll every minute if the group is sneaking around the perimeter of a defensive position, or every few miles if they&rsquo;re trying to quietly walk the path through a dark forest without alerting the creatures that live there.</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"attribute":"agility","isCoreSkill":false,"die":{"sides":8,"modifier":0},"wild-die":{"sides":6}},"sort":500000,"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_nsugutrpau","path":"Skills","color":"#8c160f"},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.swade-core-rules.swade-skills.Stealth"}},"img":"icons/magic/nature/stealth-hide-eyes-green.webp","effects":[],"folder":null,"permission":{"default":0}},{"_id":"BQ3OOQlkZvCl1Lfb","name":"Untrained","type":"skill","data":{"description":"<div class=\"sweb-core\">\n<p>If a character doesn&rsquo;t have a skill for an action he&rsquo;s attempting, he rolls a d4 for his skill die (and a Wild Die if a @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Wild Cards and Extras]{Wild Card}) and subtracts 2 from the total.</p>\n<p>The GM may decide certain tasks cannot be attempted unskilled, such as performing complex surgery or flying a commercial jet.</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"attribute":"agility","isCoreSkill":false,"die":{"sides":4,"modifier":"-2"},"wild-die":{"sides":6}},"sort":1100000,"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_nsugutrpau","path":"Skills","color":"#8c160f"},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.swade-core-rules.swade-skills.zcn1epcU4FEJGGyI"}},"img":"icons/magic/symbols/question-stone-yellow.webp","effects":[],"folder":null,"permission":{"default":0}},{"_id":"uaVAhwDnUDLFZFXm","name":"Unarmed strike","type":"weapon","data":{"description":"","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"quantity":1,"weight":0,"price":0,"equippable":false,"equipped":true,"isVehicular":false,"mods":1,"actions":{"skill":"","skillMod":"","dmgMod":"","additional":{}},"damage":"@str","range":"","rof":"1","ap":"0","minStr":"","shots":"0","currentShots":"0","ammo":"","autoReload":false},"sort":1400000,"flags":{},"img":"icons/skills/melee/unarmed-punch-fist.webp","effects":[],"folder":null,"permission":{"default":0}},{"_id":"GjcL17dCtOeFUvbu","name":"Fighting","type":"skill","data":{"description":"<div class=\"sweb-core\">\n<p>Fighting covers all hand-to-hand (melee) attacks, whether it&rsquo;s with fists, axes, laser swords, or martial arts. See @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Combat]{Chapter Three} for the combat rules and the various maneuvers a warrior might attempt.</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"attribute":"agility","isCoreSkill":false,"die":{"sides":8,"modifier":0},"wild-die":{"sides":6}},"sort":1500000,"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_qals24wpyph","path":"Skills","color":"#8c160f"},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.swade-core-rules.swade-skills.wWiwjPlzAQU3TN9l"}},"img":"icons/skills/melee/hand-grip-sword-white-brown.webp","effects":[],"folder":null,"permission":{"default":0}},{"_id":"6Ier1mvn4BHudZkK","name":"Boating","type":"skill","img":"icons/environment/settlement/ship.webp","data":{"description":"<div class=\"sweb-core\"><p>Characters with this skill can handle most any boat or ship common to their setting. They also know how to handle common tasks associated with their vessel such as tying knots, rigging sails, or following currents.</p></div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"attribute":"agility","isCoreSkill":false,"die":{"sides":8,"modifier":0},"wild-die":{"sides":6}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"3HvtK4sMp7flYKmT":3,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_qals24wpyph","path":"Skills","color":"#8c160f"},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.swade-core-rules.swade-skills.WMWgIVDuAW4cHxj2"}}},{"_id":"1kzaTdRoipFAiPwN","name":"Intimidation","type":"skill","img":"icons/skills/wounds/injury-face-impact-orange.webp","data":{"description":"<div class=\"sweb-core\">\n<p>Intimidation is the art of frightening an opponent so that he backs down, reveals information, or flees.</p>\n<p>Intimidation is an @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Trait Rolls]{opposed roll} resisted by the opponent&rsquo;s @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Traits]{Spirit}. In combat, this is a @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Test]{Test}. Out of combat, a successful roll means the foe backs down for the most part, reveals some information, or slinks away when the opportunity presents itself.</p>\n<p>A @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Raises]{raise} might mean he backs down for the remainder of the scene, spills all the beans, or runs away as fast as he can.</p>\n<p>In or out of combat, a @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Trait Rolls]{Critical Failure} means the target is immune to this character&rsquo;s Intimidation attempts for the remainder of this encounter!</p>\n<p><strong>Networking:</strong> Intimidation can also be used as a &ldquo;macro&rdquo; skill to simulate several hours of working the streets. See @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Networking]{Networking} to see how to crack some heads for favors or information.</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"attribute":"spirit","isCoreSkill":false,"die":{"sides":8,"modifier":0},"wild-die":{"sides":6}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"3HvtK4sMp7flYKmT":3,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_qals24wpyph","path":"Skills","color":"#8c160f"},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.swade-core-rules.swade-skills.RrgAZp50CgQyyY6w"}}},{"_id":"uoRshBWE0ihCmMES","name":"Shooting","type":"skill","img":"icons/skills/ranged/target-bullseye-arrow-glowing.webp","data":{"description":"<div class=\"sweb-core\">\n<p>Shooting covers all attempts to hit a target with a ranged weapon such as a bow, pistol, or rocket launcher (thrown weapons use @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Athletics]{Athletics}). See @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Combat]{Chapter Three} for details on ranged combat.</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"attribute":"agility","isCoreSkill":false,"die":{"sides":8,"modifier":0},"wild-die":{"sides":6}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"3HvtK4sMp7flYKmT":3,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_qals24wpyph","path":"Skills","color":"#8c160f"},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.swade-core-rules.swade-skills.sOHfVvBDhe3Oy3r1"}}},{"_id":"o3ChBi570IETeE8m","name":"Thievery","type":"skill","img":"icons/skills/social/theft-pickpocket-bribery-brown.webp","data":{"description":"<div class=\"sweb-core\">\n<p>Lockpicking, safecracking, picking pockets, sleight of hand, setting and disabling traps and similar acts of misdirection, sabotage, subterfuge, and manipulation are called Thievery.</p>\n<p>If used to pick a lock, crack a safe, disable a trap, or perform a simple unopposed action, @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Trait Rolls]{success} opens or disables the device, and a @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Raises]{raise} does it in less time, without tripping alarms, or whatever else the GM feels is appropriate.</p>\n<p>Sleight of hand, hiding or planting an item, or picking a pocket require a simple @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Trait Rolls]{success}. If foes are actively watching the character, Thievery is @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Trait Rolls]{opposed} by @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Notice]{Notice}.</p>\n<p>The Game Master should assign @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Trait Rolls]{penalties} for particularly difficult circumstances. Picking a heavy padlock might have a &minus;4 penalty, while hiding a revolver in bulky winter clothing might grant a +1 bonus. @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Trait Rolls]{Failure} typically means the character is spotted or it takes too much time (after which the character can try again). A @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Trait Rolls]{Critical Failure} typically sets off the trap, alerts the victim, or jams the device so that it must be opened or interacted with in a different way.</p>\n<p><strong>Limited: </strong>Using Thievery on an electronic device, such as a keypad, is limited by the thief&rsquo;s @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Electronics]{Electronics} skill. Use the lowest of the two skills.</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"attribute":"agility","isCoreSkill":false,"die":{"sides":6,"modifier":0},"wild-die":{"sides":6}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"3HvtK4sMp7flYKmT":3,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_qals24wpyph","path":"Skills","color":"#8c160f"},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.swade-core-rules.swade-skills.wZbyJkisWIfmcZNt"}}},{"_id":"k8v1L207iHau3c21","name":"Deception","type":"skill","img":"icons/skills/toxins/poison-skull-herbs-bottle-pink.webp","data":{"description":"<div class=\"sweb-core\">\n<p>Deception determines whether the hero can convincingly hide the truth, either verbally or through her actions. This deception can encompass everything from misleading others through ambiguity to telling outright lies.</p>\n<p>Typical situations include trying to fast-talk a guard, con a merchant, dull someone's suspicions with false assurances, or maintain a straight face while telling a blatant lie.</p>\n<p>Usually, a character successfully passing herself off in a disguise, or trying to impersonate the sound of someone else's voice would be a @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Performance]{Performance} check rather than a deception check. </p>\n<p><em><strong>Source: Savage Eberron</strong></em></p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"attribute":"spirit","isCoreSkill":false,"die":{"sides":8,"modifier":0},"wild-die":{"sides":6}},"effects":[],"folder":"vdiWDU7Bqdgk8RH2","sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"flags":{"journal-links":{},"core":{"sourceId":"Item.E0BVumGwbaczoPjD"},"cf":null}},{"_id":"hwO64Y6PkFzE7SMw","name":"Leather Armor","type":"armor","img":"icons/equipment/chest/breastplate-layered-grey.webp","data":{"description":"","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"quantity":1,"weight":3,"price":5,"equippable":false,"equipped":true,"minStr":"d4","armor":1,"isNaturalArmor":false,"locations":{"head":false,"torso":true,"arms":true,"legs":false}},"effects":[],"folder":"XQoSmfkzvuK8FNo1","sort":100000,"permission":{"default":0,"ZvqefCj0L7TxJS56":3,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"flags":{"journal-links":{},"core":{"sourceId":"Item.PRPRsNmJyfvoy6hH"}}},{"_id":"R5nE2NWsRvRUQICV","name":"Yellow","type":"hindrance","img":"icons/magic/holy/yin-yang-balance-symbol.webp","data":{"description":"<div class=\"sweb-core\">\n<p>Not everyone has ice water in their veins. Your hero is squeamish at the sight of blood and gore and terrified of coming to harm. He subtracts 2 from @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Fear]{Fear} </span>checks and when resisting @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Intimidation]{Intimidation}.</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"major":true},"effects":[],"folder":"1updrtPaYhKD0fRY","sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"3HvtK4sMp7flYKmT":3,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"flags":{"cf":null,"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.swade-core-rules.swade-hindrances.YZW0gutCe8gKBVnn"}}},{"_id":"g0QRC9Fnyn6VyRFj","name":"Greedy","type":"hindrance","img":"icons/magic/holy/yin-yang-balance-symbol.webp","data":{"description":"<div class=\"sweb-core\">\n<p>A miser measures worth in material possessions or wealth. If a @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Characters]{Minor} Hindrance, he argues bitterly for more than his fair share of any loot or reward the party might come across. As a @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Characters]{Major} @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Hindrances]{Hindrance}, he fights over anything he considers unfair, and may even kill for it if he feels slighted or covets something he cannot have.</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"major":false},"effects":[],"folder":"1updrtPaYhKD0fRY","sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"3HvtK4sMp7flYKmT":3,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"flags":{"cf":null,"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.swade-core-rules.swade-hindrances.rIWvJoLH8WegsbrL"}}},{"_id":"U1dF3bixY2xCw91a","name":"Mean","type":"hindrance","img":"icons/magic/holy/yin-yang-balance-symbol.webp","data":{"description":"<div class=\"sweb-core\">\n<p>This curmudgeon is ill-tempered and disagreeable. He has trouble doing anything kind for anyone else, must be paid for his troubles, and doesn&rsquo;t accept awards or favors graciously. Besides the obvious roleplaying issues, Mean characters subtract 1 from @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Persuasion]{Persuasion} @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Trait Rolls]{rolls}.</span></p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"major":false},"effects":[],"folder":"1updrtPaYhKD0fRY","sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"3HvtK4sMp7flYKmT":3,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"flags":{"cf":null,"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.swade-core-rules.swade-hindrances.sNgSwqh2fGyM6i14"}}},{"_id":"YibKi8hNWDOzbFQu","name":"Rogue","type":"edge","img":"icons/skills/melee/strike-dagger-skull-white.webp","data":{"description":"<div class=\"sweb-core\">\n<p>Life is an endless adventure for those who live by their wits. Ever just one step ahead of danger, rogues bank on their cunning, skill, and charm to bend fate to their favor. Never knowing what to expect, they tend to prepare for everything. Out of necessity, they become adept manipulators, agile acrobats, or shadowy stalkers. They are thieves and gamblers, fast talkers and diplomats, bandits and bounty hunters, or explorers and investigators.</p>\n<p>Although many rogues favor the opportunities of towns and cities, some embrace life on the road. They wander from place to place, meeting exotic people and facing fantastic danger in pursuit of endless riches. In the end, all rogues desire to shape their fates and live life on their own terms.</p>\n<p>Rogues gain the following abilities:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Rogue Armor Restriction (Light)]{Rogue Armor Restriction (Light)}</li>\n<li>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Skill Monkey]{Skill Monkey}</li>\n<li>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Trap Sense]{Trap Sense}</li>\n</ul>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Novice, Agility d6+, Notice d6+, Stealth d6+, Thievery d6+"}},"effects":[],"folder":"zzeiXM6YEGI9jNRc","sort":500000,"permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"flags":{"journal-links":{},"core":{"sourceId":"Item.UBXzgLMsycquNmh2"}}},{"_id":"mPsjNqsQiXccjHZ7","name":"Skill Monkey","type":"edge","img":"icons/skills/melee/strike-dagger-skull-white.webp","data":{"description":"<div class=\"sweb-core\">\n<p>To survive, rogues have become adept at learning all sorts of skills and trades, both to survive and to con people. Whether trained by a mentor, a guild member, a house, or the streets, rogues have picked up additional skills and training.</p>\n<p>Rogues gain two skill points they can put into increasing the die type of two of the following skills: @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Athletics]{Athletics}, @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Common Knowledge]{Common Knowledge}, @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Deception]{Deception}, @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Gambling]{Gambling}, @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Intimidation]{Intimidation}, @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Notice]{Notice}, @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Performance]{Performance}, @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Persuasion]{Persuasion}, @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Stealth]{Stealth}, or @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Thievery]{Thievery}.</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Novice, Rogue"}},"effects":[],"folder":"zzeiXM6YEGI9jNRc","sort":400000,"permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"flags":{"journal-links":{},"core":{"sourceId":"Item.Voq7KPCbPVjrEjZP"}}},{"_id":"x0RriqTjEan86VSh","name":"Trap Sense","type":"edge","img":"icons/skills/melee/strike-dagger-skull-white.webp","data":{"description":"<div class=\"sweb-core\">\n<p>Rogues are adept at spotting and defeating all but the most clever snares and traps. They get a @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Notice]{Notice} roll anytime a detectable trap is about to be sprung within 5&rdquo; (10 yards). They must have line of sight to the trap and can&rsquo;t be @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Damage Effects]{Shaken} or @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Stunned]{Stunned}. This works generally like @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Danger Sense]{Danger Sense} but applies only to mechanical and magical traps.</p>\n<p>If the trap is detected and may be @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Evasion]{Evaded}, the rogue and anyone she warns ignores 2 points of @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Evasion]{Evasion} penalties to do so. If the trap can&rsquo;t normally be @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Evasion]{Evaded}, anyone warned may @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Evasion]{Evade} at the usual &minus;2 penalty.</p>\n<p><strong>Disarming Traps:</strong> Rogues with Trap Sense ignore up 2 points of @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Thievery]{Thievery} penalties when attempting to disarm traps.</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Novice, Rogue"}},"effects":[],"folder":"zzeiXM6YEGI9jNRc","sort":400000,"permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"flags":{"journal-links":{},"core":{"sourceId":"Item.gMhsswekqyI1hslR"}}},{"_id":"stjuAnzvJS5al95M","name":"Sneak Attack","type":"edge","img":"icons/skills/melee/strike-dagger-skull-white.webp","data":{"description":"<div class=\"sweb-core\">\n<p>Rogues add an additional d6 to their damage when they have @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.The Drop]{the Drop} on their victim, or the victim is @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Distracted and Vulnerable]{Vulnerable}. This applies to @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Athletics]{Athletics} (throwing), @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Fighting]{Fighting}, or @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Shooting]{Shooting} attacks.</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Seasoned, Rogue"}},"effects":[],"folder":"zzeiXM6YEGI9jNRc","sort":300000,"permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"flags":{"journal-links":{},"core":{"sourceId":"Item.5ggl5Khobnfxq698"}}},{"_id":"zccYegdCY96cR2I1","name":"Quick","type":"edge","img":"icons/environment/people/group.webp","data":{"description":"<div class=\"sweb-core\">\n<p>Quick characters have lightning-fast reflexes and a cool head. Whenever you are dealt an @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Action Cards (Initiative)]{Action Card} of Five or lower, you may discard it and draw again until you get a card higher than Five.</span></p>\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Characters]{Characters} with both the @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Level Headed]{Level Headed} and Quick Edges first draw their additional card and choose which to take. If that card is a Five or less, the Quick Edge may be used to draw a replacement until it&rsquo;s Six or higher.</span></p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Novice, Agility d8+"}},"effects":[],"folder":"EnpCvbp1xbBRZIf1","sort":1800000,"permission":{"default":0,"3HvtK4sMp7flYKmT":3,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"flags":{"cf":null,"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.swade-core-rules.swade-edges.XHguf9iQ3N9yHN4Z"}}},{"_id":"7tCUPCgVHLXej974","name":"Rogue Armor Restriction (Light)","type":"hindrance","img":"icons/skills/melee/strike-dagger-skull-white.webp","data":{"description":"<div class=\"sweb-core\">\n<p>Rogues are nimble and deadly acrobats. Bulky armor interferes with their abilities, so they subtract 4 from @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Traits]{Agility} and @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Traits]{Agility-based} skill rolls when wearing medium or heavy armor, or using medium or heavy shields.</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"major":false},"effects":[],"folder":"zzeiXM6YEGI9jNRc","sort":100000,"permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"flags":{"journal-links":{},"core":{"sourceId":"Item.B1jMHG6GDPNV0kYU"}}},{"_id":"bsKrKyvrK8j2EGm5","name":"Language (Common)","type":"skill","img":"icons/sundries/documents/document-letter-formal-tan.webp","data":{"description":"<div class=\"sweb-core\">\n<p>In some settings, such as those that focus on pulp action or &ldquo;planetary romance&rdquo; (where characters frequently travel among many strange civilizations), speaking various languages can simply be roleplayed with halting dialogue and campy accents that start out a little difficult and are quickly forgotten. The GM may ignore this skill altogether in these settings, or use the @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Multiple Languages]{Multiple Languages} &shy;option in the @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Setting Rules]{Setting Rules}.</p>\n<p>In more realistic settings, communication can be a major barrier that requires characters to put skill points into additional languages. In a 1980s World War Three game, for example, a group of United Nations paratroopers won&rsquo;t be able to speak with their foes unless they take Russian, Polish, or other languages common to the Warsaw Pact.</p>\n<p>If the Language skill is in use, it should be listed as Language (Spanish), Language (American Sign Language), etc. A character&rsquo;s die type also notes how fluent he is in it. (Characters start with a d8 in their own Language.)</p>\n<div class=\"sweb-core\">\n<table class=\"table value-table\"><caption class=\"table-caption\">\n<h2 class=\"table-title\">Language Proficiency</h2>\n</caption>\n<tbody>\n<tr class=\"table-header-row\">\n<th class=\"table-column-header\" scope=\"col\">Skill</th>\n<th class=\"table-column-header\" scope=\"col\">Ability</th>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td>d4</td>\n<td>The character can read, write and speak common words and phrases.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>d6</td>\n<td>The speaker can carry on a prolonged but occasionally halting conversation.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>d8</td>\n<td>The character can speak fluently.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>d10</td>\n<td>The hero can mimic other dialects within the language.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>d12</td>\n<td>The speaker can masterfully recite important literary or oral works.</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>\n</div>\n<p><strong>Limited: </strong>Use whichever skill is lowest when performing an action that requires knowledge of a foreign language. @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Intimidation]{Intimidation} (if verbal), @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Persuasion]{Persuasion}, @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Research]{Research}, @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Taunt]{Taunt}, etc., are all limited by the character&rsquo;s Language skill.</p>\n<p>This limitation never applies to a character&rsquo;s native tongue.</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"attribute":"smarts","isCoreSkill":false,"die":{"sides":8,"modifier":0},"wild-die":{"sides":6}},"effects":[],"folder":"kFghWjY7gP7MEqav","sort":1,"permission":{"default":0,"3HvtK4sMp7flYKmT":3,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_nsugutrpau","path":"Skills","color":"#8c160f"},"journal-links":{},"core":{"sourceId":"Item.B8Z0BJ0B2ULcZFmw"}}},{"_id":"34XXKChBYz4ixBQ6","name":"Language (Dwarvish)","type":"skill","img":"icons/sundries/documents/document-letter-formal-tan.webp","data":{"description":"<div class=\"sweb-core\">\n<p>In some settings, such as those that focus on pulp action or &ldquo;planetary romance&rdquo; (where characters frequently travel among many strange civilizations), speaking various languages can simply be roleplayed with halting dialogue and campy accents that start out a little difficult and are quickly forgotten. The GM may ignore this skill altogether in these settings, or use the @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Multiple Languages]{Multiple Languages} &shy;option in the @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Setting Rules]{Setting Rules}.</p>\n<p>In more realistic settings, communication can be a major barrier that requires characters to put skill points into additional lang