ion":"<div class=\"sweb-core\">\n<p>Low Light Vision ignores up &ndash;2 penalties for @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Illumination]{Dim and Dark Illumination}. @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Illumination]{Pitch Darkness} remains unaffected.</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"subtype":"special","grantsPowers":false},"effects":[],"folder":"cZShSnwTPtovR6Ah","sort":500000,"permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"flags":{"journal-links":{},"core":{"sourceId":"Item.E6a9fFWIn3Dzqo9Q"}}},{"_id":"PtgIm2WVxNkR6sLA","name":"Survival","type":"skill","img":"icons/environment/settlement/tent.webp","data":{"description":"<div class=\"sweb-core\">\n<p>Survival allows a character to find food, water, or shelter in hostile environments. It can also be used to navigate wilderness environments, figure out which plants are good to eat and which aren&rsquo;t, and so on.</p>\n<p>A @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Trait Rolls]{successful} Survival roll provides enough food and water for one person for one day; or five people with a @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Raises]{raise}.</p>\n<p>More detailed information on @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Hunger]{Hunger} and @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Thirst]{Thirst} can be found under @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Hazards]{Hazards} section.</p>\n<p><strong>Tracking: </strong>Survival can also be used to detect and follow tracks. Each roll generally covers following the tracks for one mile, but the GM should adjust this as needed for specific circumstances.</p>\n<p>The Game Master should assign a @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Trait Rolls]{bonus or penalty} based on the target, environment, and time. Tracking a large group that recently passed through a snow-covered area might grant a bonus of +4, while following a single person over rocks and streams after more than a day incurs a &minus;4 penalty.</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"attribute":"smarts","isCoreSkill":false,"die":{"sides":4,"modifier":0},"wild-die":{"sides":6}},"effects":[],"folder":"cgfmurTJRwbCvmCc","sort":1075001,"permission":{"default":0,"3HvtK4sMp7flYKmT":3,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_qals24wpyph","path":"Skills","color":"#8c160f"},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.swade-core-rules.swade-skills.15aEAJjDEjQy4fHF"}}},{"_id":"C1tzd541xo1mDsV4","name":"Potion of Blur (Melee)","type":"gear","img":"icons/consumables/potions/potion-flask-corked-orange.webp","data":{"description":"<div class=\"sweb-core\">\n<p>A bottle with a bright orange liquid that is hard to focus on. </p>\n<p>This potion duplicates <em>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Deflection]{deflection}</em> power. Determine if it works against melee or ranged attacks randomly when the potion is found.</p>\n<p><strong>Craft:</strong> <em>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Deflection]{Deflection}</em>; 50 gp</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"quantity":1,"weight":0.25,"price":100,"equippable":false,"equipped":true,"isVehicular":false,"mods":1},"effects":[],"folder":"8k28PFt4exlHUcFS","sort":5800001,"permission":{"default":0,"ZvqefCj0L7TxJS56":3,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"flags":{"journal-links":{},"core":{"sourceId":"Item.9SfHJ2ViVbJVJAXz"}}}],"effects":[{"_id":"r8Yvo2O9hVzqOqxv","changes":[{"key":"data.stats.parry.modifier","mode":2,"value":"-1"}],"disabled":false,"duration":{"startTime":28973116800},"icon":"icons/weapons/misc/whip-red-yellow.webp","label":"Whip Parry Penalty","origin":"Actor.iW4BE69zathTSmtE.Item.YH7Ky48QsQ1SAhZz","tint":null,"transfer":false,"flags":{}}],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"flags":{"journal-links":{"references":{}},"cf":{"id":"temp_3a04s0jrz4j","path":"Pirates of Cyre Bestiary#/CF_SEP/NPC's","color":"#000000"}}}
{"_id":"gytbnCnNuCBAS9FR","name":"Mister Lagraa","type":"npc","img":"https://assets.forge-vtt.com/5f43f8ea1a91d63438d13159/artwork-adventures/pirates-of-cyre/characters/mister-lagraa.webp","data":{"attributes":{"agility":{"die":{"sides":8,"modifier":0},"wild-die":{"sides":6}},"smarts":{"die":{"sides":8,"modifier":0},"wild-die":{"sides":6},"animal":false},"spirit":{"die":{"sides":6,"modifier":0},"wild-die":{"sides":6},"unShakeBonus":0},"strength":{"die":{"sides":10,"modifier":0},"wild-die":{"sides":6},"encumbranceSteps":0},"vigor":{"die":{"sides":8,"modifier":0},"wild-die":{"sides":6}}},"stats":{"speed":{"runningDie":"6","runningMod":0,"value":6},"toughness":{"value":0,"armor":0,"modifier":0},"parry":{"value":7,"modifier":0},"size":1},"details":{"biography":{"value":"<div class=\"sweb-core\">\n<p>Mister Lagraa is Black Red's bullying and sadistic first mate. She is an angry young orc that is a huge, hulking muscled orc. At over 8' in height and over 400 lbs of pure muscle. Her face is fixed in an almost constant grimace, and her teeth are gray and yellow. She dresses in more traditional trible orcs clothes, but clearly takes great pride in herself. With everything well kept, well groomed, and shining.</p>\n</div>"},"species":{"name":""},"currency":500,"wealth":{"die":6,"modifier":0,"wild-die":6},"conviction":{"value":0,"active":false},"autoCalcToughness":true,"autoCalcParry":true},"powerPoints":{},"fatigue":{"value":0,"min":0,"max":2},"wounds":{"value":0,"min":0,"max":3,"ignored":0},"advances":{"value":0,"rank":"Novice","details":""},"bennies":{"value":2,"max":2},"status":{"isShaken":false,"isDistracted":false,"isVulnerable":false,"isStunned":false,"isEntangled":false,"isBound":false},"initiative":{"hasHesitant":false,"hasLevelHeaded":false,"hasImpLevelHeaded":false,"hasQuick":false},"additionalStats":{},"wildcard":true},"token":{"flags":{},"name":"Blank","displayName":30,"img":"modules/etu-rules/assets/bestiary_tokens/sonya-alvarez-min.png","tint":null,"width":1,"height":1,"scale":1,"mirrorX":false,"mirrorY":false,"lockRotation":false,"rotation":0,"vision":true,"dimSight":0,"brightSight":0,"dimLight":0,"brightLight":0,"sightAngle":0,"lightAngle":0,"lightColor":null,"lightAlpha":1,"lightAnimation":{"speed":5,"intensity":5},"actorId":null,"actorLink":true,"disposition":0,"displayBars":0,"bar1":{"attribute":""},"bar2":{"attribute":""},"randomImg":false,"alpha":1},"items":[{"_id":"UZW0tLJicg0VZOp4","name":"Athletics","type":"skill","data":{"description":"<div class=\"sweb-core\">\n<p>Athletics combines an individual&rsquo;s coordin&shy;ation with learned skills such as climbing, jumping, balancing, biking, wrestling, skiing, swimming, throwing, or catching. Characters who rely on physical power more than coordination can take the @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Brute]{Brute} Edge to link this skill to @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Traits]{Strength} instead of @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Traits]{Agility}.</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"attribute":"agility","isCoreSkill":false,"die":{"sides":8,"modifier":0},"wild-die":{"sides":6}},"sort":100000,"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_nsugutrpau","path":"Skills","color":"#8c160f"},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.swade-core-rules.swade-skills.Athletics"}},"img":"icons/magic/control/buff-strength-muscle-damage.webp","effects":[],"folder":null,"permission":{"default":0}},{"_id":"W5lfcCNjirSPUH42","name":"Common Knowledge","type":"skill","data":{"description":"<div class=\"sweb-core\"><p>Characters roll Common Knowledge to know people, places, and things of their world, including etiquette, geography, culture, popular technology, contacts, and customs.</p></div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"attribute":"smarts","isCoreSkill":false,"die":{"sides":6,"modifier":0},"wild-die":{"sides":6}},"sort":200000,"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_nsugutrpau","path":"Skills","color":"#8c160f"},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.swade-core-rules.swade-skills.Common Knowledge"}},"img":"icons/sundries/documents/document-official-capital.webp","effects":[],"folder":null,"permission":{"default":0}},{"_id":"quj5jF3vNls1j5E3","name":"Notice","type":"skill","data":{"description":"<div class=\"sweb-core\">\n<p>Notice is a hero&rsquo;s general awareness and alertness. It&rsquo;s used to sense sights, sounds, tastes, and smells, spot clues, detect ambushes, spot hidden weapons on a foe, or tell if a rival is lying, frightened, happy, etc.</p>\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Trait Rolls]{Success} conveys basic information&mdash;the character hears movement in the forest, smells distant smoke, or senses someone isn&rsquo;t being completely truthful.</p>\n<p>A @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Raises]{raise} grants more detail, such as the direction of a sound or odor or what topic a person is avoiding or lying about.</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"attribute":"smarts","isCoreSkill":false,"die":{"sides":6,"modifier":0},"wild-die":{"sides":6}},"sort":300000,"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_nsugutrpau","path":"Skills","color":"#8c160f"},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.swade-core-rules.swade-skills.ZvwjzMLxsneptV4T"}},"img":"icons/creatures/eyes/human-single-blue.webp","effects":[],"folder":null,"permission":{"default":0}},{"_id":"TOEzoo2Lf4A5JXOF","name":"Persuasion","type":"skill","data":{"description":"<div class=\"sweb-core\">\n<p>Persuasion is the ability to convince others to do what you want through reason, cajoling, deception, rewards, or other friendly means. Persuasion isn&rsquo;t mind control. It can change someone&rsquo;s attitude but not their goals. A bandit may let you keep a sentimental piece of jewelry with a good Persuasion roll but still takes all your other goods.</p>\n<p>When used to @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Support]{Support} allies it&rsquo;s an unopposed roll. If the target is resistant, it&rsquo;s an @JournalEntry[JBxsGv2wAoAmoCDe]{opposed} roll vs. the target&rsquo;s @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Traits]{Spirit}. The GM should modify the roll as she sees fit based on roleplaying, any pertinent @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Edges]{Edges} or @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Hindrances]{Hindrances} that affect the conversation, and the circumstances.</p>\n<p><strong>Reaction Level:</strong> How much a person is willing to cooperate depends largely on their attitude toward whoever&rsquo;s talking to them. The Game Master can decide how nonplayer characters feel based on the setting, or roll on the @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-tables.Reaction Table]{Reaction Table} if she has no preconceived notions.</p>\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Trait Rolls]{Success} improves the target&rsquo;s attitude one level and a raise improves it two. Further increases aren&rsquo;t generally possible in the same encounter&mdash;it takes individuals a little time to adjust their biases.</p>\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Trait Rolls]{Failure} means the target won&rsquo;t change his mind this scene or until the situation changes in some important way. A @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Trait Rolls]{Critical Failure} also <em>reduces</em> the target&rsquo;s attitude two levels.</p>\n<p>Only one roll should generally be allowed per interaction unless new information is revealed, a substantial reward is offered, etc.</p>\n<p><strong>Networking: </strong>Characters can also use Persuasion as a &ldquo;macro skill,&rdquo; simulating a few hours or an evening&rsquo;s time hobnobbing and socializing to gain favors or information. See @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Networking]{Networking}.</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"attribute":"spirit","isCoreSkill":false,"die":{"sides":4,"modifier":0},"wild-die":{"sides":6}},"sort":400000,"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_nsugutrpau","path":"Skills","color":"#8c160f"},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.swade-core-rules.swade-skills.Persuasion"}},"img":"icons/skills/social/diplomacy-handshake.webp","effects":[],"folder":null,"permission":{"default":0}},{"_id":"8VzaSa3EEDrMz6PR","name":"Stealth","type":"skill","data":{"description":"<div class=\"sweb-core\">\n<p>Stealth is the ability to hide and move quietly. A simple @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Trait Rolls]{success} on a Stealth roll means the character avoids detection if enemies aren&rsquo;t particularly alert. If the character @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Trait Rolls]{fails} the roll, the enemy realizes something is amiss and begins actively searching for whatever roused them.</p>\n<p>Once foes are alerted and active, Stealth is opposed by @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Notice]{Notice} (a @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Trait Rolls]{group roll} if there are many foes.</p>\n<p>The GM should apply any circumstantial penalties to @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Notice]{Notice} rolls for @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Illumination]{darkness}, @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Cover and Obstacles]{cover}, noise, distractions, and any difference in the target&rsquo;s @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Size and Scale]{Scale} (just like when attacking). Sneaking through dry leaves might subtract 2 from the Stealth roll, for example, while spotting someone in the dark uses the @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Illumination]{Illumination} penalty (&minus;4). Don&rsquo;t apply the same modifier to both rolls, however. If Stealth is at &minus;2 for the leaves, don&rsquo;t give Notice a +2 for them as well.</p>\n<p><strong>Sneak Attack: </strong> Sneaking up close enough to make a melee attack <em>always</em> requires an @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Trait Rolls]{opposed} Stealth roll versus the target&rsquo;s @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Notice]{Notice}, whether the guard is actively looking for trouble or not. If successful, the victim is @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Distracted and Vulnerable]{Vulnerable} to the attacker, but only until the attacker&rsquo;s turn ends. With a raise, the attacker has @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.The Drop]{The Drop} instead.</p>\n<p><strong>Movement:</strong> In combat, characters roll Stealth each turn as a @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Actions]{free action} at the end of their move or any action the GM thinks might draw attention.</p>\n<p>Out of combat, the distance moved depends entirely on the situation. The GM might want a roll every minute if the group is sneaking around the perimeter of a defensive position, or every few miles if they&rsquo;re trying to quietly walk the path through a dark forest without alerting the creatures that live there.</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"attribute":"agility","isCoreSkill":false,"die":{"sides":6,"modifier":0},"wild-die":{"sides":6}},"sort":500000,"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_nsugutrpau","path":"Skills","color":"#8c160f"},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.swade-core-rules.swade-skills.Stealth"}},"img":"icons/magic/nature/stealth-hide-eyes-green.webp","effects":[],"folder":null,"permission":{"default":0}},{"_id":"BQ3OOQlkZvCl1Lfb","name":"Untrained","type":"skill","data":{"description":"<div class=\"sweb-core\">\n<p>If a character doesn&rsquo;t have a skill for an action he&rsquo;s attempting, he rolls a d4 for his skill die (and a Wild Die if a @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Wild Cards and Extras]{Wild Card}) and subtracts 2 from the total.</p>\n<p>The GM may decide certain tasks cannot be attempted unskilled, such as performing complex surgery or flying a commercial jet.</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"attribute":"agility","isCoreSkill":false,"die":{"sides":4,"modifier":"-2"},"wild-die":{"sides":6}},"sort":1100000,"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_nsugutrpau","path":"Skills","color":"#8c160f"},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.swade-core-rules.swade-skills.zcn1epcU4FEJGGyI"}},"img":"icons/magic/symbols/question-stone-yellow.webp","effects":[],"folder":null,"permission":{"default":0}},{"_id":"uaVAhwDnUDLFZFXm","name":"Unarmed strike","type":"weapon","data":{"description":"","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"quantity":1,"weight":0,"price":0,"equippable":false,"equipped":true,"isVehicular":false,"mods":1,"actions":{"skill":"","skillMod":"","dmgMod":"","additional":{}},"damage":"@str","range":"","rof":"1","ap":"0","minStr":"","shots":"0","currentShots":"0","ammo":"","autoReload":false},"sort":1400000,"flags":{},"img":"icons/skills/melee/unarmed-punch-fist.webp","effects":[],"folder":null,"permission":{"default":0}},{"_id":"GjcL17dCtOeFUvbu","name":"Fighting","type":"skill","data":{"description":"<div class=\"sweb-core\">\n<p>Fighting covers all hand-to-hand (melee) attacks, whether it&rsquo;s with fists, axes, laser swords, or martial arts. See @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Combat]{Chapter Three} for the combat rules and the various maneuvers a warrior might attempt.</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"attribute":"agility","isCoreSkill":false,"die":{"sides":10,"modifier":0},"wild-die":{"sides":6}},"sort":1500000,"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_qals24wpyph","path":"Skills","color":"#8c160f"},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.swade-core-rules.swade-skills.wWiwjPlzAQU3TN9l"}},"img":"icons/skills/melee/hand-grip-sword-white-brown.webp","effects":[],"folder":null,"permission":{"default":0}},{"_id":"s8YLnRMZBKFrbqXe","name":"Intimidation","type":"skill","img":"icons/skills/wounds/injury-face-impact-orange.webp","data":{"description":"<div class=\"sweb-core\">\n<p>Intimidation is the art of frightening an opponent so that he backs down, reveals information, or flees.</p>\n<p>Intimidation is an @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Trait Rolls]{opposed roll} resisted by the opponent&rsquo;s @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Traits]{Spirit}. In combat, this is a @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Test]{Test}. Out of combat, a successful roll means the foe backs down for the most part, reveals some information, or slinks away when the opportunity presents itself.</p>\n<p>A @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Raises]{raise} might mean he backs down for the remainder of the scene, spills all the beans, or runs away as fast as he can.</p>\n<p>In or out of combat, a @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Trait Rolls]{Critical Failure} means the target is immune to this character&rsquo;s Intimidation attempts for the remainder of this encounter!</p>\n<p><strong>Networking:</strong> Intimidation can also be used as a &ldquo;macro&rdquo; skill to simulate several hours of working the streets. See @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Networking]{Networking} to see how to crack some heads for favors or information.</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"attribute":"spirit","isCoreSkill":false,"die":{"sides":10,"modifier":2},"wild-die":{"sides":6}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"3HvtK4sMp7flYKmT":3,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_qals24wpyph","path":"Skills","color":"#8c160f"},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.swade-core-rules.swade-skills.RrgAZp50CgQyyY6w"}}},{"_id":"DZaUSUgNMyMTaS6e","name":"Language (Common)","type":"skill","img":"icons/sundries/documents/document-letter-formal-tan.webp","data":{"description":"<div class=\"sweb-core\">\n<p>In some settings, such as those that focus on pulp action or &ldquo;planetary romance&rdquo; (where characters frequently travel among many strange civilizations), speaking various languages can simply be roleplayed with halting dialogue and campy accents that start out a little difficult and are quickly forgotten. The GM may ignore this skill altogether in these settings, or use the @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Multiple Languages]{Multiple Languages} &shy;option in the @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Setting Rules]{Setting Rules}.</p>\n<p>In more realistic settings, communication can be a major barrier that requires characters to put skill points into additional languages. In a 1980s World War Three game, for example, a group of United Nations paratroopers won&rsquo;t be able to speak with their foes unless they take Russian, Polish, or other languages common to the Warsaw Pact.</p>\n<p>If the Language skill is in use, it should be listed as Language (Spanish), Language (American Sign Language), etc. A character&rsquo;s die type also notes how fluent he is in it. (Characters start with a d8 in their own Language.)</p>\n<div class=\"sweb-core\">\n<table class=\"table value-table\"><caption class=\"table-caption\">\n<h2 class=\"table-title\">Language Proficiency</h2>\n</caption>\n<tbody>\n<tr class=\"table-header-row\">\n<th class=\"table-column-header\" scope=\"col\">Skill</th>\n<th class=\"table-column-header\" scope=\"col\">Ability</th>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td>d4</td>\n<td>The character can read, write and speak common words and phrases.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>d6</td>\n<td>The speaker can carry on a prolonged but occasionally halting conversation.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>d8</td>\n<td>The character can speak fluently.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>d10</td>\n<td>The hero can mimic other dialects within the language.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>d12</td>\n<td>The speaker can masterfully recite important literary or oral works.</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>\n</div>\n<p><strong>Limited: </strong>Use whichever skill is lowest when performing an action that requires knowledge of a foreign language. @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Intimidation]{Intimidation} (if verbal), @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Persuasion]{Persuasion}, @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Research]{Research}, @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Taunt]{Taunt}, etc., are all limited by the character&rsquo;s Language skill.</p>\n<p>This limitation never applies to a character&rsquo;s native tongue.</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"attribute":"smarts","isCoreSkill":false,"die":{"sides":8,"modifier":0},"wild-die":{"sides":6}},"effects":[],"folder":"kFghWjY7gP7MEqav","sort":1,"permission":{"default":0,"3HvtK4sMp7flYKmT":3,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_nsugutrpau","path":"Skills","color":"#8c160f"},"journal-links":{},"core":{"sourceId":"Item.B8Z0BJ0B2ULcZFmw"}}},{"_id":"vtb0HNEXmdC9DPXO","name":"Language (Dwarvish)","type":"skill","img":"icons/sundries/documents/document-letter-formal-tan.webp","data":{"description":"<div class=\"sweb-core\">\n<p>In some settings, such as those that focus on pulp action or &ldquo;planetary romance&rdquo; (where characters frequently travel among many strange civilizations), speaking various languages can simply be roleplayed with halting dialogue and campy accents that start out a little difficult and are quickly forgotten. The GM may ignore this skill altogether in these settings, or use the @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Multiple Languages]{Multiple Languages} &shy;option in the @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Setting Rules]{Setting Rules}.</p>\n<p>In more realistic settings, communication can be a major barrier that requires characters to put skill points into additional languages. In a 1980s World War Three game, for example, a group of United Nations paratroopers won&rsquo;t be able to speak with their foes unless they take Russian, Polish, or other languages common to the Warsaw Pact.</p>\n<p>If the Language skill is in use, it should be listed as Language (Spanish), Language (American Sign Language), etc. A character&rsquo;s die type also notes how fluent he is in it. (Characters start with a d8 in their own Language.)</p>\n<div class=\"sweb-core\">\n<table class=\"table value-table\"><caption class=\"table-caption\">\n<h2 class=\"table-title\">Language Proficiency</h2>\n</caption>\n<tbody>\n<tr class=\"table-header-row\">\n<th class=\"table-column-header\" scope=\"col\">Skill</th>\n<th class=\"table-column-header\" scope=\"col\">Ability</th>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td>d4</td>\n<td>The character can read, write and speak common words and phrases.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>d6</td>\n<td>The speaker can carry on a prolonged but occasionally halting conversation.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>d8</td>\n<td>The character can speak fluently.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>d10</td>\n<td>The hero can mimic other dialects within the language.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>d12</td>\n<td>The speaker can masterfully recite important literary or oral works.</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>\n</div>\n<p><strong>Limited: </strong>Use whichever skill is lowest when performing an action that requires knowledge of a foreign language. @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Intimidation]{Intimidation} (if verbal), @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Persuasion]{Persuasion}, @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Research]{Research}, @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Taunt]{Taunt}, etc., are all limited by the character&rsquo;s Language skill.</p>\n<p>This limitation never applies to a character&rsquo;s native tongue.</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"attribute":"smarts","isCoreSkill":false,"die":{"sides":8,"modifier":0},"wild-die":{"sides":6}},"effects":[],"folder":"kFghWjY7gP7MEqav","sort":1,"permission":{"default":0,"3HvtK4sMp7flYKmT":3,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_nsugutrpau","path":"Skills","color":"#8c160f"},"journal-links":{},"core":{"sourceId":"Item.B8Z0BJ0B2ULcZFmw"}}},{"_id":"IJQAmJPJ7wDpJN7B","name":"Shooting","type":"skill","img":"icons/skills/ranged/target-bullseye-arrow-glowing.webp","data":{"description":"<div class=\"sweb-core\">\n<p>Shooting covers all attempts to hit a target with a ranged weapon such as a bow, pistol, or rocket launcher (thrown weapons use @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Athletics]{Athletics}). See @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Combat]{Chapter Three} for details on ranged combat.</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"attribute":"agility","isCoreSkill":false,"die":{"sides":6,"modifier":0},"wild-die":{"sides":6}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"3HvtK4sMp7flYKmT":3,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_qals24wpyph","path":"Skills","color":"#8c160f"},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.swade-core-rules.swade-skills.sOHfVvBDhe3Oy3r1"}}},{"_id":"9izbwRBef2TPadUL","name":"Boating","type":"skill","img":"icons/environment/settlement/ship.webp","data":{"description":"<div class=\"sweb-core\"><p>Characters with this skill can handle most any boat or ship common to their setting. They also know how to handle common tasks associated with their vessel such as tying knots, rigging sails, or following currents.</p></div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"attribute":"agility","isCoreSkill":false,"die":{"sides":8,"modifier":0},"wild-die":{"sides":6}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"3HvtK4sMp7flYKmT":3,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_qals24wpyph","path":"Skills","color":"#8c160f"},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.swade-core-rules.swade-skills.WMWgIVDuAW4cHxj2"}}},{"_id":"2HNpJlUkXn8aDKq8","name":"Mean","type":"hindrance","img":"icons/magic/holy/yin-yang-balance-symbol.webp","data":{"description":"<div class=\"sweb-core\">\n<p>This curmudgeon is ill-tempered and disagreeable. He has trouble doing anything kind for anyone else, must be paid for his troubles, and doesn&rsquo;t accept awards or favors graciously. Besides the obvious roleplaying issues, Mean characters subtract 1 from @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Persuasion]{Persuasion} @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Trait Rolls]{rolls}.</span></p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"major":false},"effects":[],"folder":"1updrtPaYhKD0fRY","sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"3HvtK4sMp7flYKmT":3,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"flags":{"cf":null,"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.swade-core-rules.swade-hindrances.sNgSwqh2fGyM6i14"}}},{"_id":"zhbz3wrBr6XLhACp","name":"Suspicious","type":"hindrance","img":"icons/magic/holy/yin-yang-balance-symbol.webp","data":{"description":"<div class=\"sweb-core\">\n<p>Your character is suspicious of everyone. As a @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Characters]{Minor} @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Hindrances]{Hindrance}, his paranoia causes frequent trust issues. He might demand full payment before doing a task, want every agreement in writing, or believe even his friends are out to get him.</p>\n<p>As a @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Characters]{Major} @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Hindrances]{Hindrance}, @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Support]{Support} @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Trait Rolls]{rolls} to aid the distrustful individual are made at -2.</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"major":false},"effects":[],"folder":"1updrtPaYhKD0fRY","sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"3HvtK4sMp7flYKmT":3,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"flags":{"cf":null,"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.swade-core-rules.swade-hindrances.OKRpEOPTwa1gX5c9"}}},{"_id":"TxH0M4E7JugBO5HP","name":"Driven (Captain her own ship)","type":"hindrance","img":"icons/magic/holy/yin-yang-balance-symbol.webp","data":{"description":"<div class=\"sweb-core\">\n<p>A vow is a commitment to others. Driven characters want something for themselves. It may be to protect the realm, become a decorated officer, prove you&rsquo;re the best gladiator in Rome, or the best pilot in the galactic fleet.</p>\n<p>The @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Characters]{Minor} version shapes the character and pushes his decisions but either happens rarely or is fairly harmless. As a @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Characters]{Major} @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Hindrances]{Hindrance} it&rsquo;s an overriding desire that comes up frequently or causes peril for the heroine and those around her.</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"major":false},"effects":[],"folder":"1updrtPaYhKD0fRY","sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"3HvtK4sMp7flYKmT":3,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"flags":{"cf":null,"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.swade-core-rules.swade-hindrances.I7XFI1uVE9xqx8gu"}}},{"_id":"nFA5TtK7rZl54VD6","name":"Language (Orcish)","type":"skill","img":"icons/sundries/documents/document-letter-formal-tan.webp","data":{"description":"<div class=\"sweb-core\">\n<p>In some settings, such as those that focus on pulp action or &ldquo;planetary romance&rdquo; (where characters frequently travel among many strange civilizations), speaking various languages can simply be roleplayed with halting dialogue and campy accents that start out a little difficult and are quickly forgotten. The GM may ignore this skill altogether in these settings, or use the @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Multiple Languages]{Multiple Languages} &shy;option in the @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Setting Rules]{Setting Rules}.</p>\n<p>In more realistic settings, communication can be a major barrier that requires characters to put skill points into additional languages. In a 1980s World War Three game, for example, a group of United Nations paratroopers won&rsquo;t be able to speak with their foes unless they take Russian, Polish, or other languages common to the Warsaw Pact.</p>\n<p>If the Language skill is in use, it should be listed as Language (Spanish), Language (American Sign Language), etc. A character&rsquo;s die type also notes how fluent he is in it. (Characters start with a d8 in their own Language.)</p>\n<div class=\"sweb-core\">\n<table class=\"table value-table\"><caption class=\"table-caption\">\n<h2 class=\"table-title\">Language Proficiency</h2>\n</caption>\n<tbody>\n<tr class=\"table-header-row\">\n<th class=\"table-column-header\" scope=\"col\">Skill</th>\n<th class=\"table-column-header\" scope=\"col\">Ability</th>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td>d4</td>\n<td>The character can read, write and speak common words and phrases.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>d6</td>\n<td>The speaker can carry on a prolonged but occasionally halting conversation.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>d8</td>\n<td>The character can speak fluently.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>d10</td>\n<td>The hero can mimic other dialects within the language.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>d12</td>\n<td>The speaker can masterfully recite important literary or oral works.</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>\n</div>\n<p><strong>Limited: </strong>Use whichever skill is lowest when performing an action that requires knowledge of a foreign language. @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Intimidation]{Intimidation} (if verbal), @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Persuasion]{Persuasion}, @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Research]{Research}, @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Taunt]{Taunt}, etc., are all limited by the character&rsquo;s Language skill.</p>\n<p>This limitation never applies to a character&rsquo;s native tongue.</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"attribute":"smarts","isCoreSkill":false,"die":{"sides":8,"modifier":0},"wild-die":{"sides":6}},"effects":[],"folder":"onRNTIr80exOb3zL","sort":400000,"permission":{"default":0,"3HvtK4sMp7flYKmT":3,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_nsugutrpau","path":"Skills","color":"#8c160f"},"journal-links":{},"core":{"sourceId":"Item.B8Z0BJ0B2ULcZFmw"}}},{"_id":"R2EXexl18VPrLgtv","name":"Primal Brute","type":"ability","img":"icons/creatures/eyes/humanoid-single-red-brown.webp","data":{"description":"<div class=\"sweb-core\">\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Orc]{Orcs} focus on core strength and fitness over coordination and flexibility. They treat @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Athletics]{Athletics} as linked to @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Traits]{Strength} instead of @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Traits]{Agility} for purposes of @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Advancement]{Advancement}. The character may also resist @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Athletics]{Athletics} @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Test]{Tests} with @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Traits]{Strength} if she chooses.</p>\n<p>Finally, @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Orc]{orcs} increase the @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Range]{Short Range} of any thrown item by +1. Double that for the adjusted @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Range]{Medium Range} , and double again for @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Range]{Long Range}. If a thrown item&rsquo;s @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Range]{Range} is 3/6/12, for example, an @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Orc]{orc's} @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Range]{Range} is 4/8/16.</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"subtype":"special","grantsPowers":false},"effects":[],"folder":"onRNTIr80exOb3zL","sort":500000,"permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"flags":{"journal-links":{},"core":{"sourceId":"Item.NvIGTQvwpA2rek6y"}}},{"_id":"EOOaKgZNfrdnNJGi","name":"Primal Passion","type":"hindrance","img":"icons/creatures/eyes/humanoid-single-red-brown.webp","data":{"description":"<div class=\"sweb-core\">\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Orc]{Orcs} are reactive and driven by a primal passion. They often take action without thinking things through.</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"major":true},"effects":[],"folder":"onRNTIr80exOb3zL","sort":300000,"permission":{"default":0,"ZvqefCj0L7TxJS56":3,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"flags":{"journal-links":{},"core":{"sourceId":"Item.lTwGLJJQ4OHToNdH"}}},{"_id":"HMxTvVxVWIYaTyU1","name":"Language (Elvish)","type":"skill","img":"icons/sundries/documents/document-letter-formal-tan.webp","data":{"description":"<div class=\"sweb-core\">\n<p>In some settings, such as those that focus on pulp action or &ldquo;planetary romance&rdquo; (where characters frequently travel among many strange civilizations), speaking various languages can simply be roleplayed with halting dialogue and campy accents that start out a little difficult and are quickly forgotten. The GM may ignore this skill altogether in these settings, or use the @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Multiple Languages]{Multiple Languages} &shy;option in the @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Setting Rules]{Setting Rules}.</p>\n<p>In more realistic settings, communication can be a major barrier that requires characters to put skill points into additional languages. In a 1980s World War Three game, for example, a group of United Nations paratroopers won&rsquo;t be able to speak with their foes unless they take Russian, Polish, or other languages common to the Warsaw Pact.</p>\n<p>If the Language skill is in use, it should be listed as Language (Spanish), Language (American Sign Language), etc. A character&rsquo;s die type also notes how fluent he is in it. (Characters start with a d8 in their own Language.)</p>\n<div class=\"sweb-core\">\n<table class=\"table value-table\"><caption class=\"table-caption\">\n<h2 class=\"table-title\">Language Proficiency</h2>\n</caption>\n<tbody>\n<tr class=\"table-header-row\">\n<th class=\"table-column-header\" scope=\"col\">Skill</th>\n<th class=\"table-column-header\" scope=\"col\">Ability</th>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td>d4</td>\n<td>The character can read, write and speak common words and phrases.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>d6</td>\n<td>The speaker can carry on a prolonged but occasionally halting conversation.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>d8</td>\n<td>The character can speak fluently.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>d10</td>\n<td>The hero can mimic other dialects within the language.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>d12</td>\n<td>The speaker can masterfully recite important literary or oral works.</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>\n</div>\n<p><strong>Limited: </strong>Use whichever skill is lowest when performing an action that requires knowledge of a foreign language. @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Intimidation]{Intimidation} (if verbal), @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Persuasion]{Persuasion}, @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Research]{Research}, @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Taunt]{Taunt}, etc., are all limited by the character&rsquo;s Language skill.</p>\n<p>This limitation never applies to a character&rsquo;s native tongue.</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"attribute":"smarts","isCoreSkill":false,"die":{"sides":6,"modifier":0},"wild-die":{"sides":6}},"effects":[],"folder":"kFghWjY7gP7MEqav","sort":1,"permission":{"default":0,"3HvtK4sMp7flYKmT":3,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_nsugutrpau","path":"Skills","color":"#8c160f"},"journal-links":{},"core":{"sourceId":"Item.B8Z0BJ0B2ULcZFmw"}}},{"_id":"9RBt7voVmiV81ZVl","name":"Strong Willed","type":"edge","img":"icons/skills/social/diplomacy-unity-alliance.webp","data":{"description":"<div class=\"sweb-core\">\n<p>Self-confidence is powerful armor against those who attempt to attack this individual&rsquo;s will. He adds +2 to his total when resisting @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Test]{Tests} with @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Traits]{Smarts} or @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Traits]{Spirit}.</span></p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Novice, Spirit d8+"}},"effects":[],"folder":"4qgDgsPe5IZFyuwd","sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"3HvtK4sMp7flYKmT":3,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"flags":{"cf":null,"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.swade-core-rules.swade-edges.LXKTnJkZTAKTl9hs"}}},{"_id":"wRjFwQakSQhW2HDq","name":"Trademark Weapon (Cutlass)","type":"edge","img":"icons/environment/people/charge.webp","data":{"description":"<div class=\"sweb-core\">\n<p>The hero knows one unique weapon (Excalibur, Old Betsy, Sting) like the back of his hand. When using it, he adds +1 to his @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Athletics]{Athletics} (throwing), @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Fighting]{Fighting}, or @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Shooting]{Shooting} rolls, and +1 to @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Characters]{Parry} when readied (even if it&rsquo;s a ranged weapon).</span></p>\n<p>A fighter can take this Edge multiple times, applying it to a different weapon each time. If a Trademark Weapon is lost, he can replace it but the benefits don&rsquo;t kick in for a few days (however long the GM feels is dramatically appropriate).</span></p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Novice, skill with chosen weapon of d8+"}},"effects":[{"_id":"viA65GSpKV0IFwsX","changes":[{"key":"data.stats.parry.value","mode":2,"value":"1"}],"disabled":false,"duration":{"startTime":null},"icon":"icons/environment/people/charge.webp","label":"Trademark Readied Weapon","transfer":true,"flags":{},"tint":null}],"folder":"hsEO07bFB8oM1LJo","sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"3HvtK4sMp7flYKmT":3,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"flags":{"cf":null,"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.swade-core-rules.swade-edges.QHBtO0jmIzfl8TDE"}}},{"_id":"9OvmPgMkvLo0N6gw","name":"Menacing","type":"edge","img":"icons/skills/social/diplomacy-unity-alliance.webp","data":{"description":"<div class=\"sweb-core\">\n<p>Being a brutish lout isn&rsquo;t always a drawback if you know how to use it. Menacing allows a character to put her bad looks or worse attitude to good use. The goon adds +2 to her @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Intimidation]{Intimidation} rolls.</span></p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Novice, any one of Bloodthirsty, Mean, Ruthless, or Ugly"}},"effects":[],"folder":"4qgDgsPe5IZFyuwd","sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"3HvtK4sMp7flYKmT":3,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"flags":{"cf":null,"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.swade-core-rules.swade-edges.WRpK5JTq57sLcfOq"}}},{"_id":"LNpii9QGtw623CEf","name":"Two-Weapon Fighting","type":"edge","img":"icons/environment/people/charge.webp","data":{"description":"<div class=\"sweb-core\">\n<p>If a character battles with a weapon in each hand, the hero can attack with the &ldquo;good hand&rdquo; on one action and the other hand in a later action.</p>\n<p>The second attack doesn&rsquo;t inflict a @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Multi-Actions]{Multi-Action} penalty. The @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Off-Hand Attacks]{off-hand} penalty still applies unless he&rsquo;s @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Ambidextrous]{Ambidextrous}, however.</p>\n<p>The character can choose to make a @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Fighting]{Fighting} attack with each hand, a throwing (@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Athletics]{Athletics}) attack with each hand, or one of each, depending on the readied weapons.</p>\n<p class=\"embedded-example\"><strong>Example: </strong>A fighter wields a longsword in one hand and a dagger in the other. He has Two-Weapon Fighting so he rolls @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Fighting]{Fighting} on one action with the sword, and then makes a second @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Fighting]{Fighting} roll&mdash;or a throwing roll (@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Athletics]{Athletics})&mdash; with the dagger, with no @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Multi-Actions]{Multi-Action} penalty to either.</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Novice, Agility d8+"}},"effects":[],"folder":"hsEO07bFB8oM1LJo","sort":1100000,"permission":{"default":2,"ZvqefCj0L7TxJS56":3,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"flags":{"journal-links":{},"core":{"sourceId":"Item.Fk7h9WOsyy1eaVlo"}}},{"_id":"QNQQquHtFVhcj6F1","name":"Low Light Vision","type":"ability","img":"icons/creatures/eyes/human-single-brown.webp","data":{"description":"<div class=\"sweb-core\">\n<p>Low Light Vision ignores up &ndash;2 penalties for @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Illumination]{Dim and Dark Illumination}. @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Illumination]{Pitch Darkness} remains unaffected.</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"subtype":"special","grantsPowers":false},"effects":[],"folder":"cZShSnwTPtovR6Ah","sort":500000,"permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"flags":{"journal-links":{},"core":{"sourceId":"Item.E6a9fFWIn3Dzqo9Q"}}},{"_id":"yc348ic3KkNEo69r","name":"Killer Instinct","type":"edge","img":"icons/environment/people/charge.webp","data":{"description":"<div class=\"sweb-core\"><p>This hero hates losing. He gets a free reroll in any opposed @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Test]{Test} he initiates</span> </p></div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Seasoned"}},"effects":[],"folder":"hsEO07bFB8oM1LJo","sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"3HvtK4sMp7flYKmT":3,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"flags":{"cf":null,"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.swade-core-rules.swade-edges.QomybVyELXkYseoC"}}},{"_id":"8y0ZMqrIIapH2Nyw","name":"Tidewater Cutlass","type":"weapon","img":"icons/weapons/swords/scimitar-guard-brown.webp","data":{"description":"<div class=\"sweb-core\">\n<p>The blade of this cutlass is spotted with rust, and its basket hilt is cast in the likeness of a grinning skull. It is @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Masterwork]{Masterwork} and has the @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Accurate]{Accurate} enchantment.</p>\n<p>The wielder of this cutlass can cause it blast forth a tidal wave of water as an action once per day. This is as per the <em>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Havoc]{havoc}</em> power using a @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Area Effect Attacks]{Cone Template} and @Item[Fighting]{Fighting} as the casting roll.</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"quantity":1,"weight":2,"price":12310,"equippable":false,"equipped":true,"isVehicular":false,"mods":1,"actions":{"skill":"Fighting","skillMod":"+2","dmgMod":"","additional":{}},"damage":"@str+d6","range":"","rof":"1","ap":"1","minStr":"d6","shots":"0","currentShots":"0","ammo":"","autoReload":false},"effects":[],"folder":"IV0OqLxQENP62AG9","sort":100000,"permission":{"default":0,"ZvqefCj0L7TxJS56":3,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"flags":{"journal-links":{},"core":{"sourceId":"Item.BzFluL4CPr0x3oDS"}}},{"_id":"LxyXA1uoyiSUtZsD","name":"Cat-o-nine Tails","type":"weapon","img":"icons/weapons/misc/whip-red-yellow.webp","data":{"description":null,"notes":"","additionalStats":{},"quantity":1,"weight":1,"price":7,"equippable":true,"equipped":true,"isVehicular":false,"mods":1,"actions":{"skill":"Fighting","skillMod":"","dmgMod":"","additional":{}},"damage":"@str+d4","range":"","rof":"0","ap":"0","minStr":"d4","shots":"0","currentShots":"0","ammo":"","autoReload":false},"effects":[],"folder":"tnIhNgfhxgoXoVDh","sort":1300001,"permission":{"default":0,"3HvtK4sMp7flYKmT":3,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_rz46r8sengj","path":"Equipment#/CF_SEP/Personal Weapons#/CF_SEP/Melee Weapons, Medieval","color":"#000000"},"journal-links":{},"core":{"sourceId":"Item.GBIV4MIh57FGTxWB"}}},{"_id":"kHLocbr1Q8kK0Hhk","name":"Shackles of Compliance","type":"gear","img":"icons/sundries/survival/cuffs-shackles-steel.webp","data":{"description":"<div class=\"sweb-core\">\n<p>These battered iron manacles magically adjust themselves to fit around the wrists or ankles of any creature from Small to Large @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Size and Scale]{Size} and automatically lock. The lock can be picked with @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Thievery]{Thievery} roll &ndash;3.</p>\n<p>Once per day, the holder of the key to the manacles may make an @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Intimidation]{Intimidation} roll to cast the minor <em>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Puppet]{puppet}</em> power on the wearer of the shackles.</p>\n<p><strong>Craft:</strong> <em>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Puppet]{Puppet}</em>, 1,500 gp</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"quantity":1,"weight":5,"price":3000,"equippable":false,"equipped":true,"isVehicular":false,"mods":1},"effects":[],"folder":"A5d3oIg9sVmXEgI1","sort":400000,"permission":{"default":0,"ZvqefCj0L7TxJS56":3,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"flags":{"journal-links":{},"core":{"sourceId":"Item.VpLp24aWHGyVEXPA"}}},{"_id":"HJdTNOqGKS5xoJBC","name":"Brawny","type":"edge","img":"icons/environment/people/group.webp","data":{"description":"<div class=\"sweb-core\">\n<p>Your bruiser is very large or very fit. Her @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Size and Scale]{Size} increases by +1 (and therefore @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Characters]{Toughness} by 1) and she treats her @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Traits]{Strength} as one die type higher when determining <strong>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Gear Notes]{Encumbrance}</strong><strong> </strong>and <strong>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Minimum Strength]{Minimum Strength} </strong>to use armor, weapons, and equipment without a penalty.</p>\n<p>Brawny can&rsquo;t increase a character&rsquo;s Size above +3.</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Novice, Strength d6+, Vigor d6+"}},"effects":[{"_id":"xD9SM5eqeRZvcjF6","changes":[{"key":"data.stats.size","mode":2,"value":"1"},{"key":"data.attributes.strength.encumbranceSteps","mode":2,"value":"2"}],"disabled":false,"duration":{"startTime":null},"icon":"icons/environment/people/group.webp","label":"Brawny","transfer":true,"flags":{},"tint":null}],"folder":"EnpCvbp1xbBRZIf1","sort":600000,"permission":{"default":0,"3HvtK4sMp7flYKmT":3,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"flags":{"cf":null,"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.swade-core-rules.swade-edges.LYYfJsMEFfJVmelT"}}},{"_id":"tQyM4YhYaTa1N3Lv","name":"Deception","type":"skill","img":"icons/skills/toxins/poison-skull-herbs-bottle-pink.webp","data":{"description":"<div class=\"sweb-core\">\n<p>Deception determines whether the hero can convincingly hide the truth, either verbally or through her actions. This deception can encompass everything from misleading others through ambiguity to telling outright lies.</p>\n<p>Typical situations include trying to fast-talk a guard, con a merchant, dull someone's suspicions with false assurances, or maintain a straight face while telling a blatant lie.</p>\n<p>Usually, a character successfully passing herself off in a disguise, or trying to impersonate the sound of someone else's voice would be a @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Performance]{Performance} check rather than a deception check. </p>\n<p><em><strong>Source: Savage Eberron</strong></em></p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"attribute":"spirit","isCoreSkill":false,"die":{"sides":6,"modifier":0},"wild-die":{"sides":6}},"effects":[],"folder":"cgfmurTJRwbCvmCc","sort":700001,"permission":{"default":0,"ZvqefCj0L7TxJS56":3,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"flags":{"journal-links":{},"core":{"sourceId":"Item.E0BVumGwbaczoPjD"}}}],"effects":[{"_id":"we0WXaPtHycNu15h","changes":[{"key":"data.stats.parry.value","mode":2,"value":"1"}],"disabled":false,"duration":{"startTime":28973116800},"icon":"icons/environment/people/charge.webp","label":"Trademark Readied Weapon","origin":"Actor.DzgkbRMhHmwXuAiA.Item.wRjFwQakSQhW2HDq","tint":null,"transfer":false,"flags":{}},{"_id":"ewEGk2IXZmqDPJQ3","changes":[{"key":"data.stats.size","mode":2,"value":"1"},{"key":"data.attributes.strength.encumbranceSteps","mode":2,"value":"2"}],"disabled":false,"duration":{"startTime":28973116800},"icon":"icons/environment/people/group.webp","label":"Brawny","origin":"Actor.DzgkbRMhHmwXuAiA.Item.HJdTNOqGKS5xoJBC","tint":null,"transfer":false,"flags":{}}],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"flags":{"journal-links":{"references":{}},"cf":{"id":"temp_3a04s0jrz4j","path":"Pirates of Cyre Bestiary#/CF_SEP/NPC's","color":"#000000"}}}
{"_id":"raZYvUdO4Op0Mc0t","name":"Owlbear Hartshorn","type":"npc","img":"https://assets.forge-vtt.com/5f43f8ea1a91d63438d13159/tokens/bestiary/monstrous%20humanoid/harpy-10.png","data":{"attributes":{"agility":{"die":{"sides":6,"modifier":0},"wild-die":{"sides":6}},"smarts":{"die":{"sides":4,"modifier":0},"wild-die":{"sides":6},"animal":false},"spirit":{"die":{"sides":6,"modifier":0},"wild-die":{"sides":6},"unShakeBonus":0},"strength":{"die":{"sides":6,"modifier":0},"wild-die":{"sides":6},"encumbranceSteps":0},"vigor":{"die":{"sides":6,"modifier":0},"wild-die":{"sides":6}}},"stats":{"speed":{"runningDie":6,"runningMod":0,"value":6},"toughness":{"value":0,"armor":0,"modifier":0},"parry":{"value":5,"modifier":0},"size":0},"details":{"biography":{"value":"<div class=\"sweb-core\">\n<p>xxxxxx</p>"},"species":{"name":""},"currency":500,"wealth":{"die":6,"modifier":0,"wild-die":6},"conviction":{"value":0,"active":false},"autoCalcToughness":true,"autoCalcParry":true},"powerPoints":{},"fatigue":{"value":0,"min":0,"max":2},"wounds":{"value":0,"min":0,"max":0,"ignored":0},"advances":{"value":0,"rank":"Novice","details":""},"bennies":{"value":2,"max":2},"status":{"isShaken":false,"isDistracted":false,"isVulnerable":false,"isStunned":false,"isEntangled":false,"isBound":false},"initiative":{"hasHesitant":false,"hasLevelHeaded":false,"hasImpLevelHeaded":false,"hasQuick":false},"additionalStats":{},"wildcard":false},"token":{"name":"Blank NPC","img":"https://assets.forge-vtt.com/5f43f8ea1a91d63438d13159/tokens/bestiary/monstrous%20humanoid/harpy-*.png","displayName":30,"actorLink":false,"width":1,"height":1,"scale":1,"mirrorX":false,"mirrorY":false,"lockRotation":false,"rotation":0,"alpha":1,"vision":true,"dimSight":0,"brightSight":0,"dimLight":0,"brightLight":0,"sightAngle":0,"lightAngle":0,"lightAlpha":0.25,"lightAnimation":{"speed":5,"intensity":5},"disposition":-1,"displayBars":20,"bar1":{"attribute":""},"bar2":{"attribute":""},"flags":{"perfect-vision":{"visionRules":"default","monoVisionColor":"","sightLimit":null}},"randomImg":true,"actorId":null,"tint":null,"lightColor":null,"x":null,"y":null,"elevation":null},"items":[{"_id":"Bf0NpaRHtHmfrLb3","name":"Athletics","type":"skill","img":"icons/magic/control/buff-strength-muscle-damage.webp","data":{"description":"<div class=\"sweb-core\">\n<p>Athletics combines an individual&rsquo;s coordin&shy;ation with learned skills such as climbing, jumping, balancing, biking, wrestling, skiing, swimming, throwing, or catching. Characters who rely on physical power more than coordination can take the @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Brute]{Brute} Edge to link this skill to @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Traits]{Strength} instead of @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Traits]{Agility}.</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"attribute":"agility","isCoreSkill":false,"die":{"sides":6,"modifier":0},"wild-die":{"sides":6}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_azxylmvr7yo","path":"Skills","color":"#008000"},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.swade-core-rules.swade-skills.sAig03GZiFKqBX7p"}}},{"_id":"bJxCFLP4a8BEU0Qm","name":"Common Knowledge","type":"skill","img":"icons/sundries/documents/document-official-capital.webp","data":{"description":"<div class=\"sweb-core\"><p>Characters roll Common Knowledge to know people, places, and things of their world, including etiquette, geography, culture, popular technology, contacts, and customs.</p></div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"attribute":"smarts","isCoreSkill":false,"die":{"sides":4,"modifier":0},"wild-die":{"sides":6}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_azxylmvr7yo","path":"Skills","color":"#008000"},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.swade-core-rules.swade-skills.8N1uMThntsjaUPem"}}},{"_id":"gMAJFeCm5e3Oporq","name":"Fighting","type":"skill","img":"icons/skills/melee/hand-grip-sword-white-brown.webp","data":{"description":"<div class=\"sweb-core\">\n<p>Fighting covers all hand-to-hand (melee) attacks, whether it&rsquo;s with fists, axes, laser swords, or martial arts. See @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Combat]{Chapter Three} for the combat rules and the various maneuvers a warrior might attempt.</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"attribute":"agility","isCoreSkill":false,"die":{"sides":6,"modifier":0},"wild-die":{"sides":6}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_azxylmvr7yo","path":"Skills","color":"#008000"},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.swade-core-rules.swade-skills.wWiwjPlzAQU3TN9l"}}},{"_id":"9coycVPgGdTGpbmh","name":"Language (Common)","type":"skill","img":"icons/sundries/documents/document-letter-formal-tan.webp","data":{"description":"<div class=\"sweb-core\">\n<p>In some settings, such as those that focus on pulp action or &ldquo;planetary romance&rdquo; (where characters frequently travel among many strange civilizations), speaking various languages can simply be roleplayed with halting dialogue and campy accents that start out a little difficult and are quickly forgotten. The GM may ignore this skill altogether in these settings, or use the @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Multiple Languages]{Multiple Languages} &shy;option in the @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Setting Rules]{Setting Rules}.</p>\n<p>In more realistic settings, communication can be a major barrier that requires characters to put skill points into additional languages. In a 1980s World War Three game, for example, a group of United Nations paratroopers won&rsquo;t be able to speak with their foes unless they take Russian, Polish, or other languages common to the Warsaw Pact.</p>\n<p>If the Language skill is in use, it should be listed as Language (Spanish), Language (American Sign Language), etc. A character&rsquo;s die type also notes how fluent he is in it. (Characters start with a d8 in their own Language.)</p>\n<div class=\"sweb-core\">\n<table class=\"table value-table\"><caption class=\"table-caption\">\n<h2 class=\"table-title\">Language Proficiency</h2>\n</caption>\n<tbody>\n<tr class=\"table-header-row\">\n<th class=\"table-column-header\" scope=\"col\">Skill</th>\n<th class=\"table-column-header\" scope=\"col\">Ability</th>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td>d4</td>\n<td>The character can read, write and speak common words and phrases.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>d6</td>\n<td>The speaker can carry on a prolonged but occasionally halting conversation.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>d8</td>\n<td>The character can speak fluently.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>d10</td>\n<td>The hero can mimic other dialects within the language.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>d12</td>\n<td>The speaker can masterfully recite important literary or oral works.</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>\n</div>\n<p><strong>Limited: </strong>Use whichever skill is lowest when performing an action that requires knowledge of a foreign language. @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Intimidation]{Intimidation} (if verbal), @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Persuasion]{Persuasion}, @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Research]{Research}, @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Taunt]{Taunt}, etc., are all limited by the character&rsquo;s Language skill.</p>\n<p>This limitation never applies to a character&rsquo;s native tongue.</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"attribute":"smarts","isCoreSkill":false,"die":{"sides":8,"modifier":0},"wild-die":{"sides":6}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_azxylmvr7yo","path":"Skills","color":"#008000"},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.swade-core-rules.swade-skills.XIuR2IyQtewm5BZP"}}},{"_id":"TWqtRMnChmXvwXvN","name":"Notice","type":"skill","img":"icons/creatures/eyes/human-single-blue.webp","data":{"description":"<div class=\"sweb-core\">\n<p>Notice is a hero&rsquo;s general awareness and alertness. It&rsquo;s used to sense sights, sounds, tastes, and smells, spot clues, detect ambushes, spot hidden weapons on a foe, or tell if a rival is lying, frightened, happy, etc.</p>\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Trait Rolls]{Success} conveys basic information&mdash;the character hears movement in the forest, smells distant smoke, or senses someone isn&rsquo;t being completely truthful.</p>\n<p>A @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Raises]{raise} grants more detail, such as the direction of a sound or odor or what topic a person is avoiding or lying about.</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"attribute":"smarts","isCoreSkill":false,"die":{"sides":6,"modifier":0},"wild-die":{"sides":6}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_azxylmvr7yo","path":"Skills","color":"#008000"},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.swade-core-rules.swade-skills.yvw9bMgsrWQXuZN2"}}},{"_id":"rk3ft5Cc4sHxF5ay","name":"Stealth","type":"skill","img":"icons/magic/nature/stealth-hide-eyes-green.webp","data":{"description":"<div class=\"sweb-core\">\n<p>Stealth is the ability to hide and move quietly. A simple @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Trait Rolls]{success} on a Stealth roll means the character avoids detection if enemies aren&rsquo;t particularly alert. If the character @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Trait Rolls]{fails} the roll, the enemy realizes something is amiss and begins actively searching for whatever roused them.</p>\n<p>Once foes are alerted and active, Stealth is opposed by @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Notice]{Notice} (a @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Trait Rolls]{group roll} if there are many foes.</p>\n<p>The GM should apply any circumstantial penalties to @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Notice]{Notice} rolls for @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Illumination]{darkness}, @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Cover and Obstacles]{cover}, noise, distractions, and any difference in the target&rsquo;s @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Size and Scale]{Scale} (just like when attacking). Sneaking through dry leaves might subtract 2 from the Stealth roll, for example, while spotting someone in the dark uses the @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Illumination]{Illumination} penalty (&minus;4). Don&rsquo;t apply the same modifier to both rolls, however. If Stealth is at &minus;2 for the leaves, don&rsquo;t give Notice a +2 for them as well.</p>\n<p><strong>Sneak Attack: </strong> Sneaking up close enough to make a melee attack <em>always</em> requires an @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Trait Rolls]{opposed} Stealth roll versus the target&rsquo;s @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Notice]{Notice}, whether the guard is actively looking for trouble or not. If successful, the victim is @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Distracted and Vulnerable]{Vulnerable} to the attacker, but only until the attacker&rsquo;s turn ends. With a raise, the attacker has @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.The Drop]{The Drop} instead.</p>\n<p><strong>Movement:</strong> In combat, characters roll Stealth each turn as a @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Actions]{free action} at the end of their move or any action the GM thinks might draw attention.</p>\n<p>Out of combat, the distance moved depends entirely on the situation. The GM might want a roll every minute if the group is sneaking around the perimeter of a defensive position, or every few miles if they&rsquo;re trying to quietly walk the path through a dark forest without alerting the creatures that live there.</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"attribute":"agility","isCoreSkill":false,"die":{"sides":6,"modifier":0},"wild-die":{"sides":6}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_azxylmvr7yo","path":"Skills","color":"#008000"},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.swade-core-rules.swade-skills.z9FmdFVGOOW2kufm"}}},{"_id":"6BeiHr2FDzQaAZll","name":"Untrained","type":"skill","img":"icons/magic/symbols/question-stone-yellow.webp","data":{"description":"<div class=\"sweb-core\">\n<p>If a character doesn&rsquo;t have a skill for an action he&rsquo;s attempting, he rolls a d4 for his skill die (and a Wild Die if a @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Wild Cards and Extras]{Wild Card}) and subtracts 2 from the total.</p>\n<p>The GM may decide certain tasks cannot be attempted unskilled, such as performing complex surgery or flying a commercial jet.</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"attribute":"agility","isCoreSkill":false,"die":{"sides":4,"modifier":-2},"wild-die":{"sides":6}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_azxylmvr7yo","path":"Skills","color":"#008000"},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.swade-core-rules.swade-skills.1Pl2ZL8MPyKnaVEg"}}},{"_id":"N1OCwZvFIDN4gSVH","name":"Unarmed Strike","type":"weapon","img":"icons/skills/melee/unarmed-punch-fist.webp","data":{"description":"<div class=\"sweb-core\">\n<p>See @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Unarmed Defender]{Unarmed Defender}.</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"quantity":1,"weight":0,"price":0,"equippable":false,"equipped":true,"isVehicular":false,"mods":1,"actions":{"skill":"Fighting","skillMod":"","dmgMod":"","additional":{}},"damage":"@str+d4","range":"","rof":"1","ap":"0","minStr":"","shots":"0","currentShots":"0","ammo":"","autoReload":false},"effects":[],"folder":"651LNce8no6HR9rY","sort":100000,"permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"flags":{"journal-links":{},"core":{"sourceId":"Item.X31v8asHtqhgiaM2"}}},{"_id":"4F8Q5B0P7tADAaGa","name":"Brawler","type":"edge","img":"icons/environment/people/charge.webp","data":{"description":"<div class=\"sweb-core\">\n<p>His fists hit like hammers or his talons cut like scythes. His body feels like it&rsquo;s made of stone. Brawlers increase their @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Characters]{Toughness} by 1 and roll @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Traits]{Strength} +d4 when hitting with their fists or feet (or claws if they have them). If they already have a damage die from </span><strong>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Special Ability (Claws)]{Claws}</strong>, the @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Martial Artist]{Martial Artist} Edge, etc., increase the damage die type by one instead. </span></p>\n<p>The Brawler Edge doesn&rsquo;t make the character&rsquo;s fists </span><strong>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Natural Weapons]{Natural Weapons}</span></strong></p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Novice, Strength d8+, Vigor d8+"}},"effects":[{"_id":"kjzlcYkuLXL4NwhC","changes":[{"key":"data.stats.toughness.value","mode":2,"value":"1"}],"disabled":false,"duration":{"startTime":null},"icon":"icons/environment/people/charge.webp","label":"Brawler","transfer":true,"flags":{},"tint":null}],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_7529swwanpd","path":"Edges#/CF_SEP/Combat Edges","color":"#000000"},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.swade-core-rules.swade-edges.q5NKwGPeK9PKQdIb"}}}],"effects":[{"_id":"9ByhnGOJiAHNuQZZ","changes":[{"key":"data.stats.toughness.value","mode":2,"value":"1"}],"disabled":false,"duration":{"startTime":28973116800},"icon":"icons/environment/people/charge.webp","label":"Brawler","origin":"Actor.ctrOErn6sfvnn1xC.Item.4F8Q5B0P7tADAaGa","tint":null,"transfer":false,"flags":{}}],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_3a04s0jrz4j","path":"Pirates of Cyre Bestiary#/CF_SEP/NPC's","color":"#000000"}}}
{"_id":"NI8DuzUr5xNAOcht","name":"Rosie Cusswell","type":"npc","img":"https://assets.forge-vtt.com/5f43f8ea1a91d63438d13159/artwork-adventures/pirates-of-cyre/characters/rosie-cusswell.webp","data":{"attributes":{"agility":{"die":{"sides":8,"modifier":0},"wild-die":{"sides":6}},"smarts":{"die":{"sides":4,"modifier":0},"wild-die":{"sides":6},"animal":false},"spirit":{"die":{"sides":6,"modifier":0},"wild-die":{"sides":6},"unShakeBonus":0},"strength":{"die":{"sides":8,"modifier":0},"wild-die":{"sides":6},"encumbranceSteps":0},"vigor":{"die":{"sides":8,"modifier":0},"wild-die":{"sides":6}}},"stats":{"speed":{"runningDie":6,"runningMod":0,"value":7},"toughness":{"value":0,"armor":0,"modifier":0},"parry":{"value":6,"modifier":0},"size":-1},"details":{"biography":{"value":"<div class=\"sweb-core\">\n<p>Short but fierce, Rosie Cusswell has more muscles than most of the crew, and a fouler mouth than all of them put together. <br style=\"font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; font-weight: normal; letter-spacing: normal; line-height: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: -webkit-auto; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-size-adjust: auto; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px;\" /><br /></p>\n</div>"},"species":{"name":""},"currency":500,"wealth":{"die":6,"modifier":0,"wild-die":6},"conviction":{"value":0,"active":false},"autoCalcToughness":true,"autoCalcParry":true},"powerPoints":{},"fatigue":{"value":0,"min":0,"max":2},"wounds":{"value":0,"min":0,"max":1,"ignored":0},"advances":{"value":0,"rank":"Novice","details":""},"bennies":{"value":2,"max":2},"status":{"isShaken":false,"isDistracted":false,"isVulnerable":false,"isStunned":false,"isEntangled":false,"isBound":false},"initiative":{"hasHesitant":false,"hasLevelHeaded":false,"hasImpLevelHeaded":false,"hasQuick":true},"additionalStats":{},"wildcard":false},"token":{"flags":{},"name":"Blank","displayName":30,"img":"modules/etu-rules/assets/bestiary_tokens/sonya-alvarez-min.png","tint":null,"width":1,"height":1,"scale":1,"mirrorX":false,"mirrorY":false,"lockRotation":false,"rotation":0,"vision":true,"dimSight":0,"brightSight":0,"dimLight":0,"brightLight":0,"sightAngle":0,"lightAngle":0,"lightColor":null,"lightAlpha":1,"lightAnimation":{"speed":5,"intensity":5},"actorId":null,"actorLink":true,"disposition":0,"displayBars":0,"bar1":{"attribute":""},"bar2":{"attribute":""},"randomImg":false,"alpha":1},"items":[{"_id":"UZW0tLJicg0VZOp4","name":"Athletics","type":"skill","data":{"description":"<div class=\"sweb-core\">\n<p>Athletics combines an individual&rsquo;s coordin&shy;ation with learned skills such as climbing, jumping, balancing, biking, wrestling, skiing, swimming, throwing, or catching. Characters who rely on physical power more than coordination can take the @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Brute]{Brute} Edge to link this skill to @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Traits]{Strength} instead of @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Traits]{Agility}.</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"attribute":"agility","isCoreSkill":false,"die":{"sides":8,"modifier":0},"wild-die":{"sides":6}},"sort":100000,"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_nsugutrpau","path":"Skills","color":"#8c160f"},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.swade-core-rules.swade-skills.Athletics"}},"img":"icons/magic/control/buff-strength-muscle-damage.webp","effects":[],"folder":null,"permission":{"default":0}},{"_id":"W5lfcCNjirSPUH42","name":"Common Knowledge","type":"skill","data":{"description":"<div class=\"sweb-core\"><p>Characters roll Common Knowledge to know people, places, and things of their world, including etiquette, geography, culture, popular technology, contacts, and customs.</p></div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"attribute":"smarts","isCoreSkill":false,"die":{"sides":4,"modifier":0},"wild-die":{"sides":6}},"sort":200000,"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_nsugutrpau","path":"Skills","color":"#8c160f"},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.swade-core-rules.swade-skills.Common Knowledge"}},"img":"icons/sundries/documents/document-official-capital.webp","effects":[],"folder":null,"permission":{"default":0}},{"_id":"quj5jF3vNls1j5E3","name":"Notice","type":"skill","data":{"description":"<div class=\"sweb-core\">\n<p>Notice is a hero&rsquo;s general awareness and alertness. It&rsquo;s used to sense sights, sounds, tastes, and smells, spot clues, detect ambushes, spot hidden weapons on a foe, or tell if a rival is lying, frightened, happy, etc.</p>\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Trait Rolls]{Success} conveys basic information&mdash;the character hears movement in the forest, smells distant smoke, or senses someone isn&rsquo;t being completely truthful.</p>\n<p>A @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Raises]{raise} grants more detail, such as the direction of a sound or odor or what topic a person is avoiding or lying about.</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"attribute":"smarts","isCoreSkill":false,"die":{"sides":4,"modifier":0},"wild-die":{"sides":6}},"sort":300000,"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_nsugutrpau","path":"Skills","color":"#8c160f"},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.swade-core-rules.swade-skills.ZvwjzMLxsneptV4T"}},"img":"icons/creatures/eyes/human-single-blue.webp","effects":[],"folder":null,"permission":{"default":0}},{"_id":"TOEzoo2Lf4A5JXOF","name":"Persuasion","type":"skill","data":{"description":"<div class=\"sweb-core\">\n<p>Persuasion is the ability to convince others to do what you want through reason, cajoling, deception, rewards, or other friendly means. Persuasion isn&rsquo;t mind control. It can change someone&rsquo;s attitude but not their goals. A bandit may let you keep a sentimental piece of jewelry with a good Persuasion roll but still takes all your other goods.</p>\n<p>When used to @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Support]{Support} allies it&rsquo;s an unopposed roll. If the target is resistant, it&rsquo;s an @JournalEntry[JBxsGv2wAoAmoCDe]{opposed} roll vs. the target&rsquo;s @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Traits]{Spirit}. The GM should modify the roll as she sees fit based on roleplaying, any pertinent @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Edges]{Edges} or @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Hindrances]{Hindrances} that affect the conversation, and the circumstances.</p>\n<p><strong>Reaction Level:</strong> How much a person is willing to cooperate depends largely on their attitude toward whoever&rsquo;s talking to them. The Game Master can decide how nonplayer characters feel based on the setting, or roll on the @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-tables.Reaction Table]{Reaction Table} if she has no preconceived notions.</p>\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Trait Rolls]{Success} improves the target&rsquo;s attitude one level and a raise improves it two. Further increases aren&rsquo;t generally possible in the same encounter&mdash;it takes individuals a little time to adjust their biases.</p>\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Trait Rolls]{Failure} means the target won&rsquo;t change his mind this scene or until the situation changes in some important way. A @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Trait Rolls]{Critical Failure} also <em>reduces</em> the target&rsquo;s attitude two levels.</p>\n<p>Only one roll should generally be allowed per interaction unless new information is revealed, a substantial reward is offered, etc.</p>\n<p><strong>Networking: </strong>Characters can also use Persuasion as a &ldquo;macro skill,&rdquo; simulating a few hours or an evening&rsquo;s time hobnobbing and socializing to gain favors or information. See @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Networking]{Networking}.</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"attribute":"spirit","isCoreSkill":false,"die":{"sides":4,"modifier":-1},"wild-die":{"sides":6}},"sort":400000,"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_nsugutrpau","path":"Skills","color":"#8c160f"},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.swade-core-rules.swade-skills.Persuasion"}},"img":"icons/skills/social/diplomacy-handshake.webp","effects":[],"folder":null,"permission":{"default":0}},{"_id":"8VzaSa3EEDrMz6PR","name":"Stealth","type":"skill","data":{"description":"<div class=\"sweb-core\">\n<p>Stealth is the ability to hide and move quietly. A simple @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Trait Rolls]{success} on a Stealth roll means the character avoids detection if enemies aren&rsquo;t particularly alert. If the character @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Trait Rolls]{fails} the roll, the enemy realizes something is amiss and begins actively searching for whatever roused them.</p>\n<p>Once foes are alerted and active, Stealth is opposed by @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Notice]{Notice} (a @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Trait Rolls]{group roll} if there are many foes.</p>\n<p>The GM should apply any circumstantial penalties to @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Notice]{Notice} rolls for @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Illumination]{darkness}, @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Cover and Obstacles]{cover}, noise, distractions, and any difference in the target&rsquo;s @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Size and Scale]{Scale} (just like when attacking). Sneaking through dry leaves might subtract 2 from the Stealth roll, for example, while spotting someone in the dark uses the @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Illumination]{Illumination} penalty (&minus;4). Don&rsquo;t apply the same modifier to both rolls, however. If Stealth is at &minus;2 for the leaves, don&rsquo;t give Notice a +2 for them as well.</p>\n<p><strong>Sneak Attack: </strong> Sneaking up close enough to make a melee attack <em>always</em> requires an @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Trait Rolls]{opposed} Stealth roll versus the target&rsquo;s @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Notice]{Notice}, whether the guard is actively looking for trouble or not. If successful, the victim is @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Distracted and Vulnerable]{Vulnerable} to the attacker, but only until the attacker&rsquo;s turn ends. With a raise, the attacker has @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.The Drop]{The Drop} instead.</p>\n<p><strong>Movement:</strong> In combat, characters roll Stealth each turn as a @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Actions]{free action} at the end of their move or any action the GM thinks might draw attention.</p>\n<p>Out of combat, the distance moved depends entirely on the situation. The GM might want a roll every minute if the group is sneaking around the perimeter of a defensive position, or every few miles if they&rsquo;re trying to quietly walk the path through a dark forest without alerting the creatures that live there.</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"attribute":"agility","isCoreSkill":false,"die":{"sides":8,"modifier":0},"wild-die":{"sides":6}},"sort":500000,"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_nsugutrpau","path":"Skills","color":"#8c160f"},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.swade-core-rules.swade-skills.Stealth"}},"img":"icons/magic/nature/stealth-hide-eyes-green.webp","effects":[],"folder":null,"permission":{"default":0}},{"_id":"BQ3OOQlkZvCl1Lfb","name":"Untrained","type":"skill","data":{"description":"<div class=\"sweb-core\">\n<p>If a character doesn&rsquo;t have a skill for an action he&rsquo;s attempting, he rolls a d4 for his skill die (and a Wild Die if a @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Wild Cards and Extras]{Wild Card}) and subtracts 2 from the total.</p>\n<p>The GM may decide certain tasks cannot be attempted unskilled, such as performing complex surgery or flying a commercial jet.</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"attribute":"agility","isCoreSkill":false,"die":{"sides":4,"modifier":"-2"},"wild-die":{"sides":6}},"sort":1100000,"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_nsugutrpau","path":"Skills","color":"#8c160f"},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.swade-core-rules.swade-skills.zcn1epcU4FEJGGyI"}},"img":"icons/magic/symbols/question-stone-yellow.webp","effects":[],"folder":null,"permission":{"default":0}},{"_id":"uaVAhwDnUDLFZFXm","name":"Unarmed strike","type":"weapon","data":{"description":"","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"quantity":1,"weight":0,"price":0,"equippable":false,"equipped":true,"isVehicular":false,"mods":1,"actions":{"skill":"","skillMod":"","dmgMod":"","additional":{}},"damage":"@str+d4","range":"","rof":"1","ap":"0","minStr":"","shots":"0","currentShots":"0","ammo":"","autoReload":false},"sort":1400000,"flags":{},"img":"icons/skills/melee/unarmed-punch-fist.webp","effects":[],"folder":null,"permission":{"default":0}},{"_id":"GjcL17dCtOeFUvbu","name":"Fighting","type":"skill","data":{"description":"<div class=\"sweb-core\">\n<p>Fighting covers all hand-to-hand (melee) attacks, whether it&rsquo;s with fists, axes, laser swords, or martial arts. See @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Combat]{Chapter Three} for the combat rules and the various maneuvers a warrior might attempt.</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"attribute":"agility","isCoreSkill":false,"die":{"sides":8,"modifier":0},"wild-die":{"sides":6}},"sort":1500000,"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_qals24wpyph","path":"Skills","color":"#8c160f"},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.swade-core-rules.swade-skills.wWiwjPlzAQU3TN9l"}},"img":"icons/skills/melee/hand-grip-sword-white-brown.webp","effects":[],"folder":null,"permission":{"default":0}},{"_id":"2S25FXQXotZBbOeW","name":"Boating","type":"skill","img":"icons/environment/settlement/ship.webp","data":{"description":"<div class=\"sweb-core\"><p>Characters with this skill can handle most any boat or ship common to their setting. They also know how to handle common tasks associated with their vessel such as tying knots, rigging sails, or following currents.</p></div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"attribute":"agility","isCoreSkill":false,"die":{"sides":4,"modifier":0},"wild-die":{"sides":6}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"3HvtK4sMp7flYKmT":3,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_qals24wpyph","path":"Skills","color":"#8c160f"},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.swade-core-rules.swade-skills.WMWgIVDuAW4cHxj2"}}},{"_id":"YHhyv0RRpudIeQ8j","name":"Intimidation","type":"skill","img":"icons/skills/wounds/injury-face-impact-orange.webp","data":{"description":"<div class=\"sweb-core\">\n<p>Intimidation is the art of frightening an opponent so that he backs down, reveals information, or flees.</p>\n<p>Intimidation is an @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Trait Rolls]{opposed roll} resisted by the opponent&rsquo;s @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Traits]{Spirit}. In combat, this is a @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Test]{Test}. Out of combat, a successful roll means the foe backs down for the most part, reveals some information, or slinks away when the opportunity presents itself.</p>\n<p>A @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Raises]{raise} might mean he backs down for the remainder of the scene, spills all the beans, or runs away as fast as he can.</p>\n<p>In or out of combat, a @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Trait Rolls]{Critical Failure} means the target is immune to this character&rsquo;s Intimidation attempts for the remainder of this encounter!</p>\n<p><strong>Networking:</strong> Intimidation can also be used as a &ldquo;macro&rdquo; skill to simulate several hours of working the streets. See @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Networking]{Networking} to see how to crack some heads for favors or information.</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"attribute":"spirit","isCoreSkill":false,"die":{"sides":8,"modifier":0},"wild-die":{"sides":6}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"3HvtK4sMp7flYKmT":3,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_qals24wpyph","path":"Skills","color":"#8c160f"},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.swade-core-rules.swade-skills.RrgAZp50CgQyyY6w"}}},{"_id":"oXD9LLAdtVm2vN8a","name":"Language (Common)","type":"skill","img":"icons/sundries/documents/document-letter-formal-tan.webp","data":{"description":"<div class=\"sweb-core\">\n<p>In some settings, such as those that focus on pulp action or &ldquo;planetary romance&rdquo; (where characters frequently travel among many strange civilizations), speaking various languages can simply be roleplayed with halting dialogue and campy accents that start out a little difficult and are quickly forgotten. The GM may ignore this skill altogether in these settings, or use the @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Multiple Languages]{Multiple Languages} &shy;option in the @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Setting Rules]{Setting Rules}.</p>\n<p>In more realistic settings, communication can be a major barrier that requires characters to put skill points into additional languages. In a 1980s World War Three game, for example, a group of United Nations paratroopers won&rsquo;t be able to speak with their foes unless they take Russian, Polish, or other languages common to the Warsaw Pact.</p>\n<p>If the Language skill is in use, it should be listed as Language (Spanish), Language (American Sign Language), etc. A character&rsquo;s die type also notes how fluent he is in it. (Characters start with a d8 in their own Language.)</p>\n<div class=\"sweb-core\">\n<table class=\"table value-table\"><caption class=\"table-caption\">\n<h2 class=\"table-title\">Language Proficiency</h2>\n</caption>\n<tbody>\n<tr class=\"table-header-row\">\n<th class=\"table-column-header\" scope=\"col\">Skill</th>\n<th class=\"table-column-header\" scope=\"col\">Ability</th>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td>d4</td>\n<td>The character can read, write and speak common words and phrases.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>d6</td>\n<td>The speaker can carry on a prolonged but occasionally halting conversation.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>d8</td>\n<td>The character can speak fluently.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>d10</td>\n<td>The hero can mimic other dialects within the language.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>d12</td>\n<td>The speaker can masterfully recite important literary or oral works.</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>\n</div>\n<p><strong>Limited: </strong>Use whichever skill is lowest when performing an action that requires knowledge of a foreign language. @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Intimidation]{Intimidation} (if verbal), @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Persuasion]{Persuasion}, @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Research]{Research}, @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Taunt]{Taunt}, etc., are all limited by the character&rsquo;s Language skill.</p>\n<p>This limitation never applies to a character&rsquo;s native tongue.</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"attribute":"smarts","isCoreSkill":false,"die":{"sides":8,"modifier":0},"wild-die":{"sides":6}},"effects":[],"folder":"kFghWjY7gP7MEqav","sort":1,"permission":{"default":0,"3HvtK4sMp7flYKmT":3,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_nsugutrpau","path":"Skills","color":"#8c160f"},"journal-links":{},"core":{"sourceId":"Item.B8Z0BJ0B2ULcZFmw"}}},{"_id":"iy0z38oOByQSlz3U","name":"Language (Halfling)","type":"skill","img":"icons/sundries/documents/document-letter-formal-tan.webp","data":{"description":"<div class=\"sweb-core\">\n<p>In some settings, such as those that focus on pulp action or &ldquo;planetary romance&rdquo; (where characters frequently travel among many strange civilizations), speaking various languages can simply be roleplayed with halting dialogue and campy accents that start out a little difficult and are quickly forgotten. The GM may ignore this skill altogether in these settings, or use the @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Multiple Languages]{Multiple Languages} &shy;option in the @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Setting Rules]{Setting Rules}.</p>\n<p>In more realistic settings, communication can be a major barrier that requires characters to put skill points into additional languages. In a 1980s World War Three game, for example, a group of United Nations paratroopers won&rsquo;t be able to speak with their foes unless they take Russian, Polish, or other languages common to the Warsaw Pact.</p>\n<p>If the Language skill is in use, it should be listed as Language (Spanish), Language (American Sign Language), etc. A character&rsquo;s die type also notes how fluent he is in it. (Characters start with a d8 in their own Language.)</p>\n<div class=\"sweb-core\">\n<table class=\"table value-table\"><caption class=\"table-caption\">\n<h2 class=\"table-title\">Language Proficiency</h2>\n</caption>\n<tbody>\n<tr class=\"table-header-row\">\n<th class=\"table-column-header\" scope=\"col\">Skill</th>\n<th class=\"table-column-header\" scope=\"col\">Ability</th>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td>d4</td>\n<td>The character can read, write and speak common words and phrases.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>d6</td>\n<td>The speaker can carry on a prolonged but occasionally halting conversation.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>d8</td>\n<td>The character can speak fluently.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>d10</td>\n<td>The hero can mimic other dialects within the language.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>d12</td>\n<td>The speaker can masterfully recite important literary or oral works.</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>\n</div>\n<p><strong>Limited: </strong>Use whichever skill is lowest when performing an action that requires knowledge of a foreign language. @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Intimidation]{Intimidation} (if verbal), @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Persuasion]{Persuasion}, @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Research]{Research}, @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Taunt]{Taunt}, etc., are all limited by the character&rsquo;s Language skill.</p>\n<p>This limitation never applies to a character&rsquo;s native tongue.</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"attribute":"smarts","isCoreSkill":false,"die":{"sides":8,"modifier":0},"wild-die":{"sides":6}},"effects":[],"folder":"kFghWjY7gP7MEqav","sort":1,"permission":{"default":0,"3HvtK4sMp7flYKmT":3,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_nsugutrpau","path":"Skills","color":"#8c160f"},"journal-links":{},"core":{"sourceId":"Item.B8Z0BJ0B2ULcZFmw"}}},{"_id":"gQRQHq3VChuwmSzV","name":"Language (Elvish)","type":"skill","img":"icons/sundries/documents/document-letter-formal-tan.webp","data":{"description":"<div class=\"sweb-core\">\n<p>In some settings, such as those that focus on pulp action or &ldquo;planetary romance&rdquo; (where characters frequently travel among many strange civilizations), speaking various languages can simply be roleplayed with halting dialogue and campy accents that start out a little difficult and are quickly forgotten. The GM may ignore this skill altogether in these settings, or use the @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Multiple Languages]{Multiple Languages} &shy;option in the @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Setting Rules]{Setting Rules}.</p>\n<p>In more realistic settings, communication can be a major barrier that requires characters to put skill points into additional languages. In a 1980s World War Three game, for example, a group of United Nations paratroopers won&rsquo;t be able to speak with their foes unless they take Russian, Polish, or other languages common to the Warsaw Pact.</p>\n<p>If the Language skill is in use, it should be listed as Language (Spanish), Language (American Sign Language), etc. A character&rsquo;s die type also notes how fluent he is in it. (Characters start with a d8 in their own Language.)</p>\n<div class=\"sweb-core\">\n<table class=\"table value-table\"><caption class=\"table-caption\">\n<h2 class=\"table-title\">Language Proficiency</h2>\n</caption>\n<tbody>\n<tr class=\"table-header-row\">\n<th class=\"table-column-header\" scope=\"col\">Skill</th>\n<th class=\"table-column-header\" scope=\"col\">Ability</th>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td>d4</td>\n<td>The character can read, write and speak common words and phrases.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>d6</td>\n<td>The speaker can carry on a prolonged but occasionally halting conversation.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>d8</td>\n<td>The character can speak fluently.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>d10</td>\n<td>The hero can mimic other dialects within the language.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>d12</td>\n<td>The speaker can masterfully recite important literary or oral works.</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>\n</div>\n<p><strong>Limited: </strong>Use whichever skill is lowest when performing an action that requires knowledge of a foreign language. @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Intimidation]{Intimidation} (if verbal), @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Persuasion]{Persuasion}, @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Research]{Research}, @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Taunt]{Taunt}, etc., are all limited by the character&rsquo;s Language skill.</p>\n<p>This limitation never applies to a character&rsquo;s native tongue.</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"attribute":"smarts","isCoreSkill":false,"die":{"sides":6,"modifier":0},"wild-die":{"sides":6}},"effects":[],"folder":"kFghWjY7gP7MEqav","sort":1,"permission":{"default":0,"3HvtK4sMp7flYKmT":3,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_nsugutrpau","path":"Skills","color":"#8c160f"},"journal-links":{},"core":{"sourceId":"Item.B8Z0BJ0B2ULcZFmw"}}},{"_id":"7jA8CuOvL4lMsLbg","name":"Performance","type":"skill","img":"icons/tools/instruments/lute-gold-brown.webp","data":{"description":"<div class=\"sweb-core\">\n<p>A good entertainer can lift the spirits, rally a crowd to action, or simply earn a few bucks from the locals. Specifics depend on the situation, setting, and how well the character is known in the area.</p>\n<p>Performance covers singing, acting, playing an instrument, or similar tasks that require an audience to appreciate.</p>\n<p><strong>Raising Funds:</strong> The amount of money a character can raise by performing is extremely subjective, but as a general rule a @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Trait Rolls]{successful} performance raises 20% of the setting's @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Characters]{Starting Funds} with a success and 30% with a raise. The GM can multiply this amount by the performer's @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Advancement]{Rank} if she feels it's appropriate. These numbers work for typical performers who might be known in a small establishment or area. Larger performances can greatly boost the performer's fee, but also require more time, energy, and setup.</p>\n<p><strong>Deception: </strong>Performance can be used instead of @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Persuasion]{Persuasion} if the character is attempting to deceive, bluff, or disguise herself and the GM agrees it makes sense in the context of the situation.</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"attribute":"spirit","isCoreSkill":false,"die":{"sides":6,"modifier":0},"wild-die":{"sides":6}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"3HvtK4sMp7flYKmT":3,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_qals24wpyph","path":"Skills","color":"#8c160f"},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.swade-core-rules.swade-skills.SJ1nN0CmOHNQhfOQ"}}},{"_id":"pQV9TN9sKQnrMqBA","name":"Combat Training","type":"edge","img":"icons/environment/people/infantry.webp","data":{"description":"<div class=\"sweb-core\">\n<p>The fighter are trained and adept at feints and deception in combat to unbalance their opponent. They add +1 to the all rolls for @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Test]{Tests} in combat that use any of the following skills: @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Athletics]{Athletics}, @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Battle]{Battle}, @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Fighting]{Fighting}, @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Intimidation]{Intimidation}, or @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Shooting]{Shooting} rolls.</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Novice, Fighter"}},"effects":[],"folder":"i5aNd30ywxpcOuxy","sort":200000,"permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"flags":{"journal-links":{},"core":{"sourceId":"Item.iAxlS6GhMXNoZpnI"}}},{"_id":"MHgAVQFq1kJqhxbG","name":"Fighter","type":"edge","img":"icons/environment/people/infantry.webp","data":{"description":"<div class=\"sweb-core\">\n<p>Some take up arms for glory, wealth, or revenge. Others do battle to prove themselves, to protect others, or because they know nothing else. Still others learn the ways of weaponcraft to hone their bodies in battle and prove their mettle in the forge of war.</p>\n<p>Lords of the battlefield, fighters are a disparate lot. Some train with many weapons; some prefer just one. Whatever their tactics, fighters excel at combat. They protect their own and defeat their enemies, rarely shying away from battle. They often lead the charge, a role they relish even if they don&rsquo;t insist on it.</p>\n<p>These skilled warriors turn hunks of metal into arms capable of taming kingdoms, slaughtering monsters, and rousing the hearts of armies. Woe to those who dare stand against them.</p>\n<p>Fighters gain the following abilities:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Combat Training]{Combat Training}</li>\n<li>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Martial Flexibility]{Martial Flexibility}</li>\n</ul>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Novice, Strength d6+, Fighting d6+"}},"effects":[],"folder":"i5aNd30ywxpcOuxy","sort":100000,"permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"flags":{"journal-links":{},"core":{"sourceId":"Item.JSFKscBmodf3b9qX"}}},{"_id":"znEgpQ5w8lTh7YJ4","name":"Martial Flexibility","type":"edge","img":"icons/environment/people/infantry.webp","data":{"description":"<div class=\"sweb-core\">\n<p>Once per encounter, as a @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Actions]{free action}, a fighter can choose to gain the benefits of a single Combat Edge. He must have the same Rank or higher as the Edge's Requirements, and the benefits of the chosen Edge end when the encounter ends.</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Fighter"}},"effects":[],"folder":"i5aNd30ywxpcOuxy","sort":200000,"permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"flags":{"journal-links":{},"core":{"sourceId":"Item.xWLvdULZeijuxwnc"}}},{"_id":"HVCL8zHMcKYH2leW","name":"Fleet-Footed","type":"edge","img":"icons/environment/people/group.webp","data":{"description":"<div class=\"sweb-core\">\n<p>The hero&rsquo;s @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Movement]{Pace} is increased by +2 and his @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Movement]{running die} increases one step (from d6 to d8, for example)</span></p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Novice, Agility d6+"}},"effects":[],"folder":"EnpCvbp1xbBRZIf1","sort":1300000,"permission":{"default":0,"3HvtK4sMp7flYKmT":3,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"flags":{"cf":null,"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.swade-core-rules.swade-edges.PTPwOeAxgwnjCiIv"}}},{"_id":"bn3zEKpaewDoyKzQ","name":"Quick","type":"edge","img":"icons/environment/people/group.webp","data":{"description":"<div class=\"sweb-core\">\n<p>Quick characters have lightning-fast reflexes and a cool head. Whenever you are dealt an @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Action Cards (Initiative)]{Action Card} of Five or lower, you may discard it and draw again until you get a card higher than Five.</span></p>\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Characters]{Characters} with both the @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Level Headed]{Level Headed} and Quick Edges first draw their additional card and choose which to take. If that card is a Five or less, the Quick Edge may be used to draw a replacement until it&rsquo;s Six or higher.</span></p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Novice, Agility d8+"}},"effects":[],"folder":"EnpCvbp1xbBRZIf1","sort":1800000,"permission":{"default":0,"3HvtK4sMp7flYKmT":3,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"flags":{"cf":null,"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.swade-core-rules.swade-edges.XHguf9iQ3N9yHN4Z"}}},{"_id":"5s6yDCmY9lOlhBlf","name":"Frenzy","type":"edge","img":"icons/environment/people/charge.webp","data":{"description":"<div class=\"sweb-core\">\n<p>A character with Frenzy rolls a second @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Fighting]{Fighting} die with any one of his Fighting attacks for the turn. The extra die may be allocated to the same or different targets as he sees fit. Resolve each separately</span></p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Seasoned, Fighting d8+"}},"effects":[],"folder":"hsEO07bFB8oM1LJo","sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"3HvtK4sMp7flYKmT":3,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"flags":{"cf":null,"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.swade-core-rules.swade-edges.DugtMFQnsmkUnQiv"}}},{"_id":"rLd6OYr6j2OSWfGD","name":"Mean","type":"hindrance","img":"icons/magic/holy/yin-yang-balance-symbol.webp","data":{"description":"<div class=\"sweb-core\">\n<p>This curmudgeon is ill-tempered and disagreeable. He has trouble doing anything kind for anyone else, must be paid for his troubles, and doesn&rsquo;t accept awards or favors graciously. Besides the obvious roleplaying issues, Mean characters subtract 1 from @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Persuasion]{Persuasion} @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Trait Rolls]{rolls}.</span></p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"major":false},"effects":[],"folder":"1updrtPaYhKD0fRY","sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"3HvtK4sMp7flYKmT":3,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"flags":{"cf":null,"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.swade-core-rules.swade-hindrances.sNgSwqh2fGyM6i14"}}},{"_id":"7XiebKl6VQRApcQ6","name":"Thin Skinned","type":"hindrance","img":"icons/magic/holy/yin-yang-balance-symbol.webp","data":{"description":"<div class=\"sweb-core\">\n<p>Personal attacks really get under this individual&rsquo;s skin. As a @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Characters]{Minor} @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Hindrances]{Hindrance}, he subtracts 2 when resisting @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Intimidation]{Intimidation} attacks or insults directed towards him. As a @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Characters]{Major}, he subtracts 4.</span></p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"major":false},"effects":[],"folder":"1updrtPaYhKD0fRY","sort":1100000,"permission":{"default":0,"3HvtK4sMp7flYKmT":3,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_paujlrjlvl","path":"Hindrances","color":"#8c160f"},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.swade-core-rules.swade-hindrances.7uHyQqqlYJRZoxUp"}}},{"_id":"ApxjgFdUiM2p4Y9v","name":"Axe, Hand (mwk)","type":"weapon","img":"icons/weapons/axes/axe-broad-engraved.webp","data":{"description":"","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"quantity":1,"weight":2,"price":310,"equippable":false,"equipped":true,"isVehicular":false,"mods":1,"actions":{"skill":"Fighting","skillMod":"","dmgMod":"","additional":{"czf29uz2s1":{"name":"Athletics (throwing)","type":"skill","rof":null,"skillMod":"","skillOverride":"Athletics","shotsUsed":null}}},"damage":"@str+d6","range":"3/6/12","rof":"1","ap":"1","minStr":"d6","shots":"0","currentShots":"0","ammo":"","autoReload":false},"effects":[],"folder":"ofLOMYgHLqfG1MyP","sort":800001,"permission":{"default":0,"ZvqefCj0L7TxJS56":3,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"flags":{"journal-links":{},"core":{"sourceId":"Item.F2JNgD0SfESTyCZ6"}}},{"_id":"KGDArywrleBpgKmK","name":"Resilient","type":"ability","img":"icons/creatures/fish/fish-fangtooth-skeletal-green.webp","data":{"description":"<div class=\"sweb-core\">\n<p>Elite Extras are tougher than usual. This might include specially bred orcs in a fantasy setting, particularly tough thugs or agents in the modern world, or even mutant animals created in the lab of some mad scientist.</p>\n<p>Resilient @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Wild Cards and Extras]{Extras} can take one @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Damage Effects]{Wound} before they're @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Damage Effects]{incapacitated}. @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Wild Cards and Extras]{Wild Cards} can't be Resilient. The ability exist to bring select Extras a little closer to the heroes and villains who lead them.</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"subtype":"special","grantsPowers":false},"effects":[],"folder":"vNo3WMiRK9jNtjZL","sort":2900000,"permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"flags":{"journal-links":{},"core":{"sourceId":"Item.qw10GaZFXFDuNQcm"}}},{"_id":"YTfaBIJCrm5QYRFv","name":"Brawler","type":"edge","img":"icons/environment/people/charge.webp","data":{"description":"<div class=\"sweb-core\">\n<p>His fists hit like hammers or his talons cut like scythes. His body feels like it&rsquo;s made of stone. Brawlers increase their @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Characters]{Toughness} by 1 and roll @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Traits]{Strength} +d4 when hitting with their fists or feet (or claws if they have them). If they already have a damage die from </span><strong>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Special Ability (Claws)]{Claws}</strong>, the @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Martial Artist]{Martial Artist} Edge, etc., increase the damage die type by one instead. </span></p>\n<p>The Brawler Edge doesn&rsquo;t make the character&rsquo;s fists </span><strong>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Natural Weapons]{Natural Weapons}</span></strong></p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Novice, Strength d8+, Vigor d8+"}},"effects":[{"_id":"kjzlcYkuLXL4NwhC","changes":[{"key":"data.stats.toughness.value","mode":2,"value":"1"}],"disabled":false,"duration":{"startTime":null},"icon":"icons/environment/people/charge.webp","label":"Brawler","transfer":true,"flags":{},"tint":null}],"folder":"hsEO07bFB8oM1LJo","sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"3HvtK4sMp7flYKmT":3,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"flags":{"cf":null,"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.swade-core-rules.swade-edges.q5NKwGPeK9PKQdIb"}}},{"_id":"kX2e3UbprC1SDnII","name":"Brave","type":"edge","img":"icons/skills/social/peace-luck-insult.webp","data":{"description":"<div class=\"sweb-core\">\n<p>Those with this Edge have learned to master their fear, or have dealt with so many horrors they&rsquo;ve become jaded. These valiant explorers add +2 to @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Fear]{Fear} checks and subtract 2 from </span><strong>@Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-tables.Fear Table]{Fear Table} </span></strong>results.</span></p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Novice, Spirit d6+"}},"effects":[],"folder":"RXzRwNmHRkixYrfR","sort":500000,"permission":{"default":0,"3HvtK4sMp7flYKmT":3,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_9dc4ijzy8uh","path":"Edges#/CF_SEP/Background Edges","color":"#000000"},"journal-links":{},"core":{"sourceId":"Item.WJbfV0MEvQBjHEaE"}}},{"_id":"fxWX3PiDspiVbDas","name":"Luck","type":"edge","img":"icons/skills/social/peace-luck-insult.webp","data":{"description":"<div class=\"sweb-core\">\n<p>The adventurer seems to be blessed by fate, karma, the gods, or whatever external forces he believes in (or believe in him!). </span></p>\n<p>He draws one extra @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Bennies]{Benny} at the beginning of each game session, allowing him to succeed at important tasks more often than most, and survive incredible dangers.</span></p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Novice"}},"effects":[{"_id":"ypFj4ugwOSUtjOLm","changes":[{"key":"data.bennies.max","mode":2,"value":"1"}],"disabled":false,"duration":{"startTime":null},"icon":"icons/skills/social/peace-luck-insult.webp","label":"Luck","transfer":true,"flags":{},"tint":null}],"folder":"RXzRwNmHRkixYrfR","sort":400000,"permission":{"default":0,"3HvtK4sMp7flYKmT":3,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_9dc4ijzy8uh","path":"Edges#/CF_SEP/Background Edges","color":"#000000"},"journal-links":{},"core":{"sourceId":"Item.a5BHUWx93nGoO2mo"}}}],"effects":[{"_id":"PfqXp0vlhAqmaicN","changes":[{"key":"data.stats.toughness.value","mode":2,"value":"1"}],"disabled":false,"duration":{"startTime":28973116800},"icon":"icons/environment/people/charge.webp","label":"Brawler","origin":"Actor.WN58p23HYeWyTQXL.Item.YTfaBIJCrm5QYRFv","tint":null,"transfer":false,"flags":{}},{"_id":"as7pjFynmnQL6H4G","changes":[{"key":"data.bennies.max","mode":2,"value":"1"}],"disabled":false,"duration":{"startTime":28973116800},"icon":"icons/skills/social/peace-luck-insult.webp","label":"Luck","origin":"Actor.WN58p23HYeWyTQXL.Item.fxWX3PiDspiVbDas","tint":null,"transfer":false,"flags":{}}],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"flags":{"journal-links":{"references":{}},"cf":{"id":"temp_3a04s0jrz4j","path":"Pirates of Cyre Bestiary#/CF_SEP/NPC's","color":"#000000"}}}
{"_id":"7lLpzNGV5uDjF3qL","name":"Sandara Quinn","type":"npc","img":"https://assets.forge-vtt.com/5f43f8ea1a91d63438d13159/artwork-adventures/pirates-of-cyre/characters/sandara-quinn.webp","data":{"attributes":{"agility":{"die":{"sides":6,"modifier":0},"wild-die":{"sides":6}},"smarts":{"die":{"sides":6,"modifier":0},"wild-die":{"sides":6},"animal":false},"spirit":{"die":{"sides":8,"modifier":0},"wild-die":{"sides":6},"unShakeBonus":0},"strength":{"die":{"sides":6,"modifier":0},"wild-die":{"sides":6},"encumbranceSteps":0},"vigor":{"die":{"sides":6,"modifier":0},"wild-die":{"sides":6}}},"stats":{"speed":{"runningDie":"6","runningMod":0,"value":6},"toughness":{"value":0,"armor":0,"modifier":0},"parry":{"value":4,"modifier":0},"size":0},"details":{"biography":{"value":"<div class=\"sweb-core\">\n<p>Crowned with a mane of fiery red locks, Sandara looks like someone not to be crossed. Yet the smile lines at the corners of her eyes and the easy way she holds herself hint at a lighter side. She dresses to accentuate her figure, and her whole appearance speaks of the sea, from the seagull feather in her tricorne hat to the sailor tattoos on her arms and the clay pipe thrust into the corner ofher mouth.</p>\n</div>"},"species":{"name":""},"currency":500,"wealth":{"die":6,"modifier":0,"wild-die":6},"conviction":{"value":0,"active":false},"autoCalcToughness":true,"autoCalcParry":true},"powerPoints":{"value":10,"max":10,"Cleric":{"value":0,"max":0}},"fatigue":{"value":0,"min":0,"max":2},"wounds":{"value":0,"min":0,"max":3,"ignored":0},"advances":{"value":0,"rank":"Novice","details":""},"bennies":{"value":3,"max":3},"status":{"isShaken":false,"isDistracted":false,"isVulnerable":false,"isStunned":false,"isEntangled":false,"isBound":false},"initiative":{"hasHesitant":false,"hasLevelHeaded":false,"hasImpLevelHeaded":false,"hasQuick":false},"additionalStats":{},"wildcard":true},"token":{"flags":{},"name":"Blank","displayName":30,"img":"modules/etu-rules/assets/bestiary_tokens/sonya-alvarez-min.png","tint":null,"width":1,"height":1,"scale":1,"mirrorX":false,"mirrorY":false,"lockRotation":false,"rotation":0,"vision":true,"dimSight":0,"brightSight":0,"dimLight":0,"brightLight":0,"sightAngle":0,"lightAngle":0,"lightColor":null,"lightAlpha":1,"lightAnimation":{"speed":5,"intensity":5},"actorId":null,"actorLink":true,"disposition":0,"displayBars":0,"bar1":{"attribute":""},"bar2":{"attribute":""},"randomImg":false,"alpha":1},"items":[{"_id":"UZW0tLJicg0VZOp4","name":"Athletics","type":"skill","data":{"description":"<div class=\"sweb-core\">\n<p>Athletics combines an individual&rsquo;s coordin&shy;ation with learned skills such as climbing, jumping, balancing, biking, wrestling, skiing, swimming, throwing, or catching. Characters who rely on physical power more than coordination can take the @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Brute]{Brute} Edge to link this skill to @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Traits]{Strength} instead of @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Traits]{Agility}.</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"attribute":"agility","isCoreSkill":false,"die":{"sides":6,"modifier":0},"wild-die":{"sides":6}},"sort":100000,"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_nsugutrpau","path":"Skills","color":"#8c160f"},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.swade-core-rules.swade-skills.Athletics"}},"img":"icons/magic/control/buff-strength-muscle-damage.webp","effects":[],"folder":null,"permission":{"default":0}},{"_id":"W5lfcCNjirSPUH42","name":"Common Knowledge","type":"skill","data":{"description":"<div class=\"sweb-core\"><p>Characters roll Common Knowledge to know people, places, and things of their world, including etiquette, geography, culture, popular technology, contacts, and customs.</p></div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"attribute":"smarts","isCoreSkill":false,"die":{"sides":6,"modifier":0},"wild-die":{"sides":6}},"sort":200000,"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_nsugutrpau","path":"Skills","color":"#8c160f"},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.swade-core-rules.swade-skills.Common Knowledge"}},"img":"icons/sundries/documents/document-official-capital.webp","effects":[],"folder":null,"permission":{"default":0}},{"_id":"quj5jF3vNls1j5E3","name":"Notice","type":"skill","data":{"description":"<div class=\"sweb-core\">\n<p>Notice is a hero&rsquo;s general awareness and alertness. It&rsquo;s used to sense sights, sounds, tastes, and smells, spot clues, detect ambushes, spot hidden weapons on a foe, or tell if a rival is lying, frightened, happy, etc.</p>\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Trait Rolls]{Success} conveys basic information&mdash;the character hears movement in the forest, smells distant smoke, or senses someone isn&rsquo;t being completely truthful.</p>\n<p>A @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Raises]{raise} grants more detail, such as the direction of a sound or odor or what topic a person is avoiding or lying about.</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"attribute":"smarts","isCoreSkill":false,"die":{"sides":6,"modifier":0},"wild-die":{"sides":6}},"sort":300000,"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_nsugutrpau","path":"Skills","color":"#8c160f"},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.swade-core-rules.swade-skills.ZvwjzMLxsneptV4T"}},"img":"icons/creatures/eyes/human-single-blue.webp","effects":[],"folder":null,"permission":{"default":0}},{"_id":"TOEzoo2Lf4A5JXOF","name":"Persuasion","type":"skill","data":{"description":"<div class=\"sweb-core\">\n<p>Persuasion is the ability to convince others to do what you want through reason, cajoling, deception, rewards, or other friendly means. Persuasion isn&rsquo;t mind control. It can change someone&rsquo;s attitude but not their goals. A bandit may let you keep a sentimental piece of jewelry with a good Persuasion roll but still takes all your other goods.</p>\n<p>When used to @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Support]{Support} allies it&rsquo;s an unopposed roll. If the target is resistant, it&rsquo;s an @JournalEntry[JBxsGv2wAoAmoCDe]{opposed} roll vs. the target&rsquo;s @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Traits]{Spirit}. The GM should modify the roll as she sees fit based on roleplaying, any pertinent @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Edges]{Edges} or @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Hindrances]{Hindrances} that affect the conversation, and the circumstances.</p>\n<p><strong>Reaction Level:</strong> How much a person is willing to cooperate depends largely on their attitude toward whoever&rsquo;s talking to them. The Game Master can decide how nonplayer characters feel based on the setting, or roll on the @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-tables.Reaction Table]{Reaction Table} if she has no preconceived notions.</p>\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Trait Rolls]{Success} improves the target&rsquo;s attitude one level and a raise improves it two. Further increases aren&rsquo;t generally possible in the same encounter&mdash;it takes individuals a little time to adjust their biases.</p>\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Trait Rolls]{Failure} means the target won&rsquo;t change his mind this scene or until the situation changes in some important way. A @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Trait Rolls]{Critical Failure} also <em>reduces</em> the target&rsquo;s attitude two levels.</p>\n<p>Only one roll should generally be allowed per interaction unless new information is revealed, a substantial reward is offered, etc.</p>\n<p><strong>Networking: </strong>Characters can also use Persuasion as a &ldquo;macro skill,&rdquo; simulating a few hours or an evening&rsquo;s time hobnobbing and socializing to gain favors or information. See @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Networking]{Networking}.</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"attribute":"spirit","isCoreSkill":false,"die":{"sides":6,"modifier":0},"wild-die":{"sides":6}},"sort":400000,"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_nsugutrpau","path":"Skills","color":"#8c160f"},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.swade-core-rules.swade-skills.Persuasion"}},"img":"icons/skills/social/diplomacy-handshake.webp","effects":[],"folder":null,"permission":{"default":0}},{"_id":"8VzaSa3EEDrMz6PR","name":"Stealth","type":"skill","data":{"description":"<div class=\"sweb-core\">\n<p>Stealth is the ability to hide and move quietly. A simple @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Trait Rolls]{success} on a Stealth roll means the character avoids detection if enemies aren&rsquo;t particularly alert. If the character @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Trait Rolls]{fails} the roll, the enemy realizes something is amiss and begins actively searching for whatever roused them.</p>\n<p>Once foes are alerted and active, Stealth is opposed by @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Notice]{Notice} (a @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Trait Rolls]{group roll} if there are many foes.</p>\n<p>The GM should apply any circumstantial penalties to @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Notice]{Notice} rolls for @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Illumination]{darkness}, @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Cover and Obstacles]{cover}, noise, distractions, and any difference in the target&rsquo;s @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Size and Scale]{Scale} (just like when attacking). Sneaking through dry leaves might subtract 2 from the Stealth roll, for example, while spotting someone in the dark uses the @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Illumination]{Illumination} penalty (&minus;4). Don&rsquo;t apply the same modifier to both rolls, however. If Stealth is at &minus;2 for the leaves, don&rsquo;t give Notice a +2 for them as well.</p>\n<p><strong>Sneak Attack: </strong> Sneaking up close enough to make a melee attack <em>always</em> requires an @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Trait Rolls]{opposed} Stealth roll versus the target&rsquo;s @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Notice]{Notice}, whether the guard is actively looking for trouble or not. If successful, the victim is @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Distracted and Vulnerable]{Vulnerable} to the attacker, but only until the attacker&rsquo;s turn ends. With a raise, the attacker has @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.The Drop]{The Drop} instead.</p>\n<p><strong>Movement:</strong> In combat, characters roll Stealth each turn as a @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Actions]{free action} at the end of their move or any action the GM thinks might draw attention.</p>\n<p>Out of combat, the distance moved depends entirely on the situation. The GM might want a roll every minute if the group is sneaking around the perimeter of a defensive position, or every few miles if they&rsquo;re trying to quietly walk the path through a dark forest without alerting the creatures that live there.</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"attribute":"agility","isCoreSkill":false,"die":{"sides":4,"modifier":0},"wild-die":{"sides":6}},"sort":500000,"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_nsugutrpau","path":"Skills","color":"#8c160f"},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.swade-core-rules.swade-skills.Stealth"}},"img":"icons/magic/nature/stealth-hide-eyes-green.webp","effects":[],"folder":null,"permission":{"default":0}},{"_id":"BQ3OOQlkZvCl1Lfb","name":"Untrained","type":"skill","data":{"description":"<div class=\"sweb-core\">\n<p>If a character doesn&rsquo;t have a skill for an action he&rsquo;s attempting, he rolls a d4 for his skill die (and a Wild Die if a @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Wild Cards and Extras]{Wild Card}) and subtracts 2 from the total.</p>\n<p>The GM may decide certain tasks cannot be attempted unskilled, such as performing complex surgery or flying a commercial jet.</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"attribute":"agility","isCoreSkill":false,"die":{"sides":4,"modifier":"-2"},"wild-die":{"sides":6}},"sort":1100000,"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_nsugutrpau","path":"Skills","color":"#8c160f"},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.swade-core-rules.swade-skills.zcn1epcU4FEJGGyI"}},"img":"icons/magic/symbols/question-stone-yellow.webp","effects":[],"folder":null,"permission":{"default":0}},{"_id":"uaVAhwDnUDLFZFXm","name":"Unarmed strike","type":"weapon","data":{"description":"","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"quantity":1,"weight":0,"price":0,"equippable":false,"equipped":true,"isVehicular":false,"mods":1,"actions":{"skill":"","skillMod":"","dmgMod":"","additional":{}},"damage":"@str","range":"","rof":"1","ap":"0","minStr":"","shots":"0","currentShots":"0","ammo":"","autoReload":false},"sort":1400000,"flags":{},"img":"icons/skills/melee/unarmed-punch-fist.webp","effects":[],"folder":null,"permission":{"default":0}},{"_id":"GjcL17dCtOeFUvbu","name":"Fighting","type":"skill","data":{"description":"<div class=\"sweb-core\">\n<p>Fighting covers all hand-to-hand (melee) attacks, whether it&rsquo;s with fists, axes, laser swords, or martial arts. See @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Combat]{Chapter Three} for the combat rules and the various maneuvers a warrior might attempt.</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"attribute":"agility","isCoreSkill":false,"die":{"sides":4,"modifier":0},"wild-die":{"sides":6}},"sort":1500000,"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_qals24wpyph","path":"Skills","color":"#8c160f"},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.swade-core-rules.swade-skills.wWiwjPlzAQU3TN9l"}},"img":"icons/skills/melee/hand-grip-sword-white-brown.webp","effects":[],"folder":null,"permission":{"default":0}},{"_id":"rnaYYVJUWiKmHIEq","name":"Religion","type":"skill","img":"icons/environment/settlement/gazebo.webp","data":{"description":"<div class=\"sweb-core\">\n<p>Religion reflects knowledge about ancient religions, mythic history, eccelsiastic tradition, holy symbols, undead, as well as details about all the religions of Eberron.</p>\n<p>A successful Religion roll reveals basic information about a topic, and a raise grants more details.</p>\n<p><em><strong>Source: Savage Eberron</strong></em></p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"attribute":"smarts","isCoreSkill":false,"die":{"sides":6,"modifier":0},"wild-die":{"sides":6}},"effects":[],"folder":"vdiWDU7Bqdgk8RH2","sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"flags":{"journal-links":{},"core":{"sourceId":"Item.HdShAatiWIBLgv8z"},"cf":null}},{"_id":"W863k0rTlzte6ZVH","name":"Shooting","type":"skill","img":"icons/skills/ranged/target-bullseye-arrow-glowing.webp","data":{"description":"<div class=\"sweb-core\">\n<p>Shooting covers all attempts to hit a target with a ranged weapon such as a bow, pistol, or rocket launcher (thrown weapons use @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Athletics]{Athletics}). See @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Combat]{Chapter Three} for details on ranged combat.</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"attribute":"agility","isCoreSkill":false,"die":{"sides":6,"modifier":0},"wild-die":{"sides":6}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"3HvtK4sMp7flYKmT":3,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_qals24wpyph","path":"Skills","color":"#8c160f"},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.swade-core-rules.swade-skills.sOHfVvBDhe3Oy3r1"}}},{"_id":"1ZGuEqSa5Nq3W0rL","name":"Healing","type":"skill","img":"icons/magic/nature/root-vine-caduceus-healing.webp","data":{"description":"<div class=\"sweb-core\">\n<p>Healing has multiple uses, from treating @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Damage Effects]{Wounds} to diagnosing diseases and analyzing certain kinds of forensic evidence.</p>\n<p>See @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Healing]{Healing} for rules on mending and treating @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Damage Effects]{Wounds}, and @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Hazards]{Hazards} for treatment of disease or poison.</p>\n<p><strong>Forensics: </strong> Healing can also be used to analyze evidence that relates to anatomical trauma, including cause and time of death, angle of attack, and similar matters. @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Trait Rolls]{Success} provides basic information and a @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Raises]{raise} increases the details uncovered.</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"attribute":"smarts","isCoreSkill":false,"die":{"sides":6,"modifier":0},"wild-die":{"sides":6}},"effects":[],"folder":"vdiWDU7Bqdgk8RH2","sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"3HvtK4sMp7flYKmT":3,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"flags":{"cf":null,"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.swade-core-rules.swade-skills.Dc50EUXxlsJl7sph"}}},{"_id":"TxsVd8wipyZmfMJ8","name":"Performance","type":"skill","img":"icons/tools/instruments/lute-gold-brown.webp","data":{"description":"<div class=\"sweb-core\">\n<p>A good entertainer can lift the spirits, rally a crowd to action, or simply earn a few bucks from the locals. Specifics depend on the situation, setting, and how well the character is known in the area.</p>\n<p>Performance covers singing, acting, playing an instrument, or similar tasks that require an audience to appreciate.</p>\n<p><strong>Raising Funds:</strong> The amount of money a character can raise by performing is extremely subjective, but as a general rule a @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Trait Rolls]{successful} performance raises 20% of the setting's @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Characters]{Starting Funds} with a success and 30% with a raise. The GM can multiply this amount by the performer's @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Advancement]{Rank} if she feels it's appropriate. These numbers work for typical performers who might be known in a small establishment or area. Larger performances can greatly boost the performer's fee, but also require more time, energy, and setup.</p>\n<p><strong>Deception: </strong>Performance can be used instead of @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Persuasion]{Persuasion} if the character is attempting to deceive, bluff, or disguise herself and the GM agrees it makes sense in the context of the situation.</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"attribute":"spirit","isCoreSkill":false,"die":{"sides":4,"modifier":0},"wild-die":{"sides":6}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"3HvtK4sMp7flYKmT":3,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_qals24wpyph","path":"Skills","color":"#8c160f"},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.swade-core-rules.swade-skills.SJ1nN0CmOHNQhfOQ"}}},{"_id":"c4D6T1p2nkLcWMrM","name":"Faith","type":"skill","img":"icons/magic/holy/prayer-hands-glowing-yellow.webp","data":{"description":"<div class=\"sweb-core\"><p>Faith is the arcane skill required for @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Arcane Background (Miracles)]{Arcane Background (Miracles)}.</p></div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"attribute":"spirit","isCoreSkill":false,"die":{"sides":8,"modifier":0},"wild-die":{"sides":6}},"effects":[],"folder":"cgfmurTJRwbCvmCc","sort":1600001,"permission":{"default":0,"3HvtK4sMp7flYKmT":3,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_qals24wpyph","path":"Skills","color":"#8c160f"},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.swade-core-rules.swade-skills.YI5rxzYzsqXwAo9A"}}},{"_id":"2CDspjGP8uyG3SpP","name":"Lore","type":"skill","img":"icons/sundries/books/book-stack.webp","data":{"description":"<div class=\"sweb-core\">\n<p>Lore reflects knowledge and your ability to recall bits of information about history, archaeology, different Ages, legends, other continents, literature, song, poetry, and similar fields. This would also include knowledge about the more common races of the worlds.</p>\n<p>If an explorer wants to remember when the Dhakaani empire collapsed or know when the Qualabrin were destroyed on Xen'drik, this is the skill to have.</p>\n<p>A successful Lore roll reveals basic information about a topic, and a raise grants more details.</p>\n<p><em><strong>Source: Savage Eberron replaces Academics</strong></em></p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"attribute":"smarts","isCoreSkill":false,"die":{"sides":4,"modifier":0},"wild-die":{"sides":6}},"effects":[],"folder":"cgfmurTJRwbCvmCc","sort":700001,"permission":{"default":0,"ZvqefCj0L7TxJS56":3,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"flags":{"journal-links":{},"core":{"sourceId":"Item.E0BVumGwbaczoPjD"}}},{"_id":"KHgBtd5M9NUusdTx","name":"Cleric","type":"edge","img":"icons/environment/people/cleric-grey.webp","data":{"description":"<div class=\"sweb-core\">\n<p>In faith and the miracles of the divine, many find a greater purpose. Called to serve powers beyond most mortal understanding, all priests provide for the spiritual needs of their people. More than mere preachers, clerics serve as emissaries of their gods. These ecclesiastics vow to spread the tenets, knowledge, and truth of their faith.</p>\n<p>While clerics of different faiths may share similar abilities, they prove as different from one another as the divinities they serve. Some offer healing and redemption, others judge law and truth, and still others spread conflict and corruption.</p>\n<p>Clerics gain the following abilities:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Arcane Background (Cleric)]{Arcane Background (Cleric)}</li>\n<li>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Channel Energy]{Channel Energy}</li>\n<li>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Vow of Faith]{Vow of Faith}</li>\n</ul>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Novice, Spirit d6+, Religion d6+"}},"effects":[],"folder":"RlvFYBE8BDHKhq30","sort":100000,"permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"flags":{"journal-links":{},"core":{"sourceId":"Item.ouw6W4r3rYVJQIqG"}}},{"_id":"SLN29WvDxuI2HQZj","name":"Arcane Background (Cleric)","type":"edge","img":"icons/environment/people/cleric-grey.webp","data":{"description":"<div class=\"sweb-core\">\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Arcane Background (Cleric)]{Arcane Background (Cleric)}</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"isArcaneBackground":true,"requirements":{"value":"Novice"}},"effects":[],"folder":"RlvFYBE8BDHKhq30","sort":600000,"permission":{"default":2,"ZvqefCj0L7TxJS56":3,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"flags":{"journal-links":{},"core":{"sourceId":"Item.E6yOW6PfzFWgHuPD"}}},{"_id":"DAsE1IVRzYWoDYcF","name":"Channel Energy","type":"edge","img":"icons/environment/people/cleric-grey.webp","data":{"description":"<div class=\"sweb-core\">\n<p>Clerics can cast the <em>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Healing]{healing}</em> power at a Range of Spirit rather than Touch. Their <em>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Healing]{healing}</em> power also has the Additional Recipients Power Modifier, allowing them to heal nearby allies at the cost of one extra Power Point each.</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Cleric"}},"effects":[],"folder":"RlvFYBE8BDHKhq30","sort":200000,"permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"flags":{"journal-links":{},"core":{"sourceId":"Item.VO5siJEofAatX9Hf"}}},{"_id":"PJzJ4ctYtPx62CSN","name":"Luck","type":"edge","img":"icons/environment/people/group.webp","data":{"description":"<div class=\"sweb-core\">\n<p>The adventurer seems to be blessed by fate, karma, the gods, or whatever external forces he believes in (or believe in him!). </span></p>\n<p>He draws one extra @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Bennies]{Benny} at the beginning of each game session, allowing him to succeed at important tasks more often than most, and survive incredible dangers.</span></p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Novice"}},"effects":[],"folder":"EnpCvbp1xbBRZIf1","sort":1700000,"permission":{"default":0,"3HvtK4sMp7flYKmT":3,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"flags":{"cf":null,"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.swade-core-rules.swade-edges.p00apKW5V2grVRw2"}}},{"_id":"FnP3wCwHjboMpiiN","name":"Curious","type":"hindrance","img":"icons/magic/holy/yin-yang-balance-symbol.webp","data":{"description":"<div class=\"sweb-core\"><p>It killed the cat, and it might kill your warrior as well. Curious characters have to check out everything and always want to know what&rsquo;s behind a potential mystery or secret.</span></p></div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"major":true},"effects":[],"folder":"1updrtPaYhKD0fRY","sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"3HvtK4sMp7flYKmT":3,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"flags":{"cf":null,"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.swade-core-rules.swade-hindrances.GULnKHGQlhgqZ7Hn"}}},{"_id":"vDW5GGdBlqh54eDp","name":"Vow of Faith (Protect nature and the seas)","type":"hindrance","img":"icons/environment/people/cleric-grey.webp","data":{"description":"<div class=\"sweb-core\">\n<p>Clerics have a major vow to serve their deity. Those who wish to draw energy from divine sources must uphold the principles of their @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Domains]{Domains}.</p>\n<p>If the cleric violates their deity's trust (DM's call) the cleric subtracts 2 from @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Faith]{Faith} rolls for a week. Truly sacrilegious acts might rob her of her powers entirely until she atones in some way.</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"major":true},"effects":[],"folder":"RlvFYBE8BDHKhq30","sort":700000,"permission":{"default":0,"3HvtK4sMp7flYKmT":3,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_paujlrjlvl","path":"Hindrances","color":"#8c160f"},"journal-links":{},"core":{"sourceId":"Item.YwWXS95TWbqBIyLE"}}},{"_id":"GyeY5S2b007h2GaH","name":"Crossbow, Light","type":"weapon","img":"icons/weapons/crossbows/crossbow-simple-black.webp","data":{"description":null,"notes":"Hand-drawn","additionalStats":{},"quantity":1,"weight":5,"price":25,"equippable":false,"equipped":true,"isVehicular":false,"mods":1,"actions":{"skill":"Shooting","skillMod":"","dmgMod":"","additional":{}},"damage":"2d6","range":"10/20/40","rof":"1","ap":"2","minStr":"d6","shots":"20","currentShots":"20","ammo":"","autoReload":false},"effects":[],"folder":"zDTfLKxjq2F4ebrl","sort":600001,"permission":{"default":0,"ZvqefCj0L7TxJS56":3,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"flags":{"journal-links":{},"core":{"sourceId":"Item.cXYnSp8h1A8bQn7H"}}},{"_id":"SrGZN1xogifXjNxQ","name":"Rapier (mwk)","type":"weapon","img":"icons/weapons/swords/scimitar-guard-gold.webp","data":{"description":"<div class=\"sweb-core\">\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Parry]{Parry} +1</p>\n</div>","notes":"Parry +1","additionalStats":{},"quantity":1,"weight":3,"price":325,"equippable":false,"equipped":true,"isVehicular":false,"mods":1,"actions":{"skill":"Fighting","skillMod":"","dmgMod":"","additional":{}},"damage":"@str+d4","range":"","rof":"1","ap":"1","minStr":"d4","shots":"0","currentShots":"0","ammo":"","autoReload":false},"effects":[{"_id":"2K9kgErsmseqr2AH","flags":{},"changes":[{"key":"data.stats.parry.modifier","mode":2,"value":"1"}],"disabled":false,"duration":{"startTime":null},"icon":"icons/weapons/swords/scimitar-guard-gold.webp","label":"Rapier Parry Bonus","tint":null,"transfer":true}],"folder":"wKOO5vrTtLr5gJsf","sort":700001,"permission":{"default":0,"ZvqefCj0L7TxJS56":3,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"flags":{"journal-links":{},"core":{"sourceId":"Item.yPRx9vOmWYL1MgBF"}}},{"_id":"oEICVIuh21SDMqCp","name":"Dagger","type":"weapon","img":"icons/weapons/daggers/dagger-double-red.webp","data":{"description":"","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"quantity":1,"weight":1,"price":2,"equippable":false,"equipped":true,"isVehicular":false,"mods":1,"actions":{"skill":"Fighting","skillMod":"","dmgMod":"","additional":{"oyxuzdjora":{"name":"Athletics (throwing)","type":"skill","rof":null,"skillMod":"","skillOverride":"Athletics","shotsUsed":null}}},"damage":"@str+d4","range":"3/6/12","rof":"1","ap":"0","minStr":"d4","shots":"0","currentShots":"0","ammo":"","autoReload":false},"effects":[],"folder":"ofLOMYgHLqfG1MyP","sort":400001,"permission":{"default":0,"ZvqefCj0L7TxJS56":3,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"flags":{"journal-links":{},"core":{"sourceId":"Item.GxVNY83rIxMpxCqB"}}},{"_id":"tlD3nDmoApkuFlOI","name":"Waters of Life","type":"power","img":"icons/magic/life/heart-area-circle-red-green.webp","data":{"description":"<div class=\"sweb-core\">\n<p><strong>School: </strong>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Schools of Magic]{Conjuration}</p>\n<p><em>Healing </em>removes @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Damage Effects]{Wounds} less than an hour old. A @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Trait Rolls]{success} removes one Wound, and a @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Raises]{raise} removes two. The power may be cast additional times to remove additional Wounds within that hour and as long as the healer has enough @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Arcane Backgrounds]{Power Points}.</p>\n<p>For @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Wild Cards and Extras]{Extras}, the GM must first determine if the ally is still alive (see @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Healing]{Aftermath}). If so, a successful arcane skill roll returns the ally to action (@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Damage Effects]{Shaken} if it matters).</p>\n<p><strong>Helpful Links:</strong> @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Using Magic]{Using Magic} - <h3 class=\"red-label\">@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.4 Power Modifiers]{Modifiers}</p>\n<h3>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Power Modifiers]{Modifiers}</h3>\n<ul class=\"red-bullet-list\">\n<li><strong>Greater Healing (+10):</strong> <em>Greater healing</em> can restore any @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Damage Effects]{Wound}, including those more than an hour old.</li>\n<li><strong>Crippling Injuries (+20):</strong> The power can heal a permanent @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-tables.Injury Table]{Crippling Injury} (see @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Damage Effects]{Incapacitation}). This requires an hour of preparation and only one casting is permitted per injury. If it @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Trait Rolls]{fails}, this caster cannot <em>heal </em>that particular injury (but somoene else may try). If successful, the subject is @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Fatigue]{Exhausted} for 24 hours.</li>\n<li class=\"star\"><strong>Mass Healing (+2/+3):</strong> For a +2 @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Arcane Backgrounds]{Power Points}, healing affects all allies within a @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Area Effect Attacks]{Medium Blast Template} centered on the caster (or a @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Area Effect Attacks]{Large Blast Template} for +3).</li>\n<li><strong>Neutralize Poison or Disease (+1):</strong> A successful <em>healing </em>roll negates any @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Poison]{poison} or @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Disease]{disease}. If the poison or disease has a bonus or penalty associated with it, the modifier applies to the @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Arcane Backgrounds]{arcane skill} roll as well.</li>\n</ul>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"equippable":false,"equipped":true,"actions":{"skill":"Faith","skillMod":"","dmgMod":"","additional":{}},"rank":"Novice","pp":"3","damage":"","range":"Touch","duration":"Instant","trapping":"Using water to heal wounds","arcane":"","skill":"","modifiers":[]},"effects":[],"folder":"8NyF3ZLDhkqHw0IP","sort":2000000,"permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"flags":{"cf":null,"journal-links":{},"core":{"sourceId":"Item.L3HoTKUKSXvZNAqa"}}},{"_id":"BjEQUAm7nhUjq2o7","name":"Obscuring Mist","type":"power","img":"icons/magic/light/torch-fire-orange.webp","data":{"description":"<div class=\"sweb-core\">\n<p><strong>School: </strong>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Schools of Magic]{Evocation}</p>\n<p><em>Light </em>creates bright @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Illumination]{illumination} in a @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Area Effect Attacks]{Large Blast Template}. With a raise, the light can be focused into a 5&Prime; (10 yard) beam as well.</p>\n<p><em>Darkness </em>blocks @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Illumination]{illumination} in an area the size of a @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Area Effect Attacks]{Large Blast Template}, making the area Dark, or Pitch Darkness with a raise (see @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Illumination]{Illumination}).</p>\n<p>If <em>light </em>and <em>darkness </em>overlap, they create a patch of @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Illumination]{Dim light} (&minus;2).</p>\n<p><strong>Helpful Links:</strong> @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Using Magic]{Using Magic} - <h3 class=\"red-label\">@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.4 Power Modifiers]{Modifiers}</p>\n<h3>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Power Modifiers]{Modifiers}</h3>\n<ul class=\"red-bullet-list\">\n<li class=\"star\"><strong>Area Effect (+2): </strong>The <em>light</em> expands to the caster&rsquo;s @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Traits]{Smarts} in radius, with a Range of @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Traits]{Smarts} &times;2. The light is sunlight and has the same effect on certain creatures (such as vampires) as natural sunlight.</li>\n<li class=\"star\"><strong>True Darkness (+2):</strong> The <em>darkness</em> blocks @Compendium[savage-eberron-bestiary.savage-eberron-bestiary-abilities.Infravision]{Infravision}, @Compendium[savage-eberron-bestiary.savage-eberron-bestiary-abilities.Low Light Vision]{Low Light Vision}, and @Compendium[savage-eberron-bestiary.savage-eberron-bestiary-abilities.Darkvision]{Darkvision}. It has no effect on magical sight such as <em>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Detect/Conceal Arcana]{detect arcana}</em>.</li>\n<li><strong>Mobile (+1):</strong> The caster can move the area of effect up to his @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Arcane Backgrounds]{arcane skill} die type each @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Actions]{round} after casting, or attach it to an inanimate object when first cast. </li>\n</ul>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"equippable":false,"equipped":true,"actions":{"skill":"Faith","skillMod":"","dmgMod":"","additional":{}},"rank":"Novice","pp":"1","damage":"","range":"Smarts","duration":"10 minutes","trapping":"Thick fog","arcane":"","skill":"","modifiers":[]},"effects":[],"folder":"8NyF3ZLDhkqHw0IP","sort":2300000,"permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"flags":{"cf":null,"journal-links":{},"core":{"sourceId":"Item.gEg0cmKVXZN0LEYt"}}},{"_id":"GJNLSbYrjlDoVAcL","name":"Calm Sea Creatures","type":"power","img":"icons/skills/social/diplomacy-handshake-yellow.webp","data":{"description":"<div class=\"sweb-core\">\n<p><strong>School: </strong>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Schools of Magic]{Enchantment}</p>\n<p>A successful arcane skill vs @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Traits]{Spirit} roll gives the caster insight into a target's basic emotions. This grants him a +1 bonus (+2 with a @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Raises]{raise}) to all @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Intimidation]{Intimidation}, @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Persuasion]{Persuasion}, @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Performance]{Performance}, or @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Taunt]{Taunt} rolls against the target for the Duration of the power.</p>\n<p><em>Empathy</em> works on animals, adding +1 (+2 with a @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Raises]{raise}) to @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Riding]{Riding} or other rolls to interact with the creature.</p>\n<p><strong>Helpful Links:</strong> @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Using Magic]{Using Magic} - <h3 class=\"red-label\">@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.4 Power Modifiers]{Modifiers}</p>\n<h3>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Power Modifiers]{Modifiers}</h3>\n<ul class=\"red-bullet-list\">\n<li><strong>Additional Recipients (+1):</strong> The power may affect more than one target for 1 additional @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Arcane Backgrounds]{Power Point} each.</li>\n<li><strong>Charm (+2): </strong>If the target is Uncooperative or Neutral, a successful casting makes him Cooperative, or Friendly with a raise. The spell is instantly broken if the caster or her allies attack the victim or her allies.</li>\n<li><strong>Duration (+1):</strong> Duration is measured in minutes instead of rounds. If the character Critically Fails any of the affected skill rolls against the target, the effect terminates immediately.</li>\n<li class=\"star\"><strong>Truth (+2):</strong> The caster knows if the target believes he's telling the truth or not.</li>\n</ul>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"equippable":false,"equipped":true,"actions":{"skill":"Faith","skillMod":"+1","dmgMod":"","additional":{}},"rank":"Novice","pp":"1","damage":"","range":"Smarts","duration":"5","trapping":"Concentration when in sight of a sea creature","arcane":"","skill":"","modifiers":[]},"effects":[],"folder":"8NyF3ZLDhkqHw0IP","sort":1500000,"permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"flags":{"cf":null,"journal-links":{},"core":{"sourceId":"Item.eAQAHjnqokcoEg0F"}}},{"_id":"5Zex12p1RS3tEFix","name":"Deception","type":"skill","img":"icons/skills/toxins/poison-skull-herbs-bottle-pink.webp","data":{"description":"<div class=\"sweb-core\">\n<p>Deception determines whether the hero can convincingly hide the truth, either verbally or through her actions. This deception can encompass everything from misleading others through ambiguity to telling outright lies.</p>\n<p>Typical situations include trying to fast-talk a guard, con a merchant, dull someone's suspicions with false assurances, or maintain a straight face while telling a blatant lie.</p>\n<p>Usually, a character successfully passing herself off in a disguise, or trying to impersonate the sound of someone else's voice would be a @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Performance]{Performance} check rather than a deception check. </p>\n<p><em><strong>Source: Savage Eberron</strong></em></p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"attribute":"spirit","isCoreSkill":false,"die":{"sides":4,"modifier":0},"wild-die":{"sides":6}},"effects":[],"folder":"cgfmurTJRwbCvmCc","sort":700001,"permission":{"default":0,"ZvqefCj0L7TxJS56":3,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"flags":{"journal-links":{},"core":{"sourceId":"Item.E0BVumGwbaczoPjD"}}},{"_id":"eyvcxPWXw8oc71zS","name":"Arcana","type":"skill","img":"icons/magic/symbols/circled-gem-pink.webp","data":{"description":"<div class=\"sweb-core\">\n<p>Arcana reflects knowledge about spells, artifacts, magic items, eldritch symbols, magical traditions, dragons, forbidden lore, magical beasts, analyzing alchemical compounds and other ritual paraphernalia, translate magical runes, guess what spell was cast based on physical evidence left behind, etc.</p>\n<p>A successful Arcana roll reveals basic information about a magical topic, and a raise grants more details.</p>\n<p><em><strong>Source: Savage Eberron</strong></em></p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"attribute":"smarts","isCoreSkill":false,"die":{"sides":4,"modifier":0},"wild-die":{"sides":6}},"effects":[],"folder":"cgfmurTJRwbCvmCc","sort":200001,"permission":{"default":0,"ZvqefCj0L7TxJS56":3,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"flags":{"journal-links":{},"core":{"sourceId":"Item.lr6HSv7xgo5Dsp1N"}}}],"effects":[{"_id":"reSt8fiHSfjirLvv","changes":[{"key":"data.stats.parry.modifier","mode":2,"value":"1"}],"disabled":false,"duration":{"startTime":28973116800},"icon":"icons/weapons/swords/scimitar-guard-gold.webp","label":"Rapier Parry Bonus","origin":"Actor.B0KGbgsH18F6JMvD.Item.SrGZN1xogifXjNxQ","tint":null,"transfer":false,"flags":{}}],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"flags":{"journal-links":{"references":{}},"cf":{"id":"temp_3a04s0jrz4j","path":"Pirates of Cyre Bestiary#/CF_SEP/NPC's","color":"#000000"}}}
{"_id":"VVQDwlLpBEkpiBnV","name":"#[CF_tempEntity]","type":"character","img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","data":{"attributes":{"agility":{"die":{"sides":4,"modifier":0},"wild-die":{"sides":6}},"smarts":{"die":{"sides":4,"modifier":0},"wild-die":{"sides":6},"animal":false},"spirit":{"die":{"sides":4,"modifier":0},"wild-die":{"sides":6},"unShakeBonus":0},"strength":{"die":{"sides":4,"modifier":0},"wild-die":{"sides":6},"encumbranceSteps":0},"vigor":{"die":{"sides":4,"modifier":0},"wild-die":{"sides":6}}},"stats":{"speed":{"runningDie":6,"runningMod":0,"value":6},"toughness":{"value":0,"armor":0,"modifier":0},"parry":{"value":0,"modifier":0},"size":0},"details":{"biography":{"value":""},"species":{"name":""},"currency":500,"wealth":{"die":6,"modifier":0,"wild-die":6},"conviction":{"value":0,"active":false},"autoCalcToughness":true,"autoCalcParry":true},"powerPoints":{},"fatigue":{"value":0,"min":0,"max":2},"wounds":{"value":0,"min":0,"max":3,"ignored":0},"advances":{"value":0,"rank":"Novice","details":""},"bennies":{"value":3,"max":3},"status":{"isShaken":false,"isDistracted":false,"isVulnerable":false,"isStunned":false,"isEntangled":false,"isBound":false},"initiative":{"hasHesitant":false,"hasLevelHeaded":false,"hasImpLevelHeaded":false,"hasQuick":false},"additionalStats":{},"wildcard":true},"token":{"name":"#[CF_tempEntity]","img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","displayName":0,"actorLink":false,"width":1,"height":1,"scale":1,"mirrorX":false,"mirrorY":false,"lockRotation":false,"rotation":0,"alpha":1,"vision":false,"dimSight":0,"brightSight":0,"dimLight":0,"brightLight":0,"sightAngle":0,"lightAngle":0,"lightAlpha":0.25,"lightAnimation":{"speed":5,"intensity":5},"disposition":-1,"displayBars":0,"bar1":{"attribute":null},"bar2":{"attribute":null},"flags":{},"randomImg":false,"actorId":null},"items":[{"_id":"BAaFJq4Ss7Bgmt8w","name":"Persuasion","type":"skill","img":"icons/skills/social/diplomacy-handshake.webp","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p>Persuasion is the ability to convince others to do what you want through reason, cajoling, deception, rewards, or other friendly means. Persuasion isn&rsquo;t mind control. It can change someone&rsquo;s attitude but not their goals. A bandit may let you keep a sentimental piece of jewelry with a good Persuasion roll but still takes all your other goods.</p>\n<p>When used to @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Support]{Support} allies it&rsquo;s an unopposed roll. If the target is resistant, it&rsquo;s an @JournalEntry[JBxsGv2wAoAmoCDe]{opposed} roll vs. the target&rsquo;s @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Traits]{Spirit}. The GM should modify the roll as she sees fit based on roleplaying, any pertinent @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Edges]{Edges} or @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Hindrances]{Hindrances} that affect the conversation, and the circumstances.</p>\n<p><strong>Reaction Level:</strong> How much a person is willing to cooperate depends largely on their attitude toward whoever&rsquo;s talking to them. The Game Master can decide how nonplayer characters feel based on the setting, or roll on the @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-tables.Reaction Table]{Reaction Table} if she has no preconceived notions.</p>\n<p>@Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{Success} improves the target&rsquo;s attitude one level and a raise improves it two. Further increases aren&rsquo;t generally possible in the same encounter&mdash;it takes individuals a little time to adjust their biases.</p>\n<p>@Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{Failure} means the target won&rsquo;t change his mind this scene or until the situation changes in some important way. A @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{Critical Failure} also <em>reduces</em> the target&rsquo;s attitude two levels.</p>\n<p>Only one roll should generally be allowed per interaction unless new information is revealed, a substantial reward is offered, etc.</p>\n<p><strong>Networking: </strong>Characters can also use Persuasion as a &ldquo;macro skill,&rdquo; simulating a few hours or an evening&rsquo;s time hobnobbing and socializing to gain favors or information. See @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Networking]{Networking}.</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"attribute":"spirit","isCoreSkill":true,"die":{"sides":4,"modifier":0},"wild-die":{"sides":6}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_azxylmvr7yo","path":"Skills","color":"#008000"},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.swade-core-rules.swade-skills.xOmuCR92Ys9jD5vg"}}},{"_id":"Dk7MTEB8I6MuoNKP","name":"Notice","type":"skill","img":"icons/creatures/eyes/human-single-blue.webp","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p>Notice is a hero&rsquo;s general awareness and alertness. It&rsquo;s used to sense sights, sounds, tastes, and smells, spot clues, detect ambushes, spot hidden weapons on a foe, or tell if a rival is lying, frightened, happy, etc.</p>\n<p>@Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{Success} conveys basic information&mdash;the character hears movement in the forest, smells distant smoke, or senses someone isn&rsquo;t being completely truthful.</p>\n<p>A @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{raise} grants more detail, such as the direction of a sound or odor or what topic a person is avoiding or lying about.</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"attribute":"smarts","isCoreSkill":true,"die":{"sides":4,"modifier":0},"wild-die":{"sides":6}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_azxylmvr7yo","path":"Skills","color":"#008000"},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.swade-core-rules.swade-skills.yvw9bMgsrWQXuZN2"}}},{"_id":"X0BYJUZclN1vQeaV","name":"Athletics","type":"skill","img":"icons/magic/control/buff-strength-muscle-damage.webp","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p>Athletics combines an individual&rsquo;s coordin&shy;ation with learned skills such as climbing, jumping, balancing, biking, wrestling, skiing, swimming, throwing, or catching. Characters who rely on physical power more than coordination can take the @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Brute]{Brute} Edge to link this skill to @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Traits]{Strength} instead of @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Traits]{Agility}.</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"attribute":"agility","isCoreSkill":true,"die":{"sides":4,"modifier":0},"wild-die":{"sides":6}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_azxylmvr7yo","path":"Skills","color":"#008000"},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.swade-core-rules.swade-skills.sAig03GZiFKqBX7p"}}},{"_id":"d8bbwVTHdQpb5AFb","name":"Stealth","type":"skill","img":"icons/magic/nature/stealth-hide-eyes-green.webp","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p>Stealth is the ability to hide and move quietly. A simple @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{success} on a Stealth roll means the character avoids detection if enemies aren&rsquo;t particularly alert. If the character @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{fails} the roll, the enemy realizes something is amiss and begins actively searching for whatever roused them.</p>\n<p>Once foes are alerted and active, Stealth is opposed by @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Notice]{Notice} (a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{group roll} if there are many foes.</p>\n<p>The GM should apply any circumstantial penalties to @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Notice]{Notice} rolls for @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Illumination]{darkness}, @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Cover and Obstacles]{cover}, noise, distractions, and any difference in the target&rsquo;s @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Size and Scale]{Scale} (just like when attacking). Sneaking through dry leaves might subtract 2 from the Stealth roll, for example, while spotting someone in the dark uses the @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Illumination]{Illumination} penalty (&minus;4). Don&rsquo;t apply the same modifier to both rolls, however. If Stealth is at &minus;2 for the leaves, don&rsquo;t give Notice a +2 for them as well.</p>\n<p><strong>Sneak Attack: </strong> Sneaking up close enough to make a melee attack <em>always</em> requires an @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{opposed} Stealth roll versus the target&rsquo;s @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Notice]{Notice}, whether the guard is actively looking for trouble or not. If successful, the victim is @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Distracted and Vulnerable]{Vulnerable} to the attacker, but only until the attacker&rsquo;s turn ends. With a raise, the attacker has @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.The Drop]{The Drop} instead.</p>\n<p><strong>Movement:</strong> In combat, characters roll Stealth each turn as a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Actions]{free action} at the end of their move or any action the GM thinks might draw attention.</p>\n<p>Out of combat, the distance moved depends entirely on the situation. The GM might want a roll every minute if the group is sneaking around the perimeter of a defensive position, or every few miles if they&rsquo;re trying to quietly walk the path through a dark forest without alerting the creatures that live there.</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"attribute":"agility","isCoreSkill":true,"die":{"sides":4,"modifier":0},"wild-die":{"sides":6}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_azxylmvr7yo","path":"Skills","color":"#008000"},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.swade-core-rules.swade-skills.z9FmdFVGOOW2kufm"}}},{"_id":"wT9Ir2pYgNXXi5iA","name":"Common Knowledge","type":"skill","img":"icons/sundries/documents/document-official-capital.webp","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\"><p>Characters roll Common Knowledge to know people, places, and things of their world, including etiquette, geography, culture, popular technology, contacts, and customs.</p></div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"attribute":"smarts","isCoreSkill":true,"die":{"sides":4,"modifier":0},"wild-die":{"sides":6}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_azxylmvr7yo","path":"Skills","color":"#008000"},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.swade-core-rules.swade-skills.8N1uMThntsjaUPem"}}},{"name":"Untrained","type":"skill","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/skill.svg","data":{"description":"","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"attribute":"","isCoreSkill":false,"die":{"sides":4,"modifier":-2},"wild-die":{"sides":6}},"_id":"zg149xozs1a7wpb6","effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0},"flags":{}}],"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_3a04s0jrz4j","path":"Pirates of Cyre Bestiary#/CF_SEP/NPC's","color":"#000000","name":"NPC's","children":["2OH6BHW2dWwq8OFH","56twwTP4lR2skY8E","CDp0gPIh75K20LjT","z2qkrFSshkwFRNra","Q5asnYfjlp4vQD7W","JdZmTO2mCUBMDTaY","gytbnCnNuCBAS9FR","raZYvUdO4Op0Mc0t","NI8DuzUr5xNAOcht","7lLpzNGV5uDjF3qL"],"folderPath":["temp_pw543v57cu"]}}}
{"_id":"HaEE59Dzh7i0zZov","name":"Storm Reaver","type":"vehicle","img":"modules/savage-eberron-bestiary/assets/vehicle-tokens/watercraft/ship.webp","data":{"size":14,"scale":6,"classification":"Watercraft","handling":-2,"cost":300000,"topspeed":"12","description":"<div class=\"sweb-core\">\n<p><strong>Masts:</strong> 4</p>\n<p><strong>Cargo Holds:</strong> 16</p>\n<p><strong>Notes: </strong>Square-rigged and fore-aft sails; true beast of the seas, @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Vehicle Notes]{Heavy Armor}.</p>\n<p>Galleons come in a wide variety of sizes and designs. These ships all have one thing in common: they are huge, often having 3 or more decks, usually have catapults or ballista on deck, and have large castles mounted fore and aft so that their defenders can fire on enemy crews from above.</p>\n<p><strong>Weapons:</strong> Galleons can hold up to 12 @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-equipment.Ballista]{Ballista} in banks of 6 positioned on the port and starboard sides of the ship. In addition, up to 2 @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-equipment.Catapult]{Catapults} or @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-equipment.Ballista]{Ballista} may be positioned on the forecastle and sterncastle sides of the ship. These seige engines can be swiveled to fire out the sides of the ship or either forward or aft, depending on their position.</p>\n</div>","toughness":{"total":"20","armor":"4"},"wounds":{"value":2,"max":6,"ignored":0},"crew":{"required":{"value":"20","max":"20"},"optional":{"value":"40","max":"40"}},"driver":{"id":null,"skill":"Boating","skillAlternative":""},"status":{"isOutOfControl":false,"isWrecked":false},"initiative":{"hasHesitant":false,"hasLevelHeaded":false,"hasImpLevelHeaded":false,"hasQuick":false},"additionalStats":{},"maxCargo":16,"maxMods":8},"token":{"flags":{},"name":"Galleon","displayName":30,"img":"modules/swade-core-rules/assets/art/vehicles/vehicle-water-galleon.webp","tint":null,"width":3,"height":3,"scale":1,"lockRotation":false,"rotation":0,"vision":false,"dimSight":0,"brightSight":0,"dimLight":0,"brightLight":0,"sightAngle":0,"lightAngle":0,"lightAlpha":1,"lightAnimation":{"speed":5,"intensity":5},"actorId":"bZl2AvryDydlOMrb","actorLink":false,"disposition":-1,"displayBars":0,"bar1":{"attribute":null},"bar2":{"attribute":null},"randomImg":false,"mirrorX":false,"mirrorY":false,"alpha":1},"items":[{"_id":"zIMNBBFfdNnncDMc","name":"Ballista (x12)","type":"weapon","data":{"description":"<div class=\"sweb-core\">\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Heavy Weapon (HW)]{Heavy Weapon}, @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Reload]{Reload} time is 5 minutes for a solo operator, or 2 minutes with a crew of 2.</p>\n<hr />\n<p>A ballista is a mechanical engine designed to fire a massive crossbow bolt. One person can fire the device (@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Shooting]{Shooting}). One person can reload, although it&rsquo;s faster with two people.</p>\n</div>","notes":"HW","additionalStats":{},"quantity":1,"weight":0,"price":500,"equippable":false,"equipped":true,"isVehicular":true,"mods":1,"actions":{"skill":"Shooting","skillMod":"","dmgMod":"","additional":{}},"damage":"3d6","range":"15/30/60","rof":"1","ap":"4","minStr":"","shots":"0","currentShots":"0","ammo":"","autoReload":false},"sort":200001,"flags":{},"img":"icons/weapons/artillery/ballista-wood-green.webp","effects":[],"folder":null,"permission":{"default":0}},{"_id":"lIKUN2Xe9HwczqzA","name":"Catapult","type":"weapon","data":{"description":"<div class=\"sweb-core\">\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Area Effect Attacks]{Medium Blast Template}, @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Heavy Weapon (HW)]{Heavy Weapon}, @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Reload]{Reload} time is every 5 minutes with a crew of 4.</p>\n<hr />\n<p>Catapults are simple devices that hurl large stones at enemy defenses or ranks of troops. They normally require a crew of eight to load the projectile, crank down the lever that propels it, then sight and aim it. Firing can be done by a single person, but loading the projectile takes at least four.</p>\n</div>","notes":"MBT, Heavy Weapon, Reload time is every 5 minutes with a crew of 4.","additionalStats":{},"quantity":1,"weight":0,"price":800,"equippable":false,"equipped":true,"isVehicular":true,"mods":1,"actions":{"skill":"Shooting","skillMod":"","dmgMod":"","additional":{}},"damage":"3d6","range":"24/48/96","rof":"1","ap":"4","minStr":"","shots":"0","currentShots":"0","ammo":"","autoReload":false},"sort":300001,"flags":{},"img":"icons/weapons/artillery/catapult-simple.webp","effects":[],"folder":null,"permission":{"default":0}},{"_id":"JpnKrAAeohBHldC7","name":"Soarwood","type":"gear","img":"icons/commodities/wood/lumber-stack-grey.webp","data":{"description":"<div class=\"sweb-core\">\n<p>Rare even in the abundant forests of Aerenal, soarwood possesses a magical buoyancy. Ships made from soarwood skim effortlessly over the surface of the water. Soarwood is a necessary component of the airships and elemental galleons manufactured by @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-lore.House Lyrandar]{House Lyrandar} and @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-lore.House Cannith]{House Cannith}.</p>\n<p>The speed of a boat or ship made from soarwood is double that of an equivalent boat made from ordinary wood, and the cost is four times normal. it also improves the Handling of the ship by 1.</p>\n<p>Soarwood has the same physical characteristics as normal wood, but weighs only 75% as much.</p>\n<p><em><strong>Note: </strong></em>All elemental galleons are made from soarwood, so this is already included in the speed of the vessel.</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"quantity":1,"weight":0,"price":0,"equippable":true,"equipped":"true","isVehicular":true,"mods":1},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"flags":{}},{"_id":"wd3itVhwigGHRYZg","name":"Heavy Armor","type":"gear","img":"icons/commodities/wood/lumber-stack.webp","data":{"description":"<div class=\"sweb-core\">\n<p>Only weapons marked as Heavy Weapons can hurt this vehicle, regardless of the damage roll. This keeps a lucky bow shot from destroying a longship, for example. Vehicles with Heavy Armor halve damage they take from colliding with other obstacles (including vehicles) that don&rsquo;t have Heavy Armor. This is not to be confused with the heavy category of personal armor.</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"quantity":1,"weight":0,"price":0,"equippable":false,"equipped":"true","isVehicular":true,"mods":1},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"flags":{}}],"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_z59ej144gfl","path":"Pirates of Cyre Bestiary#/CF_SEP/Vehicles","color":"#000000"},"journal-links":{}}}
{"_id":"xg2XDD84JzvWBg9M","name":"#[CF_tempEntity]","type":"character","img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","data":{"attributes":{"agility":{"die":{"sides":4,"modifier":0},"wild-die":{"sides":6}},"smarts":{"die":{"sides":4,"modifier":0},"wild-die":{"sides":6},"animal":false},"spirit":{"die":{"sides":4,"modifier":0},"wild-die":{"sides":6},"unShakeBonus":0},"strength":{"die":{"sides":4,"modifier":0},"wild-die":{"sides":6},"encumbranceSteps":0},"vigor":{"die":{"sides":4,"modifier":0},"wild-die":{"sides":6}}},"stats":{"speed":{"runningDie":6,"runningMod":0,"value":6},"toughness":{"value":0,"armor":0,"modifier":0},"parry":{"value":0,"modifier":0},"size":0},"details":{"biography":{"value":""},"species":{"name":""},"currency":500,"wealth":{"die":6,"modifier":0,"wild-die":6},"conviction":{"value":0,"active":false},"autoCalcToughness":true,"autoCalcParry":true},"powerPoints":{},"fatigue":{"value":0,"min":0,"max":2},"wounds":{"value":0,"min":0,"max":3,"ignored":0},"advances":{"value":0,"rank":"Novice","details":""},"bennies":{"value":3,"max":3},"status":{"isShaken":false,"isDistracted":false,"isVulnerable":false,"isStunned":false,"isEntangled":false,"isBound":false},"initiative":{"hasHesitant":false,"hasLevelHeaded":false,"hasImpLevelHeaded":false,"hasQuick":false},"additionalStats":{},"wildcard":true},"token":{"name":"#[CF_tempEntity]","img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","displayName":0,"actorLink":false,"width":1,"height":1,"scale":1,"mirrorX":false,"mirrorY":false,"lockRotation":false,"rotation":0,"alpha":1,"vision":false,"dimSight":0,"brightSight":0,"dimLight":0,"brightLight":0,"sightAngle":0,"lightAngle":0,"lightAlpha":0.25,"lightAnimation":{"speed":5,"intensity":5},"disposition":-1,"displayBars":0,"bar1":{"attribute":null},"bar2":{"attribute":null},"flags":{},"randomImg":false,"actorId":null},"items":[{"_id":"BAaFJq4Ss7Bgmt8w","name":"Persuasion","type":"skill","img":"icons/skills/social/diplomacy-handshake.webp","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p>Persuasion is the ability to convince others to do what you want through reason, cajoling, deception, rewards, or other friendly means. Persuasion isn&rsquo;t mind control. It can change someone&rsquo;s attitude but not their goals. A bandit may let you keep a sentimental piece of jewelry with a good Persuasion roll but still takes all your other goods.</p>\n<p>When used to @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Support]{Support} allies it&rsquo;s an unopposed roll. If the target is resistant, it&rsquo;s an @JournalEntry[JBxsGv2wAoAmoCDe]{opposed} roll vs. the target&rsquo;s @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Traits]{Spirit}. The GM should modify the roll as she sees fit based on roleplaying, any pertinent @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Edges]{Edges} or @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Hindrances]{Hindrances} that affect the conversation, and the circumstances.</p>\n<p><strong>Reaction Level:</strong> How much a person is willing to cooperate depends largely on their attitude toward whoever&rsquo;s talking to them. The Game Master can decide how nonplayer characters feel based on the setting, or roll on the @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-tables.Reaction Table]{Reaction Table} if she has no preconceived notions.</p>\n<p>@Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{Success} improves the target&rsquo;s attitude one level and a raise improves it two. Further increases aren&rsquo;t generally possible in the same encounter&mdash;it takes individuals a little time to adjust their biases.</p>\n<p>@Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{Failure} means the target won&rsquo;t change his mind this scene or until the situation changes in some important way. A @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{Critical Failure} also <em>reduces</em> the target&rsquo;s attitude two levels.</p>\n<p>Only one roll should generally be allowed per interaction unless new information is revealed, a substantial reward is offered, etc.</p>\n<p><strong>Networking: </strong>Characters can also use Persuasion as a &ldquo;macro skill,&rdquo; simulating a few hours or an evening&rsquo;s time hobnobbing and socializing to gain favors or information. See @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Networking]{Networking}.</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"attribute":"spirit","isCoreSkill":true,"die":{"sides":4,"modifier":0},"wild-die":{"sides":6}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_azxylmvr7yo","path":"Skills","color":"#008000"},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.swade-core-rules.swade-skills.xOmuCR92Ys9jD5vg"}}},{"_id":"Dk7MTEB8I6MuoNKP","name":"Notice","type":"skill","img":"icons/creatures/eyes/human-single-blue.webp","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p>Notice is a hero&rsquo;s general awareness and alertness. It&rsquo;s used to sense sights, sounds, tastes, and smells, spot clues, detect ambushes, spot hidden weapons on a foe, or tell if a rival is lying, frightened, happy, etc.</p>\n<p>@Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{Success} conveys basic information&mdash;the character hears movement in the forest, smells distant smoke, or senses someone isn&rsquo;t being completely truthful.</p>\n<p>A @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{raise} grants more detail, such as the direction of a sound or odor or what topic a person is avoiding or lying about.</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"attribute":"smarts","isCoreSkill":true,"die":{"sides":4,"modifier":0},"wild-die":{"sides":6}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_azxylmvr7yo","path":"Skills","color":"#008000"},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.swade-core-rules.swade-skills.yvw9bMgsrWQXuZN2"}}},{"_id":"X0BYJUZclN1vQeaV","name":"Athletics","type":"skill","img":"icons/magic/control/buff-strength-muscle-damage.webp",